	(22, 'We Will Glorify ', 'Twila Paris. ', '~Verse 1\r\nWe will glorify the King of Kings.\r\nWe will glorify the Lamb.\r\nWe will glorify the Lord of Lords\r\nWho is the Great I AM.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord Jehovah reigns in majesty.\r\nWe will bow before His throne.\r\nWe will worship Him in righteousness.\r\nWe will worship Him alone.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe is Lord of Heaven, Lord of earth.\r\nHe is Lord of all who live.\r\nHe is Lord above the universe.\r\nAll praise to Him we give.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO Hallelujah to the King of Kings.\r\nHallelujah to the Lamb.\r\nHallelujah to the Lord of Lords\r\nWho is the Great I AM.\r\n', '', ' 1982 Singspiration Music/ASCAP', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/4skT9ndv6ng&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '', 'We will glorify the King of Kings. We will glorify the Lamb. We will glorify the Lord of Lords Who is the Great I AM. Lord Jehovah reigns in majesty. We will bow before His throne. We will worship Him in righteousness. We will worship Him alone. He is Lord of Heaven, Lord of earth. He is Lord of all who live. He is Lord above the universe. All praise to Him we give. O Hallelujah to the King of Kings. Hallelujah to the Lamb. Hallelujah to the Lord of Lords Who is the Great I AM.'),
	(23, 'Alleluia! Sing To Jesus', 'Willimas C. Dix, music by Rowland H. Prichard, ', '~Verse 1\r\nAlleluia! sing to Jesus!\r\nHis the sceptre, His the throne;\r\nAlleluia! His the truimph,\r\nHis the victory alone;\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHark! the songs of peaceful Zion\r\nThunder like a mighty flood;\r\n"Jesus, out of ev\'ry nation\r\nHas redeemed us by His blood."\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAlleluia! not as orphans\r\nAre we left in sorrow now;\r\nAlleluia! He is near us,\r\nFaith believes, not questions how:\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThrough the clouds from sight received Him\r\nWhen the forty days were o\'er\r\nShall our hearts forget His promise,\r\n"I am with you evermore"?\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAlleluia! Bread of heaven,\r\nYou on earth our food, and stay!\r\nAlleluia! Here the sinful\r\nFlee to You from day to day;\r\n~Verse 6\r\nIntercessor, Friend of sinners,\r\nEarth\'s Redeemer, plead for me,\r\nWhere the songs of all the sinless\r\nSweep across the crystal sea\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/bBdKVC58nGY&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Alleluia! sing to Jesus! His the sceptre, His the throne; Alleluia! His the truimph, His the victory alone; Hark! the songs of peaceful Zion Thunder like a mighty flood; \\"Jesus, out of ev\\\'ry nation Has redeemed us by His blood.\\" Alleluia! not as orphans Are we left in sorrow now; Alleluia! He is near us, Faith believes, not questions how: Through the clouds from sight received Him When the forty days were o\\\'er Shall our hearts forget His promise, \\"I am with you evermore\\"? Alleluia! Bread of heaven, You on earth our food, and stay! Alleluia! Here the sinful Flee to You from day to day; Intercessor, Friend of sinners, Earth\\\'s Redeemer, plead for me, Where the songs of all the sinless Sweep across the crystal sea'),
	(24, 'Worthy, Worthy Are You Lord', 'Mark Kinzer  c. 1976, 1980 The Word of God  (adm. by Servant Pub.) ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSinging Hallelujah! Lamb upon the throne,\r\nWe worship and adore You,\r\nYou\'ve made Your glories known.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWorthy, oh worthy are You, Lord\r\nWorthy to be thanked and praised\r\nAnd worshipped and adored.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHallelujah, glory to the King!\r\nYou\'re more than a conqueror,\r\nAnd You\'re Lord of everything.\r\n', '', ' 1976, 1980 The Word of God  (adm. by Servant Pub.) ', '', '', 'Singing Hallelujah! Lamb upon the throne, We worship and adore You, You\'ve made Your glories known. Worthy, oh worthy are You, Lord Worthy to be thanked and praised And worshipped and adored. Hallelujah, glory to the King! You\'re more than a conqueror, And You\'re Lord of everything.'),
	(25, 'Joyful, Joyful, We Adore Thee (Hymn #1)', 'Henry van Dyke and music by Ludwig van Beethoven.', '~Verse 1\r\nJoyful, joyful, we adore Thee,\r\nGod of glory, Lord of love;\r\nHearts unfold like flowers\r\nbefore Thee,\r\nOpening to the sun above.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMelt the clouds of sin and sadness,\r\nDrive the dark of doubt away;\r\nGiver of immortal gladness,\r\nFill us with the light of day.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll Thy works with joy surround Thee,\r\nEarth and heaven reflect Thy rays;\r\nStars and angels sing around Thee,\r\nCenter of unbroken praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nField and forest, vale and mountain,\r\nFlowery meadow, flashing sea,\r\nChanting bird and flowing fountain,\r\nCall us to rejoice in Thee.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThou art giving and forgiving,\r\nEver blessing, ever blest;\r\nWellspring of the joy of living,\r\nOcean depth of happy rest!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThou our Father, Christ, our brother,\r\nAll who live in love are Thine;\r\nTeach us how to love each other,\r\nLift us to the joy divine.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nMortals, join the happy chorus,\r\nWhich the morning stars began;\r\nFather love is reigning o\'er us,\r\nBrother love binds man to man.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nEver singing, march we onward,\r\nVictors in the midst of strife;\r\nJoyful music leads us sunward\r\nIn the triumph song of life.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/HxEUIJuDQfA', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Joyful, joyful, we adore Thee, God of glory, Lord of love; Hearts unfold like flowers before Thee, Opening to the sun above. Melt the clouds of sin and sadness, Drive the dark of doubt away; Giver of immortal gladness, Fill us with the light of day. All Thy works with joy surround Thee, Earth and heaven reflect Thy rays; Stars and angels sing around Thee, Center of unbroken praise. Field and forest, vale and mountain, Flowery meadow, flashing sea, Chanting bird and flowing fountain, Call us to rejoice in Thee. Thou art giving and forgiving, Ever blessing, ever blest; Wellspring of the joy of living, Ocean depth of happy rest! Thou our Father, Christ, our brother, All who live in love are Thine; Teach us how to love each other, Lift us to the joy divine. Mortals, join the happy chorus, Which the morning stars began; Father love is reigning o\'er us, Brother love binds man to man. Ever singing, march we onward, Victors in the midst of strife; Joyful music leads us sunward In the triumph song of life.).'),
	(26, 'Draw Me', 'Kent Blanton    C. 1996 Kent Blanton', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nDraw me, draw me to You.\r\nDraw me, draw me to You.\r\nDeep within my soul,\r\nPlace a longing for You.\r\nAnd draw me, draw me to you.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI come, I come to You.\r\nI come, I come to You.\r\nLord, I feel You drawing me\r\nWith cords of love.\r\nSo I come, I come to You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI run, I run to You.\r\nI run, I run to You.\r\nLord, where else can I go?\r\nYou alone are my hope.\r\nSo I run, I run to You.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Kent Blanton', '', '', 'Draw me, draw me to You. Draw me, draw me to You. Deep within my soul, Place a longing for You. And draw me, draw me to you. I come, I come to You. I come, I come to You. Lord, I feel You drawing me With cords of love. So I come, I come to You. I run, I run to You. I run, I run to You. Lord, where else can I go? You alone are my hope. So I run, I run to You.'),
	(27, 'Nobody Fills My Heart Like Jesus', 'Dennis Jernigan', '~Verse 1\r\nI\'d like to say Lord, from the start\r\nThank You for breaking through my heart!\r\nThank You for tearing every chain apart.\r\nWhen I was lost You made a way.\r\nYou turned the darkest night to day.\r\nYou are my joy and Lord I\'d like to say.\r\n~Chorus\r\nNobody fills my heart like Jesus.\r\nNobody thrills me like You do.\r\nO, nobody fills my heart like Jesus.\r\nNobody Lord, but You\r\nNobody but You!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen I am weak, my Lord, You\'re strong.\r\nLoving me even when I\'m wrong\r\nLord, You are my salvation and my song.\r\nEvery day I\'ll make the choice\r\nJust listening, following Your voice\r\nBeing with You I can\'t help but rejoice.\r\n', '', '1992 Shepherds Heart Music, Inc.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/0d1paMyCnEo', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I\'d like to say Lord, from the start Thank You for breaking through my heart! Thank You for tearing every chain apart. When I was lost You made a way. You turned the darkest night to day. You are my joy and Lord I\'d like to say. Nobody fills my heart like Jesus. Nobody thrills me like You do. O, nobody fills my heart like Jesus. Nobody Lord, but You Nobody but You! When I am weak, my Lord, You\'re strong. Loving me even when I\'m wrong Lord, You are my salvation and my song. Every day I\'ll make the choice Just listening, following Your voice Being with You I can\'t help but rejoice.).'),
	(28, 'Who Can Satisfy My Soul Like You', 'Dennis Jernigan.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWho can satisfy my soul like You?\r\nWho, on earth, could comfort me\r\nAnd love me like You do?\r\nWho could ever be more faithful, true?\r\nI will trust in You!\r\nI will trust in You, my God!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLiving Water rain down Your life on me\r\nCleansing me, refreshing me\r\nWith life abundantly\r\nRiver full of life, I\'ll go where You lead\r\nI will trust in You!\r\nLord, I will trust in You, My God!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere is a Fountain who is a King.\r\nVictorious Warrior and Lord of everything.\r\nMy Rock, my Shelter, my very own\r\nBlessed Redeemer\r\nWho reigns upon the throne.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWho could ever be more faithful, true?\r\nLord Jesus, Lord Jesus,\r\nLord Jesus, there\'s none but You.\r\n', '', ' 1989 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, Inc., c/o Northstar Ltd. ', '', '', 'Who can satisfy my soul like You? Who, on earth, could comfort me And love me like You do? Who could ever be more faithful, true? I will trust in You! I will trust in You, my God! Living Water rain down Your life on me Cleansing me, refreshing me With life abundantly River full of life, I\'ll go where You lead I will trust in You! Lord, I will trust in You, My God! There is a Fountain who is a King. Victorious Warrior and Lord of everything. My Rock, my Shelter, my very own Blessed Redeemer Who reigns upon the throne. Who could ever be more faithful, true? Lord Jesus, Lord Jesus, Lord Jesus, there\'s none but You.'),
	(29, 'You You Are God', 'Walker Beach. ', '~Verse 1\r\nHere I am, I\'ve come to find You\r\nHere I am to see Your grace\r\nTo bring to You an offering\r\nI have to ask myself one thing\r\nHow can I do anything\r\nBut praise, I praise\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHere I am, I\'ve come to thank You\r\nHere I am, a life You\'ve changed\r\nBecause You gave Your life for me\r\nYou crucified Your Son for me\r\nHow can I do anything\r\nBut praise, I praise\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou, You are God\r\nYou are Lord\r\nYou are all I\'m living for\r\nYou are King of everything\r\nI want my life to praise You\r\n', '', '2003 Walker Beach/Gateway', 'hhttps://www.youtube.com/v/p0ubulj53bs', '<a href="https://geo.itunes.apple.com/ca/album/you-you-are-god/id606823438?i=606823759&app=itunes" style="display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;background:url(http://linkmaker.itunes.apple.com/images/badges/en-us/badge_itunes-sm.svg) no-repeat;width:80px;height:15px;"></a>', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Here I am, I\'ve come to find You Here I am to see Your grace To bring to You an offering I have to ask myself one thing How can I do anything But praise, I praise Here I am, I\'ve come to thank You Here I am, a life You\'ve changed Because You gave Your life for me You crucified Your Son for me How can I do anything But praise, I praise You, You are God You are Lord You are all I\'m living for You are King of everything I want my life to praise You).'),
	(30, 'We Will Rejoice', 'J. Paul Williams, music by Patti Drennan. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe is mighty, creator of all things.\r\nHe made the world and all that it contains.\r\nHe is holy and righteous are His ways.\r\nLet us exalt Him.\r\nCome with songs of praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSee the wonders,\r\nGreat things that He has done.\r\nWho is like Him, the heavens are His throne.\r\nCome before Him on bended knee.\r\nCome and adore Him, God of majesty.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord forever,\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord, our God.\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord forever,\r\nWe will rejoice, rejoice in the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord forever,\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord, our God.\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord forever,\r\nWe will rejoice, rejoice in the\r\nRejoice, rejoice, rejoice in the Lord our God.\r\nWe will rejoice in the Lord forever,\r\nWe will rejoice, rejoice in the Lord,\r\nRejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1997 GlorySound', '', '', 'He is mighty, creator of all things. He made the world and all that it contains. He is holy and righteous are His ways. Let us exalt Him. Come with songs of praise. See the wonders, Great things that He has done. Who is like Him, the heavens are His throne. Come before Him on bended knee. Come and adore Him, God of majesty. We will rejoice in the Lord forever, We will rejoice in the Lord, our God. We will rejoice in the Lord forever, We will rejoice, rejoice in the Lord. We will rejoice in the Lord forever, We will rejoice in the Lord, our God. We will rejoice in the Lord forever, We will rejoice, rejoice in the Rejoice, rejoice, rejoice in the Lord our God. We will rejoice in the Lord forever, We will rejoice, rejoice in the Lord, Rejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord.'),
	(31, 'How Great Our Joy', '', '~Verse 1\r\nWhile by the sheep \r\nWe watched at night,\r\nGlad tidings brought\r\nAn angel bright.\r\n~Chorus\r\nHow great our joy! Great our joy!\r\nJoy, joy, joy, joy, joy, joy!\r\nPraise we the Lord in heav\'n on high!\r\nPraise we the Lord in heav\'n on high!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThere shall be born, So he did say,\r\nIn Bethlehem a Child today.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere shall the child lie in a stall,\r\nThis Child who shall Redeem us all.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThis gift of God we\'ll cherish well,\r\nThat ever joy our hearts shall fill.', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'While by the sheep We watched at night, Glad tidings brought An angel bright. How great our joy! Great our joy! Joy, joy, joy, joy, joy, joy! Praise we the Lord in heav\\\'n on high! Praise we the Lord in heav\\\'n on high! There shall be born, So he did say, In Bethlehem a Child today. There shall the child lie in a stall, This Child who shall Redeem us all. This gift of God we\\\'ll cherish well, That ever joy our hearts shall fill.'),
