	(32, 'All Hail King Jesus!', 'Dave Moody', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]ALL HAIL KING [D]JESUS\r\nALL HAIL EM[C]MANU[G]EL\r\nKING OF [Em]KINGS, [G]LORD OF [Em7]LORDS \r\n[A7]BRIGHT MORNING [Am7]STAR[D7]\r\nAND THROUGH[[G]]OUT ETERNI[[Dm7]]TY\r\n[G]I\'LL [G7]SING YOUR [C]PRAISES[Cm6]\r\nAND I\'LL [G]REIGN WITH [Em]YOU \r\nTHROUGH[Am7]OUT E[D7]TERNI[G]TY\r\n', '', '1981 Glory Alleluia Music', '', '', 'ALL HAIL KING JESUS ALL HAIL EMMANUEL KING OF KINGS, LORD OF LORDS BRIGHT MORNING STAR AND THROUGH]OUT ETERNI]TY I\'LL SING YOUR PRAISES AND I\'LL REIGN WITH YOU THROUGHOUT ETERNITY'),
	(33, 'We Cry Hosanna, Lord ', 'Mimi Farra', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBehold, our Savior comes,\r\nBehold the Son of our God\r\nHe offers Himself \r\nand He comes among us,\r\nA lowly servant to men.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nWe cry "Hosanna, Lord"\r\nYes, "Hosanna, Lord"\r\nYes, "Hosanna, Lord" to you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nChildren wave their palms\r\nAs the King of all kings rides by.\r\nShould we forget \r\nto praise our God,\r\nThe very stones would sing;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe comes to set us free,  \r\nHe gives us liberty.\r\nHis vict\'ry over death\r\nIs th\' eternal sign \r\nof God\'s love for us.\r\n', '', '1975,1987 Celebration Music  (Adm.by Maranatha Music)', '', '', 'Behold, our Savior comes, Behold the Son of our God He offers Himself and He comes among us, A lowly servant to men. We cry "Hosanna, Lord" Yes, "Hosanna, Lord" Yes, "Hosanna, Lord" to you. Children wave their palms As the King of all kings rides by. Should we forget to praise our God, The very stones would sing; He comes to set us free, He gives us liberty. His vict\'ry over death Is th\' eternal sign of God\'s love for us.'),
	(34, 'What A Day', 'John Chisum and George Searcy ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nToday is the day He has made,\r\nHe\'s crowned us with mercy\r\n And called us to praise;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhat a day to celebrate the love of the Lord,\r\nGiving praise drives away\r\n the cares of this world;\r\nNew ev\'ry morning,\r\nHis love is new ev\'ry day.\r\nWhat a day to celebrate.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe has provided all \r\nThe riches of His grace,\r\nWhat a day, \r\nWhat a day to celebrate!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nRejoice in the joy of the Lord,\r\nHe\'s promised us heaven \r\nAnd all it affords;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHe has supplied us \r\nWith His love forevermore,\r\nWhat a day, \r\nWhat a day to celebrate!\r\n', '', ' 1996 ThreeFold Amen Music  (ASCAP) c/o ROM Administration, 8315 Twin Lakes Drive, Mobile, AL 36695/', '', '', 'Today is the day He has made, He\'s crowned us with mercy And called us to praise; What a day to celebrate the love of the Lord, Giving praise drives away the cares of this world; New ev\'ry morning, His love is new ev\'ry day. What a day to celebrate. He has provided all The riches of His grace, What a day, What a day to celebrate! Rejoice in the joy of the Lord, He\'s promised us heaven And all it affords; He has supplied us With His love forevermore, What a day, What a day to celebrate!'),
	(35, 'Glorify Thy Name', 'Donna Adkins', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFather we love You, \r\nWe praise You, we adore You.\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\nGlorify Thy name, glorify Thy name\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJesus we love you\r\nWe praise You, we adore You.\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\nGlorify Thy name, glorify Thy name\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSpirit we love you\r\nWe praise You, we adore You.\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\nGlorify Thy name, glorify Thy name\r\nGlorify Thy name in all the earth.\r\n', '', ' 1982 Maranatha! Music', '', '', 'Father we love You, We praise You, we adore You. Glorify Thy name in all the earth. Glorify Thy name, glorify Thy name Glorify Thy name in all the earth. Jesus we love you We praise You, we adore You. Glorify Thy name in all the earth. Glorify Thy name, glorify Thy name Glorify Thy name in all the earth. Spirit we love you We praise You, we adore You. Glorify Thy name in all the earth. Glorify Thy name, glorify Thy name Glorify Thy name in all the earth.'),
	(36, 'You Are Here', 'Kent Blanton', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe\'re gathered here once again today;\r\nWe\'ve come to bless You\r\n And seek Your holy face.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWith hearts that are hurting \r\nAnd needy of Your grace\r\nWe come and acknowledge\r\nYour presence as we say . . .\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou promised us by Your holy word,\r\nWhere two or three are gathered\r\n You will be there, too. \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHelp us not to miss You \r\nAs You walk here today\r\nAmong your precious children\r\n Who worship You and say . . . .\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nYou are here in the midst of Your church,\r\nYou are here enthroned on our praise,\r\nYou are here in glory and strength,\r\nCome and touch us with Your grace \r\nAs we say, "You are here."\r\n', '', ' 1996 Kent Blanton  ', '', '', 'We\'re gathered here once again today; We\'ve come to bless You And seek Your holy face. With hearts that are hurting And needy of Your grace We come and acknowledge Your presence as we say . . . You promised us by Your holy word, Where two or three are gathered You will be there, too. Help us not to miss You As You walk here today Among your precious children Who worship You and say . . . . You are here in the midst of Your church, You are here enthroned on our praise, You are here in glory and strength, Come and touch us with Your grace As we say, "You are here."'),
	(37, 'Show Your Power', 'Kevin Prosch', '~Intro\r\n[G] [Am] [G] [D]\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWell [G]He is the Lord and [C]He reigns on [G]high\r\n[D]He is the [G]Lord\r\nSpoke [G]into the darkness cre[C]ated the [G]light\r\n[D]He is the [G]Lord\r\nWho is [G]like unto Him never [C]ending in [G]days\r\n[D]He is the [G]Lord\r\nAnd [G]He comes in power when we [C]call on His [G]name\r\n[D]He is the [G]Lord\r\n~Chorus\r\nShow Your [G]po[C]wer\r\nOh [G]Lord our [D]God\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour gospel oh Lord is the hope for our nation\r\nYou are the Lord\r\nIts the power of God for our salvation\r\nYou are the Lord\r\nWe ask not for riches but look to the cross\r\nYou are the Lord\r\nAnd for our inheritence give us the lost\r\nYou are the Lord\r\n', '', ' 1991 Mercy Publishing , ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/rXH6RmIx9iM&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Well He is the Lord and He reigns on high He is the Lord Spoke into the darkness created the light He is the Lord Who is like unto Him never ending in days He is the Lord And He comes in power when we call on His name He is the Lord Show Your power Oh Lord our God Your gospel oh Lord is the hope for our nation You are the Lord Its the power of God for our salvation You are the Lord We ask not for riches but look to the cross You are the Lord And for our inheritence give us the lost You are the Lord'),
	(38, 'Commune With Me', 'Kirk Dearman,  C. 1981 Maranatha! Music', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCommune with me\r\nCommune with me\r\nBetween the wings of the Cherubim\r\nCommune with me \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI worship You\r\nI worship You\r\nBetween the wings of the Cherubim\r\nI worship You\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI\'ll meet You there\r\nI\'ll meet You there\r\nBetween the wings of the Cherubim\r\nI\'ll meet You there\r\n', '', ' 1981 Maranatha! Music', '', '', 'Commune with me Commune with me Between the wings of the Cherubim Commune with me I worship You I worship You Between the wings of the Cherubim I worship You I\'ll meet You there I\'ll meet You there Between the wings of the Cherubim I\'ll meet You there'),
	(39, 'One God', 'Bob Fitts', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAnd thou shalt love the Lord thy God\r\nWith all thy heart, with all thy might;\r\nAnd give Him glory, King of glory,\r\nIn His ways delight.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere is no other Savior,\r\nNo other life Redeemer;\r\nWe give our all to praise You\r\nAnd lift our voice in declaration.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHear, O Israel, the Lord, thy God\r\nIs one God, Hallelujah!  \r\n', '', 'S.,', '', '', 'And thou shalt love the Lord thy God With all thy heart, with all thy might; And give Him glory, King of glory, In His ways delight. There is no other Savior, No other life Redeemer; We give our all to praise You And lift our voice in declaration. Hear, O Israel, the Lord, thy God Is one God, Hallelujah!'),
