sp\'rate cry, And He saw my past Through merciful eyes. Whatever you\'ve done, You can\'t go too far That His eyes of mercy Can\'t see where you are; Sin had stolen my dignity And all my self-esteem; But I was made brand new again, When mercy looked at me. He loves you too much To leave you alone, You\'re flesh of His flesh And bone of His bone. And His heart cries out For your heart today, See yourself through His eyes And then you can say).'),
	(42, 'Father Of Lights', 'John Barnett', '[A]Father of lights, You de[D]light in Your ch[A]ildren\r\n[A]Father of lights, You de[D]light in Your ch[A]ildren\r\n~Chorus\r\nEvery [A]good and perfect [E]gift comes from You[D]\r\nEvery [A]good and perfect [E]gift comes from You[D]\r\nEvery [A]good and perfect [E]gift comes from You[D]\r\nFather of [A]lights[D] [A] [D]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[A]Father of lights, You never cha[D]nge\r\nYou have no tu[A]rning\r\n[A]Father of lights, You never cha[D]nge\r\nYou have no tu[A]rning\r\n~Guitar Solo\r\n[D]  [A]  [D]  [A]\r\n[F#m]  [D]  [A]\r\n[G]  [D]\r\n', '', ' 1991 Mercy Publishing;', '', '', 'Father of lights, You delight in Your children Father of lights, You delight in Your children Every good and perfect gift comes from You Every good and perfect gift comes from You Every good and perfect gift comes from You Father of lights Father of lights, You never change You have no turning Father of lights, You never change You have no turning'),
	(43, 'The Welcome Song', 'Kent Blanton. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWelcome, welcome,\r\nWe\'re so glad you\'re here this morning\r\nWelcome, welcome,\r\nMay God bless you today.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMay he reveal His love, reveal His truth\r\nReveal how much He cares for you,\r\nMy friend\r\nOh may He fill you up and make you whole\r\nAnd cause His face to shine on You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGod bless you today\r\nOh I bless you today\r\nWe bless you today\r\nMay God bless you today.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Kent Blanton.', '', '', 'Welcome, welcome, We\'re so glad you\'re here this morning Welcome, welcome, May God bless you today. May he reveal His love, reveal His truth Reveal how much He cares for you, My friend Oh may He fill you up and make you whole And cause His face to shine on You. God bless you today Oh I bless you today We bless you today May God bless you today.'),
	(44, 'Onward Christian Soldiers', 'Sabine Baring-Gould; Music by Arthur S. Sullivan', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nOnward, Christian soldiers,\r\nMarching as to war,\r\nWith the cross of Jesus\r\nGoing on before!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlory, laud and honor\r\nUnto Christ the King\r\nThis thru countless ages\r\nMen and angels sing. \r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nChrist, the royal Master,\r\nLeads against the foe;\r\nForward into battle\r\nSee His banners go!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAt the sign of triumph\r\nSatan\'s host doth flee;\r\nOn, then, Christian soldiers,\r\nOn to victory!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHell\'s foundations quiver\r\nAt the shout of praise;\r\nBrother, lift your voices,\r\nLoud your anthems raise!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nLike a mighty army\r\nMoves the Church of God,\r\nBrothers, we are treading\r\nWhere the saints have trod.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nWe are not divided,\r\nAll one body we -\r\nOne in hope and doctrine,\r\nOne in charity.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nOnward, then ye people,\r\nJoin our happy throng;\r\nBlend with ours your voices\r\nIn the triumph song.\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 12\r\nOnward, Christian soldiers\r\nMarching as to war,\r\nWith the cross of Jesus\r\nGoing on before.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Onward, Christian soldiers, Marching as to war, With the cross of Jesus Going on before! Glory, laud and honor Unto Christ the King This thru countless ages Men and angels sing. Christ, the royal Master, Leads against the foe; Forward into battle See His banners go! At the sign of triumph Satan\'s host doth flee; On, then, Christian soldiers, On to victory! Hell\'s foundations quiver At the shout of praise; Brother, lift your voices, Loud your anthems raise! Like a mighty army Moves the Church of God, Brothers, we are treading Where the saints have trod. We are not divided, All one body we - One in hope and doctrine, One in charity. Onward, then ye people, Join our happy throng; Blend with ours your voices In the triumph song. Onward, Christian soldiers Marching as to war, With the cross of Jesus Going on before.'),
	(46, 'We Bow Down', 'Twila Paris', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]You are Lord of [F]creation and [G]Lord of my [C]life\r\n[G]Lord of the land and the seas\r\nYou were [C]Lord of the [F]heavens be[G]fore there was [Am]time\r\nAnd [F]Lord of all [G]lords you will [C]be\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C]We bow [F]down and we [G]worship you, [C]Lord\r\nWe bow [F]down and we [G]worship you, [C]Lord\r\nWe bow [F]down and we [G]worship you, [C]Lord\r\n[F]Lord of all [G]lords you will [C]be\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[C]You are king of [F]creation and [G]king of my [C]life\r\n[G]King of the land and the sea\r\nYou were [C]king of the [F]heavens be[G]fore there was [Am]time\r\nAnd [F]King of all [G]Kings you will [C]be\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C]We bow [F]down and we [G]crown you the [C]king\r\nWe bow [F]down and we [G]crown you the [C]king\r\nwe bow [F]down and we [G]crown you the [C]king\r\n[F]King of all [G]Kings you will [C]be', '', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/1rjmBNKk-4w', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/we-bow-down/id17328291?i=17328252&uo=4" target="itunes_store">We Bow Down - Twila Paris - Greatest Hits</a>', 'You are Lord of creation and Lord of my life Lord of the land and the seas You were Lord of the heavens before there was time And Lord of all lords you will be We bow down and we worship you, Lord We bow down and we worship you, Lord We bow down and we worship you, Lord Lord of all lords you will be You are king of creation and king of my life King of the land and the sea You were king of the heavens before there was time And King of all Kings you will be We bow down and we crown you the king We bow down and we crown you the king we bow down and we crown you the king King of all Kings you will be'),
	(47, 'What A Friend I\'ve Found', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhat a Friend I\'ve found,\r\ncloser than a brother;\r\nI have felt Your touch,\r\nmore intimate than lovers.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhat a hope I\'ve found,\r\nMore faithful than a mother;\r\nIt would break my heart\r\nTo ever lose each other.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, Jesus,\r\nJesus, Friend forever.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'What a Friend I\'ve found, closer than a brother; I have felt Your touch, more intimate than lovers. What a hope I\'ve found, More faithful than a mother; It would break my heart To ever lose each other. Jesus, Jesus, Jesus, Friend forever.'),
	(48, 'Scripture Isaiah 9', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIsaiah 7:14\r\n\r\nTherefore the Lord himself will give you a sign: The virgin will be with child and will give birth to a son, and will call him Immanuel.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLuke 2:1-7\r\nIn those days Caesar Augustus issued a decree that a census should be taken of the entire Roman world. (This was the first census that took place while Quirinius was governor of Syria.) And everyone went to his own town to register. \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nSo Joseph also went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Judea, to Bethlehem the town of David, because he belonged to the house and line of David. He went there to register with Mary, who was pledged to be married to him and was expecting a child. \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nWhile they were there, the time came for the baby to be born, and she gave birth to her firstborn, a son. She wrapped him in cloths and placed him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\n"The Word of the Lord."\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\nCongregation:  "Thanks be to God."\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Isaiah 7:14 Therefore the Lord himself will give you a sign: The virgin will be with child and will give birth to a son, and will call him Immanuel. Luke 2:1-7 In those days Caesar Augustus issued a decree that a census should be taken of the entire Roman world. (This was the first census that took place while Quirinius was governor of Syria.) And everyone went to his own town to register. So Joseph also went up from the town of Nazareth in Galilee to Judea, to Bethlehem the town of David, because he belonged to the house and line of David. He went there to register with Mary, who was pledged to be married to him and was expecting a child. While they were there, the time came for the baby to be born, and she gave birth to her firstborn, a son. She wrapped him in cloths and placed him in a manger, because there was no room for them in the inn. "The Word of the Lord." Congregation:  "Thanks be to God."'),
	(49, 'All My Heart', 'Kent Blanton. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLong time ago I heard Your voice\r\nAs You called me by my name\r\nYou said, "Child, I love you so much\r\nThat I died and took your blame."\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n"Believe in me and you will find\r\nThat I\'ll give you a brand new start."\r\nSo I chose to receive his precious gift\r\nAnd in turn I gave Him my heart.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAs time went on I let other things\r\nCreep in and take a hold\r\nCares of this life, worldly desires\r\nTurned the warmth inside to cold\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n"You can\'t serve two masters," He said,\r\n"You must choose and make up your mind."\r\n"I want to reign on the throne of your life,\r\nNot be pushed aside one more time."\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSo I remembered from the past\r\nThe sweetness of His love\r\nThe joy I\'d known deep in my heart,\r\nThe sound of His voice from above\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThen I chose to lay aside my pride\r\nAnd humble myself anew\r\nGot down on my knees and cried aloud,\r\n"O Father, how I need You!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nIf abundant life you want each day\r\nThen you must make a choice\r\nTo lay down your life and follow Christ,\r\nListen obey His voice.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nNothing else can fill the void\r\nHe created down deep inside\r\nBut to those who hear His voice and choose,\r\nHe will give eternal life.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nAll my heart, the only thing that matters\r\nAll my heart, nothing else will do.\r\nAll my heart, this is what He longs for,\r\nSo I gave to Him all my heart.\r\n', '', ' 2004 Kent Blanton.', '', '', 'Long time ago I heard Your voice As You called me by my name You said, "Child, I love you so much That I died and took your blame." "Believe in me and you will find That I\'ll give you a brand new start." So I chose to receive his precious gift And in turn I gave Him my heart. As time went on I let other things Creep in and take a hold Cares of this life, worldly desires Turned the warmth inside to cold "You can\'t serve two masters," He said, "You must choose and make up your mind." "I want to reign on the throne of your life, Not be pushed aside one more time." So I remembered from the past The sweetness of His love The joy I\'d known deep in my heart, The sound of His voice from above Then I chose to lay aside my pride And humble myself anew Got down on my knees and cried aloud, "O Father, how I need You!" If abundant life you want each day Then you must make a choice To lay down your life and follow Christ, Listen obey His voice. Nothing else can fill the void He created down deep inside But to those who hear His voice and choose, He will give eternal life. All my heart, the only thing that matters All my heart, nothing else will do. All my heart, this is what He longs for, So I gave to Him all my heart.'),
	(50, 'I Love To Praise Him', '', '~Verse 1\r\nI love to praise Him,\r\nI love to praise Him,\r\nI love to praise Him,\r\nAnd lift up His holy name.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSinging hallelujah,\r\nSinging hallelujah,\r\nSinging hallelujah\r\nUnto Jesus, our Lord;\r\nWe exalt Him on high.\r\n', '', '1983 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music c/oIntegrity Music, Inc.', '', '', 'I love to praise Him, I love to praise Him, I love to praise Him, And lift up His holy name. Singing hallelujah, Singing hallelujah, Singing hallelujah Unto Jesus, our Lord; We exalt Him on high.'),
	(51, 'Lord, Release Your Fire', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord, release Your fire into my life;\r\nLet it burn bright, let it burn strong.\r\nConsume the things within\r\nThat are not of You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord I want to make a difference,\r\nI want to see things change.\r\nJesus my Lord be patient with me.\r\nPlease take me on at any cost,\r\nI want to pay the price.\r\nJesus my Lord!  Jesus my Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd all that\'s good, and all that\'s pure.\r\nLord, now empower:\r\nSpark turn to flame.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nLord, release Your fire;\r\nBring to an end,\r\nThe greater loves that come before You.\r\nAnd teach me how to pray\r\nAnd seek Your face.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHelp me to hear Your shepherd\'s voice;\r\nLord, hear my cry,\r\nI\'m crying to You.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Lord, release Your fire into my life; Let it burn bright, let it burn strong. Consume the things within That are not of You. Lord I want to make a difference, I want to see things change. Jesus my Lord be patient with me. Please take me on at any cost, I want to pay the price. Jesus my Lord!  Jesus my Lord. And all that\'s good, and all that\'s pure. Lord, now empower: Spark turn to flame. Lord, release Your fire; Bring to an end, The greater loves that come before You. And teach me how to pray And seek Your face. Help me to hear Your shepherd\'s voice; Lord, hear my cry, I\'m crying to You.'),
	(52, 'Bless His Holy Name', 'Andrae Crouch, c. 1973 Lexicon Music', '~Verse 1\r\nBless the Lord, O my soul,\r\nAnd all that is within me,\r\nBless His holy Name.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe has done great things,\r\nHe has done great things,\r\nHe has done great things,\r\nBless His Holy Name.\r\n', '', ' 1973 Lexicon Music', 'https://youtu.be/tp-UOjstQ1o', '<a href="https://geo.itunes.apple.com/us/album/bless-his-holy-name/id253192784?i=253194463&app=music" style="display:inline-block;overflow:hidden;background:url(http://linkmaker.itunes.apple.com/images/badges/en-us/badge_music-lrg.svg) no-repeat;width:165px;height:40px;"></a>', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Bless the Lord, O my soul, And all that is within me, Bless His holy Name. He has done great things, He has done great things, He has done great things, Bless His Holy Name.).'),
	(54, 'It\'s Your Blood', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIt\'s Your blood that cleanses me\r\nIt\'s Your blood that gives me life\r\nIt\'s Your blood that took my place\r\nIn redeeming sacrifice\r\nWashes me, whiter than snow\r\nThan the snow, my Jesus\r\nGod\'s precious sacrifice.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIt\'s Your love that cleanses me\r\nIt\'s Your love that gives me life\r\nIt\'s Your love that took my place\r\nIn redeeming sacrifice\r\nWashes me, whiter than snow\r\nThan the snow, my Jesus\r\nGod\'s precious sacrifice.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'It\'s Your blood that cleanses me It\'s Your blood that gives me life It\'s Your blood that took my place In redeeming sacrifice Washes me, whiter than snow Than the snow, my Jesus God\'s precious sacrifice. It\'s Your love that cleanses me It\'s Your love that gives me life It\'s Your love that took my place In redeeming sacrifice Washes me, whiter than snow Than the snow, my Jesus God\'s precious sacrifice.'),
	(55, 'Victory In Jesus', 'Eugene M. Bartlett, Sr.  Public Domain', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI heard an old, old story \r\nHow a Savior came from glory,\r\nHow He gave His life\r\nOn Calvary \r\nTo save a wretch like me;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI heard about His groaning,\r\n Of His precious\r\nBlood\'s atoning,\r\nThen I repented of my sins\r\n And won the victory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO victory in Jesus,\r\nMy Savior, forever,\r\nHe sought me and bo\'t me \r\nWith His redeeming blood;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI heard about His healing,\r\n Of His cleansing\r\nPow\'r revealing,\r\nHow He made the lame\r\nTo walk again\r\n And caused the blind to see;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd then I cried, "Dear Jesus,\r\n Come and heal\r\nMy broken spirit,"\r\nAnd somehow Jesus came\r\n And bro\'t to me the victory.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI heard about a mansion\r\n He has built for me in glory,\r\nAnd I heard about\r\nThe streets of gold \r\nBeyond the crystal sea;\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAbout the angels singing, \r\nAnd the old redemption story,\r\nAnd some sweet day\r\nI\'ll sing up there \r\nThe song of victory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nHe loved me ere I knew Him,\r\n and all my love is due Him, \r\nHe plunged me to victory \r\nbeneath the cleansing flood.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I heard an old, old story How a Savior came from glory, How He gave His life On Calvary To save a wretch like me; I heard about His groaning, Of His precious Blood\'s atoning, Then I repented of my sins And won the victory. O victory in Jesus, My Savior, forever, He sought me and bo\'t me With His redeeming blood; I heard about His healing, Of His cleansing Pow\'r revealing, How He made the lame To walk again And caused the blind to see; And then I cried, "Dear Jesus, Come and heal My broken spirit," And somehow Jesus came And bro\'t to me the victory. I heard about a mansion He has built for me in glory, And I heard about The streets of gold Beyond the crystal sea; About the angels singing, And the old redemption story, And some sweet day I\'ll sing up there The song of victory. He loved me ere I knew Him, and all my love is due Him, He plunged me to victory beneath the cleansing flood.'),
