	(65, 'Thou Art Worthy', 'Pauline Michael Mills', '[A]Thou art w[A7]orthy, T[D]hou art worthy, [A]thou art [F#m7]worthy, O L[Bm]ord.[E]\r\n[A]Thou art w[A7]orthy, [D]to receive g[B7]lory, [A]glory and [E7sus]honor a[E7]nd p[A]ower.\r\n~\r\nFor [Bm7]Thou hast cre[E7]ated, hast [A]all things cre[F#m]ated.\r\nFor [Bm7]Thou hast cre[E7]ated all th[A]ings, and for Thy pl[A7]easure, t[D]hey are cre[Dm6]ated.\r\nT[A]hou art [E7sus]worthy [E7]O Lo[A]rd.\r\n', '', '1963, 1975 Fred Bock Music Co., USA', '', '', 'Thou art worthy, Thou art worthy, thou art worthy, O Lord. Thou art worthy, to receive glory, glory and honor and power. For Thou hast created, hast all things created. For Thou hast created all things, and for Thy pleasure, they are created. Thou art worthy O Lord.'),
	(66, 'To God Be The Glory', 'Fannie J. Crosby  and William H. Doane.', '{t:To God Be the Glory!}\r\nTo God be the glory! great things he hath done;\r\nSo loved he the world that he gave us his Son;\r\nWho yielded his life an atonement for sin,\r\nAnd opened the life-gate that all may go in.\r\n{soc}\r\nPraise the Lord, praise the Lord!\r\nLet the earth hear his voice;\r\nPraise the Lord, praise the Lord!\r\nLet the people rejoice:\r\nO come to the Father, through Jesus the Son,\r\nAnd give him the glory; great things he hath done!\r\n{eoc}\r\n\r\nO perfect redemption, the purchase of blood!\r\nTo ev\'ry believer the promise of God;\r\nThe vilest offender who truly believes\r\nThat monment from Jesus a pardon receives.\r\n\r\nGreat things he hath taught us, great things he hath done,\r\nAnd great our rejoicing through Jesus the Son;\r\nBut purer, and higher, and greater will be\r\nOur wonder, our rapture, when Jesus we see.\r\n\r\n{c:Text: Frances Jane van Alstyne (Fanny J. Crosby), 1875}\r\n{c:Music: William Howard Doane, 1875}\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/QZtPx9npoGQ', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/to-god-be-the-glory/id148268873?i=148268878&uo=4" target="itunes_store">To God Be The Glory - Break Through</a>', 'To God be the glory! great things he hath done; So loved he the world that he gave us his Son; Who yielded his life an atonement for sin, And opened the life-gate that all may go in. Praise the Lord, praise the Lord! Let the earth hear his voice; Praise the Lord, praise the Lord! Let the people rejoice: O come to the Father, through Jesus the Son, And give him the glory; great things he hath done! O perfect redemption, the purchase of blood! To ev\'ry believer the promise of God; The vilest offender who truly believes That monment from Jesus a pardon receives. Great things he hath taught us, great things he hath done, And great our rejoicing through Jesus the Son; But purer, and higher, and greater will be Our wonder, our rapture, when Jesus we see.'),
	(67, 'Forever Grateful', 'Mark Altrogge, c. 1985 People of Destiny Music', '~Verse 1\r\nYou did not wait for me to draw near to You\r\nBut You clothed Yourself with frail humanity;\r\nYou did not wait for me to cry out to You\r\nBut You let me hear Your voice calling me.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd I\'m forever grateful to You\r\nI\'m forever grateful for the cross;\r\nI\'m forever grateful to You\r\nThat You came to seek and save the lost.\r\n', '', ' 1985 People of Destiny Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/ffsQKJwKJnw', '', 'You did not wait for me to draw near to You But You clothed Yourself with frail humanity; You did not wait for me to cry out to You But You let me hear Your voice calling me. And I\'m forever grateful to You I\'m forever grateful for the cross; I\'m forever grateful to You That You came to seek and save the lost.'),
	(68, 'Diamonds And Pearls', 'R. Rife. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nDiamonds and pearls, amethyst afternoon,\r\nWinter clear - a pastel sky.\r\nThis my world, if for an afternoon,\r\nPuts the colour in my eyes.\r\nAnd it\'s so fine, fine, fine.\r\nAnd it\'s all mine, mine, mine.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLighter than air,\r\nJust like a Mozart string quartet,\r\nI trip along.\r\nI\'ll do as I dare, singing a carefree song,\r\nAnd strum the heart of my guitar,\r\nAnd it\'s so fine, fine, fine.\r\nAnd it\'s all mine, mine, mine.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThink I can see it - coming at the right time,\r\nFilling up my senses, a dollar for a dime.\r\nAnd if you\'re askin\' me how I feel\r\nI\'ll tell you no lies.\r\nAsk me to touch the sky\r\nI\'ll just tell you that it\'s my size\r\nIt\'s God up above bringing life to my soul.\r\n', '', ' 1992 Rob Rife.', '', '', 'Diamonds and pearls, amethyst afternoon, Winter clear - a pastel sky. This my world, if for an afternoon, Puts the colour in my eyes. And it\'s so fine, fine, fine. And it\'s all mine, mine, mine. Lighter than air, Just like a Mozart string quartet, I trip along. I\'ll do as I dare, singing a carefree song, And strum the heart of my guitar, And it\'s so fine, fine, fine. And it\'s all mine, mine, mine. Think I can see it - coming at the right time, Filling up my senses, a dollar for a dime. And if you\'re askin\' me how I feel I\'ll tell you no lies. Ask me to touch the sky I\'ll just tell you that it\'s my size It\'s God up above bringing life to my soul.'),
	(69, 'Make Us A House Of Prayer', 'Daniel Brymer', '~Verse 1\r\nMake us a house of prayer,\r\nThat we might meet You there,\r\nOn behalf of the nations;\r\nA dying generation.\r\nMake us a house of prayer.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO Lord, teach us to pray\r\nUnceasingly, night and day!\r\nMake our intercession,\r\nFor You, a mighty weapon!\r\nO Lord, teach us to pray.\r\n', '', '1990 GRACE! Music.', '', '', 'Make us a house of prayer, That we might meet You there, On behalf of the nations; A dying generation. Make us a house of prayer. O Lord, teach us to pray Unceasingly, night and day! Make our intercession, For You, a mighty weapon! O Lord, teach us to pray.'),
	(70, 'Come Be Enthroned On My Praise!', 'Dennis Jernigan ', '~Verse 1\r\nCome be enthroned on my praise!\r\nAlmighty God!\r\nCome in majesty!\r\nCome and reign in me!\r\nBy Your staff and Your rod!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCome be enthroned on my praise!\r\nAlmighty God!\r\nCome in majesty! In authority!\r\nI will worship Your Holy royalty!\r\nCome be enthroned on my praise!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nCome in majesty! In authority!\r\nI will worship Your Holy royalty!\r\nCome be enthroned on my praise!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHail to the King! \r\n', '', '1989 Shepherds Heart Music, c/northstar Ltd., ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/UKlNvYn-FNY', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Come be enthroned on my praise! Almighty God! Come in majesty! Come and reign in me! By Your staff and Your rod! Come be enthroned on my praise! Almighty God! Come in majesty! In authority! I will worship Your Holy royalty! Come be enthroned on my praise! Come in majesty! In authority! I will worship Your Holy royalty! Come be enthroned on my praise! Hail to the King!).'),
	(72, 'We Praise Thee, O God, Our Redeemer, Creator (#16)', 'Julia Cady Cory; c. 1986 Word Music,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe praise Thee, O God, \r\nour Redeemer, Creator,\r\nIn grateful devotion, our tribute we bring;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe lay it before Thee,\r\nWe kneel and adore Thee,\r\nWe bless Thy holy Name,\r\nGlad praises we sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe worship Thee,\r\nGod of our fathers, we bless Thee\r\nThrough life\'s storm and tempest\r\nOur Guide hast Thou been;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhen perils o\'er take us,\r\nEscape Thou wilt make us,\r\nAnd with Thy help, O Lord,\r\nOur battles we win.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWith voices united, our praises we offer\r\nTo Thee, Great Jehovah,\r\nGlad anthems we raise;\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nThy strong arm will guide us,\r\nOur God is beside us,\r\nTo Thee, our Great Redeemer,\r\nForever be praise!\r\n', '', ' 1986 Word Music,', '', '', 'We praise Thee, O God, our Redeemer, Creator, In grateful devotion, our tribute we bring; We lay it before Thee, We kneel and adore Thee, We bless Thy holy Name, Glad praises we sing. We worship Thee, God of our fathers, we bless Thee Through life\'s storm and tempest Our Guide hast Thou been; When perils o\'er take us, Escape Thou wilt make us, And with Thy help, O Lord, Our battles we win. With voices united, our praises we offer To Thee, Great Jehovah, Glad anthems we raise; Thy strong arm will guide us, Our God is beside us, To Thee, our Great Redeemer, Forever be praise!'),
	(74, 'Praise Adonai', 'Paul Baloche', '~Verse 1\r\n[Bm]Who is like Him\r\nThe Lion and the L[D]amb\r\nSeated on the t[A]hrone\r\n[Bm]Mountains bow down\r\nEvery ocean roa[D]rs\r\nTo the Lord of ho[A]sts\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]Praise Adonai\r\nFrom the ri[A]sing of the sun\r\n\'Til[G] the end of every day\r\n[G]Praise Adonai\r\nAll the n[A]ations of the earth\r\nAll the [G]angels and the saints\r\nSing [Bm]praise\r\n', '', '1999 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/EZft6nWynyc&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Who is like Him The Lion and the Lamb Seated on the throne Mountains bow down Every ocean roars To the Lord of hosts Praise Adonai From the rising of the sun \\\'Til the end of every day Praise Adonai All the nations of the earth All the angels and the saints Sing praise'),
