	(76, 'One Heart', 'Kent Blanton. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe need You Lord and call out for Your help\r\nWe bow our knees and humbly pray\r\nWe confess that You alone\r\nHave mighty pow\'r to save\r\nWe seek Your face and with our voices say\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nOpen our blind eyes and let us see our sin\r\nCome with your Spirit,\r\nPurge us with Your flame\r\nChange our complacency\r\nTo passion that consumes\r\nRevive your church\r\nAnd cause us to proclaim \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBreak every snare the evil one has set\r\nMay his schemes be evident and fail\r\nRelease a wave of prayer\r\nThat swallows up the dark\r\nHelp us to overcome,\r\nLet Your Church prevail\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLet Your mighty power\r\nBe seen within Your church\r\nO Lord, we cry for You to move\r\nLet every mountain and hill be made low\r\nEvery valley raised,\r\nThe rugged places smooth\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nOne Lord, one Spirit,\r\nOne God and Father of us all.\r\nOne Body, one faith,\r\nOne purpose - to follow Christ.\r\n', '', ' 2004 Kent Blanton, ', '', '', 'We need You Lord and call out for Your help We bow our knees and humbly pray We confess that You alone Have mighty pow\'r to save We seek Your face and with our voices say Open our blind eyes and let us see our sin Come with your Spirit, Purge us with Your flame Change our complacency To passion that consumes Revive your church And cause us to proclaim Break every snare the evil one has set May his schemes be evident and fail Release a wave of prayer That swallows up the dark Help us to overcome, Let Your Church prevail Let Your mighty power Be seen within Your church O Lord, we cry for You to move Let every mountain and hill be made low Every valley raised, The rugged places smooth One Lord, one Spirit, One God and Father of us all. One Body, one faith, One purpose - to follow Christ.'),
