	(83, 'Let Your Spirit Come', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet Your Spirit come, \r\nFall upon me now; \r\nLet Your Spirit come, \r\nFall upon me now. \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLet the rain fall down,\r\nPour upon my soul; \r\nCome and wash me now, \r\nCome and make me whole. \r\n', '', ' 1989 Arise Music (a div. of Star Song)', '', '', 'Let Your Spirit come, Fall upon me now; Let Your Spirit come, Fall upon me now. Let the rain fall down, Pour upon my soul; Come and wash me now, Come and make me whole.'),
	(84, 'Draw Me Close', 'Kelly Carpenter', '~Intro\r\n[Gm] [Dm/F] [Ebmaj7] [Bb2/D]\n[Cm7] [F7sus] [F7] [Bb]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[Bb] Draw me close to you[Eb/Bb]\n[F/Bb] Never let me go[Bb]\n[F2/A] I lay it all dow[Eb2/G]n again\n[Gm9] To [Gm9/F]hear You say that [Ebmaj7]I\'m Your friend[Eb6]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[Bb] You are my desire[Eb/Bb]\n[F/Bb] No one else will do[Bb]\n[F2/A] \'Cause nothing else could take[Eb2/G] Your place\n[Gm9] To [Gm9/F]feel the warmth of Your[Ebmaj7] embrace[Eb6]\r\n~Tag\r\n[Bb/F] Help me find the way[Eb/F]\n[F]Bring me back to [Bb]you[Eb/F][F]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[Bb] You\'re all[F/Bb] I want[Eb2/Bb]\n[Bb] You\'re all[F/A] I\'ve ev[Eb2/G]er need[F7sus]ed[F7]\n[Bb] You\'re all[F/Bb] I want[Eb2/Bb]\n[F7sus] Help me know [F]You are [Bb]near\n', '', ' 1994 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/3-07PKW9PRI&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Draw me close to you Never let me go I lay it all down again To hear You say that I\'m Your friend You are my desire No one else will do \'Cause nothing else could take Your place To feel the warmth of Your embrace Help me find the way Bring me back to you You\'re all I want You\'re all I\'ve ever needed You\'re all I want Help me know You are near'),
	(85, 'Innocent', 'Mark Lee and Music by Third Day', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIt seemed like I had \r\nrun out of second chances\r\nAnd they sentenced me to die\r\nAnd I was just like a dead man walking\r\nI was running out of time\r\nBut you came to me and opened my eyes\r\nyou gave me a brand new life\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMany years have passed \r\nsince the day that I met you\r\nBut your words are still the same\r\nAnd every time I find \r\nmyself with joy or sadness\r\nI am calling out your name\r\n\'Cause you came to me \r\nand opened my eyes\r\nYou gave to me a brand new life\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI am innocent and I have been set free\r\nI no longer have chains around my feet\r\nAnd no matter where I go or what they say\r\nI am innocent\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'It seemed like I had run out of second chances And they sentenced me to die And I was just like a dead man walking I was running out of time But you came to me and opened my eyes you gave me a brand new life Many years have passed since the day that I met you But your words are still the same And every time I find myself with joy or sadness I am calling out your name \'Cause you came to me and opened my eyes You gave to me a brand new life I am innocent and I have been set free I no longer have chains around my feet And no matter where I go or what they say I am innocent'),
	(86, 'All Glory, Laud And Honor (Hymn #173)', 'Theodulph of Orleans, translated by John M. Neale, ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAll glory, laud and honor\r\nTo Thee, Redeemer, King,\r\nTo whom the lips of children\r\nMade sweet hosannas ring:\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThou art the King of Israel,\r\nThou David\'s royal Son,\r\nWho in the Lord\'s name contest,\r\nThe King and blessed One!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe company of angels\r\nAre praising Thee on high,\r\nAnd mortal men and all things\r\nCreated make reply:\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThe people of the Hebrews\r\nWith palms before Thee went:\r\nOur praise and prayer and anthems\r\nBefore Thee we present.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nTo Thee, before Thy passion,\r\nThey sang their hymns of praise;\r\nTo Thee, now high exalted,\r\nOur melody we raise:\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThou didst accept their praises\r\nAccept the praise we bring,\r\nWho in all good delightest,\r\nThou good and gracious King! \r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'All glory, laud and honor To Thee, Redeemer, King, To whom the lips of children Made sweet hosannas ring: Thou art the King of Israel, Thou David\'s royal Son, Who in the Lord\'s name contest, The King and blessed One! The company of angels Are praising Thee on high, And mortal men and all things Created make reply: The people of the Hebrews With palms before Thee went: Our praise and prayer and anthems Before Thee we present. To Thee, before Thy passion, They sang their hymns of praise; To Thee, now high exalted, Our melody we raise: Thou didst accept their praises Accept the praise we bring, Who in all good delightest, Thou good and gracious King!'),
	(87, 'Have Faith In God', 'B.B. McKinney, c. 1934 Renewal 1962 Broadman Press; ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHave faith in God\r\nWhen your pathway is lonely,\r\nHe sees and knows\r\nAll the way you have trod;\r\nNever alone are the least of His children,\r\nHave faith in God, have faith in God.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHave faith in God, He\'s on His throne;\r\nHave faith in God,\r\nHe watches o\'er His own;\r\nHe cannot fail, He must prevail;\r\nHave faith in God, have faith in God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHave faith in God\r\nWhen your pray\'rs are unanswered,\r\nYour earnest plea He will never forget;\r\nWait on the Lord,\r\nTrust His Word and be patient,\r\nHave faith in God,\r\nHe\'ll answer yet.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHave faith in God\r\nIn your pain and your sorrow;\r\nHis heart is touched\r\nWith your grief and despair;\r\nCast all your cares\r\nAnd your burdens upon Him,\r\nAnd leave them there,\r\nOh, leave them there.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHave faith in God\r\nTho all else fail about you;\r\nHave faith in God,\r\nHe provides for His own;\r\nHe cannot fail\r\nTho all kingdoms shall perish;\r\nHe rules, He reigns upon His throne.\r\n', '', ' 1934 Renewal 1962 Broadman Press; ', '', '', 'Have faith in God When your pathway is lonely, He sees and knows All the way you have trod; Never alone are the least of His children, Have faith in God, have faith in God. Have faith in God, He\'s on His throne; Have faith in God, He watches o\'er His own; He cannot fail, He must prevail; Have faith in God, have faith in God. Have faith in God When your pray\'rs are unanswered, Your earnest plea He will never forget; Wait on the Lord, Trust His Word and be patient, Have faith in God, He\'ll answer yet. Have faith in God In your pain and your sorrow; His heart is touched With your grief and despair; Cast all your cares And your burdens upon Him, And leave them there, Oh, leave them there. Have faith in God Tho all else fail about you; Have faith in God, He provides for His own; He cannot fail Tho all kingdoms shall perish; He rules, He reigns upon His throne.'),
	(88, 'Offering (Christmas Version)', 'Paul Baloche', '~Verse 1\r\nOver the skies of Bethlehem\r\nAppeared a star\r\nWhile angels sang to lowly shepherds\r\nThree wise men seeking truth\r\nTraveled from afar\r\nHoping to find the child from heaven\r\n~Pre-Chorus 1\r\nFalling on their knees\r\nThey bowed before the humble\r\nPrince of Peace\r\n~Pre-Chorus 2\r\nIt\'s only by Your blood\r\nAnd it\'s only through Your mercy\r\nLord, I come\r\n~Chorus\r\nI bring an offering of worship to my King\r\nNo one on earth deserves\r\nThe praises that I sing\r\nJesus, may You receive\r\nThe honor that You\'re due\r\nO Lord, I bring an offering to You\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe sun cannot compare\r\nTo the glory of Your love\r\nThere is no shadow in Your presence\r\nNo mortal man would dare\r\nTo stand before Your throne\r\nBefore the Holy One of Heaven\r\n', '', '2003 Integritys Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/EDsiQYBDyJ0', '<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/offering-christmas-version/id644039638?i=644039887&uo=4" target="itunes_store">Offering (Christmas Version) - Songs 4 Worship Christmas Joy</a>', 'Over the skies of Bethlehem Appeared a star While angels sang to lowly shepherds Three wise men seeking truth Traveled from afar Hoping to find the child from heaven Falling on their knees They bowed before the humble Prince of Peace It\'s only by Your blood And it\'s only through Your mercy Lord, I come I bring an offering of worship to my King No one on earth deserves The praises that I sing Jesus, may You receive The honor that You\'re due O Lord, I bring an offering to You The sun cannot compare To the glory of Your love There is no shadow in Your presence No mortal man would dare To stand before Your throne Before the Holy One of Heaven'),
	(89, 'O Come All Ye Faithful (Hymn 145)', 'John Francis Wade', '~Verse 1\r\nO [G]come, all ye [D]faithful, [G]joyful [C]and tri[G]ump[D]hant,\r\nO [Em]come ye, O [D]come ye to Be-[A7]thle[D]hem;\r\n[G]Come and be[Am7]hold [G]Him, [D]born the [Em]King of [D]angels.\r\n~Chorus\r\nO [G]come, let us [C]ad[G]ore Him, O [G]come let us [C]ad[G]ore [D]Him,\r\nO [C]come, let [A]us a[D]dore [C]Him, [G]Chri[D]st the [G]Lord.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSing, choirs of angels, sing in exultation.\r\nO sing, all ye citizens of heaven above:\r\nGlory to God, glory in the highest!\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYea, Lord, we greet Thee, born this happy morning.\r\nJesus, to Thee be all glory given;\r\nWord of the Father now in flesh appearing.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/bcJYW1oN6fw', '<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/o-come-all-ye-faithful/id291831478?i=291831513&uo=4" target="itunes_store">O Come All Ye Faithful - Peace On Earth</a>', 'O come, all ye faithful, joyful and triumphant, O come ye, O come ye to Be-thlehem; Come and behold Him, born the King of angels. O come, let us adore Him, O come let us adore Him, O come, let us adore Him, Christ the Lord. Sing, choirs of angels, sing in exultation. O sing, all ye citizens of heaven above: Glory to God, glory in the highest! Yea, Lord, we greet Thee, born this happy morning. Jesus, to Thee be all glory given; Word of the Father now in flesh appearing.'),
	(90, 'The Celebration Song', 'Brent Chambers', '~Verse\r\n[A7+]In the [Dm]presence of Your [Dm/A]people\r\n[A]I [A/C#]will [Dm]praise [A]Your n[Dm/A]ame, [D]\r\nFo[D/F#]r alo[Gm7]ne You are [C]holy\r\nent[Fmaj7]hroned on the [Bb]praises of [Gm/A]Israe[A]l.[Bb] [A]\r\n~Tag\r\nLai lai lai...\r\n~Bridge\r\nLet us ce[Dm]lebrate Your g[Dm/A]oodness \r\n[A] a[A/C#]nd Your s[Dm]teadf[A]ast l[Dm/A]ove. [D]\r\nMa[D/F#]y Your n[Gm7]ame be exa[C]lted [Fmaj7]here\r\non e[Bb]arth and in [Gm7]heaven [A7]abo[Dm]ve.\r\n', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/jTq3kLmcm3A', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(In the presence of Your people I will praise Your name, For alone You are holy enthroned on the praises of Israel. Lai lai lai... Let us celebrate Your goodness and Your steadfast love. May Your name be exalted here on earth and in heaven above.).'),
	(91, 'Let The Praises Ring', 'Lincoln Brewster. ', '~Verse 1\r\nO Lord my God in You I put my trust\r\nO Lord my God in You I put my hope\r\nO Lord my God in You I put my trust\r\nO Lord my God in You I put my hope\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO Lord my God to You I give my hands\r\nO Lord my God to You I give my feet\r\nO Lord my God to You I give my everything\r\nO Lord my God to You I give my life\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIn You, in You I find my peace\r\nIn You, in You I find my strength\r\nIn You I live and move and breathe\r\nLet everything I say and do\r\nBe founded by my faith in You\r\nI lift up holy hands and sing\r\nLet the praises ring\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLet the praises ring\r\nLet the praises ring\r\nLet the praises ring.\r\n', '', ' 2002 Integrity\'s Praise! Music. ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/wIg6RIbLz1c&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'O Lord my God in You I put my trust O Lord my God in You I put my hope O Lord my God in You I put my trust O Lord my God in You I put my hope O Lord my God to You I give my hands O Lord my God to You I give my feet O Lord my God to You I give my everything O Lord my God to You I give my life In You, in You I find my peace In You, in You I find my strength In You I live and move and breathe Let everything I say and do Be founded by my faith in You I lift up holy hands and sing Let the praises ring Let the praises ring Let the praises ring Let the praises ring.'),
	(92, 'Refiner\'s Fire', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Purif[A]y my he[Bm]art\r\nlet me be as [Em7]gold and [Asus]precio[A]us [Asus]silve[A]r\r\n[D]Purif[A]y my he[Bm]art,\r\nlet me be as [Em7]gold, [D]pure [A]gold\r\n~Chorus\r\n[D]Refi[G]ner\'s [A]fire\r\n[D]My heart\'s [G]one de[A]sire\r\nis to [D]be [A]holy\r\n[D]set apa[G]rt for [Asus]You L[A]ord.\r\nI choose to [D]be [A]holy\r\n[D]set apa[G]rt for yo[D]u my mas[A]ter,\r\n[Em]ready to[Asus] do y[A]our [G]will.   [D]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[D]Purif[A]y my h[Bm]eart,\r\ncleanse me from wit[Em7]hin and [Asus]make [A]me[Asus] holy[A].\r\n[D]Purif[A]y my h[Bm]eart,\r\ncleanse me from my [Em7]sin, d[D]eep w[A]ithin\r\n', '', '1989 Langley Vineyard Music. ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/9Y8zP34AhuU&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Purify my heart let me be as gold and precious silver Purify my heart, let me be as gold, pure gold Refiner\\\'s fire My heart\\\'s one desire is to be holy set apart for You Lord. I choose to be holy set apart for you my master, ready to do your will. Purify my heart, cleanse me from within and make me holy. Purify my heart, cleanse me from my sin, deep within'),
	(93, 'Silent Night', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]Silent night!  Holy night!\r\n[E]All is calm, [A]all is bright\r\n[D]Round yon Virgin, [A]Mother and Child!\r\n[D]Holy infant, so [A]tender and mild,\r\n[E]Sleep in heavenly [A]pe - [F#m7]ace,\r\n[A]Sleep in [E]heavenly [A]peace.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSilent night!  Holy night!\r\nShepherds quake at the sight;\r\nGlories stream from heaven afar,\r\nHeavn\'ly hosts sing Alleluia;\r\nChrist, the Saviour, is born!\r\nChrist, the Saviour, is born!\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSilent night!  Holy night!\r\nSon of God, love\'s pure light\r\nRadiant beams from thy holy face,\r\nWith the dawn of redeeming grace,\r\nJesus, Lord, at thy birth!\r\nJesus, Lord, at thy birth!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Silent night!  Holy night! All is calm, all is bright Round yon Virgin, Mother and Child! Holy infant, so tender and mild, Sleep in heavenly pe - ace, Sleep in heavenly peace. Silent night!  Holy night! Shepherds quake at the sight; Glories stream from heaven afar, Heavn\'ly hosts sing Alleluia; Christ, the Saviour, is born! Christ, the Saviour, is born! Silent night!  Holy night! Son of God, love\'s pure light Radiant beams from thy holy face, With the dawn of redeeming grace, Jesus, Lord, at thy birth! Jesus, Lord, at thy birth!'),
	(94, 'Here Am I', 'Bob Kilpatrick  c. 1987 Bob Kilpatrick Music', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAsk of me\r\nAnd I will give the nations\r\nAs an inheritance for you,\r\nAs an inheritance for you,\r\nMy children.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAsk of me\r\nAnd I will give the nations\r\nAs an inheritance for you,\r\nAsk of me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHere am I\r\nSend me to the nations\r\nAs an ambassador for me,\r\nAs an ambassador for you,\r\nMy Father.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHere am I \r\nSend me to the nations\r\nAs an ambassador for You,\r\nHere am I.\r\n', '', ' 1987 Bob Kilpatrick Music', '', '', 'Ask of me And I will give the nations As an inheritance for you, As an inheritance for you, My children. Ask of me And I will give the nations As an inheritance for you, Ask of me. Here am I Send me to the nations As an ambassador for me, As an ambassador for you, My Father. Here am I Send me to the nations As an ambassador for You, Here am I.'),
	(95, 'In His Time', 'Diane Ball, c. 1978, Maranatha! Music, USA.', '~Verse 1\r\nIn His time, in His time,\r\nHe makes all things beautiful in His time.\r\nLord, please show me every day,\r\nAs You\'re teaching me Your way,\r\nThat You do just what You say, in Your time.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIn Your time, in Your time,\r\nYou make all things beautiful in Your time.\r\nLord, my life to You I bring,\r\nMay each song I have to sing\r\nBe to You a lovely thing, in Your time.\r\n', '', ' 1978, Maranatha! Music, USA.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/Wo-rGzx2OZk', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(In His time, in His time, He makes all things beautiful in His time. Lord, please show me every day, As You\'re teaching me Your way, That You do just what You say, in Your time. In Your time, in Your time, You make all things beautiful in Your time. Lord, my life to You I bring, May each song I have to sing Be to You a lovely thing, in Your time.).'),
	(96, 'We Three Kings', 'John H. Hopkins, Jr.  Public Domain', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe three kings of Orient are\r\nBearing gifts we traverse afar\r\nField and fountain, moor and mountain\r\nFollowing yonder star.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBorn a King on Bethlehem\'s plain\r\nGold I bring to crown Him again\r\nKing forever, ceasing never\r\nOver us all to reign.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFrankincense to offer have I\r\nIncense owns a Deity nigh\r\nPrayer and praising, all men raising\r\nWorship Him, God on high.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nMyrrh is mine its bitter perfume\r\nBreathes a life of gathering gloom\r\nSorr\'wing, sighing, bleeding, dying\r\nSealed in the stone-cold tomb.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nGlorious now behold Him arise\r\nKing and God and Sacrifice\r\nAlleluia, Alleluia\r\nEarth to heaven replies.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nStar of wonder, star of night\r\nStar with royal beauty bright\r\nWestward leading, still proceeding\r\nGuide us to thy perfect light.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'We three kings of Orient are Bearing gifts we traverse afar Field and fountain, moor and mountain Following yonder star. Born a King on Bethlehem\'s plain Gold I bring to crown Him again King forever, ceasing never Over us all to reign. Frankincense to offer have I Incense owns a Deity nigh Prayer and praising, all men raising Worship Him, God on high. Myrrh is mine its bitter perfume Breathes a life of gathering gloom Sorr\'wing, sighing, bleeding, dying Sealed in the stone-cold tomb. Glorious now behold Him arise King and God and Sacrifice Alleluia, Alleluia Earth to heaven replies. Star of wonder, star of night Star with royal beauty bright Westward leading, still proceeding Guide us to thy perfect light.'),
	(97, 'Thank You Song', 'Larry Hampton, c. 1995 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO Lord, our God\r\nYou are high above the earth\r\nYou will reign forevermore\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO Lord, our God\r\nYou are greatly to be praised\r\nFor the things You have done\r\nAnd the things You will do\r\nO Lord,  there is no one like You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO Lord, our God\r\nYou are high above the earth\r\nAnd in the hearts of all Your people\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO Lord, our God\r\nYou are greatly to be praised\r\nFor the things You have done for us\r\nAnd the things You will do\r\nO Lord, there is no One like You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nSo we praise You, love and adore You\r\nThank you Lord\r\nAnd we honor You, worship before You\r\nThank you Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing. ', '', '', 'O Lord, our God You are high above the earth You will reign forevermore O Lord, our God You are greatly to be praised For the things You have done And the things You will do O Lord,  there is no one like You. O Lord, our God You are high above the earth And in the hearts of all Your people O Lord, our God You are greatly to be praised For the things You have done for us And the things You will do O Lord, there is no One like You. So we praise You, love and adore You Thank you Lord And we honor You, worship before You Thank you Lord.'),
	(100, 'Your Love For Me', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy eyes can see Your hand\r\nat every passing glance.\r\nYour glory covers all the earth and sky.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYour goodness fills my life\r\nin every circumstance.\r\nMy heart is open wide,\r\nmy hands are lifted high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou are my God and I am Your servant.\r\nI am in awe of your love for me.\r\nYour mercy flows though I don\'t deserve it.\r\nI want to shout it out:\r\n"I\'m in awe of Your love for me!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI found a deeper faith\r\nwithin Your love\'s embrace.\r\nwhere all I want is what you have for me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI\'m drinking from the cup,\r\nof pure and endless grace.\r\nMy heart is open wide,\r\nmy hands are lifted high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nMy heart is open wide\r\nMy hands are lifted high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nI want to shout it out:\r\n"I\'m in awe of Your love for me!"\r\n"I\'m in awe of Your love for me!"\r\n"I\'m in awe of Your love for me!"\r\n', '', ' 2000 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'My eyes can see Your hand at every passing glance. Your glory covers all the earth and sky. Your goodness fills my life in every circumstance. My heart is open wide, my hands are lifted high. You are my God and I am Your servant. I am in awe of your love for me. Your mercy flows though I don\'t deserve it. I want to shout it out: "I\'m in awe of Your love for me!" I found a deeper faith within Your love\'s embrace. where all I want is what you have for me. I\'m drinking from the cup, of pure and endless grace. My heart is open wide, my hands are lifted high. My heart is open wide My hands are lifted high. I want to shout it out: "I\'m in awe of Your love for me!" "I\'m in awe of Your love for me!" "I\'m in awe of Your love for me!"'),
	(101, 'We Believe', 'Graham Kendrick', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe believe in God the Father\r\nMaker of the universe\r\nAnd in Christ, His Son, our Savior\r\nCome to us by virgin birth\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus Lord of all - Lord of all (4x)\r\nWe believe He sends His Spirit\r\nOn His church with gifts of power\r\nGod, His Word of truth affirming\r\nSends us to the nations now\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe will come again in glory\r\nJudge the living and the dead\r\nEv-ery knee shall bow before Him\r\nThen must every tongue confess\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe believe He died to save us\r\nBore our sins - was crucified\r\nThen from death He rose victorious\r\nAscended to the Father\'s side\r\n', '', '1986 Make Way Music/Thank You Music/ASCAP', '', '', 'We believe in God the Father Maker of the universe And in Christ, His Son, our Savior Come to us by virgin birth Jesus Lord of all - Lord of all (4x) We believe He sends His Spirit On His church with gifts of power God, His Word of truth affirming Sends us to the nations now He will come again in glory Judge the living and the dead Ev-ery knee shall bow before Him Then must every tongue confess We believe He died to save us Bore our sins - was crucified Then from death He rose victorious Ascended to the Father\'s side'),
	(102, 'The Solid Rock (You re the Solid Rock On Which I Stand)', 'Don Harris', 'The Solid Rock\r\n\r\n\r\nChorus 1\r\nYou\'re the solid Rock on which I stand (ECHO)\r\nYou are the Christ the risen Lamb (ECHO)\r\nThe Lamb who sits upon the throne (ECHO)\r\nWith tender mercies for His own (ECHO)\r\nI praise You now O risen Lamb (ECHO)\r\n(The solid Rock on which I stand)\r\nYou\'re the solid Rock on which I stand\r\n(The solid Rock on which I stand)\r\n\r\n\r\nVerse 1\r\nDay after day I will praise Your name\r\nIn ev\'rything I will be glad\r\nFor by Your grace You saved me\r\nAnd on Your ev\'ry word I will depend\r\n\r\nCCLI Song # 862481\r\nDon Harris\r\n© 1992 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music (Admin. by Capitol CMG Publishing (IMI))\r\nFor use solely with the SongSelect Terms of Use.  All rights reserved. www.ccli.com\r\nCCLI License # 218004\r\n', '', '1992 Integritys Hosanna Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/v6a0A_-VP-E', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(The Solid Rock Chorus 1 You\'re the solid Rock on which I stand (ECHO) You are the Christ the risen Lamb (ECHO) The Lamb who sits upon the throne (ECHO) With tender mercies for His own (ECHO) I praise You now O risen Lamb (ECHO) (The solid Rock on which I stand) You\'re the solid Rock on which I stand (The solid Rock on which I stand) Verse 1 Day after day I will praise Your name In ev\'rything I will be glad For by Your grace You saved me And on Your ev\'ry word I will depend CCLI Song # 862481 Don Harris © 1992 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music (Admin. by Capitol CMG Publishing (IMI)) For use solely with the SongSelect Terms of Use.  All rights reserved. www.ccli.com CCLI License # 218004).'),
	(103, 'My Hope Is In The Lord', 'Norman J. Clayton; Descant and choral ending by Michael James. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy hope is in the Lord\r\nWho gave Himself for me,\r\nAnd paid the price of\r\nAll my sin at Calvary.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNo merit of my own\r\nHis anger to suppress,\r\nMy only hope is found\r\nIn Jesus\' righteousness.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd now for me He stands\r\nBefore the Father\'s throne,\r\nHe shows His wounded hands,\r\nAnd names me as His own.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHis grace has planned it all,\r\n\'Tis mine but to believe,\r\nAnd recognize His work\r\nOf love and Christ receive.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor me He died,\r\nFor me He lives,\r\nFor me He died,\r\nFor me He lives,\r\nAnd everlasting life and light\r\nHe freely gives.\r\nAnd everlasting life and light\r\nHe freely gives.\r\n', '', ' 1945 Norman J. Clayton; &copy; Renewed 1973, Descant and choral ending', '', '', 'My hope is in the Lord Who gave Himself for me, And paid the price of All my sin at Calvary. No merit of my own His anger to suppress, My only hope is found In Jesus\' righteousness. And now for me He stands Before the Father\'s throne, He shows His wounded hands, And names me as His own. His grace has planned it all, \'Tis mine but to believe, And recognize His work Of love and Christ receive. For me He died, For me He lives, For me He died, For me He lives, And everlasting life and light He freely gives. And everlasting life and light He freely gives.'),
	(104, 'Stand Up, Stand Up For Jesus', 'George Duffield, Jr., Music by George J. Webb.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nStand up, stand up for Jesus\r\nYe soldiers of the cross,\r\nLift on high His royal banner,\r\nIt must not suffer loss;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFrom victory unto victory\r\nHis army shall He lead,\r\nTill every foe is vanquished\r\nAnd Christ is Lord indeed.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nStand up, stand up for Jesus,\r\nThe trumpet call obey;\r\nForth to the mighty conflict\r\nIn this His glorious day,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYe that are men, now serve Him\r\nAgainst unnumbered foes;\r\nLet courage rise with danger,\r\nAnd strength to strength oppose.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nStand up, stand up for Jesus,\r\nStand in His strength alone;\r\nThe arm of flesh will fail you -\r\nYe dare not trust your own;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nPut on the gospel armor\r\nEach piece put on with prayer;\r\nWhere duty calls, or danger,\r\nBe never wanting there.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nStand up, stand up for Jesus,\r\nThe strife will not be long;\r\nThis day the noise of battle,\r\nThe next, the victor\'s song;\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nTo him who overcometh\r\nA crown of life shall be;\r\nHe with the King of glory\r\nShall reign eternally.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Word Music (a div. of Word, Inc.).  ', '', '', 'Stand up, stand up for Jesus Ye soldiers of the cross, Lift on high His royal banner, It must not suffer loss; From victory unto victory His army shall He lead, Till every foe is vanquished And Christ is Lord indeed. Stand up, stand up for Jesus, The trumpet call obey; Forth to the mighty conflict In this His glorious day, Ye that are men, now serve Him Against unnumbered foes; Let courage rise with danger, And strength to strength oppose. Stand up, stand up for Jesus, Stand in His strength alone; The arm of flesh will fail you - Ye dare not trust your own; Put on the gospel armor Each piece put on with prayer; Where duty calls, or danger, Be never wanting there. Stand up, stand up for Jesus, The strife will not be long; This day the noise of battle, The next, the victor\'s song; To him who overcometh A crown of life shall be; He with the King of glory Shall reign eternally.'),
	(105, 'What Child Is This', 'William C. Dix, Music Traditional  English Melody', '~Verse 1\r\nWhat c[Em]hild is t[G]his who l[D]aid to re[Bm]st\r\nOn M[Em]ary\'s la[Am]p is sle[B]eping?\r\nWhom [Em]angels gr[G]eet with an[D]thems sw[Bm]eet\r\nWhile she[Em]pherds wa[B]tch are k[Em]eeping?\r\n~Chorus\r\nThi[G]s, this is Chr[D]ist the King\r\nWhom s[Em]hepher[Am]ds guard and a[B]ngels sing\r\nHas[G]te, haste to br[D]ing him Laud\r\nThe b[Em]abe, the s[B7]on of M[Em]ary\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhy lies he in such mean estate\r\nWhere ox and ass are feeding?\r\nGood Christian, fear, for sinners here\r\nThe silent word is pleading\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSo br[Em]ing him in[G]cense, go[D]ld, and my[Bm]rrh\r\nCome pe[Em]asant, K[Am]ing, to ow[B]n him\r\nThe Ki[Em]ng of K[G]ings salva[D]tion b[Bm]rings\r\nLet lo[Em]ving hea[B]rts enth[Em]rone him\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'What child is this who laid to rest On Mary\'s lap is sleeping? Whom angels greet with anthems sweet While shepherds watch are keeping? This, this is Christ the King Whom shepherds guard and angels sing Haste, haste to bring him Laud The babe, the son of Mary Why lies he in such mean estate Where ox and ass are feeding? Good Christian, fear, for sinners here The silent word is pleading So bring him incense, gold, and myrrh Come peasant, King, to own him The King of Kings salvation brings Let loving hearts enthrone him'),
	(106, 'You Are My King (Amazing Love)', 'Billy James Foote.', '~Verse 1\r\nI[A]\'m fo[D]rgiven bec[E]ause You were forsaken\r\nI[A]\'m ac[D]cepted, y[E]ou were condemned\r\nI[A]\'m al[D]ive and well, Your sp[E]irit is within me\r\nBe[D]cause You d[E]ied and rose ag[A]ain\r\n~Chorus\r\n[A]Amazing love, h[D]ow can it be\r\n[A]That You, my King, should die for [E]me?\r\n[A]Amazing love, [D]I know it\'s true\r\n[A]It\'s my joy to honor Y[E]ou\r\nIn all I [D]do, [E]to honor Y[A]ou\r\n~Tag\r\n[A]You are my King\r\nJesus, Y[A]ou are my king\r\n[A]You are my King\r\n', '', ' 1999 worshiptogether.com songs (admin. by EMI Christian Music Publishing).', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/hNousF-YMHo', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/amazing-love/id115213233?i=115213215&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Hillsong - Amazing Love - Amazing Love" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'I\\\'m forgiven because You were forsaken I\\\'m accepted, you were condemned I\\\'m alive and well, Your spirit is within me Because You died and rose again Amazing love, how can it be That You, my King, should die for me? Amazing love, I know it\\\'s true It\\\'s my joy to honor You In all I do, to honor You You are my King Jesus, You are my king You are my King'),
	(107, 'Savior, Like A Shepherd Lead Us', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSavior, like a shepherd lead us,\r\nMuch we need Thy tender care;\r\nIn Thy pleasant pastures feed us,\r\nFor our use Thy folds prepare;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nThou hast bought us, Thine we are;\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nThou hast bought us, Thine we are.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe are Thine - do Thou befriend us,\r\nBe the Guardian of our way;\r\nKeep Thy flock, from sin defend us,\r\nSeek us when we go astray;\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nHear, O hear us when we pray;\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nHear, O hear us when we pray.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThou hast promised to receive us,\r\nPoor and sinful tho we be;\r\nThou hast mercy to relieve us,\r\nGrace to cleanse and pow\'r to free;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nEarly let us turn to Thee;\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus.\r\nEarly let us turn to Thee.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nEarly let us seek Thy favor,\r\nEarly let us do Thy will;\r\nBlessed Lord and only Savior\r\nWith Thy love our bosoms fill,\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nBlessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nThou hast loved us, love us still;\r\nBlessed Jeus, Blessed Jesus,\r\nThou hast loved us, love us still.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Savior, like a shepherd lead us, Much we need Thy tender care; In Thy pleasant pastures feed us, For our use Thy folds prepare; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Thou hast bought us, Thine we are; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Thou hast bought us, Thine we are. We are Thine - do Thou befriend us, Be the Guardian of our way; Keep Thy flock, from sin defend us, Seek us when we go astray; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Hear, O hear us when we pray; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Hear, O hear us when we pray. Thou hast promised to receive us, Poor and sinful tho we be; Thou hast mercy to relieve us, Grace to cleanse and pow\'r to free; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Early let us turn to Thee; Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus. Early let us turn to Thee. Early let us seek Thy favor, Early let us do Thy will; Blessed Lord and only Savior With Thy love our bosoms fill, Blessed Jesus, Blessed Jesus, Thou hast loved us, love us still; Blessed Jeus, Blessed Jesus, Thou hast loved us, love us still.'),
	(108, 'In The Garden', 'C. Austin Miles. Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI come to the garden alone,\r\nWhile the dew is still on the roses;\r\nAnd the voice if hear, falling on my ear,\r\nThe Son of God discloses.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe speaks, and the sound of His voice\r\nIs so sweet the birds hush their singing;\r\nAnd the melody that He gave to me\r\nWithin my heart is ringing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI\'d stay in the garden with Him\r\nTho the night around me be falling;\r\nBut He bids me go thru the voice of woe,\r\nHis voice to me is calling.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd He walks with me,\r\nAnd He talks with me,\r\nAnd He tells me I am His own,\r\nAnd the joy we share as we tarry there\r\nNone other has ever known.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I come to the garden alone, While the dew is still on the roses; And the voice if hear, falling on my ear, The Son of God discloses. He speaks, and the sound of His voice Is so sweet the birds hush their singing; And the melody that He gave to me Within my heart is ringing. I\'d stay in the garden with Him Tho the night around me be falling; But He bids me go thru the voice of woe, His voice to me is calling. And He walks with me, And He talks with me, And He tells me I am His own, And the joy we share as we tarry there None other has ever known.'),
	(109, 'Believe', 'Donna Lasit  c. 1999 City Bible Music', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI say on Sunday\r\nHow much I want revival\r\nBut then by Monday\r\nI can\'t even find my Bible\r\nWhere\'s the power,\r\nThe power of the cross in my life\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI\'m sick of playing the game of religion\r\nI\'m tired of losing my reason for living\r\nWhere\'s the power,\r\nThe power of the cross in my life\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI\'m not content just to walk \r\nthrough my life\r\nGiving in to the lies,\r\nWalking in compromises\r\nNow we cry out as a generation\r\nThat was lost but now is found\r\nIn the power of the cross\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe believe in You\r\nWe believe in the power\r\nOf Your Word and its truth\r\nWe believe in You\r\nSo, we lay down our cause\r\nThat our cross might be \r\nfound in You\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI\'m not satisfied oing it my own way\r\nI\'m not satisfied\r\nTo do church and walk away\r\nI\'m not satisfied,\r\nThere\'s no love in my life but You\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nI\'m not satisfied living in \r\nyesterday\'s hour\r\nI\'m not satisfied to have the form\r\nBut not the power\r\nI\'m not satisfied,\r\nLord I am crucified in You\r\n', '', ' 1999 City Bible Music', '', '', 'I say on Sunday How much I want revival But then by Monday I can\'t even find my Bible Where\'s the power, The power of the cross in my life I\'m sick of playing the game of religion I\'m tired of losing my reason for living Where\'s the power, The power of the cross in my life I\'m not content just to walk through my life Giving in to the lies, Walking in compromises Now we cry out as a generation That was lost but now is found In the power of the cross We believe in You We believe in the power Of Your Word and its truth We believe in You So, we lay down our cause That our cross might be found in You I\'m not satisfied oing it my own way I\'m not satisfied To do church and walk away I\'m not satisfied, There\'s no love in my life but You I\'m not satisfied living in yesterday\'s hour I\'m not satisfied to have the form But not the power I\'m not satisfied, Lord I am crucified in You'),
	(861, 'Even Now', 'Brent Anderson', '~Verse 1\r\nEven [D]now He\'s [A/D]waiting for [D]us\r\nTo [Em]fall on our knees and [A]worship\r\nEven [D]now He\'s [A/D]ready for [D]us\r\nTo [Em]lift up our hands to His [A]name\r\n~Chorus 1\r\nEven [G]now as our [A/G]praises go forth\r\nThe [D/F#]heavens will pour out [G2]on us\r\nAnd His [Em]glory will fill this [A]place\r\n1. even [D]now (Verse [G2]2)[A]\r\n2. even [D]now (Inst)[Asus]\r\n3. even [C/D]now (Chorus [D]2)\r\n~Verse 2\r\nEven [D]now He\'s [A/D]waiting for [D]us\r\nTo [Em]fall on our faces and [A]worship\r\nEven [D]now He\'s [A/D]ready for [D]us\r\nTo [Em]offer that sweet sacri - [A]fice (Chorus 1)\r\n~Chorus 2\r\nEven [G]now as our [A/G]praises go forth\r\nThe [D/F#]heavens will pour out [G2]on us\r\nAnd His [Em]glory will fill this [A]place\r\nAnd His [Em]glory will fill this [A]place\r\nWe need Your [Em]glory in this [Asus]place\r\nEven [D]now\r\n', '', '2007 Brent D. Anderson', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/RtdkMAx8GDg&hl=en&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=290198997&id=290198984&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Cape First Worship with Brent Anderson - To Know Your Heart (Disc. 1) - Even Now" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Even now He\\\'s waiting for us To fall on our knees and worship Even now He\\\'s ready for us To lift up our hands to His name Even now as our praises go forth The heavens will pour out on us And His glory will fill this place 1. even now (Verse 2) 2. even now (Inst) 3. even now (Chorus 2) Even now He\\\'s waiting for us To fall on our faces and worship Even now He\\\'s ready for us To offer that sweet sacri - fice (Chorus 1) Even now as our praises go forth The heavens will pour out on us And His glory will fill this place And His glory will fill this place We need Your glory in this place Even now'),
	(111, 'Jesus All For Jesus', 'Robin Mark', '~Verse 1\r\nJesus, all for Jesus,\r\nAll I am and have and ever hope to be;\r\nJesus, all for Jesus,\r\nAll I am and have and ever hope to be.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAll of my ambitions, hopes, and plans\r\nI surrender these into Your hands.\r\nAll of my ambitions, hopes, and plans\r\nI surrender these into Your hands.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor it\'s only in Your will that I am free,\r\nFor it\'s only in Your will that I am free.\r\nJesus, all for Jesus,\r\nAll I am and have and ever hope to be.\r\n', '', '1991 Word\'s Spirit of Praise Music (admin. by Maranatha! Music), c/o The Copyright Company', '', '', 'Jesus, all for Jesus, All I am and have and ever hope to be; Jesus, all for Jesus, All I am and have and ever hope to be. All of my ambitions, hopes, and plans I surrender these into Your hands. All of my ambitions, hopes, and plans I surrender these into Your hands. For it\\\'s only in Your will that I am free, For it\\\'s only in Your will that I am free. Jesus, all for Jesus, All I am and have and ever hope to be.'),
