	(114, 'Jesus My Saviour', 'Jack W. Hayford', '~Verse 1\r\nJesus my saviour I rise to praise You.\r\nJesus my master, to You I bow.\r\nJesus my leader, this day I\'ll follow.\r\nJesus my captain, calling me now.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord I now listen, tuned to Your Spirit.\r\nLord I am watching, looking above.\r\nLord I am waiting, speak, I will answer.\r\nLord I am open, filled with Your love.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nChrist be my conqueror, victor in battle.\r\nChrist be my freedom, truth making free.\r\nChrist my provider, bread for today\'s needs.\r\nChrist be all fullness, overflow me.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSon of Salvation, God of all glory.\r\nFountain of life, the wellspring of joy.\r\nLord Jesus Christ now King above all Kings,\r\nYour highest praises, I now employ.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGlory and honour, praise, adoration,\r\nWisdom and riches, all majesty.\r\nStrength, power and blessings \r\nOf all You\'re worthy,\r\nJesus the Lamb reigns eternally.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Jesus my saviour I rise to praise You. Jesus my master, to You I bow. Jesus my leader, this day I\\\'ll follow. Jesus my captain, calling me now. Lord I now listen, tuned to Your Spirit. Lord I am watching, looking above. Lord I am waiting, speak, I will answer. Lord I am open, filled with Your love. Christ be my conqueror, victor in battle. Christ be my freedom, truth making free. Christ my provider, bread for today\\\'s needs. Christ be all fullness, overflow me. Son of Salvation, God of all glory. Fountain of life, the wellspring of joy. Lord Jesus Christ now King above all Kings, Your highest praises, I now employ. Glory and honour, praise, adoration, Wisdom and riches, all majesty. Strength, power and blessings Of all You\\\'re worthy, Jesus the Lamb reigns eternally.'),
	(115, 'Call To Me (Jeremiah Song)', 'Carol McHardy', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIn your heart, I see great strife\r\nYou don\'t know what to do\r\nBow your head, give me your life,\r\nI\'ll give you life anew.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou can stand the test\r\nYou will know my rest\r\nYou\'ll receive my best\r\nWhen you enter my rest.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIf you\'ll just\r\nCall to me, call to me\r\nI will give you rest.\r\nCall to me, call to me\r\nI will give you My best.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI\'ll show you great and unsearchable things\r\nThings you do not know\r\nI will reveal My love to you\r\nI\'ll show you where to go.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCall to me, call to me\r\nAnd I will answer you.\r\nCall to me, call to me\r\nI\'ll show you what to do.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'In your heart, I see great strife You don\'t know what to do Bow your head, give me your life, I\'ll give you life anew. You can stand the test You will know my rest You\'ll receive my best When you enter my rest. If you\'ll just Call to me, call to me I will give you rest. Call to me, call to me I will give you My best. I\'ll show you great and unsearchable things Things you do not know I will reveal My love to you I\'ll show you where to go. Call to me, call to me And I will answer you. Call to me, call to me I\'ll show you what to do.'),
	(116, 'The Blood Will Never Lose Its Power', 'Andrae Crouch.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe blood that Jesus shed for me,\r\n\'Way back on Calvary;\r\nThe blood that gives me strength\r\nFrom day to day,\r\nIt will never lose its power.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIt soothes my doubts and calms my fears,\r\nAnd it dries all my tears;\r\nThe blood that gives me strength\r\nFrom day to day,\r\nIt will never lose its power.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt reaches to the highest mountain.\r\nIt flows to the lowest valley.\r\nThe blood that gives me strength\r\nFrom day to day,\r\nIt will never lose its power.\r\n', '', ' 1966 by Manna Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'The blood that Jesus shed for me, \'Way back on Calvary; The blood that gives me strength From day to day, It will never lose its power. It soothes my doubts and calms my fears, And it dries all my tears; The blood that gives me strength From day to day, It will never lose its power. It reaches to the highest mountain. It flows to the lowest valley. The blood that gives me strength From day to day, It will never lose its power.'),
	(118, 'Revive Us Again (Hymn #295)', 'William P. Mackay and Music by John J. Husband', '~Verse 1\r\nWe praise Thee, O God,\r\nFor the Son of Thy love,\r\nFor Jesus who died\r\nAnd is now gone above.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHallelujah, Thine the glory!\r\nHallelujah, amen!\r\nHallelujah, Thine the glory!\r\nRevive us again.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe praise Thee, O God,\r\nFor Thy Spirit of light,\r\nWho has shown us our Savior\r\nAnd scattered our night.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAll glory and praise\r\nTo the Lamb that was slain\r\nWho has borne all our sins\r\nAnd has cleansed ev\'ry stain.\r\n~Chorus\r\nRevive us again\r\nFill each heart with Thy love;\r\nMay each soul be rekindled\r\nWith fire from above.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'We praise Thee, O God, For the Son of Thy love, For Jesus who died And is now gone above. Hallelujah, Thine the glory! Hallelujah, amen! Hallelujah, Thine the glory! Revive us again. We praise Thee, O God, For Thy Spirit of light, Who has shown us our Savior And scattered our night. All glory and praise To the Lamb that was slain Who has borne all our sins And has cleansed ev\\\'ry stain. Revive us again Fill each heart with Thy love; May each soul be rekindled With fire from above.'),
	(119, 'Your Name Is Jesus', 'Don Moen and Tom Brooks;', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nKing of kings and Lord of lords, \r\nCreator of all things;\r\nKing of kings and Lord of lords,\r\nLet all the nations sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYour name is Jesus, the Lord of all,\r\nYou reign in majesty, at Your feet we fall;\r\nWe lift our hands to You,\r\nO Lord we worship You,\r\nYour name is Jesus, the Lord of all.\r\n', '', ' 1991 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music; c/o Integrity Music, Inc.,', '', '', 'King of kings and Lord of lords, Creator of all things; King of kings and Lord of lords, Let all the nations sing. Your name is Jesus, the Lord of all, You reign in majesty, at Your feet we fall; We lift our hands to You, O Lord we worship You, Your name is Jesus, the Lord of all.'),
	(120, 'Be Glorified', 'Chris Tomlin, Jesse Reeves and Louie Giglio', '~Intro\r\n[G] [Csus2] [Fsus2] [Csus2]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[G]Your [Csus2]love  has [Fsus2]captured [Csus2]me.\r\n[G]Your [Csus2]grace has [D]set me free;\r\n[G]Your [Csus2]life, the [Fsus2]air i [Csus2]breathe.\r\n[Am7]     Be glorified[D] in me.\r\n~Chorus\r\n[Csus2]You set my feet to dancing\r\n[G]You set my heart on fire.\r\nIn the [Csus2]presence of a thousand kings,\r\nYou [G]are my one desire.\r\n[Csus2]and i stand before you now with [Em7]trembling [D]hands lifted [Csus2]high.\r\nBe glorified\r\n~Bridge\r\n[G]       Be glor[G/B]ified[C] in [D]me,\r\nBe glor[G/B]ified[C] in [D]me,\r\nBe glor[G/B]ified[C] in [D]me,\r\nBe glor[G/B]ified[C]\r\n', '', ' 1999 worshiptogether.com songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/PWctTVa9dVk&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Your love  has captured me. Your grace has set me free; Your life, the air i breathe. Be glorified in me. You set my feet to dancing You set my heart on fire. In the presence of a thousand kings, You are my one desire. and i stand before you now with trembling hands lifted high. Be glorified Be glorified in me, Be glorified in me, Be glorified in me, Be glorified'),
	(121, 'At The Name Of Jesus', 'Dennis L. Jernigan. ', '~Verse 1\r\nAt the name of Jesus\r\nEv\'ry knee will bow!\r\nHe is Lord! He is Lord!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAt the name of Jesus\r\nEv\'ry tongue will shout!\r\nHe is Lord! He is Lord!\r\nHe is Lord! He is Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBlessed is the Holy name!\r\nBlessed is the King who reigns!\r\nBlessed is the Holy name \r\nof Jesus!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nPraise His Holy name! \r\nPraise His Holy name!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAt Your name Lord Jesus\r\nEv\'ry knee will bow!\r\nYou are Lord! You are Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAt Your name Lord Jesus\r\nEv\'ry tongue will shout!\r\nYou are Lord! You are Lord!\r\nYou are Lord! You are Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nPraise Your Holy Name!\r\nPraise Your Holy Name!\r\n', '', ' 1988 Shepherd\'s Heart Music,', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/Qj901wSgIpQ', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(At the name of Jesus Ev\'ry knee will bow! He is Lord! He is Lord! At the name of Jesus Ev\'ry tongue will shout! He is Lord! He is Lord! He is Lord! He is Lord! Blessed is the Holy name! Blessed is the King who reigns! Blessed is the Holy name of Jesus! Praise His Holy name! Praise His Holy name! At Your name Lord Jesus Ev\'ry knee will bow! You are Lord! You are Lord! At Your name Lord Jesus Ev\'ry tongue will shout! You are Lord! You are Lord! You are Lord! You are Lord! Praise Your Holy Name! Praise Your Holy Name!).'),
	(122, 'I Sing The Mighty Power Of God', 'Isaac Watts, Music Public domain ', '~Verse 1\r\nI sing the mighty pow\'r of God, \r\nThat made the mountains rise;\r\nThat spread the flowing seas abroad,\r\nAnd built the lofty skies.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI sing the wisdom that ordained\r\n The sun to rule the day;\r\nThe moon shines full at His command, \r\nAnd all the stars obey.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI sing the goodness of the Lord,\r\nThat filled the earth with food;\r\nHe formed the creatures with His word, \r\nAnd then pronounced them good.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLord, how Thy wonders are displayed,\r\nWhere\'er I turn my eye:\r\nIf I survey the ground I tread, \r\nOr gaze upon the sky!\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere\'s not a plant or flow\'r below,\r\nBut makes Thy glories known;\r\nAnd clouds arise, and tempests blow, \r\nBy order from Thy throne;\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhile all that borrows life from Thee \r\nIs ever in Thy care,\r\nAnd ev\'rywhere that man can be,\r\nThou, God, art present there.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I sing the mighty pow\\\'r of God, That made the mountains rise; That spread the flowing seas abroad, And built the lofty skies. I sing the wisdom that ordained The sun to rule the day; The moon shines full at His command, And all the stars obey. I sing the goodness of the Lord, That filled the earth with food; He formed the creatures with His word, And then pronounced them good. Lord, how Thy wonders are displayed, Where\\\'er I turn my eye: If I survey the ground I tread, Or gaze upon the sky! There\\\'s not a plant or flow\\\'r below, But makes Thy glories known; And clouds arise, and tempests blow, By order from Thy throne; While all that borrows life from Thee Is ever in Thy care, And ev\\\'rywhere that man can be, Thou, God, art present there.'),
	(123, 'Rejoice, Ye Pure In Heart', 'Edward h. Plumptre and Music by Arthur H. Messiter', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRejoice, ye pure in heart,\r\nRejoice, give thanks, and sing;\r\nYour festal banner wave on high,\r\nThe cross of Christ your King.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nRejoice, rejoice, rejoice, rejoice,\r\nRejoice, give thanks, and sing!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWith all the angel choirs,\r\nWith all the saints on earth;\r\nPour out the strains of joy and bliss,\r\nTrue rapture, no blest mirth!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nYes, on through life\'s long path,\r\nStill chanting as we go;\r\nFrom youth to age, by night and day;\r\nIn gladness and in woe.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nStill lift your standard high,\r\nStill march in firm array;\r\nAs warriors through the darkness toil,\r\nTill dawns the golden day\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Rejoice, ye pure in heart, Rejoice, give thanks, and sing; Your festal banner wave on high, The cross of Christ your King. Rejoice, rejoice, rejoice, rejoice, Rejoice, give thanks, and sing! With all the angel choirs, With all the saints on earth; Pour out the strains of joy and bliss, True rapture, no blest mirth! Yes, on through life\'s long path, Still chanting as we go; From youth to age, by night and day; In gladness and in woe. Still lift your standard high, Still march in firm array; As warriors through the darkness toil, Till dawns the golden day'),
	(124, 'Lord, I Come', 'Billy Funk. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord, I come, take my life\r\nI offer it to You, a living sacrifice \r\nBy Your grace, by Your blood \r\nI come into the Holy of Holies.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll I want to do\r\nIs dwell in Your presence,\r\nAnd drink from the well\r\nThat never runs dry;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAll I want to see\r\nIs the light of Your glory,\r\nJust one glimpse, just one drink\r\nAnd my soul is satisfied.\r\n', '', ' 1997 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music,', '', '', 'Lord, I come, take my life I offer it to You, a living sacrifice By Your grace, by Your blood I come into the Holy of Holies. All I want to do Is dwell in Your presence, And drink from the well That never runs dry; All I want to see Is the light of Your glory, Just one glimpse, just one drink And my soul is satisfied.'),
	(125, 'Come, Christians, Join To Sing', 'Christian H. Bateman, Music:  Traditional Spanish Melody ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, Christians, join to sing,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLoud praise to Christ our King;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet all, with heart and voice,\r\nBefore His throne rejoice;\r\nPraise is His gracious choice:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCome, lift your hearts on high,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLet praises fill the sky;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nPraise yet our Christ again,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLife shall not end the strain;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe is our Guide and Friend;\r\nTo us He\'ll condescend;\r\nHis love shall never end:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nOn heaven\'s blissful shore,\r\nHis goodness we\'ll adore,\r\nSinging forevermore:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Come, Christians, join to sing, Alleluia!  Amen! Loud praise to Christ our King; Alleluia!  Amen! Let all, with heart and voice, Before His throne rejoice; Praise is His gracious choice: Alleluia!  Amen! Come, lift your hearts on high, Alleluia!  Amen! Let praises fill the sky; Alleluia!  Amen! Praise yet our Christ again, Alleluia!  Amen! Life shall not end the strain; Alleluia!  Amen! He is our Guide and Friend; To us He\'ll condescend; His love shall never end: Alleluia!  Amen! On heaven\'s blissful shore, His goodness we\'ll adore, Singing forevermore: Alleluia!  Amen!'),
	(126, 'I Will Bless The Lord At All Times', 'Daniel Gardner', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will bless the Lord at all times,\r\nBless the Lord at all times;\r\nHis praise shall continually be in my mouth\r\nI will bless the Lord at all times,\r\nBless the Lord at all times;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHis praise shall continually be in my mouth.\r\nO magnify the Lord with me\r\nAnd let us exalt His name together.\r\nI will bless the Lord at all times,\r\nBless the Lord at all times;\r\nHis praise shall continually be in my mouth.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I will bless the Lord at all times, Bless the Lord at all times; His praise shall continually be in my mouth I will bless the Lord at all times, Bless the Lord at all times; His praise shall continually be in my mouth. O magnify the Lord with me And let us exalt His name together. I will bless the Lord at all times, Bless the Lord at all times; His praise shall continually be in my mouth.'),
	(127, 'Love Devine, All Loves Excelling', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLove divine, all loves excelling, \r\nJoy of heav\'n, to earth come down;\r\nFix in us Thy humble dwelling,\r\nAll Thy faithful mercies crown.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, Thou art all compassion,\r\nPure, unbounded love Thou art;\r\nVisit us with Thy salvation, \r\nEnter ev\'ry trembling heart.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBreathe, O breathe Thy loving Spirit\r\nInto ev\'ry troubled breast!\r\nLet us all in Thee inherit, \r\nLet us find that promised rest.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThee we would be always blessing,\r\nServe Thee as Thy hosts above,\r\nPray and praise Thee without ceasing, \r\nGlory in Thy perfect love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCome, almighty to deliver, \r\nLet us all Thy life receive;\r\nSuddenly return, and  never, \r\nNevermore Thy temples leave.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nChanged from glory into glory,\r\nTill in heav\'n we take our place,\r\nTill we cast our crowns before Thee,\r\nLost in wonder, love and praise!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Love divine, all loves excelling, Joy of heav\'n, to earth come down; Fix in us Thy humble dwelling, All Thy faithful mercies crown. Jesus, Thou art all compassion, Pure, unbounded love Thou art; Visit us with Thy salvation, Enter ev\'ry trembling heart. Breathe, O breathe Thy loving Spirit Into ev\'ry troubled breast! Let us all in Thee inherit, Let us find that promised rest. Thee we would be always blessing, Serve Thee as Thy hosts above, Pray and praise Thee without ceasing, Glory in Thy perfect love. Come, almighty to deliver, Let us all Thy life receive; Suddenly return, and  never, Nevermore Thy temples leave. Changed from glory into glory, Till in heav\'n we take our place, Till we cast our crowns before Thee, Lost in wonder, love and praise!'),
	(128, 'O How He Loves You And Me', 'Kurt Kaier. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO, how He loves you and me.\r\nO, how He loves you and me;\r\nHe gave His life, \r\nWhat more could He give?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO, how he loves you;\r\nO, how He loves me;\r\nO, how He loves you and me!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nJesus to Calv\'ry did go,\r\nHis love for mankind to show;\r\nWhat He did there\r\n Brought hope from despair;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nO, how He loves you;\r\nO, how He loves me;\r\nO, how He loves you and me!\r\n', '', ' 1975 Word Music.', '', '', 'O, how He loves you and me. O, how He loves you and me; He gave His life, What more could He give? O, how he loves you; O, how He loves me; O, how He loves you and me! Jesus to Calv\'ry did go, His love for mankind to show; What He did there Brought hope from despair; O, how He loves you; O, how He loves me; O, how He loves you and me!'),
	(129, 'Let Your Spirit Rise Within Me', 'Randy Speir  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet your Spirit rise within me,\r\nLet Your Spirit rise within me.\r\nYou set my feet a dancin\'\r\nAnd my heart rejoicin\' \r\nAnd my mouth singin\' out Your praise. \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou alone are great, God,\r\nAnd worthy to be praised.\r\nYou alone are great, God,\r\nAnd worthy to be praised.\r\n', '', '1982 Integrity Hosanna! Music   ', '', '', 'Let your Spirit rise within me, Let Your Spirit rise within me. You set my feet a dancin\' And my heart rejoicin\' And my mouth singin\' out Your praise. You alone are great, God, And worthy to be praised. You alone are great, God, And worthy to be praised.'),
	(130, 'My Love And My Light', 'Don Moen.  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWill we ever know\r\n What we have been given?\r\nHe has chosen us \r\nAnd called us His own\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe will bless Your name\r\n For always and ever:\r\nAnd offer up\r\nThe sacrifices of praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou are my love and my light,\r\nYou are my purpose for living;\r\nYou are my hope in the night,\r\n	 My reason for singing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nYou bring a joy to my life,\r\nAnd You\'re making it better and better;\r\nAnd I will give thanks \r\nForever and ever.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nFlowing from His throne, \r\nThere is a river;\r\nBringing life and health\r\n Wherever it goes.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nTeach us, Lord, We pray, \r\nTo live in Your presence\r\nMake us more and more\r\n Like You every day.\r\n', '', ' 1997 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'Will we ever know What we have been given? He has chosen us And called us His own We will bless Your name For always and ever: And offer up The sacrifices of praise. You are my love and my light, You are my purpose for living; You are my hope in the night, My reason for singing. You bring a joy to my life, And You\'re making it better and better; And I will give thanks Forever and ever. Flowing from His throne, There is a river; Bringing life and health Wherever it goes. Teach us, Lord, We pray, To live in Your presence Make us more and more Like You every day.'),
	(131, 'Help Us!', 'Randy Wright, c.1990 Grace! Music ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe need Your grace; \r\nLet it flow like water.\r\nWe need Your mercy; \r\nLet it fall like rain.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHelp us! Help us!\r\nBurn within our hearts \r\nYour true desire,\r\nHelp us! Help us!\r\nPurify us with Your Holy fire!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe need Your help, Lord, \r\nFor we are so helpless;\r\nWe need You, Jesus, \r\nTo set our lives aflame.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGive us Your word; \r\nWe\'ll take it to the nations.\r\nGive us compassion,\r\n And we will feed the poor.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nGrant us an ear \r\nTo listen to Your Spirit,\r\nGrant us Your boldness,\r\nFearlessly to stand!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nGrant us anointing \r\n	 To move in signs and wonders.\r\nSpirit of Power, \r\nConfirm Your word again!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nGive us Your power,\r\n	  And move upon the children;\r\nHeavenly Father,\r\n Open wide the door!\r\n', '', '1990 Grace! Music ', '', '', 'We need Your grace; Let it flow like water. We need Your mercy; Let it fall like rain. Help us! Help us! Burn within our hearts Your true desire, Help us! Help us! Purify us with Your Holy fire! We need Your help, Lord, For we are so helpless; We need You, Jesus, To set our lives aflame. Give us Your word; We\'ll take it to the nations. Give us compassion, And we will feed the poor. Grant us an ear To listen to Your Spirit, Grant us Your boldness, Fearlessly to stand! Grant us anointing To move in signs and wonders. Spirit of Power, Confirm Your word again! Give us Your power, And move upon the children; Heavenly Father, Open wide the door!'),
	(132, 'I\'ll Fly Away', 'Albert E. Brumley', '~Verse 1\r\nSome glad morning \r\nwhen this life is over,\r\nI\'ll fly away\r\nTo a home\r\nOn God\'s celestial shore,\r\nI\'ll fly away.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen the shadows\r\nof this life are over,\r\nI\'ll fly away.\r\nLike a bird from\r\nprison bars has flown,\r\nI\'ll fly away.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI\'ll fly away, O glory\r\nI\'ll fly away\r\nWhen I die, hallelujah,\r\nby and by\r\nI\'ll fly away !\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJust a few more weary ays and then,\r\nI\'ll fly away\r\nTo a land where joys\r\nshall never end,\r\nI\'ll fly away\r\n', '', '1932, Wonderful Message', '', '', 'Some glad morning when this life is over, I\\\'ll fly away To a home On God\\\'s celestial shore, I\\\'ll fly away. When the shadows of this life are over, I\\\'ll fly away. Like a bird from prison bars has flown, I\\\'ll fly away. I\\\'ll fly away, O glory I\\\'ll fly away When I die, hallelujah, by and by I\\\'ll fly away ! Just a few more weary ays and then, I\\\'ll fly away To a land where joys shall never end, I\\\'ll fly away'),
	(134, 'Hallelujah To The Lamb', 'Don Moen and Debbye Graafsma ', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, I stand in the midst of a multitude \r\nOf those from every tribe and tongue;\r\nWe are Your people\r\nRedeemed by Your blood,\r\nRescued from death by Your love.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThere are no words good enough\r\nTo thank You,\r\nThere are no words to express my praise;\r\nBut I will lift up my voice and sing \r\nFrom my heart with all of my strength.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHallelujah, hallelujah, \r\nHallelujah to the Lamb\r\nHallelujah, hallelujah, \r\nBy the blood of Christ we stand.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nEvery tongue, every tribe,\r\nEvery people, every land;\r\nGiving glory, giving honor, \r\nGiving praise unto the Lamb of God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLord, we stand by grace in Your presence,\r\nCleansed by the blood of the Lamb;\r\nWe are Your children called by Your name,\r\nHumbly we bow and we pray.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nRelease Your power\r\nTo work in us and through us,\r\n\'Til we are changed to be more like You;\r\nThen all the nations will see\r\nYour glory revealed\r\nAnd worship You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nEvery knee shall bow;\r\nEvery tongue confess\r\nThat you are Lord of all \r\n', '', ' 1997 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music c/o Integrity Music, Inc. P.O. Box 851622, Mobile, AL 36685-1622 ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/otmcqZhfy8w', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Lord, I stand in the midst of a multitude Of those from every tribe and tongue; We are Your people Redeemed by Your blood, Rescued from death by Your love. There are no words good enough To thank You, There are no words to express my praise; But I will lift up my voice and sing From my heart with all of my strength. Hallelujah, hallelujah, Hallelujah to the Lamb Hallelujah, hallelujah, By the blood of Christ we stand. Every tongue, every tribe, Every people, every land; Giving glory, giving honor, Giving praise unto the Lamb of God. Lord, we stand by grace in Your presence, Cleansed by the blood of the Lamb; We are Your children called by Your name, Humbly we bow and we pray. Release Your power To work in us and through us, \'Til we are changed to be more like You; Then all the nations will see Your glory revealed And worship You. Every knee shall bow; Every tongue confess That you are Lord of all).'),
	(135, 'My Only Crown (with Fairest Lord Jesus)', '', '~Verse 1\r\nFairest Lord Jesus,\r\nRuler of all nature;\r\nO, Thou of God and man the Son;\r\nThee will I cherish, Thee will I honor,\r\nThou, my soul\'s glory, joy and crown.40\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nTraditional - Public Domain. Words Anonymous German hymn,\r\nMunster Gesangbuch, 1677 stanzas 1-3; Joseph Seiss, stanza 4.\r\nMusic Schlesische Volkslieder, 1842. Arranged by Paul Baloche.\r\nThis arrangement c. 2003 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Media, Inc.\r\nARR, UBP, CCLI #218004\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFair are the meadows;\r\nFairer still the woodlands,\r\nRobed in the blooming garb of spring;\r\nJesus, You\'re fairer; Jesus, You\'re purer;\r\nYou make the woeful heart to sing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMy only crown is knowing You,\r\nAnd to be found in You my only glory;\r\nAnd on that day I will bow down\r\nAnd bring to You my only crown.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nThee will I cherish,\r\nThee will I honor,\r\nThou, my soul\'s glory, joy and crown.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/8n0a4B-sQYo&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '', 'Fairest Lord Jesus, Ruler of all nature; O, Thou of God and man the Son; Thee will I cherish, Thee will I honor, Thou, my soul\\\'s glory, joy and crown.40 Traditional - Public Domain. Words Anonymous German hymn, Munster Gesangbuch, 1677 stanzas 1-3; Joseph Seiss, stanza 4. Music Schlesische Volkslieder, 1842. Arranged by Paul Baloche. This arrangement c. 2003 Integrity\\\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Media, Inc. ARR, UBP, CCLI #218004 Fair are the meadows; Fairer still the woodlands, Robed in the blooming garb of spring; Jesus, You\\\'re fairer; Jesus, You\\\'re purer; You make the woeful heart to sing. My only crown is knowing You, And to be found in You my only glory; And on that day I will bow down And bring to You my only crown. Thee will I cherish, Thee will I honor, Thou, my soul\\\'s glory, joy and crown.'),
	(136, 'We Exalt Your Name', 'Andy Park. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are the Holy One,\r\nThe Lord Most High,\r\nYou reign in majesty\r\nYou reign on high!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou are the Worthy One,\r\nLamb that was slain\r\nYou bought us with Your blood,\r\nAnd with you we\'ll reign.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are the King of Kings,\r\nThe Lord of Lords\r\nAll men will bow to You,\r\nBefore Your throne.\r\n', '', ' 1988 Mercy Publishing.', '', '', 'You are the Holy One, The Lord Most High, You reign in majesty You reign on high! You are the Worthy One, Lamb that was slain You bought us with Your blood, And with you we\'ll reign. You are the King of Kings, The Lord of Lords All men will bow to You, Before Your throne.'),
	(138, 'Immanuel, O Immanuel', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBowed in awe I worship at Your feet,\r\nAnd sing Immanuel, God is with us,\r\nSharing my humanness, my shame,\r\nFeeling my weaknesses, my pain,\r\nTaking the punishment, the blame,\r\nImmanuel.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nImmanuel, Immanuel, Immanuel.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd now my words cannot explain,\r\nAll that my heart cannot contain,\r\nHow great are the glories of Your name,\r\nImmanuel.\r\n', '', ' 1988 Make Way Music; Thankyou Music', '', '', 'Bowed in awe I worship at Your feet, And sing Immanuel, God is with us, Sharing my humanness, my shame, Feeling my weaknesses, my pain, Taking the punishment, the blame, Immanuel. Immanuel, Immanuel, Immanuel. And now my words cannot explain, All that my heart cannot contain, How great are the glories of Your name, Immanuel.'),
	(140, 'Rise Up And Praise Him', 'Paul Baloche and Gary Sadler', '~Verse 1\r\nLet the heavens rejoice,\r\n Let the earth be glad;\r\nLet the people of God \r\nSing His praise \r\nall over the land.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nRise up and praise Him,\r\n He deserves our love;\r\nRise up and praise Him,\r\nWorship the Holy One\r\nWith all your heart, \r\nWith all your soul, \r\nWith all your might,\r\nRise up and praise Him.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nEveryone in the valley, \r\nCome and lift your voice;\r\nAll those on the mountaintop\r\nBe glad and shout for joy.\r\n', '', '1996 Integrity Hosanna! Music  ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/WR5mHcxvNFI&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Let the heavens rejoice, Let the earth be glad; Let the people of God Sing His praise all over the land. Rise up and praise Him, He deserves our love; Rise up and praise Him, Worship the Holy One With all your heart, With all your soul, With all your might, Rise up and praise Him. Everyone in the valley, Come and lift your voice; All those on the mountaintop Be glad and shout for joy.'),
	(141, 'Our God Reigns (Hymn #229)', 'Leonard E. Smith', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]How lovely o[D]n the mou[E]ntains are the f[A]eet of him\r\nwho brings good ne[E]ws[E7], good [A]new[A7]s\r\nAnn[A7]ouncing pe[D]ace, pro[E]claiming news of ha[A]ppiness\r\n~Chorus\r\nOur God r[E]eig[E7]ns, Our God r[A]eig[A7]ns\r\nOur God re[D]igns, our God re[A]igns,\r\nOur God rei[D]gn[E]s, our God r[A]eigns\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe had no stately form, He had no majesty\r\nThat we should be drawn to Him\r\nHe was despised and we took no account of Him\r\nYet now He reigns with the Most High\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt was our sin and guilt that bruised and wounded Him,\r\nIt was our sin that brought Him down\r\nWhen we like sheep had gone astray, our Shepherd came\r\nAnd on His shoulders bore our shame.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nOut from the tomb He came with grace and majesty,\r\nHe is alive - He is alive! God loves us so - see here\r\nHis hands, His feet, His side Yes, we know, He is alive!\r\n', '', '1974, 1978 L.E. Smith', '', '', 'How lovely on the mountains are the feet of him who brings good news, good news Announcing peace, proclaiming news of happiness Our God reigns, Our God reigns Our God reigns, our God reigns, Our God reigns, our God reigns He had no stately form, He had no majesty That we should be drawn to Him He was despised and we took no account of Him Yet now He reigns with the Most High It was our sin and guilt that bruised and wounded Him, It was our sin that brought Him down When we like sheep had gone astray, our Shepherd came And on His shoulders bore our shame. Out from the tomb He came with grace and majesty, He is alive - He is alive! God loves us so - see here His hands, His feet, His side Yes, we know, He is alive!'),
	(142, 'Hosanna, Hosanna', 'Carl Tuttle', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHosanna, Hosanna,\r\nHosanna in the highest \r\nHosanna in the highest \r\nLord, we lift up Your Name\r\nWith hearts full of praise\r\nBe exalted, O Lord, my God\r\nHosanna in the highest.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlory, Glory,\r\nGlory, to the King of Kings \r\nGlory, to the King of Kings \r\nLord, we lift up Your Name\r\nWith hearts full of praise\r\nBe exalted, O Lord, my God\r\nGlory to the King of Kings.\r\n', '', ' 1985 Mercy Pub., ', '', '', 'Hosanna, Hosanna, Hosanna in the highest Hosanna in the highest Lord, we lift up Your Name With hearts full of praise Be exalted, O Lord, my God Hosanna in the highest. Glory, Glory, Glory, to the King of Kings Glory, to the King of Kings Lord, we lift up Your Name With hearts full of praise Be exalted, O Lord, my God Glory to the King of Kings.'),
