eights of Heaven Your glory, Lord, is far and wide Through history You reign on high From the depths of the sea To the mountain\'s summit Your power, Lord, it knows no bounds A higher love cannot be found So let the universe proclaim Your great power and Your great name'),
	(152, 'Wonderful Grace Of Jesus', 'Haldor Lilenas; ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWonderful grace of Jesus,\r\n greater than all my sin;\r\nHow shall my tongue describe it,\r\n where shall its praise begin?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWonderful the matchless grace of Jesus,\r\nDeeper than the mighty rolling sea;\r\nHigher than the mountain,\r\n sparkling like a fountain,\r\nAll sufficient grace for even me;\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBroader than the scope\r\n of my transgressions,\r\nGreater than all my sin and shame;\r\nO magnify the precious name of Jesus,\r\nPraise His name!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nTaking away my burden, \r\nsetting my spirit free,\r\nFor the wonderful grace of Jesus\r\n reaches me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWonderful grace of Jesus,\r\n reaching to all the	 lost,\r\nBy it I have been pardoned,\r\n saved to the uttermost;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nChains have been torn asunder, \r\ngiving me liberty,\r\nFor the wonderful grace of Jesus \r\nreaches me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nWonderful grace of Jesus,\r\n reaching the most defiled,\r\nBy its transforming power \r\nmaking him God\'s 	 dear child,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nPurchasing peace and heaven \r\nfor all eternity;\r\nFor the wonderful grace of Jesus \r\nreaches me.\r\n', '', ' 1918 Renewal 1946 by Hope Publishing Co.; Carol Stream, ILL 60188; ', '', '', 'Wonderful grace of Jesus, greater than all my sin; How shall my tongue describe it, where shall its praise begin? Wonderful the matchless grace of Jesus, Deeper than the mighty rolling sea; Higher than the mountain, sparkling like a fountain, All sufficient grace for even me; Broader than the scope of my transgressions, Greater than all my sin and shame; O magnify the precious name of Jesus, Praise His name! Taking away my burden, setting my spirit free, For the wonderful grace of Jesus reaches me. Wonderful grace of Jesus, reaching to all the	 lost, By it I have been pardoned, saved to the uttermost; Chains have been torn asunder, giving me liberty, For the wonderful grace of Jesus reaches me. Wonderful grace of Jesus, reaching the most defiled, By its transforming power making him God\'s 	 dear child, Purchasing peace and heaven for all eternity; For the wonderful grace of Jesus reaches me.'),
	(153, 'Give Thanks', 'Henry Smith, ', '~Verse 1\r\nGive thanks with a grateful heart\r\nGive thanks to the Holy One\r\nGive thanks because He\'s given\r\nJesus Christ His Son,\r\n \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd now, let the weak say, "I am strong" \r\nLet the poor say, "I am rich\r\nBecause of what the Lord has done for us"\r\n', '', ' 1978 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/xtxmSAqMtDA?fs=1&amp;hl=en_US', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/give-thanks/id252351061?i=252354948&uo=4" target="itunes_store">Give Thanks - Top 25 Praise Songs</a>', 'Give thanks with a grateful heart Give thanks to the Holy One Give thanks because He\\\'s given Jesus Christ His Son, And now, let the weak say, \\"I am strong\\" Let the poor say, \\"I am rich Because of what the Lord has done for us\\"'),
	(154, 'God, Our Father, We Adore Thee', 'George W. Frazier, Music by John Zundel, ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGod, our Father, we adore Thee!\r\nWe, Thy children, bless Thy name!\r\nChosen in the Christ before Thee,\r\nWe are "holy without blame."\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSon Eternal, we adore Thee!\r\nLamb upon the throne on high!\r\nLamb of God, we bow before Thee,\r\nThou hast brought Thy people nigh!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHoly Spirit, we adore Thee!\r\nParaclete and heav\'nly guest!\r\nSent from God and from the Savior,\r\nThou hast led us into rest.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFather, Son, and Holy Spirit -\r\nThree in One! We give Thee praise!\r\nFor the riches we inherit,\r\nHeart and voice to Thee we raise!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nAbba\'s praises we proclaim!\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nAbba\'s praises we proclaim!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nSon of God, who came to die!\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nSon of God, who came to die!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nBy Thy grace forever blest:\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nBy Thy grace forever blest!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nThee we bless, thro\' endless days!\r\nWe adore Thee! We adore Thee!\r\nThee we bless, thro\' endless days!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'God, our Father, we adore Thee! We, Thy children, bless Thy name! Chosen in the Christ before Thee, We are "holy without blame." Son Eternal, we adore Thee! Lamb upon the throne on high! Lamb of God, we bow before Thee, Thou hast brought Thy people nigh! Holy Spirit, we adore Thee! Paraclete and heav\'nly guest! Sent from God and from the Savior, Thou hast led us into rest. Father, Son, and Holy Spirit - Three in One! We give Thee praise! For the riches we inherit, Heart and voice to Thee we raise! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Abba\'s praises we proclaim! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Abba\'s praises we proclaim! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Son of God, who came to die! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Son of God, who came to die! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! By Thy grace forever blest: We adore Thee! We adore Thee! By Thy grace forever blest! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Thee we bless, thro\' endless days! We adore Thee! We adore Thee! Thee we bless, thro\' endless days!'),
	(155, 'Over And Over', ' Paul Baloche', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe wind is beginning to blow,\r\nI can feel it, I can feel it;\r\nThe river is starting to flow,\r\nI can hear it, I can hear it.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOver and over, \r\nLet Your mercy cover me;\r\nOver and over \r\nLet Your river run through me,\r\nO, Holy Spirit, \r\npour down like rain;\r\nOver and over again.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThese are the days,\r\n The days of Your presence;\r\nSeasons of change,\r\nTimes of refreshing,\r\n', '', ' 1998, Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music c/o Integrity Music, Inc.,', '', '', 'The wind is beginning to blow, I can feel it, I can feel it; The river is starting to flow, I can hear it, I can hear it. Over and over, Let Your mercy cover me; Over and over Let Your river run through me, O, Holy Spirit, pour down like rain; Over and over again. These are the days, The days of Your presence; Seasons of change, Times of refreshing,'),
	(156, 'Changed By Your Glory', 'Andy Park  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIn You I see a reflection\r\nOf the one You are making me to be.\r\nAs I behold your reflection\r\nI am changed by the brightness\r\nOf your glory.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, how I long to be with You,\r\nHow I long for the day when I\'ll be home.\r\nSo for this time I will seek You\r\nAnd for all of my life\r\nI\'ll strive to please you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHow I long to see You, to be with You\r\nTo forever be changed by your glory.\r\nHow I long to see You, to be with You\r\nTo forever be taken into glory\r\nYour glory.\r\n', '', '1989 Mercy Publishing.', '', '', 'In You I see a reflection Of the one You are making me to be. As I behold your reflection I am changed by the brightness Of your glory. Lord, how I long to be with You, How I long for the day when I\'ll be home. So for this time I will seek You And for all of my life I\'ll strive to please you. How I long to see You, to be with You To forever be changed by your glory. How I long to see You, to be with You To forever be taken into glory Your glory.'),
	(158, 'When I Survey The Wondrous Cross', 'Isaac Watts', '~Verse 1\r\nWhen I survey the wondrous cross,\r\nOn which the Prince of glory died,\r\nMy richest gain I count but loss,\r\nAnd pour contempt on all my pride.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nForbid it, Lord, that I should boast,\r\nSave in the death of Christ, my God;\r\nAll the vain things that charm me most\r\nI sacrifice them to His blood,\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSee, from His head, His hands, His feet,\r\nSorrow and love flow mingled down;\r\nDid e\'er such love and sorrow meet,\r\nOr thorns compose so rich a crown?\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWere the whole realm of nature mine,\r\nThat were a present far too small;\r\nLove so amazing, so divine,\r\nDemands my soul, my life, my all.\r\n~Chorus\r\nO the wonderful cross,\r\nO the wonderful cross;\r\nAll who gather here by grace\r\nDraw near and bless Your name.\r\n~Chorus 2\r\nO the wonderful cross,\r\nO the wonderful cross \r\nBids me come and die\r\nAnd find that I may truly live.\r\n~Tag\r\nLove so amazing, so divine,\r\nDemands my soul, my life, my all.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/Tkx8WAycYAc', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(When I survey the wondrous cross, On which the Prince of glory died, My richest gain I count but loss, And pour contempt on all my pride. Forbid it, Lord, that I should boast, Save in the death of Christ, my God; All the vain things that charm me most I sacrifice them to His blood, See, from His head, His hands, His feet, Sorrow and love flow mingled down; Did e\'er such love and sorrow meet, Or thorns compose so rich a crown? Were the whole realm of nature mine, That were a present far too small; Love so amazing, so divine, Demands my soul, my life, my all. O the wonderful cross, O the wonderful cross; All who gather here by grace Draw near and bless Your name. O the wonderful cross, O the wonderful cross Bids me come and die And find that I may truly live. Love so amazing, so divine, Demands my soul, my life, my all.).'),
	(159, 'Guide Me, O Thou Great Jehovah', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGuide me, O Thou great Jehovah,\r\nPilgrim through this barren land;\r\nI am weak, but Thou art mighty;\r\nHold me with Thy pow\'rful hand;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBread of heaven, Bread of heaven,\r\nFeed me till I want no more, \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nOpen now the crystal fountain,\r\nWhence the healing stream doth flow;\r\nLet the fire and cloudy pillar\r\nLead me all my journey through;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSongs of praises, songs of praises \r\nI will ever give to Thee,  \r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhen I tread the verge of Jordan,\r\nBid my anxious fears subside;\r\nBear me thro\' the swelling current,\r\nLand me safe on Canaan\'s side;\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nStrong Deliverer, strong Deliverer,\r\nBe Thou still my strength and shield, \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Guide me, O Thou great Jehovah, Pilgrim through this barren land; I am weak, but Thou art mighty; Hold me with Thy pow\'rful hand; Bread of heaven, Bread of heaven, Feed me till I want no more, Open now the crystal fountain, Whence the healing stream doth flow; Let the fire and cloudy pillar Lead me all my journey through; Songs of praises, songs of praises I will ever give to Thee, When I tread the verge of Jordan, Bid my anxious fears subside; Bear me thro\' the swelling current, Land me safe on Canaan\'s side; Strong Deliverer, strong Deliverer, Be Thou still my strength and shield,'),
	(160, 'Faithful God', 'David Baroni and Wayne Tate.', '~Intro\r\n[Bm] [A] [G]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[Bm]In the darkest ni[G]ght, when the sun doesn\'t sh[D2/F#]ine\r\nIn the dark night of my so[A]ul\r\n[Bm]I hear you call my na[G]me\r\nI see you walk in the ra[D2/F#]in\r\nAnd I know you\'re in cont[A]rol\r\n~Tag\r\n[D2/F#]You know the depth of my deepest si[G]n\r\nYet you call me as your fr[Bm]iend\r\nYou gave your ve[D2]ry be[G]st to m[A]e\r\n~Chorus\r\n[D]Every morning I seek your fa[D][C#][Bm]ce\r\n[Bm]Every evening I feel your grace\r\nYou are my fir[G]st love, you are my fa[A]ithful God\r\n[D]Every day is a brand new da[D][C#][Bm]y\r\n[Bm]I see your face as you look my way\r\nYou are my fi[G]rst love, you are my fai[A]thful God\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen the strong winds blow\r\nLord, I feel so alone\r\nThe waves of life crash over me\r\nI bow my head to you\r\nLord, I know your word is true\r\nYou are the truth who sets me free\r\n', '', ' 2000 Integrity\'s Praise! Music & Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music.', '', '', 'In the darkest night, when the sun doesn\'t shine In the dark night of my soul I hear you call my name I see you walk in the rain And I know you\'re in control You know the depth of my deepest sin Yet you call me as your friend You gave your very best to me Every morning I seek your face Every evening I feel your grace You are my first love, you are my faithful God Every day is a brand new day I see your face as you look my way You are my first love, you are my faithful God When the strong winds blow Lord, I feel so alone The waves of life crash over me I bow my head to you Lord, I know your word is true You are the truth who sets me free'),
	(161, 'He Keeps Me Singing', 'Luther B. Bridgers', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere\'s within my heart a melody\r\nJesus whispers sweet and low,\r\n"Fear not, I am with thee peace be still,"\r\nIn all of life\'s ebb and flow.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, Jesus, Jesus \r\nSweetest name I know,\r\nFills my ev\'ry longing, \r\nKeeps me singing as I go.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAll my life was wrecked by sin and strife\r\nDiscord filled my heart with pain;\r\nJesus swept across the broken strings,\r\nStirr\'d the slumb\'ring chords again.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFeasting on the riches of His grace,\r\nResting \'neath His shelt\'ring wing,\r\nAlways looking on His smiling face,\r\nThat is why I shout and sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTho sometimes He leads thru waters deep,\r\nTrials fall across the way,\r\nTho sometimes the path\r\nSeems rough and steep,\r\nSee His footprints all the way.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nSoon He\'s coming back to welcome me\r\nFar beyond the starry sky;\r\nI shall wing my flight to worlds unknown,\r\nI shall reign with Him on high.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'There\'s within my heart a melody Jesus whispers sweet and low, "Fear not, I am with thee peace be still," In all of life\'s ebb and flow. Jesus, Jesus, Jesus Sweetest name I know, Fills my ev\'ry longing, Keeps me singing as I go. All my life was wrecked by sin and strife Discord filled my heart with pain; Jesus swept across the broken strings, Stirr\'d the slumb\'ring chords again. Feasting on the riches of His grace, Resting \'neath His shelt\'ring wing, Always looking on His smiling face, That is why I shout and sing. Tho sometimes He leads thru waters deep, Trials fall across the way, Tho sometimes the path Seems rough and steep, See His footprints all the way. Soon He\'s coming back to welcome me Far beyond the starry sky; I shall wing my flight to worlds unknown, I shall reign with Him on high.'),
	(162, 'I Believe The Presence', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI believe the promise\r\nAbout the visions and the dreams\r\nThat the Holy Spirit\r\nWill be poured out\r\nAnd His power will be seen\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI believe that the presence\r\nOf God is here;\r\nThere\'s not one thing\r\nThat can\'t be changed\r\nWhen the Spirit of God is near.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI believe that the presence\r\nOf God is here\r\nWhen two or three are gathered,\r\nWhen people rise in faith,\r\nI believe God answers, \r\nAnd His presence is in this place\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nNo thing on earth or heaven\r\nCan stop the pow\'r of God,\r\nInto our hand is given\r\nThe call to take it on;\r\nNo ocean can contain it,\r\nNo star can rise above,\r\nInto our hearts are given\r\nThe pow\'r of His love\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWell, the time is now\r\nAnd the place is here\r\nAnd His people have come in faith\r\nThere\'s a mighty sound\r\nAnd a touch of fire\r\nWhen we\'re gathered in one place.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Russell Fragar/Hillsongs Australia (adm. in U.S. and Canada by ', '', '', 'I believe the promise About the visions and the dreams That the Holy Spirit Will be poured out And His power will be seen I believe that the presence Of God is here; There\'s not one thing That can\'t be changed When the Spirit of God is near. I believe that the presence Of God is here When two or three are gathered, When people rise in faith, I believe God answers, And His presence is in this place No thing on earth or heaven Can stop the pow\'r of God, Into our hand is given The call to take it on; No ocean can contain it, No star can rise above, Into our hearts are given The pow\'r of His love Well, the time is now And the place is here And His people have come in faith There\'s a mighty sound And a touch of fire When we\'re gathered in one place.'),
	(163, 'I Wonder As I Wander', 'John Jacob Niles', '~Verse 1\r\nWhen Mary birthed Jesus, \r\n\'Twas in a cow\'s stall,\r\nWith wise men and farmers\r\n And shepherds and all.\r\nBut high from God\'s heaven\r\n A star\'s light did fall,\r\nThe promise of ages it then did re-call.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIf Jesus had wanted for any wee thing,\r\nA star in the sky or a bird on the wing,\r\nOr all of God\'s angels in heav\'n for to sing,\r\nHe surely could have it,\r\n \'Cause He was the King.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI wonder as I wander, out under the sky,\r\nHow Jesus the Saviour did come for to die\r\nFor poor, orn\'ry people like you and like I;\r\nI wonder as I wander, out under the sky.\r\n', '', '1945 by G. Schirmer, Inc. - Renewed', '', '', 'When Mary birthed Jesus, \\\'Twas in a cow\\\'s stall, With wise men and farmers And shepherds and all. But high from God\\\'s heaven A star\\\'s light did fall, The promise of ages it then did re-call. If Jesus had wanted for any wee thing, A star in the sky or a bird on the wing, Or all of God\\\'s angels in heav\\\'n for to sing, He surely could have it, \\\'Cause He was the King. I wonder as I wander, out under the sky, How Jesus the Saviour did come for to die For poor, orn\\\'ry people like you and like I; I wonder as I wander, out under the sky.'),
	(164, 'Jesus I Love You', 'Dennis Jernigan', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYour love reached to the sky \r\n    With arms stretched open wide\r\nYou took my sin and died, \r\nO, how could I ever thank You?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe sweetest melody in perfect harmony \r\nA love song just for me\r\nO, how could I ever thank You?\r\nI want to thank You for my life\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBut I cannot lift my hands that high\r\nAll that I know is I must try\r\nYou lifted up Your hands to die \r\nTo tell me You love me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBut I cannot sing one note that sweet\r\nWords that I say seem incomplete\r\nBut living or dying I\'ll repeat\r\nJesus, I love You, Jesus, I love You,\r\nJesus, I love You, Jesus I love You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLord, my heart is longing\r\n To tell You how I feel \r\nYou make my life worth living\r\nSo with my life, I will thank You\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI am ever grateful for Your cleansing blood \r\nNo praise would be enough, Lord\r\nSo with my life I will thank You\r\nI want to thank You for my life\r\n', '', ' ', '', '', 'Your love reached to the sky With arms stretched open wide You took my sin and died, O, how could I ever thank You? The sweetest melody in perfect harmony A love song just for me O, how could I ever thank You? I want to thank You for my life But I cannot lift my hands that high All that I know is I must try You lifted up Your hands to die To tell me You love me. But I cannot sing one note that sweet Words that I say seem incomplete But living or dying I\'ll repeat Jesus, I love You, Jesus, I love You, Jesus, I love You, Jesus I love You. Lord, my heart is longing To tell You how I feel You make my life worth living So with my life, I will thank You I am ever grateful for Your cleansing blood No praise would be enough, Lord So with my life I will thank You I want to thank You for my life'),
	(165, 'He Is The Mighty One', 'Dennis L. Jernigan', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy children there\'s an enemy in the land!\r\nAnd many he\'ll devour if we don\'t stand!\r\nJesus called us out of the night\r\nTo declare His glorious light\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHoly army rise up and see\r\nThat the Truth can set all men free,\r\nSo declare it,\r\nDeclare the truth that:\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe is the Mighty One\r\n He is the Holy One\r\nJesus has overcome \r\nVictory has been won\r\nHe is the truth\r\nThat sets men free; \r\nHe is!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBelievers let up rise up here in this land\r\nDeclaring war against the enemy stand\r\nJesus called us out of the night\r\nTo declare His glorious light\r\n  \r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHoly army rise up and see\r\nThat the truth can set all men free,\r\nSo declare it\r\nDeclare the truth that:  \r\n', '', ' 1991 Shepherd\'s Heart Music', '', '', 'My children there\'s an enemy in the land! And many he\'ll devour if we don\'t stand! Jesus called us out of the night To declare His glorious light Holy army rise up and see That the Truth can set all men free, So declare it, Declare the truth that: He is the Mighty One He is the Holy One Jesus has overcome Victory has been won He is the truth That sets men free; He is! Believers let up rise up here in this land Declaring war against the enemy stand Jesus called us out of the night To declare His glorious light Holy army rise up and see That the truth can set all men free, So declare it Declare the truth that:'),
	(166, 'Lion Of Judah', 'Robin Mark. ', '~Verse 1\r\nYou\'re the Lion of Judah\r\nThe Lamb Who was slain\r\nYou ascended to Heaven\r\nAnd evermore will reign\r\nAt the end of the age\r\nWhen the earth You reclaim\r\nYou will gather the nations before You\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nAnd the eyes of all men\r\nWill be fixed on the Lamb\r\nWho was crucified\r\nWith wisdom and mercy\r\nAnd justice You\'ll reign\r\nAt Your Father\'s side\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd the angels will cry\r\nHail the Lamb\r\nWho was slain for the world\r\nRule in power\r\nAnd the earth will reply\r\nYou shall reign\r\nAs the King of all kings\r\nAnd the Lord of all lords\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere\'s a shield in our hand\r\nAnd a sword at our side\r\nThere\'s a fire in our spirits\r\nThat cannot be denied\r\n\'Cause the Father has told us\r\nFor these You have died\r\nFor the nations who gather before You\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAnd the ears of all men\r\nNeed to hear of the Lamb\r\nWho was crucified \r\nWho descended to hell\r\nYet was raised up to reign\r\nAt His Father\'s side\r\n', '', ' 1997 Daybreak Music, Ltd.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/QOYlr_42FUU?fs=1&hl=en_US', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/youre-the-lion-of-judah/id200910031?i=200910166&uo=4" target="itunes_store">Youâ€™re the Lion of Judah - Revival In Belfast</a>', 'You\\\'re the Lion of Judah The Lamb Who was slain You ascended to Heaven And evermore will reign At the end of the age When the earth You reclaim You will gather the nations before You And the eyes of all men Will be fixed on the Lamb Who was crucified With wisdom and mercy And justice You\\\'ll reign At Your Father\\\'s side And the angels will cry Hail the Lamb Who was slain for the world Rule in power And the earth will reply You shall reign As the King of all kings And the Lord of all lords There\\\'s a shield in our hand And a sword at our side There\\\'s a fire in our spirits That cannot be denied \\\'Cause the Father has told us For these You have died For the nations who gather before You And the ears of all men Need to hear of the Lamb Who was crucified Who descended to hell Yet was raised up to reign At His Father\\\'s side'),
	(167, 'Jesus Name Above All Names', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus name above all names,\r\nBeautiful Saviour,\r\nGlorious Lord.\r\nEmmanuel, God is with us.\r\nBlessed Redeemer, \r\nLiving Word.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1974, 1979, Scripture In Song, New Zealand; Thankyou Music, England;', '', '', 'Jesus name above all names, Beautiful Saviour, Glorious Lord. Emmanuel, God is with us. Blessed Redeemer, Living Word.'),
	(168, 'O Canada', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n\r\nO Canada!\r\nOur home and native land,\r\nTrue patriot love\r\nIn all our sons command.\r\nWith glowing hearts we see thee rise,\r\nThe true north strong and free.\r\nFrom far and wide, O Canada!\r\nWe stand on guard for thee.\r\nGod keep our land glorious and free!\r\nO Canada! We stand on guard for thee.\r\nO Canada! We stand on guard for thee.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'O Canada! Our home and native land, True patriot love In all our sons command. With glowing hearts we see thee rise, The true north strong and free. From far and wide, O Canada! We stand on guard for thee. God keep our land glorious and free! O Canada! We stand on guard for thee. O Canada! We stand on guard for thee.'),
	(169, 'Within The Veil', 'Ruth Dryden, c. 1978 Genesis Music. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWithin the veil\r\nI now would come\r\nInto the Holy Place\r\nTo look upon His face\r\nI see such beauty there\r\nNone other can compare\r\nI worship You my God\r\nWithin the veil\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWithin the veil\r\nI see Your face\r\nI see such glory there\r\nI see such wondrous grace\r\nYour tender mercies flow\r\nLike white and driven snow\r\nTo cover all my sin\r\nAnd make me pure\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWithin my heart\r\nI share Your love\r\nWithin my heart dear Lord\r\nI share the Heavenly Dove\r\nWithin my mind and will\r\nI share the Father\'s will\r\nWithin my soul dear Lord\r\nYour presence still\r\n', '', ' 1978 Genesis Music. ', '', '', 'Within the veil I now would come Into the Holy Place To look upon His face I see such beauty there None other can compare I worship You my God Within the veil Within the veil I see Your face I see such glory there I see such wondrous grace Your tender mercies flow Like white and driven snow To cover all my sin And make me pure Within my heart I share Your love Within my heart dear Lord I share the Heavenly Dove Within my mind and will I share the Father\'s will Within my soul dear Lord Your presence still'),
	(170, 'Not By Might', 'Robin Mark ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHealer of hearts, \r\nbinder of wounds\r\nLives that are lost restored\r\nFlow through this land\r\n\'Til every man praises \r\nYour name once more\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNo, not by might\r\nNor even power\r\nBut by Your Spirit O Lord\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFlow through this land\r\n\'Til every man \r\nPraises Your name once more.\r\n', '', ' 1998 Daybreak Music Ltd.  ', '', '', 'Healer of hearts, binder of wounds Lives that are lost restored Flow through this land \'Til every man praises Your name once more No, not by might Nor even power But by Your Spirit O Lord Flow through this land \'Til every man Praises Your name once more.'),
	(171, 'Standing On The Promises', 'R. Kelso Carter.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nStanding on the promises of Christ my King\r\nThro\' eternal ages let His praises ring;\r\nGlory in the highest, I will shout and sing,\r\nStanding on the promises of God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nStanding on the promises that cannot fail,\r\nWhen the howling storms \r\nof doubt and fear assail,\r\nBy the living Word of God I shall prevail,\r\nStanding on the promises of God.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nStanding on the promises of Christ the Lord,\r\nBound to Him eternally by love\'s strong cord,\r\nOvercoming daily with the Spirit\'s sword,\r\nStanding on the promises of God.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nStanding on the promises I cannot fall,\r\nList\'ning every moment to the Spirit\'s call,\r\nResting in my Savior as my all in all,\r\nStanding on the promises of God\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nStanding, standing,\r\nStanding on the promises\r\n of God my Saviour;\r\nStanding, standing,\r\nI\'m standing on the promises of God\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Standing on the promises of Christ my King Thro\' eternal ages let His praises ring; Glory in the highest, I will shout and sing, Standing on the promises of God. Standing on the promises that cannot fail, When the howling storms of doubt and fear assail, By the living Word of God I shall prevail, Standing on the promises of God. Standing on the promises of Christ the Lord, Bound to Him eternally by love\'s strong cord, Overcoming daily with the Spirit\'s sword, Standing on the promises of God. Standing on the promises I cannot fall, List\'ning every moment to the Spirit\'s call, Resting in my Savior as my all in all, Standing on the promises of God Standing, standing, Standing on the promises of God my Saviour; Standing, standing, I\'m standing on the promises of God'),
	(172, 'Hide Me In Your Holiness', 'Steve Ragsdale. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHide me, Lord, in Your holiness,\r\nEvery sin I now confess.\r\nPraise to You forgiving Lord,\r\nHide me in Your holiness,\r\nHide me in Your holiness.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1986 Maranatha! Music.', '', '', 'Hide me, Lord, in Your holiness, Every sin I now confess. Praise to You forgiving Lord, Hide me in Your holiness, Hide me in Your holiness.'),
	(173, 'Worthy Is The Lamb (Zschech)', 'Darlene Zschech. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThank You for the cross, Lord\r\nThank You for the price You paid.\r\nBearing all my sin and shame,\r\nIn love You came\r\nAnd gave amazing grace.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThank You for this love, Lord.\r\nThank You for the nail-pierced hands.\r\nWashed me in Your cleansing flow,\r\nNow all I know,\r\nYour forgiveness and embrace.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWorthy is the Lamb,\r\nSeated on the throne.\r\nCrown You now with many crowns,\r\nYou reign victorious.\r\nHigh and lifted up,\r\nJesus, Son of God.\r\nThe Darling of heaven, crucified.\r\nWorthy is the Lamb.\r\nWorthy is the Lamb.\r\n', '', ' 2000 Hillsong Publishing.', '', '', 'Thank You for the cross, Lord Thank You for the price You paid. Bearing all my sin and shame, In love You came And gave amazing grace. Thank You for this love, Lord. Thank You for the nail-pierced hands. Washed me in Your cleansing flow, Now all I know, Your forgiveness and embrace. Worthy is the Lamb, Seated on the throne. Crown You now with many crowns, You reign victorious. High and lifted up, Jesus, Son of God. The Darling of heaven, crucified. Worthy is the Lamb. Worthy is the Lamb.'),
