	(175, 'Firm Foundation', 'Nancy Gordon & Jamie Harvill', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI have a living hope, \r\nI have a future;\r\nGod has a plan for me, \r\nOf this I\'m sure.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, You\'re my firm foundation,\r\nI know I can stand secure;\r\nJesus, You\'re my firm foundation,\r\nI put my hope in Your holy Word,\r\nI put my hope in Your holy Word.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYour Word is faithful, \r\nMighty in power;\r\nGod will deliver me, \r\nOf this I\'m sure.\r\n', '', 'A.R.R..,', '', '', 'I have a living hope, I have a future; God has a plan for me, Of this I\'m sure. Jesus, You\'re my firm foundation, I know I can stand secure; Jesus, You\'re my firm foundation, I put my hope in Your holy Word, I put my hope in Your holy Word. Your Word is faithful, Mighty in power; God will deliver me, Of this I\'m sure.'),
	(176, 'Find Me In The River', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFind me in the river;\r\nfind me on my knees.\r\nI\'ve walked against the water,\r\nnow I\'m waiting, if You please.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe\'ve longed to see the roses,\r\nbut never felt the thorns,\r\nand bought our pretty crowns,\r\nbut never paid the price.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFind me in the river;\r\nfind me on my knees.\r\nI\'ve walked against the water,\r\nnow I\'m waiting, if You please.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe didn\'t count on suff\'ring,\r\nwe didn\'t count on pain,\r\nbut if the blessing\'s in the valley,\r\nthen in the river we\'ll wait.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFind me in the river;\r\nfind me there.\r\nFind me on my knees\r\nwith my soul laid bare.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nEven though You\'re gone\r\nand I\'m cracked and dry,\r\nfind me in the river;\r\nI\'m waiting here.\r\n\r\nI\'m waiting here for You.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Find me in the river; find me on my knees. I\'ve walked against the water, now I\'m waiting, if You please. We\'ve longed to see the roses, but never felt the thorns, and bought our pretty crowns, but never paid the price. Find me in the river; find me on my knees. I\'ve walked against the water, now I\'m waiting, if You please. We didn\'t count on suff\'ring, we didn\'t count on pain, but if the blessing\'s in the valley, then in the river we\'ll wait. Find me in the river; find me there. Find me on my knees with my soul laid bare. Even though You\'re gone and I\'m cracked and dry, find me in the river; I\'m waiting here. I\'m waiting here for You.'),
