	(179, 'His Eye Is On The Sparrow', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhy should I feel discouraged?\r\nWhy should the shadows come?\r\nWhy should my heart be lonely?\r\nAnd long for heaven and home\r\nWhen Jesus is my portion?\r\nMy constant friend is He:\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n"Let not your heart be troubled",\r\nHis tender words I hear;\r\nAnd resting on His goodness,\r\nI lose my doubt and fear.\r\nTho\' by the path He leadeth\r\nBut one step I may see:\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhenever I am tempted,\r\nWhenever clouds arise,\r\nWhen songs give place to sighing,\r\nWhen hope within me dies,\r\nI draw the closer to Him;\r\nFrom care He sets me free:\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHis eye is on the sparrow,\r\nAnd I know He watches me.\r\nHis eye is on the sparrow,\r\nAnd I know He watches me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI sing because I\'m happy,\r\nI sing because I\'m free;\r\nFor His eye is on the sparrow,\r\nAnd I know He watches me.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Why should I feel discouraged? Why should the shadows come? Why should my heart be lonely? And long for heaven and home When Jesus is my portion? My constant friend is He: "Let not your heart be troubled", His tender words I hear; And resting on His goodness, I lose my doubt and fear. Tho\' by the path He leadeth But one step I may see: Whenever I am tempted, Whenever clouds arise, When songs give place to sighing, When hope within me dies, I draw the closer to Him; From care He sets me free: His eye is on the sparrow, And I know He watches me. His eye is on the sparrow, And I know He watches me. I sing because I\'m happy, I sing because I\'m free; For His eye is on the sparrow, And I know He watches me.'),
	(180, 'I Belong To You', 'Kent Blanton.', '~Verse 1\r\nYou bought me with Your blood,\r\nYou forgave me in Your kindness.\r\nYou adopted me as Your child,\r\nLord, I belong to You.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIn You I\'m holy and blameless,\r\nIn You my many sins were washed away.\r\nIn You I have an inheritance\r\nAnd You are coming back\r\nTo claim me for Your own.\r\n', '', ' 1997 Kent Blanton.', '', '', 'You bought me with Your blood, You forgave me in Your kindness. You adopted me as Your child, Lord, I belong to You. In You I\\\'m holy and blameless, In You my many sins were washed away. In You I have an inheritance And You are coming back To claim me for Your own.'),
	(181, 'Merciful God', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are so gentle\r\nYou are forgiving\r\nYou hold me close \r\nTo Your heart\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhen I am distant\r\nYou show mercy\r\nYou bring me close\r\nTo Your heart\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhat a merciful, merciful,\r\nMerciful God\r\nWhat a merciful, merciful,\r\nMerciful God\r\nYou are, You are\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'You are so gentle You are forgiving You hold me close To Your heart When I am distant You show mercy You bring me close To Your heart What a merciful, merciful, Merciful God What a merciful, merciful, Merciful God You are, You are'),
	(182, 'Wiebe Coffeeptf', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome Join us for \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\nCome share with them, \r\nand hear more about their future plans.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Come Join us for Come share with them, and hear more about their future plans.'),
	(183, 'Yesterday, Today And Forever', 'Vicky Beeching. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nEverlasting God,\r\nThe years go by, but You\'re unchanging\r\nIn this fragile world,\r\nYou are the only firm foundation.\r\nAlways loving, always true,\r\nAlways merciful and good, so good.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nUncreated one,\r\nYou have no end and no beginning,\r\nEarthly powers fade,\r\nBut there is no end to Your kingdom.\r\nAlways loving, always true,\r\nAlways merciful and good, so good.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYesterday, today ,and forever,\r\nYou are the same, You never change.\r\nYesterday, today, and forever,\r\nYou are faithful, and we will trust in you.\r\nWe will trust in You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYesterday, today ,and forever,\r\nYou are the same, You never change.\r\nYesterday, today, and forever,\r\nYou are faithful, and we will trust in you.\r\nWe will trust in You.\r\nFaithful God\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nYahweh, God unchanging;\r\nYahweh, firm foundation.\r\n', '', ' 2002 Thankyou Music. ', '', '', 'Everlasting God, The years go by, but You\'re unchanging In this fragile world, You are the only firm foundation. Always loving, always true, Always merciful and good, so good. Uncreated one, You have no end and no beginning, Earthly powers fade, But there is no end to Your kingdom. Always loving, always true, Always merciful and good, so good. Yesterday, today ,and forever, You are the same, You never change. Yesterday, today, and forever, You are faithful, and we will trust in you. We will trust in You. Yesterday, today ,and forever, You are the same, You never change. Yesterday, today, and forever, You are faithful, and we will trust in you. We will trust in You. Faithful God Yahweh, God unchanging; Yahweh, firm foundation.'),
	(185, 'How Great Thou Art', 'Stuart Hine.', '~Verse 1\r\nO Lord my God,\r\n When I in awesome wonder\r\nConsider all the worlds\r\nThy hands have made,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI see the stars,\r\n I hear the rolling thunder,\r\nThy pow\'r throughout\r\n The universe displayed.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThen I shall bow\r\n In humble adoration\r\nAnd there proclaim, \r\nMy God, how great Thou art.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThen sings my soul,\r\n My Savior God, to Thee;\r\nHow great Thou art, \r\nHow great Thou art;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhen thru the woods \r\nAnd forest glades I wander\r\nAnd hear the birds\r\n Sing sweetly in the trees,\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nWhen I look down from \r\n	 Lofty mountain grandeur\r\nAnd hear the brook \r\nAnd feel the gentle breeze.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nAnd when I think \r\nThat God His Son not sparing,\r\nSent Him to die, \r\nI scarce can take it in\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nThat on the cross, \r\nMy burden gladly bearing,\r\nHe bled and died\r\n To take away my sin.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nWhen Christ shall come\r\n With shout of acclamation,\r\nAnd take me home, \r\nWhat joy shall fill my heart.\r\n', '', '1941 renewed 1981 Stuart K Hine Manna Music, Inc.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/3GKhDCsLrUg', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=263685748&id=263685277&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Paul Baloche - Our God Saves - How Great Thou Art" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'O Lord my God, When I in awesome wonder Consider all the worlds Thy hands have made, I see the stars, I hear the rolling thunder, Thy pow\'r throughout The universe displayed. Then I shall bow In humble adoration And there proclaim, My God, how great Thou art. Then sings my soul, My Savior God, to Thee; How great Thou art, How great Thou art; When thru the woods And forest glades I wander And hear the birds Sing sweetly in the trees, When I look down from Lofty mountain grandeur And hear the brook And feel the gentle breeze. And when I think That God His Son not sparing, Sent Him to die, I scarce can take it in That on the cross, My burden gladly bearing, He bled and died To take away my sin. When Christ shall come With shout of acclamation, And take me home, What joy shall fill my heart.'),
	(186, 'I Will Call Upon The Lord', 'Micheal O\'Shields', '~Verse 1\r\nI will call upon the Lord \r\nWho is worthy to be praised \r\nSo shall I be saved from my enemies. \r\nI will call upon the Lord. \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe Lord liveth and blessed be the rock,\r\nAnd let the God of my salvation\r\n Be exalted.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will call upon the Lord \r\nWho is worthy to be praised \r\nSo shall I be saved from my enemies. \r\nI will call upon the Lord.\r\n', '', '1981 Sound III,ASCAP,3773 W.95th,', '', '', 'I will call upon the Lord Who is worthy to be praised So shall I be saved from my enemies. I will call upon the Lord. The Lord liveth and blessed be the rock, And let the God of my salvation Be exalted. I will call upon the Lord Who is worthy to be praised So shall I be saved from my enemies. I will call upon the Lord.'),
	(187, 'I Will Pray', 'Danny Chambers, Israel Houghton and Samuel Thomas ', '~Verse 1\r\nI answer the call, hearing Your voice,\r\nDown on my knees I make a choice,\r\nTo humble myself and pray.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will pray and seek Your face;\r\nI will touch You with my worship.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nNo matter the cost, paying the price,\r\nLord, I will give the sacrifice\r\nTo humble myself and pray.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI will pray and seek Your face;\r\nWhen I touch You virtue flows,\r\nHealing my soul.\r\n', '', '1998 Praise on the Rock Music & Integrity\'s Praise Music ', '', '', 'I answer the call, hearing Your voice, Down on my knees I make a choice, To humble myself and pray. I will pray and seek Your face; I will touch You with my worship. No matter the cost, paying the price, Lord, I will give the sacrifice To humble myself and pray. I will pray and seek Your face; When I touch You virtue flows, Healing my soul.'),
	(189, 'The Mission', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere\'s a call going out \r\nacross the land in every nation \r\nA call to all who swear \r\nallegiance to the cross of Christ \r\nA call to true humility, \r\nto live our lives responsibly \r\nTo deepen our devotion \r\nto the cross at any price \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAs a candle is consumed \r\nby the passion of the flame \r\nSpilling light unsparingly \r\nthroughout a darkened room \r\nLet us burn to know him deeper \r\nthen Our service flaming bright \r\nWill radiate His passions \r\nand blaze with holy light \r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet us then be sober \r\nmoving only in the spirit \r\nAs aliens and strangers \r\nin a hostile foreign land \r\nThe message we\'re proclaiming \r\nis repentance and forgiveness \r\nThe offer of salvation \r\nto the dying race of man \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nTo love the Lord our God \r\nis the heartbeat of our mission \r\nThe spring from which \r\nour service overflows \r\nAcross the street or around the world \r\nThe mission\'s still the same \r\nProclaim and live the truth \r\nin Jesus\'s name \r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nTo love the Lord our God is the heartbeat \r\nof our mission \r\nTo love the Lord our God is the heartbeat \r\nof our mission\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'There\'s a call going out across the land in every nation A call to all who swear allegiance to the cross of Christ A call to true humility, to live our lives responsibly To deepen our devotion to the cross at any price As a candle is consumed by the passion of the flame Spilling light unsparingly throughout a darkened room Let us burn to know him deeper then Our service flaming bright Will radiate His passions and blaze with holy light Let us then be sober moving only in the spirit As aliens and strangers in a hostile foreign land The message we\'re proclaiming is repentance and forgiveness The offer of salvation to the dying race of man To love the Lord our God is the heartbeat of our mission The spring from which our service overflows Across the street or around the world The mission\'s still the same Proclaim and live the truth in Jesus\'s name To love the Lord our God is the heartbeat of our mission To love the Lord our God is the heartbeat of our mission'),
	(190, 'Go Forth', 'Mark Altrogge. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRise up, you champions of God,\r\nRise up you royal nation;\r\nRise up and bear His light abroad,\r\nWe\'ll reach this generation.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFeel now the burden of the Lord,\r\nFeel how He longs to save them;\r\nFeel now for those who never heard\r\nAbout the Son He gave them.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe\'ve got our marching orders,\r\nWe\'ve got our marching orders,\r\nNow is the time to carry them forth.\r\nGo forth, Jesus loves them,\r\nGo forth, take the Gospel;\r\nGo forth, the time is now,\r\nThe harvest is ripening,\r\nGo forth!\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1987 People of Destiny Music.', '', '', 'Rise up, you champions of God, Rise up you royal nation; Rise up and bear His light abroad, We\'ll reach this generation. Feel now the burden of the Lord, Feel how He longs to save them; Feel now for those who never heard About the Son He gave them. We\'ve got our marching orders, We\'ve got our marching orders, Now is the time to carry them forth. Go forth, Jesus loves them, Go forth, take the Gospel; Go forth, the time is now, The harvest is ripening, Go forth!'),
