	(194, 'Let There Be Joy', 'Bruce Napier  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet there be joy,  \r\nLet there be peace,\r\nLet there be power,\r\nLet there be praise,\r\nLet there be joy,\r\nJoy in the Holy Ghost. \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt was for freedom\r\nThat we were set free,\r\nLet every mountain \r\nbe cast to the sea.\r\nLet there be joy,\r\nJoy in the Holy Ghost.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe will declare it to the heavens,\r\nThe righteousness of God\r\nIn which we stand.\r\nWe will proclaim it \r\nto the nations;\r\nEvery eye shall see,\r\nEvery ear shall hear,\r\nEvery heart will understand.\r\n', '', ' 1998 Ironspiration Music/MCPS  ', '', '', 'Let there be joy, Let there be peace, Let there be power, Let there be praise, Let there be joy, Joy in the Holy Ghost. It was for freedom That we were set free, Let every mountain be cast to the sea. Let there be joy, Joy in the Holy Ghost. We will declare it to the heavens, The righteousness of God In which we stand. We will proclaim it to the nations; Every eye shall see, Every ear shall hear, Every heart will understand.'),
	(195, 'And Can It Be', 'Words by Charles Wesley, Music by Thomas Campbell', '~Verse 1\r\nA[G]nd can it be, that [Am]I sh[D]ould g[G]ain\r\nAn [C]int\'r[D]est [G]in the S[D]avio[A7]ur\'s bl[D]ood?\r\nD[D]ied He for [G/D]me, w[D7]ho ca[G]used His p[D]ain?\r\nFor [C]me, who H[G]im to d[G/D]eath p[D7]ursu[G]ed?\r\nA[G]mazing love!  How c[C]an [A]it [D]be,\r\nThat t[G]hou, my G[C]od, shouldst d[D]ie for [G]me?\r\nAm[G]azing l[D]ove!  How c[D7]an it [G]be,\r\nThat th[C]ou, my [G/B]God, sh[Am]ouldst [G/D]die [D7]for [G]me?\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\'Tis mystery all!  Th\' immortal dies:\r\nWho can explore His strange design?\r\nIn vain the firstborn seraph tries,\r\nTo sound the depth of love divine.\r\n\'Tis mercy all!  Let earth adore,\r\nLet angel minds inquire no more.\r\n\'Tis mercy all!  Let earth adore,\r\nLet angel minds inquire no more.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe left His Father\'s throne above,\r\nSo free, so infinite His grace.\r\nEmptied Himself of all but love,\r\nAnd bled for Adam\'s helpless race.\r\n\'Tis mercy all, immense and free;\r\nFor, O my God, it found out me!\r\n\'Tis mercy all, immense and free;\r\nFor, O my God, it found out me!\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLong my imprison\'d spirit lay,\r\nFast bound in sin and nature\'s night;\r\nThine eye diffused a quick\'ning ray,\r\nI woke, the dungeon flamed with light;\r\nMy chains fell off, my heart was free,\r\nI rose, went forth, and followed Thee.\r\nMy chains fell off, my heart was free,\r\nI rose, went forth, and followed Thee.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nNo condemnation now I dread;\r\nJesus, and all in Him, is mine!\r\nAlive in Him, my living Head,\r\nAnd clothed with righteousness divine.\r\nBold I approach th\'eternal throne,\r\nAnd claim the crown, through Christ, my own.\r\nBold I approach th\'eternal throne,\r\nAnd claim the crown, through Christ, my own.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/lnzJ5BUdcyo&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'And can it be, that I should gain An int\'rest in the Saviour\'s blood? Died He for me, who caused His pain? For me, who Him to death pursued? Amazing love!  How can it be, That thou, my God, shouldst die for me? Amazing love!  How can it be, That thou, my God, shouldst die for me? \'Tis mystery all!  Th\' immortal dies: Who can explore His strange design? In vain the firstborn seraph tries, To sound the depth of love divine. \'Tis mercy all!  Let earth adore, Let angel minds inquire no more. \'Tis mercy all!  Let earth adore, Let angel minds inquire no more. He left His Father\'s throne above, So free, so infinite His grace. Emptied Himself of all but love, And bled for Adam\'s helpless race. \'Tis mercy all, immense and free; For, O my God, it found out me! \'Tis mercy all, immense and free; For, O my God, it found out me! Long my imprison\'d spirit lay, Fast bound in sin and nature\'s night; Thine eye diffused a quick\'ning ray, I woke, the dungeon flamed with light; My chains fell off, my heart was free, I rose, went forth, and followed Thee. My chains fell off, my heart was free, I rose, went forth, and followed Thee. No condemnation now I dread; Jesus, and all in Him, is mine! Alive in Him, my living Head, And clothed with righteousness divine. Bold I approach th\'eternal throne, And claim the crown, through Christ, my own. Bold I approach th\'eternal throne, And claim the crown, through Christ, my own.'),
	(196, 'Whiter Than Snow', 'James Nicholson, music by William G. Fischer.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord Jesus, I long to be perfectly whole;\r\nI want Thee forever to live in my soul.\r\nBreak down every idol, cast out every foe\r\nNow wash me and I shall be\r\nWhiter than snow.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord Jesus, look down from Your\r\nThrone in the skies\r\nAnd help me to make a complete sacrifice.\r\nI give up myself and whatever I know\r\nNow wash me and I shall be\r\nWhiter than snow.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord Jesus, for this I most humbly entreat;\r\nI wait, blessed Lord, at Thy crucified feet.\r\nBy faith, for my cleansing\r\nI see Your blood flow\r\nNow wash me and I shall be\r\nWhiter than snow.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLord Jesus, before You I patiently wait;\r\nCome now within me a new heart create.\r\nTo those who have sought You,\r\nYou never said, "No"\r\nNow wash me and I shall be\r\nWhiter than snow.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhiter than snow,\r\nYes, whiter than snow\r\nNow wash me and I shall be\r\nWhiter than snow\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Lord Jesus, I long to be perfectly whole; I want Thee forever to live in my soul. Break down every idol, cast out every foe Now wash me and I shall be Whiter than snow. Lord Jesus, look down from Your Throne in the skies And help me to make a complete sacrifice. I give up myself and whatever I know Now wash me and I shall be Whiter than snow. Lord Jesus, for this I most humbly entreat; I wait, blessed Lord, at Thy crucified feet. By faith, for my cleansing I see Your blood flow Now wash me and I shall be Whiter than snow. Lord Jesus, before You I patiently wait; Come now within me a new heart create. To those who have sought You, You never said, "No" Now wash me and I shall be Whiter than snow. Whiter than snow, Yes, whiter than snow Now wash me and I shall be Whiter than snow'),
	(197, 'Victory Chant', 'Joseph Vogels', '~Verse 1\r\nHail Jesus, You\'re my king, (echo)\r\nYour life frees me to sing; (echo)\r\nI will praise You all my days, (echo)\r\nYou\'re perfect in all Your ways. (echo)\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHail Jesus, You\'re my Lord, (echo)\r\nI will obey Your word; (echo)\r\nI want to see Your kingdom come, (echo)\r\nNot my will but Yours be done. (echo)\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGlory, glory to the Lamb, (echo)\r\nYou take me into the land; (echo)\r\nWe will conquer in Your name, (echo)\r\nAnd proclaim that Jesus reigns! (echo)\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHail, hail, Lion of Judah (echo)\r\nHow powerful You are! (echo)\r\nHail, hail, Lion of Judah, (echo)\r\nHow wonderful You are! (echo)\r\n(All)	 How wonderful You are!\r\n', '', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/9V6Rp9bECb4&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/victory-chant/id259818435?i=259818666&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Joseph Vogels - Majesty - Victory Chant" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Hail Jesus, You\\\'re my king, (echo) Your life frees me to sing; (echo) I will praise You all my days, (echo) You\\\'re perfect in all Your ways. (echo) Hail Jesus, You\\\'re my Lord, (echo) I will obey Your word; (echo) I want to see Your kingdom come, (echo) Not my will but Yours be done. (echo) Glory, glory to the Lamb, (echo) You take me into the land; (echo) We will conquer in Your name, (echo) And proclaim that Jesus reigns! (echo) Hail, hail, Lion of Judah (echo) How powerful You are! (echo) Hail, hail, Lion of Judah, (echo) How wonderful You are! (echo) (All)	 How wonderful You are!'),
	(198, 'Tell The World', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nDon\'t wanna stand here\r\nAnd shout Your praise\r\nAnd walk away and forget Your name\r\nI stand for You if that\'s all I do\r\n\'Cause there is none that compares to You\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\'Cause all I want in this lifetime is You\r\nAnd all I want in this whole world is You\r\nYou You\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nNo longer I but Christ in me\r\n\'Cause it\'s the truth that set me free\r\nHow could this world be a better place\r\nBy Thy mercy\r\nBy Thy grace\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nTell the world that Jesus lives\r\nTell the world that\r\nTell the world that\r\nTell the world that He died for them\r\nTell the world that He lives again\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\n\r\n\'Cause all I want in this lifetime is You\r\nAnd all I want in this whole world is You\r\nYou You\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\nCome on come on\r\nWe\'ll tell the world about You\r\nCome on come on\r\nWe\'ll tell the world about You\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Don\'t wanna stand here And shout Your praise And walk away and forget Your name I stand for You if that\'s all I do \'Cause there is none that compares to You \'Cause all I want in this lifetime is You And all I want in this whole world is You You You No longer I but Christ in me \'Cause it\'s the truth that set me free How could this world be a better place By Thy mercy By Thy grace Tell the world that Jesus lives Tell the world that Tell the world that Tell the world that He died for them Tell the world that He lives again \'Cause all I want in this lifetime is You And all I want in this whole world is You You You Come on come on We\'ll tell the world about You Come on come on We\'ll tell the world about You'),
	(199, 'There Is No Chain', 'Dennis Jernigan.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere is no heart too wounded,\r\nNo heart so broken that He can\'t mend;\r\nThere is no child so lost he can\'t be found,\r\nNo life He can\'t defend!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThere is no valley, no pit too low,\r\nFor He is much deeper still!\r\nNo life is so hopeless! No heart so empty\r\nJesus can\'t fill!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere is no place that He cannot reach!\r\nNo hurt that He cannot see;\r\nNo matter where you cry out to Him,\r\nThere is no where that He can\'t be;\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe is here waiting, arms open wide!\r\nJust surrender to His will!\r\nNo need to be empty, hungry, or thirsty!\r\nJesus can fill!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere is no chain that can\'t be broken;\r\nThere is no pain that He can\'t feel;\r\nThere is no life that can\'t be rescued;\r\nThere is no wound too deep to heal;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThere is no mountain He can\'t conquer;\r\nThere is no storm that He can\'t still;\r\nThere is no foe that can defeat Him;\r\nBut is there a heart that He can\'t fill?\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nYou are my Father! I am Your child!\r\nThere\'s no better place to me\r\nThan to surrender to Your loving arms\r\nWhere ever I may be!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nThere is no darkness no barren place,\r\nNo desert too low or high,\r\nTo keep me from drinking life\r\nFrom the Well that never runs dry!\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nThere is one heart that Jesus can\'t fill;\r\nA heart that won\'t let Him in;\r\nBut if you will let Him,\r\nJesus will fill you again and again!\r\n', '', ' 1992 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'There is no heart too wounded, No heart so broken that He can\'t mend; There is no child so lost he can\'t be found, No life He can\'t defend! There is no valley, no pit too low, For He is much deeper still! No life is so hopeless! No heart so empty Jesus can\'t fill! There is no place that He cannot reach! No hurt that He cannot see; No matter where you cry out to Him, There is no where that He can\'t be; He is here waiting, arms open wide! Just surrender to His will! No need to be empty, hungry, or thirsty! Jesus can fill! There is no chain that can\'t be broken; There is no pain that He can\'t feel; There is no life that can\'t be rescued; There is no wound too deep to heal; There is no mountain He can\'t conquer; There is no storm that He can\'t still; There is no foe that can defeat Him; But is there a heart that He can\'t fill? You are my Father! I am Your child! There\'s no better place to me Than to surrender to Your loving arms Where ever I may be! There is no darkness no barren place, No desert too low or high, To keep me from drinking life From the Well that never runs dry! There is one heart that Jesus can\'t fill; A heart that won\'t let Him in; But if you will let Him, Jesus will fill you again and again!'),
	(202, 'Under His Wings', 'William O. Cushing, music by Ira D. Sankey.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nUnder His wings I am safely abiding,\r\nTho the night deepens\r\nAnd tempests are wild;\r\nStill I can trust Him,\r\nI know He will keep me,\r\nHe has redeemed me and I am His child.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nUnder His wings, what a refuge in sorrow!\r\nHow the heart yearningly turns to His rest!\r\nOften when earth has no balm\r\nFor my healing,\r\nThere I find comfort and there I am blest.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nUnder His wings,\r\nO what precious enjoyment!\r\nThere will I hide till life\'s trials are o\'er;\r\nSheltered, projected, no evil can harm me,\r\nResting in Jesus I\'m safe evermore.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nUnder His wings, under His wings,\r\nWho from His love can sever?\r\nUnder His wings my sold shall abide,\r\nSafely abide forever.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Under His wings I am safely abiding, Tho the night deepens And tempests are wild; Still I can trust Him, I know He will keep me, He has redeemed me and I am His child. Under His wings, what a refuge in sorrow! How the heart yearningly turns to His rest! Often when earth has no balm For my healing, There I find comfort and there I am blest. Under His wings, O what precious enjoyment! There will I hide till life\'s trials are o\'er; Sheltered, projected, no evil can harm me, Resting in Jesus I\'m safe evermore. Under His wings, under His wings, Who from His love can sever? Under His wings my sold shall abide, Safely abide forever.'),
	(203, 'All The Earth Will Sing Your Praises', 'Paul Baloche', '~Chorus\r\n[G]You lived, [D/F#]You died, [Em7]You said in [C2]three days You would [G]rise\r\n[G]You did, [Dsus]You\'re a--l--[Em7]i--v--e[C2]\r\n[G]You rule, [D/F#]You reign, [Em7]You said You\'re [C2]coming back a[G]gain\r\n[G]I kn[Dsus]ow You will, and [Em7]all the earth will [C2]sing Your praises[G][Dsus] [Em7] [C2]\r\n[C2]All the earth will sing Your praises[G] [Dsus] [Em7] [C2] [G] [Dsus] [Em7] [C2]\r\n~Verse\r\n[G]You took, [D/F#]You take our [Em7]sins away, O God\r\n[G]You give, [D/F#]You gave Your [Em7]life away for us\r\n[C2]You came down, You saved us [Em7]through the cross\r\n[C2]Our hearts are changed because of [Dsus]Your great love\r\n~Tag\r\n[G]I kno[Dsus]w You will, and [Em7]all the earth will [C2]sing Your praises\r\n~Outro\r\n[G]  [Dsus]  [Em7]  [C2] \r\n[G]  [Dsus]  [Em7]  [C2]  [C2]\r\n', '', '2003 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music/ASCAP', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/d8rY7dwwqYs&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'You lived, You died, You said in three days You would rise You did, You\'re a--l--i--v--e You rule, You reign, You said You\'re coming back again I know You will, and all the earth will sing Your praises All the earth will sing Your praises You took, You take our sins away, O God You give, You gave Your life away for us You came down, You saved us through the cross Our hearts are changed because of Your great love I know You will, and all the earth will sing Your praises'),
	(204, 'Worthy, You Are Worthy', 'Matt Redman', '~Verse1\r\nWo[G]rthy You are w[C]orthy\r\nMuch wo[G]rthy that ou[Csus2]r world\r\nI [G]cannot im[C]agine just how gl[G]orious [Gsus4]You are\r\nAnd I[Em] cannot b[C]egin to tell\r\nHow [G]deep a love Yo[Gsus4]u bring\r\nLo[Em]rd my e[C]ars have heard You\r\nAnd n[G]ow my eyes [Gsus4]have seen\r\n~Chorus\r\nYou are wo[G]rthy You are wo[C]rthy You are[G] wor[Gsus]thy  [4]\r\nYou are w[G]orthy to be pr[C]aised forever[G] and [Gsus4]a day\r\nYou are w[G]orthy You are w[C]orthy You are[G] wo[Gsus4]rthy\r\nYou are [G]worthy to be p[C]raised foreve[G]r and[Gsus4] a day\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[G]Lord I give glo[C]ry to the [G]one who saved [Gsus4]my soul\r\nYou f[G]ound me and You f[C]reed me from the s[G]hame that was [Gsus4]my own\r\nI canno[Em]t begin to t[C]ell how me[G]rciful You[Gsus4]\'ve been\r\nLord m[Em]y ears have he[C]ard of You\r\nAnd now [G]my eyes ha[Gsus4]ve seen\r\n~Tag\r\nWe\'ll si[G]ng an anthem[C] of the hi[G]ghest [Gsus4]praise\r\nWe\'ll s[G]ing an an[C]them of Your glo[G]rious[Gsus4] name\r\n', '', '1999 Thankyou Music. Administered worldwide by worshiptogether.com Songs. ', '', '', 'Worthy You are worthy Much worthy that our world I cannot imagine just how glorious You are And I cannot begin to tell How deep a love You bring Lord my ears have heard You And now my eyes have seen You are worthy You are worthy You are worthy You are worthy to be praised forever and a day You are worthy You are worthy You are worthy You are worthy to be praised forever and a day Lord I give glory to the one who saved my soul You found me and You freed me from the shame that was my own I cannot begin to tell how merciful You\'ve been Lord my ears have heard of You And now my eyes have seen We\'ll sing an anthem of the highest praise We\'ll sing an anthem of Your glorious name'),
	(205, 'Come Thou Fount Of Every Blessing', 'Robert Robinson, adapted by Margaret Clarkson; music: traditional American melody, John Wyeth\'s Repo', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, Thou Fount of every blessing,\r\nTune my heart to sing Thy grace;\r\nStreams of mercy, never ceasing,\r\nCall for songs of loudest praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nTeach me some melodious sonnet,\r\nSung by flaming tongues above;\r\nPraise His name - I\'m fixed upon it\r\nName of God\'s redeeming love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHither to Thy love has blest me;\r\nThou hast bro\'t me to this place;\r\nAnd I know Thy hand will bring me\r\nSafely home by Thy good grace.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nJesus sought me when a stranger,\r\nWandering from the fold of God;\r\nHe, to rescue me from danger,\r\nBought me with His precious blood.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nO to grace how great a debtor\r\nDaily I\'m constrained to be!\r\nLet Thy goodness, like a fetter,\r\nBind my wandering heart to Thee.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nProne to wander, Lord, I feel it,\r\nProne to leave the God I love;\r\nHere\'s my heart, O take and seal it;\r\nSeal it for Thy courts above. Amen.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, Thou Fount of every blessing, Tune my heart to sing Thy grace; Streams of mercy, never ceasing, Call for songs of loudest praise. Teach me some melodious sonnet, Sung by flaming tongues above; Praise His name - I\'m fixed upon it Name of God\'s redeeming love. Hither to Thy love has blest me; Thou hast bro\'t me to this place; And I know Thy hand will bring me Safely home by Thy good grace. Jesus sought me when a stranger, Wandering from the fold of God; He, to rescue me from danger, Bought me with His precious blood. O to grace how great a debtor Daily I\'m constrained to be! Let Thy goodness, like a fetter, Bind my wandering heart to Thee. Prone to wander, Lord, I feel it, Prone to leave the God I love; Here\'s my heart, O take and seal it; Seal it for Thy courts above. Amen.'),
	(206, 'To Be Loved', 'Dennis Jernigan; ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n(Solo)\r\nFather, if we were all to be honest,\r\n what would our greatest need consist of?\r\nWouldn\'t we say, if we were all honest, simply our greatest need is to be loved?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTo be loved is like a harbor in a storm;\r\nTo be anchored so securely at the heart, \r\nyou can\'t be torn.\r\nTo be loved is just what ev\'ry heart \r\nwould give their life to be\r\nHeld just once by One Who would not leave.\r\nTo be loved is what we need.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFrom the strong and stable man\r\n to the single-minded woman,\r\n to the man not even sure he is a man, \r\nTo the lonely hurting children, \r\nto the old, abandoned soul\r\nWe need love to make us whole.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n(Solo)\r\nOnly one love is totally true love.\r\nBearing my sin, bearing my pain!\r\nOnly one love could ever be true love.\r\nOthers will fail, but this one will remain!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThrough the fiery trials of life, \r\nthrough the endless days of prison,\r\nThrough the darkness of rejection\'s\r\n blinding rain.\r\nThrough the days we hurt so badly\r\n and we seem to cry in vain,\r\nJesus\' love will still remain!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nThis world will use you and leave you to die!\r\nThis world will crush you and abuse you\r\nand leave you hard and dry!\r\nJesus will love you and hear when you cry!\r\nHe\'ll never leave you or deceive you!\r\n He\'ll hold you near for life!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nTo be loved is like a harbour in a storm;\r\nTo be anchored so securely at the heart, \r\nyou can\'t be torn\r\nTo be loved is just what ev\'ry heart \r\nwould give their life to be.\r\nHeld just once by One Who would not leave.\r\nTo be loved is what we need.\r\nJesus\' love is what we need!\r\n', '', ' 1993 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, Inc.', '', '', '(Solo) Father, if we were all to be honest, what would our greatest need consist of? Wouldn\'t we say, if we were all honest, simply our greatest need is to be loved? To be loved is like a harbor in a storm; To be anchored so securely at the heart, you can\'t be torn. To be loved is just what ev\'ry heart would give their life to be Held just once by One Who would not leave. To be loved is what we need. From the strong and stable man to the single-minded woman, to the man not even sure he is a man, To the lonely hurting children, to the old, abandoned soul We need love to make us whole. (Solo) Only one love is totally true love. Bearing my sin, bearing my pain! Only one love could ever be true love. Others will fail, but this one will remain! Through the fiery trials of life, through the endless days of prison, Through the darkness of rejection\'s blinding rain. Through the days we hurt so badly and we seem to cry in vain, Jesus\' love will still remain! This world will use you and leave you to die! This world will crush you and abuse you and leave you hard and dry! Jesus will love you and hear when you cry! He\'ll never leave you or deceive you! He\'ll hold you near for life! To be loved is like a harbour in a storm; To be anchored so securely at the heart, you can\'t be torn To be loved is just what ev\'ry heart would give their life to be. Held just once by One Who would not leave. To be loved is what we need. Jesus\' love is what we need!'),
	(207, 'Thank You For The Cross', '', '~Verse 1\r\nThank You for the cross, the mighty cross,\r\nThat God Himself should die for such as us;\r\nAnd ev\'ryday we\'re changed\r\n Into Your image more and more, \r\n Yes, By the cross \r\nWe\'ve truly been transformed.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd we\'re so amazed, \r\nAnd we give You praise\r\nThat You would save us at such a cost;\r\nWe\'re so amazed, and we give You praise\r\nFor the power of the cross,\r\nFor the power of the cross.\r\n', '', '1987 Integrity\'s Praise ! Music/People of Destiny Music', '', '', 'Thank You for the cross, the mighty cross, That God Himself should die for such as us; And ev\\\'ryday we\\\'re changed Into Your image more and more, Yes, By the cross We\\\'ve truly been transformed. And we\\\'re so amazed, And we give You praise That You would save us at such a cost; We\\\'re so amazed, and we give You praise For the power of the cross, For the power of the cross.'),
	(208, 'Joy To The World', 'Isaac Watts and  Music by George Frederick Handel,', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Joy to the world, the Lord [A]is [D]come!\r\nLet [G]earth re[A]ceive her [D]King;\r\nLet ev\'[G]ry [D]heart prepare [G]him [D]room,\r\nAnd heav\'n and nature sing,\r\nAnd [A]heav\'n and nature [A7]sing,\r\nAnd [D]heav\'n, and heav\'n and [D]na - [A7]ture [D]sing.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJoy to the world, the Saviour reigns,\r\nLet men their songs employ;\r\nWhile fields and floods, rocks, hills, and plains\r\nRepeat the sounding joy,\r\nRepeat the sounding joy,\r\nRepeat, repeat the sounding joy.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nNo more let sin and sorrow grow,\r\nNor thorns infest the ground;\r\nHe comes to make his blessings flow\r\nFar as the curse is found,\r\nFar as the curse is found,\r\nFar as, far as the curse is found.\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe rules the world with truth and grace,\r\nAnd makes the nations prove\r\nThe glories of his righteousness,\r\nAnd wonders of his love,\r\nAnd wonders of his love,\r\nAnd wonders, wonders of his love.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Joy to the world, the Lord is come! Let earth receive her King; Let ev\'ry heart prepare him room, And heav\'n and nature sing, And heav\'n and nature sing, And heav\'n, and heav\'n and na - ture sing. Joy to the world, the Saviour reigns, Let men their songs employ; While fields and floods, rocks, hills, and plains Repeat the sounding joy, Repeat the sounding joy, Repeat, repeat the sounding joy. No more let sin and sorrow grow, Nor thorns infest the ground; He comes to make his blessings flow Far as the curse is found, Far as the curse is found, Far as, far as the curse is found. He rules the world with truth and grace, And makes the nations prove The glories of his righteousness, And wonders of his love, And wonders of his love, And wonders, wonders of his love.'),
	(209, 'Thank You Lord', 'Andy Park', '[D]Oh Lord, I[Em] am amazed at Your lo[D]ve for m[G]e\r\n[D]When I was lost and al[Em]one in the darkness\r\n[D]You found m[G]e\r\n[D]You have poured out Your in[Em]finite grace\r\n[D]Lord, what can I s[G]ay?\r\n[D]You are deserving of al[Em]l I can give\r\n[G]You deserve all of my [A]praise\r\n\r\nSo I t[D]hank You, Lo[G]rd\r\nI t[D]hank You, Lo[G]rd\r\nI t[Bm7]hank You, Lor[G]d,\r\nFor Yo[A]ur great lo[D]ve  [Em][D][G]\r\n\r\n[D]Oh Lord, h[Em]ow could I ever rep[D]ay Your lo[G]ve?\r\nFor y[D]ou have given the gr[Em]eatest treasure\r\nOf a[D]ll, Your So[G]n\r\n[D]You have shown me Your inti[Em]mate love\r\n[D]Lord, what can I sa[G]y?\r\n[D]You are deserving of a[Em]ll I can give\r\n[G]You deserve all of my pr[A]aise\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Oh Lord, I am amazed at Your love for me When I was lost and alone in the darkness You found me You have poured out Your infinite grace Lord, what can I say? You are deserving of all I can give You deserve all of my praise So I thank You, Lord I thank You, Lord I thank You, Lord, For Your great love Oh Lord, how could I ever repay Your love? For you have given the greatest treasure Of all, Your Son You have shown me Your intimate love Lord, what can I say? You are deserving of all I can give You deserve all of my praise'),
	(210, 'Be Unto Your Name', 'Robin Mark - Written By: Gary Sadler and Lynn DeShazo.', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]We are a [G]moment, [Dm]You are for[Am]ever\r\n[F]Lord of the a[C]ges, [Bb]God before [Gsus]time[G]\r\n[C]We are a [G]vapor, [Dm]You are e[Am]ternal\r\n[F]Love ever[C/E]lasting, [Bb]reigning on [Gsus]high[G]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[Am]Holy, [F]holy [C/E]Lord God Al[G]mighty\r\n[Am]Worthy [F]is the [C]Lamb Who was [Gsus]slain[G]\r\n[Am]Highest [F]praises, [C/E]honor, and [G]glory\r\n[Dm] Be un[Am]to Your [Gsus]name[G]\r\n[Dm] Be un[Am]to Your [Gsus]name[G]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe are the broken, You are the healer\r\nJesus, Redeemer, mighty to save\r\nYou are the love song we\'ll sing forever\r\nBowing before You, blessing Your name\r\n~Chorus 2\r\n[Asus]\r\n[Bm]Holy, [G]holy [D/F#]Lord God Al[A]mighty\r\n[Bm]Worthy [G]is the [D]Lamb Who was [Asus]slain[A]\r\n[Bm]Highest [G]praises, [D/F#]honor, and [A]glory\r\n[Em] Be un[Bm]to Your [Asus]name[A]\r\n[Em] Be un[Bm]to Your [Asus]name[A]\r\n', '', '1998 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/aQvi7AFXv0c', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(We are a moment, You are forever Lord of the ages, God before time We are a vapor, You are eternal Love everlasting, reigning on high Holy, holy Lord God Almighty Worthy is the Lamb Who was slain Highest praises, honor, and glory Be unto Your name Be unto Your name We are the broken, You are the healer Jesus, Redeemer, mighty to save You are the love song we\'ll sing forever Bowing before You, blessing Your name Holy, holy Lord God Almighty Worthy is the Lamb Who was slain Highest praises, honor, and glory Be unto Your name Be unto Your name).'),
	(212, 'The Highest And The Greatest', 'Nick Herbert and Tim Hughes.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWake every heart and every tongue\r\nTo sing the new eternal song\r\nAnd crown Him King of glory now\r\nConfess Him Lord of all\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe day will come when all will sing\r\nAnd glorify our matchless King\r\nYour name unrivalled stands alone\r\nYou are the Lord of all\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are the highest\r\nYou are the greatest\r\nYou are the Lord of all\r\nAngels will worship\r\nNations will bow down\r\nTo the Lord of all\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLet every heart\r\nLet every tongue\r\nSing of Your name\r\nSing of Your name\r\nLet every heart\r\nLet every tongue\r\nSing, sing, sing\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe\'re lifting You higher, \r\nhigher and higher\r\n~Verse 6\r\nLifting You higher, \r\nhigher and higher\r\n~Verse 7\r\nLifting You higher, \r\nhigher and higher\r\nO Lord\r\n', '', ' 2006 Thankyou Music.  ', '', '', 'Wake every heart and every tongue To sing the new eternal song And crown Him King of glory now Confess Him Lord of all The day will come when all will sing And glorify our matchless King Your name unrivalled stands alone You are the Lord of all You are the highest You are the greatest You are the Lord of all Angels will worship Nations will bow down To the Lord of all Let every heart Let every tongue Sing of Your name Sing of Your name Let every heart Let every tongue Sing, sing, sing We\'re lifting You higher, higher and higher Lifting You higher, higher and higher Lifting You higher, higher and higher O Lord'),
	(213, 'Let All Mortal Flesh Keep Silence', 'Gerard Moultrie.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet all mortal flesh keep silence\r\nAnd with fear and trembling stand\r\nPonder nothing worldly minded\r\nFor with blessing in His hand\r\nChrist our God to earth descendeth\r\nOur full homage to demand\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nKing of kings yet born of Mary\r\nAs of old on earth He stood\r\nLord of lords in human vesture\r\nIn the body and the blood\r\nHe will give to all the faithful\r\nHis own self for heavenly food\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAt His feet the six winged seraph\r\nCherubim with sleepless eye\r\nVeil their faces to the Presence\r\nAs with ceaseless voice they cry\r\nAlleluia, alleluia, alleluia\r\nLord Most High\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nRank on rank the host of heaven\r\nSpreads its vanguard on the way\r\nAs the Light of light descendeth\r\nFrom the realms of endless day\r\nThat the powers of hell may vanish\r\nAs the darkness clears away\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Let all mortal flesh keep silence And with fear and trembling stand Ponder nothing worldly minded For with blessing in His hand Christ our God to earth descendeth Our full homage to demand King of kings yet born of Mary As of old on earth He stood Lord of lords in human vesture In the body and the blood He will give to all the faithful His own self for heavenly food At His feet the six winged seraph Cherubim with sleepless eye Veil their faces to the Presence As with ceaseless voice they cry Alleluia, alleluia, alleluia Lord Most High Rank on rank the host of heaven Spreads its vanguard on the way As the Light of light descendeth From the realms of endless day That the powers of hell may vanish As the darkness clears away'),
	(214, 'I Stand In Awe', 'Mark Altrogge.', '~Verse 1\r\n\r\nYou are beautiful \r\nbeyond description.\r\nToo marvelous for words,\r\nToo wonderful \r\nfor comprehension.\r\nLike nothing ever \r\nseen or heard.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\nWho can grasp \r\nYour infinite wisdom.\r\nWho can fathom \r\nthe depth of Your love.\r\nYou are beautiful \r\nbeyond description,\r\nMajesty enthroned above.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nAnd I stand, \r\nI stand in awe of You.\r\nI stand, I stand \r\nin awe of You.\r\nHoly God to whom \r\nall praise is due\r\nI stand in awe of You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nYou are beautiful\r\nbeyond description,\r\nYet God crushed You\r\nfor my sin;\r\nIn agony and deep\r\naffliction,\r\nCut off that\r\nI might enter in.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\nWho can grasp such\r\ntender compassion,\r\nWho can fathom\r\nthis mercy so free?\r\nYou are beautiful\r\nbeyond description,\r\nLamb of God\r\nwho died for me.\r\n', '', ' 1987 Sovereign Grace Praise.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/ygUEH6i9E7Y', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(You are beautiful beyond description. Too marvelous for words, Too wonderful for comprehension. Like nothing ever seen or heard. Who can grasp Your infinite wisdom. Who can fathom the depth of Your love. You are beautiful beyond description, Majesty enthroned above. And I stand, I stand in awe of You. I stand, I stand in awe of You. Holy God to whom all praise is due I stand in awe of You. You are beautiful beyond description, Yet God crushed You for my sin; In agony and deep affliction, Cut off that I might enter in. Who can grasp such tender compassion, Who can fathom this mercy so free? You are beautiful beyond description, Lamb of God who died for me.).'),
	(215, 'Say To The Lord I Love You', 'Ernie Rettino & Debby Kerner.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nTouch your finger to your nose,\r\nBend from the waist\r\nWay down and touch your toes,\r\nAnd when you come up slowly,\r\nStart to sing,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nReach your hands up to the sky,\r\nLook to the left,\r\nThen right and blink your eyes,\r\nAnd when you turn around\r\nYou\'ll start to sing,\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd say to the Lord, "I love you,\r\nI love you, I love you."\r\nSay to the Lord, "I love you,\r\nI love you, I love you."\r\nSay to the Lord, "I love you."\r\n', '', ' 1981 RFetinno/Kerner Publishing (admin. by Maranatha! Music).', '', '', 'Touch your finger to your nose, Bend from the waist Way down and touch your toes, And when you come up slowly, Start to sing, Reach your hands up to the sky, Look to the left, Then right and blink your eyes, And when you turn around You\'ll start to sing, And say to the Lord, "I love you, I love you, I love you." Say to the Lord, "I love you, I love you, I love you." Say to the Lord, "I love you."'),
	(216, 'Praise To The Lord', 'Bob Fitts', '~Verse 1\r\nIn the battles, Lord, \r\n You are my peace,\r\nWhen I\'m broken, Lord,\r\n You are my strength,\r\n~Chorus\r\nPraise, praise to the Lord,\r\nPraise, praise to the Lord!\r\nFor He is good and merciful;\r\nHis love is great, \r\nHe\'s so wonderful, my Lord.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou\'re my strength, You\'re my love,\r\nYou\'re my life, You\'re my joy,\r\nMy song in the night,\r\nHow I marvel at Your mercy and I sing.\r\nI sing,\r\n', '', '1996 Integrity\'s Hosanne Music', '', '', 'In the battles, Lord, You are my peace, When I\\\'m broken, Lord, You are my strength, Praise, praise to the Lord, Praise, praise to the Lord! For He is good and merciful; His love is great, He\\\'s so wonderful, my Lord. You\\\'re my strength, You\\\'re my love, You\\\'re my life, You\\\'re my joy, My song in the night, How I marvel at Your mercy and I sing. I sing,'),
	(217, 'Psalm 24-7 Proclamation', 'Graham Kendrick', '~Verse 1\r\n(W.L.)\r\nLift up your heads, O you gates\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\nSwing wide, you everlasting doors\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\nThat the King of Glory may come in\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\nThat the King of Glory may come in\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\n~Verse 2\r\n(W.L.)  Who is this King? \r\n     (cong.)  JESUS!\r\nThis glorious King!  \r\n  (cong.)  JESUS!\r\nKing of all kings.  \r\n     (cong.)  JESUS!\r\nShout for your King!  \r\n(cong.)  JESUS!\r\n~Verse 3\r\n(W.L.)\r\nHe rose from the dead with a vict\'ry shout.\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\nAnd now He leads the pris\'ners out.\r\n	 (cong echo)\r\nHis blood won Him the right to reign\r\n	 (cong echo)\r\nThe highest throne, the highest name.\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\n~Verse 4\r\n(W.L.)\r\nWill you have this Man as your King?\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\nWill you bow your knee and worship Him?\r\n	 (cong. echo)\r\n', '', '1991 Make Way Music/Adm.  by Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', '(W.L.) Lift up your heads, O you gates (cong. echo) Swing wide, you everlasting doors (cong. echo) That the King of Glory may come in (cong. echo) That the King of Glory may come in (cong. echo) (W.L.)  Who is this King? (cong.)  JESUS! This glorious King! (cong.)  JESUS! King of all kings. (cong.)  JESUS! Shout for your King! (cong.)  JESUS! (W.L.) He rose from the dead with a vict\\\'ry shout. (cong. echo) And now He leads the pris\\\'ners out. (cong echo) His blood won Him the right to reign (cong echo) The highest throne, the highest name. (cong. echo) (W.L.) Will you have this Man as your King? (cong. echo) Will you bow your knee and worship Him? (cong. echo)'),
	(219, 'My God Is So Big', '', '~Verse 1\r\nMy God is so big, my God is so big,\r\nMy God is so big, my God is so big.\r\nMy God is so big,\r\nThere\'s nothing that He can\'t do!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMy God is so strong, my God is so strong,\r\nMy God is so strong, my God is so strong.\r\nMy God is so strong,\r\nThere\'s nothing that He can\'t do!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMy God is so mighty, my God is so mighty,\r\nMy God is so mighty, my God is so mighty.\r\nMy God is so mighty,\r\nThere\'s nothing that He can\'t do!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nMy God is so big, my God is so strong,\r\nMy God is so mighty,\r\nThere\'s nothing that He can\'t do.\r\nSo big, strong and mighty,\r\nThere\'s nothing that He can\'t do!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'My God is so big, my God is so big, My God is so big, my God is so big. My God is so big, There\\\'s nothing that He can\\\'t do! My God is so strong, my God is so strong, My God is so strong, my God is so strong. My God is so strong, There\\\'s nothing that He can\\\'t do! My God is so mighty, my God is so mighty, My God is so mighty, my God is so mighty. My God is so mighty, There\\\'s nothing that He can\\\'t do! My God is so big, my God is so strong, My God is so mighty, There\\\'s nothing that He can\\\'t do. So big, strong and mighty, There\\\'s nothing that He can\\\'t do!'),
	(220, 'Only The Blood', 'Brian Doerksen. ', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]Holiness is [C2/G]Your life in me[G]\r\nMaking me clea[D]n through Your blo[C]od    [G]\r\n[G]Holiness is [C2/G]Your fire in me[G]\r\nPurging my he[D]art like a flo[C]od    [G]\r\n[D]I know [Em9] You are [C] perfect in [G]holiness\r\n[D]Your life [Em9] in me, [C]setting me free, [Am9]making me ho[D]ly\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]Only the [C2]blood of Jesus [G] covers all of my si[D]n     [C]\r\n[G]Only the [C2]life of Jesus [G] renews me [C]from with[D]in\r\n[Em9]Your blood is enough[C]\r\n[Am9]Your mercy [C/D]com - [D]plete\r\n[Em9]Your work of at[C]onement\r\n[F]Paid for my [D/F#]debts,  [G]making me ho[C2]ly\r\n~Tag\r\n[G] Only the [C2]blood of [D]Je[G]sus\r\n', '', ' 1990 Mercy Publishing.', '', '', 'Holiness is Your life in me Making me clean through Your blood Holiness is Your fire in me Purging my heart like a flood I know  You are  perfect in holiness Your life  in me, setting me free, making me holy Only the blood of Jesus  covers all of my sin Only the life of Jesus  renews me from within Your blood is enough Your mercy com - plete Your work of atonement Paid for my debts,  making me holy Only the blood of Jesus'),
	(222, 'The Battle Belongs To The Lord', 'Jamie Owens-Collins. c. 1984 and this arrangement 1987 by Firhill music, Admin. by Word Music. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIn heavenly armor we\'ll enter the land\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\nNo weapon that\'s fashioned\r\nAgainst us will stand\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen the power of darkness\r\nComes in like a flood,\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\nHe\'s raised up a standard,\r\nThe power of his blood,\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd we sing glory, honor, power\r\nAnd strength to the Lord.\r\nWe sing glory, honor, power\r\nAnd strength to the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhen your enemy presses in hard\r\nDo not fear,\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\nTake courage, my friend,\r\nYour redemption is near,\r\nThe battle belongs to the Lord!\r\n', '', ' 1984 and this arrangement 1987 by Firhill music, Admin. by Word Music. ', '', '', 'In heavenly armor we\'ll enter the land The battle belongs to the Lord! No weapon that\'s fashioned Against us will stand The battle belongs to the Lord! When the power of darkness Comes in like a flood, The battle belongs to the Lord! He\'s raised up a standard, The power of his blood, The battle belongs to the Lord! And we sing glory, honor, power And strength to the Lord. We sing glory, honor, power And strength to the Lord. When your enemy presses in hard Do not fear, The battle belongs to the Lord! Take courage, my friend, Your redemption is near, The battle belongs to the Lord!'),
	(224, 'Overwhelming', 'Mike Engelhardt', '~Verse 1\r\nGod of the galaxies\r\nGod of the city streets\r\nGod of the deep blue seas\r\nAnd so much more!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGod of the spinning globe\r\nGod of the young and old\r\nGod of forgiven souls\r\nAnd so much more!\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGod of the second chance\r\nGod of the healing hands\r\nGod of our circumstance\r\nAnd so much more!\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGod of the darkest night\r\nGod of the tears we cry\r\nGod of the morning light\r\nAnd so much more!\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGod of the Passion\r\nGod of the cross,\r\nGod of the last\r\nAnd God of the lost,\r\n~Verse 6\r\nGod Who has suffered,\r\nGod Who has died,\r\nGod Who has risen, \r\nAnd given us life.\r\n~Verse 7\r\nGod Who has suffered,\r\nGod Who has died,\r\nGod Who has risen, \r\nAnd given us infinite life,\r\nInfinite life\r\n~Chorus\r\nOverwhelming, overflowing\r\nOver all things\r\nYes, You are!\r\nYes, You are!\r\n', '', ' 2004 Ever Devoted Music. Administered by Willow Creek Association. ', '', '', 'God of the galaxies God of the city streets God of the deep blue seas And so much more! God of the spinning globe God of the young and old God of forgiven souls And so much more! God of the second chance God of the healing hands God of our circumstance And so much more! God of the darkest night God of the tears we cry God of the morning light And so much more! God of the Passion God of the cross, God of the last And God of the lost, God Who has suffered, God Who has died, God Who has risen, And given us life. God Who has suffered, God Who has died, God Who has risen, And given us infinite life, Infinite life Overwhelming, overflowing Over all things Yes, You are! Yes, You are!'),
	(225, 'Children Of Light', 'Andy Park', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPsalm 95:6,7\r\nWe are the children of light\r\nWe are the children of day\r\nSo let us worship Him in whom\r\n	 We have our being\r\nUntil the coming of the Lord\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe are the children of God\r\nMade in the image of Christ\r\nAnd on the day He comes\r\nWe shall be made like Him\r\nFor we shall see Him as He is\r\n   \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome let us worship now\r\nLet us kneel, let us humbly bow down\r\nHe is our God, we are His people\r\nWe are the flock in His care\r\nSo come let us bow\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe are the soldiers of Christ\r\nDressed for the battle on high\r\nSo let us call on Him \r\nFor He will fight the battle\r\nAnd we will march with Him on that day\r\n   \r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWe are the faithful of God\r\nWe will endure \'til the end\r\nSo let us run the race \r\nThat He has set before us\r\nTo win the crown of righteousness\r\n', '', ' 1991 Mercy Publishing;  ', '', '', 'Psalm 95:6,7 We are the children of light We are the children of day So let us worship Him in whom We have our being Until the coming of the Lord We are the children of God Made in the image of Christ And on the day He comes We shall be made like Him For we shall see Him as He is Come let us worship now Let us kneel, let us humbly bow down He is our God, we are His people We are the flock in His care So come let us bow We are the soldiers of Christ Dressed for the battle on high So let us call on Him For He will fight the battle And we will march with Him on that day We are the faithful of God We will endure \'til the end So let us run the race That He has set before us To win the crown of righteousness'),
	(226, 'Thanks Be To God', 'Graham Kendrick; ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFather, never was love so near;\r\nTender, my deepest wounds to heal.\r\nPrecious to me, Your gift of love,\r\nFor me You gave Your only Son.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, the heart of God revealed,\r\nWith us, feeling the pain we feel.\r\nCut to the heart wounded for me\r\nTaking the blame, making me clean.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd now thanks be to God\r\nFor His gift beyond words,\r\nThe Son whom He loved,\r\nNo, He did not withold Him,\r\nBut with Him gave everything.\r\nNow He\'s everything to me.\r\n', '', ' 1988 Make Way Music/Thankyou Music; ', '', '', 'Father, never was love so near; Tender, my deepest wounds to heal. Precious to me, Your gift of love, For me You gave Your only Son. Jesus, the heart of God revealed, With us, feeling the pain we feel. Cut to the heart wounded for me Taking the blame, making me clean. And now thanks be to God For His gift beyond words, The Son whom He loved, No, He did not withold Him, But with Him gave everything. Now He\'s everything to me.'),
	(228, 'The River Is Here', 'Andy Park  ', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]Down the m[G]ountain the r[D]iver f[G]lows, \r\nAnd it b[C]rings refr[G]eshing wher[D]ever it g[G]oes.\r\n[C]Thru the v[G]alleys and [D]over the f[G]ields\r\nThe r[C]iver is r[G]ushing, and the r[D]iver is h[G]ere.\r\n~Chorus\r\nThe r[G]iver of God sets our f[C]eet a-d[G]ancing,\r\nThe r[G]iver of God fills our h[D]earts with c[G]heer.\r\nThe r[G]iver of God fills our m[C]ouths with l[G]aughter,\r\nAnd [C]we rejo[G]ice for the r[D]iver is h[G]ere.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe r[C]iver of G[G]od is t[D]eeming with l[G]ife,\r\nAnd a[C]ll who t[G]ouch it can [D]be rev[G]ived.\r\nAnd t[C]hose who l[G]inger on t[D]his river\'s s[G]hore\r\nWill c[C]ome back t[G]hirsting for m[D]ore of the L[G]ord.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nUp [C]to the m[G]ountain we l[D]ove to [G]go,\r\nTo f[C]ind the p[G]resence [D]of the L[G]ord.\r\nAl[C]ong the b[G]anks of the r[D]iver we r[G]un;\r\nWe d[C]ance with l[G]aughter, giving p[D]raise to the S[G]on.\r\n', '', '1994 Mercy Publishing', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/jQH8ddezyh0', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Down the mountain the river flows, And it brings refreshing wherever it goes. Thru the valleys and over the fields The river is rushing, and the river is here. The river of God sets our feet a-dancing, The river of God fills our hearts with cheer. The river of God fills our mouths with laughter, And we rejoice for the river is here. The river of God is teeming with life, And all who touch it can be revived. And those who linger on this river\'s shore Will come back thirsting for more of the Lord. Up to the mountain we love to go, To find the presence of the Lord. Along the banks of the river we run; We dance with laughter, giving praise to the Son.).'),
	(229, 'Come Now Is The Time To Worship', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse\r\n[E]Come, now is the time to [A]wors[E]hip\r\n[B]come, now is the time to [A]give your [B]heart\r\n[E]Come, just as you are to [A]wors[E]hip\r\n[B]Come, just as you are [A]before your [B]God     [E]come\r\n~Chorus 1\r\n[A]One day every tongue will conf[E]ess you are God\r\n[A]One day every knee will [E]bow\r\n[A]Still the greatest treasure [C#m]remains for those\r\nWho [A]gladly choose you [B]now\r\n~Tag\r\nCome, come, come, come\r\n~Chorus 2\r\n[A]Willingly we choose to surr[E]ender our lives\r\n[A]Willingly our knees will [E]bow\r\n[A]With all our heart, soul, [C#m]mind and strength\r\nWe [A]gladly choose You [B]now.\r\n', '', '1998 Vineyard Songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/NPWq8eM4lu8&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Come, now is the time to worship come, now is the time to give your heart Come, just as you are to worship Come, just as you are before your God     come One day every tongue will confess you are God One day every knee will bow Still the greatest treasure remains for those Who gladly choose you now Come, come, come, come Willingly we choose to surrender our lives Willingly our knees will bow With all our heart, soul, mind and strength We gladly choose You now.'),
	(231, 'Undivided Heart (Psalm 86)', 'Brian Doerksen, Daphne Rademaker & Cindy Rethmeier.', '~Verse 1\r\nTeach me Your way, Oh Lord\r\nAnd I will walk in Your truth\r\nShow me Your paths, Oh Lord\r\nFor I am devoted to You.\r\nPurify my heart\'s desire\r\nI long to be Your servant.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGive me an undivided heart\r\nThat I may fear Your name,\r\nGive me an undivided heart\r\nNo other gods, no other love\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGive me an undivided heart\r\nThat I may fear Your name,\r\nGive me an undivided heart\r\nNo other gods, no other love\r\nNo other gods before You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nTeach us Your way, Oh Lord\r\nAnd we will walk in Your truth\r\nShow us Your paths, Oh Lord\r\nFor we are devoted to You.\r\nPurify our heart\'s desire\r\nwe long to be Your servants.\r\n', '', ' 1991 Mercy Publishing. ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/ZcefTANqrn8', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Teach me Your way, Oh Lord And I will walk in Your truth Show me Your paths, Oh Lord For I am devoted to You. Purify my heart\'s desire I long to be Your servant. Give me an undivided heart That I may fear Your name, Give me an undivided heart No other gods, no other love Give me an undivided heart That I may fear Your name, Give me an undivided heart No other gods, no other love No other gods before You. Teach us Your way, Oh Lord And we will walk in Your truth Show us Your paths, Oh Lord For we are devoted to You. Purify our heart\'s desire we long to be Your servants.).'),
	(233, 'Let The Redeemed (of The Lord Say So)', 'Ward Ellis', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet the redeemed of the Lord say so;\r\nLet the redeemed of the Lord say so;\r\nLet the redeemed of the Lord say so;\r\n"I\'m redeemed, I\'m redeemed,\r\nPraise the Lord."\r\n\r\n', '', '1978 Ward Ellis,  ', '', '', 'Let the redeemed of the Lord say so; Let the redeemed of the Lord say so; Let the redeemed of the Lord say so; "I\'m redeemed, I\'m redeemed, Praise the Lord."'),
	(234, 'Change My Heart O God', 'Eddie Espinosa', '~Verse 1\r\nChange my heart, O God\r\nMake it ever true\r\nChange my heart, O God\r\nMay I be like You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are the potter, I am the clay\r\nMold me and make me;\r\nThis is what I pray.\r\n', '', '1982 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/CEtsHWFE6-w&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Change my heart, O God Make it ever true Change my heart, O God May I be like You. You are the potter, I am the clay Mold me and make me; This is what I pray.'),
	(235, 'Sweet Jesus', 'Paul Goodwin; ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSweet Jesus, sweet Jesus\r\nWhat a wonder You are,\r\nYou are brighter than the morning star.\r\nYou are fairer, much fairer\r\nThan the lily that grows by the wayside,\r\nPrecious, more precious than gold.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are the Rose of Sharon,\r\nThe fairest of the fair\r\nYou are all my heart could ere desire.\r\nSweet Jesus, sweet Jesus\r\nWhat a wonder You are\r\nYou are precious, more precious than gold. \r\n', '', ' 1962, 1963 by Gospel Publishing House;', '', '', 'Sweet Jesus, sweet Jesus What a wonder You are, You are brighter than the morning star. You are fairer, much fairer Than the lily that grows by the wayside, Precious, more precious than gold. You are the Rose of Sharon, The fairest of the fair You are all my heart could ere desire. Sweet Jesus, sweet Jesus What a wonder You are You are precious, more precious than gold.'),
	(236, 'Altogether Lovely', 'Words: John Chisum Music: George Searcy', '~Verse 1\r\nYou are altogether lovely,\r\nYou are altogether good,\r\nYou are altogether gentle, kind and true.\r\nThere are none so full of mercy,\r\nThere are none so great and tender,\r\nThere are none as altogether lovely, \r\nLord as You.\r\n', '', 'Tourmaline Music Inc/Ariose Music/Word Music (UK) 1989', '', '', 'You are altogether lovely, You are altogether good, You are altogether gentle, kind and true. There are none so full of mercy, There are none so great and tender, There are none as altogether lovely, Lord as You.'),
	(237, 'Refining (Burn Up)', 'Carol McHardy', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBurn up,\r\nAll of my impurity,\r\nAll the insecurity\r\nWithin my soul.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor I am your child\r\nAnd I need to have your discipline\r\nI cannot be wild\r\nIf I want your Holy Life within\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor I am your child\r\nAnd I need to have your discipline\r\nLord, I want your Holy Life within.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBurn up,\r\nEvery sin, idolatry\r\nThat keeps me from\r\nThe presence of the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI know your blood\r\nIs my ticket to eternity,\r\nIt cancels my iniquity\r\nAnd frees my soul.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nYour love\r\nIs higher than the mountains,\r\nIt calls unto the deep\r\nTo make me whole.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nMy love \r\nIs the best that I can give to you;\r\nIt shatters all resistance\r\nTo the pressing mould.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nI will obey\r\nEverything you ask of me.\r\nHow else will I stay within your fold?\r\n', '', ' 1997 Carol McHardy ', '', '', 'Burn up, All of my impurity, All the insecurity Within my soul. For I am your child And I need to have your discipline I cannot be wild If I want your Holy Life within For I am your child And I need to have your discipline Lord, I want your Holy Life within. Burn up, Every sin, idolatry That keeps me from The presence of the Lord. I know your blood Is my ticket to eternity, It cancels my iniquity And frees my soul. Your love Is higher than the mountains, It calls unto the deep To make me whole. My love Is the best that I can give to you; It shatters all resistance To the pressing mould. I will obey Everything you ask of me. How else will I stay within your fold?'),
	(238, 'You Are Worthy Of My Praise', 'Daivd Ruis', '~Verse 1\r\n[E]I will worship (I will worship)\r\nWith [D]all of my heart (with all of my heart)\r\n[A]I will praise You (I will praise You)\r\nWith [E]all of my strength ([F#m]all my [B]strength)\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[E]I will seek You (I will seek You)\r\n[D]All of my days (all of my days)\r\n[A]I will follow (I will follow)\r\n[E]All of Your ways [F#m](all Your [B]ways)\r\n~Chorus\r\n[E]I will give You [B]all my worship\r\n[A]I will give You [F#m]all my [B]praise\r\n[E]You alone I [B]long to worship\r\n[A]You alone are [F#m]worthy [B]of my [E]praise\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will bow down (I will bow down)\r\nHail You as King (hail You as King)\r\nI will serve You (I will serve You)\r\nGive you ev\'ryting (give You ev\'rything)\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI will lift up (I will lift up)\r\nMy eyes to Your throne (my eyes to Your throne)\r\nI will trust You (I will trust You)\r\nI will trust You alone (trust You alone)\r\n', '', '1993 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/hEcWkt7rxrg&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'I will worship (I will worship) With all of my heart (with all of my heart) I will praise You (I will praise You) With all of my strength (all my strength) I will seek You (I will seek You) All of my days (all of my days) I will follow (I will follow) All of Your ways (all Your ways) I will give You all my worship I will give You all my praise You alone I long to worship You alone are worthy of my praise I will bow down (I will bow down) Hail You as King (hail You as King) I will serve You (I will serve You) Give you ev\'ryting (give You ev\'rything) I will lift up (I will lift up) My eyes to Your throne (my eyes to Your throne) I will trust You (I will trust You) I will trust You alone (trust You alone)'),
	(239, 'I m Abandoned', 'Steve Fry, arranged by Gary Rhodes ', '~Verse 1\r\nWe\'ve been raised for such a time,\r\nHist\'ry comes to the finish line;\r\nAnd the saints who\'ve gone before \r\nWatch to see us end our course.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI\'m abandoned to the Captain\r\n Of the mighty Host of heaven,\r\nAnd I pledge Him my allegiance\r\n \'Til the earth beholds His Kingdom.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSo lay aside each weight that binds.\r\nEnter in the harvest time\r\nUntil the kingdoms of this world\r\nBecome the kingdoms of our Christ!\r\n', '', '1986 Birdwing Music (a div. of EMI Christian Music Pub) ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/LSoLSMN1wL8', '', 'We\'ve been raised for such a time, Hist\'ry comes to the finish line; And the saints who\'ve gone before Watch to see us end our course. I\'m abandoned to the Captain Of the mighty Host of heaven, And I pledge Him my allegiance \'Til the earth beholds His Kingdom. So lay aside each weight that binds. Enter in the harvest time Until the kingdoms of this world Become the kingdoms of our Christ!'),
	(241, 'Come Christians Join To Sing', 'Christian H. Bateman, music: Traditional', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, Christians, join to sing,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLoud praise to Christ our King;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet all, with heart and voice,\r\nBefore His throne rejoice;\r\nPraise is His gracious choice:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCome, lift your hearts on high,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLet praises fill the sky;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nPraise yet our Christ again,\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\nLife shall not end the strain;\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe is our Guide and Friend;\r\nTo us He\'ll condescend;\r\nHis love shall never end:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nOn heaven\'s blissful shore,\r\nHis goodness we\'ll adore,\r\nSinging forevermore:\r\nAlleluia!  Amen!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, Christians, join to sing, Alleluia!  Amen! Loud praise to Christ our King; Alleluia!  Amen! Let all, with heart and voice, Before His throne rejoice; Praise is His gracious choice: Alleluia!  Amen! Come, lift your hearts on high, Alleluia!  Amen! Let praises fill the sky; Alleluia!  Amen! Praise yet our Christ again, Alleluia!  Amen! Life shall not end the strain; Alleluia!  Amen! He is our Guide and Friend; To us He\'ll condescend; His love shall never end: Alleluia!  Amen! On heaven\'s blissful shore, His goodness we\'ll adore, Singing forevermore: Alleluia!  Amen!'),
	(242, 'Glory', 'Danny Daniels', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGlory, glory in the highest\r\nGlory to the Almighty\r\nGlory to the Lamb of God\r\nGlory to the Living Word\r\nGlory to the Lamb\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI give praises, praises, praises, \r\nPraises to the Lamb. \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nPraises, praises in the highest\r\nPraises to the Almighty\r\nPraises to the Lamb of God\r\nPraises to the Living Word\r\nPraises to the Lamb\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI give glory, glory, glory, \r\nGlory to the Lamb. \r\n', '', ' 1980 Mercy Publishing ', '', '', 'Glory, glory in the highest Glory to the Almighty Glory to the Lamb of God Glory to the Living Word Glory to the Lamb I give praises, praises, praises, Praises to the Lamb. Praises, praises in the highest Praises to the Almighty Praises to the Lamb of God Praises to the Living Word Praises to the Lamb I give glory, glory, glory, Glory to the Lamb.'),
	(243, 'The Name Of The Lord Is A Strong Tower', 'Clinton Utterbach. ', '~Verse 1\r\nThe Name of the Lord is a strong tower\r\nThe righteous run into it and they are safe\r\nThe Name of the Lord is a strong tower\r\nThe righteous run into it and they are safe.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBlessed be the Name of the Lord\r\nBlessed be the Name of the Lord\r\nBlessed be the Name of the Lord\r\nMost High\r\n', '', ' 1989 Polygram Int. Publishing', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/4R2AuVYgZsg', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(The Name of the Lord is a strong tower The righteous run into it and they are safe The Name of the Lord is a strong tower The righteous run into it and they are safe. Blessed be the Name of the Lord Blessed be the Name of the Lord Blessed be the Name of the Lord Most High).'),
	(244, 'Heal Our Land', 'Tom & Robin Brooks. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIf My people will humble themselves,\r\nHumble themselves and pray,\r\nIf they seek My face and humble themselves\r\nAnd turn from their wicked ways;\r\nI will hear from heaven and forgive their sin,\r\nI will hear from heaven and heal their land.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord, we bow our knee,\r\nWe humble ourselves,\r\nHumble ourselves and pray,\r\nLord, we seek Your face,\r\nWe humble ourselves\r\nAnd turn from our wicked ways;\r\nFather, in Your mercy, forgive our sin,\r\nFather, in Your mercy, come heal our land.\r\n', '', ' 1988 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music/Integrity\'s Alleluia! Music, c/o Integrity Music. ', '', '', 'If My people will humble themselves, Humble themselves and pray, If they seek My face and humble themselves And turn from their wicked ways; I will hear from heaven and forgive their sin, I will hear from heaven and heal their land. Lord, we bow our knee, We humble ourselves, Humble ourselves and pray, Lord, we seek Your face, We humble ourselves And turn from our wicked ways; Father, in Your mercy, forgive our sin, Father, in Your mercy, come heal our land.'),
