	(269, 'Holy, Holy, Holy (Hymn)', 'Reginald Heber and music by  John B. Dykes.', '~Verse 1\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy! \r\nLord God Almighty\r\nEarly in the  morning\r\nOur song shall rise to Thee.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy!\r\n Merciful and Mighty.\r\nGod in three Persons, \r\nBlessed Trinity.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy!\r\nAll the saints adore Thee\r\nCasting down their golden crowns\r\nAround the glassy sea;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nCherubim and Seraphim\r\nFalling down before Thee,\r\nWhich wert and art\r\nAnd evermore shall be.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy!\r\nLord God Almighty,\r\nAll thy works shall praise Thy name,\r\nIn earth and sky and sea;\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy!\r\nMerciful and mighty;\r\nGod in Three persons, \r\nBlessed Trinity.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy!\r\nThough the darkness hide Thee,\r\nThough the eye of sinful man, \r\nThy glory may not see;\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nOnly Thou art holy -\r\nThere is none beside Thee\r\nPerfect in pow\'r, in love and purity.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Holy, Holy, Holy! Lord God Almighty Early in the  morning Our song shall rise to Thee. Holy, Holy, Holy! Merciful and Mighty. God in three Persons, Blessed Trinity. Holy, Holy, Holy! All the saints adore Thee Casting down their golden crowns Around the glassy sea; Cherubim and Seraphim Falling down before Thee, Which wert and art And evermore shall be. Holy, Holy, Holy! Lord God Almighty, All thy works shall praise Thy name, In earth and sky and sea; Holy, Holy, Holy! Merciful and mighty; God in Three persons, Blessed Trinity. Holy, Holy, Holy! Though the darkness hide Thee, Though the eye of sinful man, Thy glory may not see; Only Thou art holy - There is none beside Thee Perfect in pow\\\'r, in love and purity.'),
