	(278, 'Hallelujah (Your Love Is Amazing)', 'Brenton Brown & Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\nYour love is am[G2/B]azing, steady and un[Csus2]changing,\r\nYour love is a [Dsus]mountain, firm beneath [Csus2]my feet,\r\nYour love is a [G2/B]mystery, how You gently [Csus2]lift me,\r\nWhen I am sur[Dsus]rounded, Your love car[Csus2]ries me.\r\n~Chorus\r\nHallel[G]ujah, halle[Dsus]lujah,\r\nHallel[Em7]ujah,[Csus2] Your love makes me sing,\r\nHallelu[G]jah, hallel[Dsus]ujah,\r\nHalle[Em7]lujah,[Csus2] Your love makes me sing.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour love is surp[G2/B]rising, I can feel it [Csus2]rising,\r\nAll the joy that\'s [Dsus]growing deep inside of[Csus2] me,\r\nEvery time I[G2/B] see You, all Your goodness [Csus2]shines through,\r\nAnd I can feel this[Dsus] God song, rising up in[Csus2] me.\r\n~Bridge\r\n[D]  Yes, You make m[Em7]e sing, [D/F#]\r\nLord, You make me [Csus2]sing, sing, sing,\r\n[D]  How You make me[Em7] sing.  [D/F#]\r\n', '', '2000 Vineyard Songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/0YTgPVBryeY&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Your love is amazing, steady and unchanging, Your love is a mountain, firm beneath my feet, Your love is a mystery, how You gently lift me, When I am surrounded, Your love carries me. Hallelujah, hallelujah, Hallelujah, Your love makes me sing, Hallelujah, hallelujah, Hallelujah, Your love makes me sing. Your love is surprising, I can feel it rising, All the joy that\\\'s growing deep inside of me, Every time I see You, all Your goodness shines through, And I can feel this God song, rising up in me. Yes, You make me sing, Lord, You make me sing, sing, sing, How You make me sing.'),
	(279, 'Til I See You', 'Jadwin Gillies and Joel Houston', '~Verse 1\r\nThe greatest l[A]ove that any[B]one could ever k[C#m7]now\r\nThat overc[A]ame the cross and g[B]rave to find my s[C#m7]oul\r\nAnd \'til I s[A]ee You face to f[B]ace\r\nAnd grace a[C#m7]mazing takes me home\r\nI\'ll trust i[A]n You\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWith all I a[A]m I live to s[B]ee Your Kingdom c[C#m7]ome\r\nAnd in my h[A]eart I pray you\'d l[B]et Your will be d[C#m7]one\r\nAnd \'til I s[A]ee You face to f[B]ace\r\nAnd grace a[C#m7]mazing takes me home\r\nI\'ll trust i[A]n You\r\n~Chorus\r\nI will l[E]ive to l[B/D#]ove You\r\nI will l[C#m7]ive to [E/G#]bring You praise\r\nI will l[A]ive a c[B]hild in awe of [C#m7]You  [B]\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are the v[A]oice that called the u[B]niverse to [C#m7]be\r\nYou are the w[A]hisper in my h[B]eart that speaks to [C#m7]me\r\nAnd \'til I [A]see You face to f[B]ace\r\nAnd grace a[C#m7]mazing takes me home\r\nI\'ll trust i[A]n You\r\n~Bridge\r\nYou al[A]one[E] are [B]God of a[C#m7]ll\r\nYou al[A]one[E] are [B]worthy [C#m7]Lord\r\nAnd with a[A]ll I a[E]m my s[B]oul will bl[C#m7]ess\r\nYour N[A]ame\r\n', '', '2004 Hillsong Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/Ir0-siER8Ns&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'The greatest love that anyone could ever know That overcame the cross and grave to find my soul And \'til I see You face to face And grace amazing takes me home I\'ll trust in You With all I am I live to see Your Kingdom come And in my heart I pray you\'d let Your will be done And \'til I see You face to face And grace amazing takes me home I\'ll trust in You I will live to love You I will live to bring You praise I will live a child in awe of You You are the voice that called the universe to be You are the whisper in my heart that speaks to me And \'til I see You face to face And grace amazing takes me home I\'ll trust in You You alone are God of all You alone are worthy Lord And with all I am my soul will bless Your Name'),
	(280, 'Surely The Presence Of The Lord', 'Lanny Wolfe ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSurely the presence of the Lord\r\n is in this place\r\nI can feel His mighty power \r\nand His grace\r\nI can hear the brush of angels wings,\r\nI see glory on each face\r\nSurely the presence of the Lord \r\nis in this place.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1977 Lanny Wolfe Music ', '', '', 'Surely the presence of the Lord is in this place I can feel His mighty power and His grace I can hear the brush of angels wings, I see glory on each face Surely the presence of the Lord is in this place.'),
	(281, 'Let\'s Just Praise The Lord', 'Gloria Gaither & William J. Gaither;', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet\'s just praise the Lord! Praise the Lord!\r\nLet\'s just lift our hearts to heaven\r\nAnd praise the Lord;\r\nLet\'s just praise the Lord, praise the Lord,\r\nLet\'s just lift our hearts to heaven\r\nAnd praise the Lord!\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1972 William J. Gaither. ', '', '', 'Let\'s just praise the Lord! Praise the Lord! Let\'s just lift our hearts to heaven And praise the Lord; Let\'s just praise the Lord, praise the Lord, Let\'s just lift our hearts to heaven And praise the Lord!'),
	(282, 'Great Are You Lord', '- Steve & Vikki Cook C 1984 Maranatha! Music', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHoly Lord, most holy Lord,\r\nYou alone are worthy of my praise;\r\nO holy Lord, most holy Lord,\r\nWith all of my heart I sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGreat are You Lord, worthy of praise;\r\nHoly and true, great are You, \r\n   Lord, most holy Lord.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Holy Lord, most holy Lord, You alone are worthy of my praise; O holy Lord, most holy Lord, With all of my heart I sing. Great are You Lord, worthy of praise; Holy and true, great are You, Lord, most holy Lord.'),
	(283, 'All I Want To Do', 'Eogan Heaslip', '~Intro      (key Ab capo 1 key G) 4x\r\n[G]  [C2] [C]  [D] [D]\r\n~Verse\r\n[G]All I want [C2]to do is be close [D]to You\r\nAnd [G]all I want [C2]to say is thank You [D]for the [Em7]way\r\n[Em7]You love [D2/F#]me ,   You [C2]love [D]me    (2x)\r\n~Chorus\r\n[D]You are [G2]faithful [C2]to  [C2/E]all that You [D]have promised\r\n[D]And [G]loving [C]in [C2/E]all of Your [D/F#]ways\r\n[G2]And [C2]still with all of my [D]failings\r\n[D]You love [C2]me, You love me, You love [D]me\r\n~Tag\r\n[G]La, la, [C2]la, la, la\r\n[C2/E]La, la, [D]la, la, la\r\n~Outro\r\n[G]  [C2] [C]  [D] [D]\r\n', '', '2000 Daybreak Music Ltd. ', '', '', 'All I want to do is be close to You And all I want to say is thank You for the way You love me ,   You love me    (2x) You are faithful to  all that You have promised And loving in all of Your ways And still with all of my failings You love me, You love me, You love me La, la, la, la, la La, la, la, la, la'),
	(284, 'Everlasting', 'Brian Doerksen and Matt Unruh. ', '~Verse 1\r\nIn holiness You stand secure \r\nthrough culture\'s shifting sands\r\nUnchanged by all the vanities of man\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd as the nations rise and fall \r\nYour sovereignty remains \r\nYou are, You are, You are \r\nthe One True God\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn faithfulness Your love extends\r\nThrough times of turbulence \r\nAdopting those who call upon Your name\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd every generation joins \r\nin songs of grateful praise You are, \r\nYou are,You are the One True God\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nFrom everlasting to everlasting\r\nYou are God\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nEternal Immortal Invisible God\r\nEternal Immortal Invisible God\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nYou are God\r\nYou are God\r\n', '', ' 2004  Integrity\'s Hosanna!  Music, c/o Integrity Media, Inc.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/fL2Bf24nu1E&hl=en&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/everlasting/id183487201?i=183487297&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Brian Doerksen - Today - Everlasting" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'In holiness You stand secure through culture\\\'s shifting sands Unchanged by all the vanities of man And as the nations rise and fall Your sovereignty remains You are, You are, You are the One True God In faithfulness Your love extends Through times of turbulence Adopting those who call upon Your name And every generation joins in songs of grateful praise You are, You are,You are the One True God From everlasting to everlasting You are God Eternal Immortal Invisible God Eternal Immortal Invisible God You are God You are God'),
	(285, 'We Are An Offering', 'Dwight Liles', '~Verse 1\r\nWe l[F/G]ift our v[C]oices,  [Dm7]   we lift our [C/E]hands, we lift our [F]lives up to [C/E]you\r\nWe are an [Bb/D]offerin[G7sus]g. - (2nd ending) [G7]We are an [C]offering.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord [F/G]use our v[C]oices,  [Dm7]   Lord use our [C/E]hands,\r\nLord use our [F]lives they are [C/E]Yours, we are an [Bb/D]offering[G7sus].[G7]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[Em]All that we [Am]have, [Dm]all that we [F]are,\r\n[E7]All that we h[Am]ope to be[E] [F#] [G#] [A]\r\nWe [F]give to [Em]You, we [Bb]give to [Dm7]You.[G7sus] [F/G]\r\n', '', '1984 Bug and Bear Music', '', '', 'We lift our voices,     we lift our hands, we lift our lives up to you We are an offering. - (2nd ending) We are an offering. Lord use our voices,     Lord use our hands, Lord use our lives they are Yours, we are an offering. All that we have, all that we are, All that we hope to be We give to You, we give to You.'),
	(287, 'Once In Royal David\'s City (Hymn #155)', '', '~Verse 1\r\nOnce in royal David\'s city\r\nStood a lowly cattle shed,\r\nWhere a mother laid her Baby\r\nIn a manger for His bed:\r\nMary was that mother mild,\r\nJesus Christ her little Child.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe came down to earth from heaven\r\nWho is God and Lord of all,\r\nAnd His shelter  was a stable,\r\nAnd His cradle was a stall:\r\nWith the poor, and mean, and lowly\r\nLived on earth, our Savior holy.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus is our childhood\'s pattern,\r\nDay by day like us He grew;\r\nHe was little, weak, and helpless,\r\nTears and smiles like us He knew:\r\nAnd He feeleth for our sadness,\r\nAnd He shareth in our gladness.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd our eyes at last shall see Him\r\nThro\' His own redeeming love;\r\nFor what Child so dear and gentle\r\nIs our Lord in heav\'n above,\r\nAnd He leads His children on\r\nTo the place where He is gone.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Once in royal David\\\'s city Stood a lowly cattle shed, Where a mother laid her Baby In a manger for His bed: Mary was that mother mild, Jesus Christ her little Child. He came down to earth from heaven Who is God and Lord of all, And His shelter  was a stable, And His cradle was a stall: With the poor, and mean, and lowly Lived on earth, our Savior holy. Jesus is our childhood\\\'s pattern, Day by day like us He grew; He was little, weak, and helpless, Tears and smiles like us He knew: And He feeleth for our sadness, And He shareth in our gladness. And our eyes at last shall see Him Thro\\\' His own redeeming love; For what Child so dear and gentle Is our Lord in heav\\\'n above, And He leads His children on To the place where He is gone.'),
	(288, 'Holy Holy Holy (the earth is filled with Your glory)', 'Larry Hampton', '~Intro\r\n[Em] [D/E] [Dsus] [D]\r\n[Em] [D/E] [D/C] [Cmaj7]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[G]   The earth is [D]filled with Your glo - [Em7]ry[Gmaj7/E][D/F#]\r\n[G]   We stand in [C]awe of Your [Dsus]majes[D]ty\r\n[Em]   Behold the [D/F#]splendor of[C] the King\r\nAnd join the [D/C]angels as[C] they sing[Dsus][D][D/F#]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]   "Holy, [D]holy, ho - [Am]ly[D/F#]\r\n[G]   Is the [D]Lamb of God[C][C/E][D/F#]\r\n[G]   Honor, [D]praise and glo [Am]- ry\r\nAre Yours,[Em7][D/E]      oh Lo[Dsus]rd,[D]    [D/C]foreve[C]r" [D/C][Cmaj9]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAs we gaze at Your beauty\r\nWe cannot help falling on our knees\r\nWe have come to adore our King\r\nAnd join the angels as they sing\r\n', '', '1994 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing', '', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(The earth is filled with Your glo - ry We stand in awe of Your majesty Behold the splendor of the King And join the angels as they sing "Holy, holy, ho - ly Is the Lamb of God Honor, praise and glo - ry Are Yours,      oh Lord,    forever" As we gaze at Your beauty We cannot help falling on our knees We have come to adore our King And join the angels as they sing).'),
	(289, 'Jesus Shall Reign', 'Isaac Watts, Music by John Hatton', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus shall reign wher\'er the sun\r\nDoes his successive journeys run;\r\nHis kingdom spread from shore to shore,\r\nTill moons shall wax and wane no more.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nTo Him shall endless prayer be made, \r\nAnd endless praises crown His head;\r\nHis name like sweet perfume shall rise \r\nWith ev\'ry morning sacrifice.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPeople and realms of ev\'ry tongue\r\nDwell on His love with sweetest song;\r\nAnd infant voices shall proclaim\r\nTheir early blessings on His name.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLet ev\'ry creature rise and bring \r\nHis grateful honors to our King;\r\nAngels descend with songs again,\r\nAnd earth repeat the loud "Amen!"\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Jesus shall reign wher\'er the sun Does his successive journeys run; His kingdom spread from shore to shore, Till moons shall wax and wane no more. To Him shall endless prayer be made, And endless praises crown His head; His name like sweet perfume shall rise With ev\'ry morning sacrifice. People and realms of ev\'ry tongue Dwell on His love with sweetest song; And infant voices shall proclaim Their early blessings on His name. Let ev\'ry creature rise and bring His grateful honors to our King; Angels descend with songs again, And earth repeat the loud "Amen!"'),
	(290, 'Trust And Obey (Hymn #349)', 'John H. Sammis and Music by Daniel B. Towner', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhen we walk with the Lord\r\nin the light of His Word,\r\nWhat a glory He sheds on our way!\r\nWhile we do His good will\r\nHe abides with us still,\r\nAnd with all who will trust and obey.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nNot a shadow can rise, \r\nnot a cloud in the skies,\r\nBut His smile quickly drives it away;\r\nNot a doubt nor a fear, not a sigh nor a tear,\r\nCan abide while we trust and obey.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nNot a burden we bear, \r\nnot a sorrow we share,\r\nBut our toil He doth richly repay;\r\nNot a grief nor a loss,\r\n not a frown nor a cross,\r\nBut is blest if we trust and obey.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBut we never can prove, \r\nthe delights of His love\r\nUntil all on the altar we lay;\r\nFor the favor He shows\r\n and the joy He bestows\r\nAre for them who will trust and obey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\nTrust and obey, for there\'s no other way\r\n	 to be happy in Jesus,\r\nBut to trust and obey.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nThen in fellowship sweet \r\nwe will sit at His feet,\r\nOr we\'ll walk by His side in the way;\r\nWhat He says He will do,\r\nWhere He sends we will go\r\nNever fear, only trust and obey.\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'When we walk with the Lord in the light of His Word, What a glory He sheds on our way! While we do His good will He abides with us still, And with all who will trust and obey. Not a shadow can rise, not a cloud in the skies, But His smile quickly drives it away; Not a doubt nor a fear, not a sigh nor a tear, Can abide while we trust and obey. Not a burden we bear, not a sorrow we share, But our toil He doth richly repay; Not a grief nor a loss, not a frown nor a cross, But is blest if we trust and obey. But we never can prove, the delights of His love Until all on the altar we lay; For the favor He shows and the joy He bestows Are for them who will trust and obey. Trust and obey, for there\'s no other way to be happy in Jesus, But to trust and obey. Then in fellowship sweet we will sit at His feet, Or we\'ll walk by His side in the way; What He says He will do, Where He sends we will go Never fear, only trust and obey.'),
	(291, 'Be Still My Soul', 'Katharina von Schlegel, translated by Jane L. Borthwick', '~Verse 1\r\nBe still, my soul! The Lord is on thy side;\r\nBear patiently the cross of grief or pain;\r\nIn every change He faithful will remain.\r\nBe still, my soul!\r\nThy best, thy heavenly Friend\r\nThro\' thorny ways leads to a joyful end.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBe still, my soul! Thy God doth undertake\r\nTo guide the future as He has the past.\r\nThy hope, thy confidence let nothing shake;\r\nAll now mysterious shall be bright at last.\r\nBe still, my soul!\r\nThe waves and winds still know His voice \r\nWho ruled them while He dwelt below.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBe still, my soul! The hour is hastening on\r\nWhen we shall be forever with the Lord,\r\nWhen disappointment, grief\r\nAnd fear are gone,\r\nSorrow forgot, love\'s purest joys restored.\r\nBe still, my soul!\r\nWhen change and tears are past,\r\nAll safe and blessed we shall meet at last.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/c9zHn4QSH-8&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Be still, my soul! The Lord is on thy side; Bear patiently the cross of grief or pain; In every change He faithful will remain. Be still, my soul! Thy best, thy heavenly Friend Thro\\\' thorny ways leads to a joyful end. Be still, my soul! Thy God doth undertake To guide the future as He has the past. Thy hope, thy confidence let nothing shake; All now mysterious shall be bright at last. Be still, my soul! The waves and winds still know His voice Who ruled them while He dwelt below. Be still, my soul! The hour is hastening on When we shall be forever with the Lord, When disappointment, grief And fear are gone, Sorrow forgot, love\\\'s purest joys restored. Be still, my soul! When change and tears are past, All safe and blessed we shall meet at last.'),
	(292, 'Say Yes', 'Graham Kendrick', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n(W.L.) All of God\'s people here\r\n(All) Say Yes!    (repeat 3x)\r\n\r\n \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n(All)     Say Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To the kingdom of heaven.\r\n(All)     Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To the King of kings.\r\n(All)     Say Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To His power and glory,\r\n(All)     All of God\'s people here say yes!   (repeat 2x)\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n(All)     Say yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To the love of the Father,\r\n(All)     Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To His only Son.\r\n(All)     Say Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  To the pow\'r of the Spirit.\r\n(All)     All of God\'s people here say yes!\r\n(repeat 2x)\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n(All)     Say Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  Let His kingdom come here,\r\n(All)     Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  Let His wil be done.\r\n(All)     Say Yes!\r\n(W.L.)  All across the nation.\r\n(All)     All of God\'s people here say yes!\r\n(repeat 4x)  \r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nJesus is Lord   (repeat 4x)\r\n', '', ' 1991 Make Way Music, Adm. in U.S. & Canada by Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music; c/o Integrity Music, Inc.', '', '', '(W.L.) All of God\'s people here (All) Say Yes!    (repeat 3x) (All)     Say Yes! (W.L.)  To the kingdom of heaven. (All)     Yes! (W.L.)  To the King of kings. (All)     Say Yes! (W.L.)  To His power and glory, (All)     All of God\'s people here say yes!   (repeat 2x) (All)     Say yes! (W.L.)  To the love of the Father, (All)     Yes! (W.L.)  To His only Son. (All)     Say Yes! (W.L.)  To the pow\'r of the Spirit. (All)     All of God\'s people here say yes! (repeat 2x) (All)     Say Yes! (W.L.)  Let His kingdom come here, (All)     Yes! (W.L.)  Let His wil be done. (All)     Say Yes! (W.L.)  All across the nation. (All)     All of God\'s people here say yes! (repeat 4x) Jesus is Lord   (repeat 4x)'),
	(293, 'Unto Thee O Lord', 'Charles F. Monroe. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nUnto Thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.\r\nUnto Thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul.\r\nO my God, I trust in Thee.\r\nLet me not be ashamed\r\nLet not mine enemies triumph over me.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1971 Charles F. Monroe.', '', '', 'Unto Thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul. Unto Thee, O Lord, do I lift up my soul. O my God, I trust in Thee. Let me not be ashamed Let not mine enemies triumph over me.'),
	(294, 'Praise The Name Of Jesus', 'Roy Hicks. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPraise the name of Jesus,\r\nPraise the name of Jesus,\r\nHe\'s my rock,\r\nHe\'s my fortress,\r\nHe\'s my deliverer,\r\nIn Him will I trust.\r\nPraise the name of Jesus.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1976', '', '', 'Praise the name of Jesus, Praise the name of Jesus, He\'s my rock, He\'s my fortress, He\'s my deliverer, In Him will I trust. Praise the name of Jesus.'),
	(295, 'Christ The Lord Is Risen Today', 'Charles Wesley, music: from Lyra Davidica,', '~Verse 1\r\nChrist the Lord is ris\'n today, Alleluia!\r\nSons of men and angels say: Alleluia!\r\nRaise your joys and triumphs high, Alleluia!\r\nSing, ye heav\'ns, and earth reply: Alleluia!\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLives again our glorious King, Alleluia!\r\nWhere, O death, is now thy sting? Alleluia!\r\nDying once He all doth save, Alleluia!\r\nWhere thy victory, O grave? Alleluia!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLove\'s redeeming work is done,\r\nAlleluia!\r\nFought the fight, the battle won,\r\nAlleluia!\r\nDeath in vain forbids Him rise, Alleluia!\r\nChrist has opened Paradise, Alleluia!\r\n~Verse 6\r\nSoar we now where Christ has led, Alleluia!\r\nFoll\'wing our exalted Head, Alleluia!\r\nMade like Him, like Him we rise,\r\nAlleluia!\r\nOurs the cross, the grave, the skies, Alleluia!', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/nzy7jFNUc3w', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Christ the Lord is ris\'n today, Alleluia! Sons of men and angels say: Alleluia! Raise your joys and triumphs high, Alleluia! Sing, ye heav\'ns, and earth reply: Alleluia! Lives again our glorious King, Alleluia! Where, O death, is now thy sting? Alleluia! Dying once He all doth save, Alleluia! Where thy victory, O grave? Alleluia! Love\'s redeeming work is done, Alleluia! Fought the fight, the battle won, Alleluia! Death in vain forbids Him rise, Alleluia! Christ has opened Paradise, Alleluia! Soar we now where Christ has led, Alleluia! Foll\'wing our exalted Head, Alleluia! Made like Him, like Him we rise, Alleluia! Ours the cross, the grave, the skies, Alleluia!).'),
