	(299, 'Arms Of Love', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]   I sing a si[D/F#]mple song of lo[Em]ve[Em/D]\r\nTo my Sa[C]vior, [Em] to my Je[D]sus\r\n[G]   I\'m grateful [D/F#]for the things You\'ve do[Em]ne\r\nMy loving Sa[C]vior, [Em] oh precious Je[D]sus\r\n[Am]   My heart is gl[Em]ad that You\'ve [D/F#]called me Your ow[G]n\r\n[Am]   There\'s no [Em]place I\'d rather be [D]\r\n~Chorus\r\n(Than) In Your [G]arm[Bm7]s of love[C]\r\nIn Your [G]arm[Bm7]s of love[C]\r\nHolding me stil[Em]l\r\n[Bm7]Holding me near[C] In Your arms of lov[G]e\r\n', '', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/XnbH7Rt2qkE&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'I sing a simple song of love To my Savior,  to my Jesus I\'m grateful for the things You\'ve done My loving Savior,  oh precious Jesus My heart is glad that You\'ve called me Your own There\'s no place I\'d rather be (Than) In Your arms of love In Your arms of love Holding me still Holding me near In Your arms of love'),
	(300, 'I Will Sing Unto The Lord', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will sing unto the Lord\r\nFor He has triumphed gloriously,\r\nThe horse and the rider thrown into the sea.\r\nThe Lord, my God, my strength and my song\r\nAnd now He is my victory!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe Lord is God and I will praise Him.\r\nMy Father\'s God, and I will exalt Him!\r\n', '', ' 1983 Sound III, Inc.', '', '', 'I will sing unto the Lord For He has triumphed gloriously, The horse and the rider thrown into the sea. The Lord, my God, my strength and my song And now He is my victory! The Lord is God and I will praise Him. My Father\'s God, and I will exalt Him!'),
	(301, 'Lord Listen To Your Children Praying', 'Ken Medema', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, listen to your children praying,\r\nLord, send your Spirit in this place;\r\nLord, listen to your children praying,\r\nSend us love,\r\nSend us power,\r\nSend us grace.\r\n', '', ' 1973 Hope Publishing Company', '', '', 'Lord, listen to your children praying, Lord, send your Spirit in this place; Lord, listen to your children praying, Send us love, Send us power, Send us grace.'),
	(302, 'Come Let Us Sing For Joy', 'Brent Chambers', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet us come before Him with thanksgiving\r\nAnd extol Him with music and song;\r\nFor the Lord, our Lord, is a great God,\r\nThe great King above all gods.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCome, let us sing for joy to the Lord,\r\nLet us shout aloud\r\nTo the Rock of our salvation.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome, let us sing for joy to the Lord \r\nCome, let us sing for joy.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLet us bow before Him in our worship,\r\nLet us kneel before God, our great King;\r\nFor He is our God and we are His people\r\nThat\'s why we shout and sing.\r\n', '', ' 1985 Scripture in Song Admin. - Maranatha! Music,', '', '', 'Let us come before Him with thanksgiving And extol Him with music and song; For the Lord, our Lord, is a great God, The great King above all gods. Come, let us sing for joy to the Lord, Let us shout aloud To the Rock of our salvation. Come, let us sing for joy to the Lord Come, let us sing for joy. Let us bow before Him in our worship, Let us kneel before God, our great King; For He is our God and we are His people That\'s why we shout and sing.'),
	(303, 'Create In Me A Clean Heart', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCreate in me a clean heart, O God\r\nAnd renew a right spirit within me.\r\nCreate in me a clean heart, O God\r\nAnd renew a right spirit within me.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCast me not away\r\nFrom Thy presence, O Lord \r\nAnd take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. \r\nRestore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, \r\nAnd renew a right spirit within me.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Create in me a clean heart, O God And renew a right spirit within me. Create in me a clean heart, O God And renew a right spirit within me. Cast me not away From Thy presence, O Lord And take not Thy Holy Spirit from me. Restore unto me the joy of Thy salvation, And renew a right spirit within me.'),
	(304, 'Higher Ground', 'Johnson Oatman, Jr. and Charles H. Gabriel', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI\'m pressing on the upward way,\r\nNew heights I\'m gaining ev\'ry day,\r\nStill praying as I\'m onward bound,\r\n"Lord, plant my feet on higher ground"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, lift me up and let me stand\r\nBy faith on heaven\'s table land;\r\nA higher plane than I have found,\r\nLord, plant my feet on higher ground.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nMy heart has no desire to stay,\r\nWhere doubts arise and fears dismay,\r\nTho some may dwell where these abound,\r\nMy pray\'r, my aim, is higher ground.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI want to live above the world,\r\nTho Satan\'s darts at me are hurled,\r\nFor faith has caught the joyful sound,\r\nThe song of saints on higher ground.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI want to scale the utmost height,\r\nAnd catch a gleam of glory bright,\r\nBut still I\'ll pray till heav\'n I\'ve found,\r\n"Lord, lead me on to higher ground"\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I\'m pressing on the upward way, New heights I\'m gaining ev\'ry day, Still praying as I\'m onward bound, "Lord, plant my feet on higher ground" Lord, lift me up and let me stand By faith on heaven\'s table land; A higher plane than I have found, Lord, plant my feet on higher ground. My heart has no desire to stay, Where doubts arise and fears dismay, Tho some may dwell where these abound, My pray\'r, my aim, is higher ground. I want to live above the world, Tho Satan\'s darts at me are hurled, For faith has caught the joyful sound, The song of saints on higher ground. I want to scale the utmost height, And catch a gleam of glory bright, But still I\'ll pray till heav\'n I\'ve found, "Lord, lead me on to higher ground"'),
	(305, 'We Exalt Thee', 'Pete Sanchez', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFor Thou O Lord\r\nArt high above all the earth,\r\nThou art exalted far above all gods. \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe exalt Thee, \r\nWe exalt Thee, \r\nWe exalt Thee, O Lord, \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'For Thou O Lord Art high above all the earth, Thou art exalted far above all gods. We exalt Thee, We exalt Thee, We exalt Thee, O Lord,'),
	(307, 'Let Us Break Bread Together', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet us break bread together on our knees,\r\nLet us break bread together on our knees;\r\nWhen I fall on my knees,\r\nWith my face to the rising sun,\r\nO Lord, have mercy on me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet us drink the cup together on our knees,\r\nLet us drink the cup together on our knees;\r\nWhen I fall on my knees,\r\nWith my face to the rising sun,\r\nO Lord, have mercy on me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet us praise God together on our knees,\r\nLet us praise God together on our knees;\r\nWhen I fall on my knees,\r\nWith my face to the rising sun,\r\nO Lord, Have mercy on me.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Let us break bread together on our knees, Let us break bread together on our knees; When I fall on my knees, With my face to the rising sun, O Lord, have mercy on me. Let us drink the cup together on our knees, Let us drink the cup together on our knees; When I fall on my knees, With my face to the rising sun, O Lord, have mercy on me. Let us praise God together on our knees, Let us praise God together on our knees; When I fall on my knees, With my face to the rising sun, O Lord, Have mercy on me.'),
	(308, 'Open Up The Sky', 'Lindell Cooley and Lenny LeBlanc. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFather, I just want to be where You are.\r\nMy life is filled with everything but You.\r\nLord, I really want to see Your glory.\r\nLet the fire of heaven fall on me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nCan You feel my passion?\r\nCan You see my hunger?\r\nDo You know how I long for You?\r\nNo walls between us.\r\nTake away this darkness.\r\nCome break this heart of stone.\r\nHear my cry, open up the sky!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCan You feel our passion?\r\nCan You see our hunger?\r\nDo You know how we long for You?\r\nNo walls between us.\r\nTake away this darkness.\r\nCome break these hearts of stone.\r\nHear our cry, open up the sky!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nEverywhere I go there is a feeling\r\nThat soon we\'re gonna see \r\nYour kingdom come.\r\nCan you hear the sound of desperation?\r\nA prayer on the lips of every nation.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\nLord we really want to see Your glory\r\nSo let the fire of Heaven fall on me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\n\r\n\r\n    Open up the sky!\r\n', '', ' 2001 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'Father, I just want to be where You are. My life is filled with everything but You. Lord, I really want to see Your glory. Let the fire of heaven fall on me. Can You feel my passion? Can You see my hunger? Do You know how I long for You? No walls between us. Take away this darkness. Come break this heart of stone. Hear my cry, open up the sky! Can You feel our passion? Can You see our hunger? Do You know how we long for You? No walls between us. Take away this darkness. Come break these hearts of stone. Hear our cry, open up the sky! Everywhere I go there is a feeling That soon we\'re gonna see Your kingdom come. Can you hear the sound of desperation? A prayer on the lips of every nation. Lord we really want to see Your glory So let the fire of Heaven fall on me. Open up the sky!'),
	(309, 'Holy, Holy, Holy Lord', 'Peter Scholtes', '~Verse 1\r\nHoly, Holy, Holy Lord\r\nGod of pow\'r and might,\r\nHeaven and earth are filled\r\nWith Your glory.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHosanna, Hosanna\r\nIn the highest.\r\n', '', '1987 FEL Publications', '', '', 'Holy, Holy, Holy Lord God of pow\\\'r and might, Heaven and earth are filled With Your glory. Hosanna, Hosanna In the highest.'),
	(310, 'His Name Is Wonderful', 'Audrey Mieir', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHis name is wonderful\r\nHis name is wonderful\r\nHis name is wonderful\r\nJesus My Lord\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBow down before Him,\r\n  Love and adore Him,\r\nHis name is Wonderful,\r\n Jesus my Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe is the mighty King,\r\nMaster of everything,\r\nHis name is Wonderful,\r\nJesus my Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe\'s the great Shepherd,\r\n  The Rock of all ages,\r\nAlmighty God is He.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 35255 Brooten Rd, Pacific City, Or. 97135  ', '', '', 'His name is wonderful His name is wonderful His name is wonderful Jesus My Lord Bow down before Him, Love and adore Him, His name is Wonderful, Jesus my Lord. He is the mighty King, Master of everything, His name is Wonderful, Jesus my Lord. He\'s the great Shepherd, The Rock of all ages, Almighty God is He.'),
	(311, 'Hark The Herald Angels Sing', 'Charles Wesley, Music by Felix Mendelssohn', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHark! the herald angels sing, \r\n"Glory to the newborn King;\r\nPeace on earth, and mercy mild,\r\nGod and sinners reconciled!"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJoyful all ye nations rise, \r\nJoin the triumph of the skies;\r\nWith th\' angelic host proclaim,\r\n"Christ is born in Bethlehem!"\r\nHark! the herald angels sing,\r\n"Glory to the newborn King."\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nChrist, by highest heav\'n adored;\r\nChrist the everlasting Lord!\r\nLate in time behold Him come,\r\nOff-spring of the Virgin\'s womb;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nVeiled in flesh the God-head see;\r\nHail th\' incarnate Deity,\r\nPleased as man with men to dwell,\r\nJesus, our Emmanuel.\r\nHark! the herald angels sing,\r\n"Glory to the newborn King.\'\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHail the heav\'n born \r\nPrince of Peace!\r\nHail the Sun of Righteousness!\r\nLight and life to all He brings,\r\nRis\'n with healing in His wings.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nMild He lays His glory by,\r\nBorn that man no more may die,\r\nBorn to raise the sons of earth,\r\nBorn to give them second birth.\r\nHark! the herald angels sing,\r\n"Glory to the newborn King."\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Hark! the herald angels sing, "Glory to the newborn King; Peace on earth, and mercy mild, God and sinners reconciled!" Joyful all ye nations rise, Join the triumph of the skies; With th\' angelic host proclaim, "Christ is born in Bethlehem!" Hark! the herald angels sing, "Glory to the newborn King." Christ, by highest heav\'n adored; Christ the everlasting Lord! Late in time behold Him come, Off-spring of the Virgin\'s womb; Veiled in flesh the God-head see; Hail th\' incarnate Deity, Pleased as man with men to dwell, Jesus, our Emmanuel. Hark! the herald angels sing, "Glory to the newborn King.\' Hail the heav\'n born Prince of Peace! Hail the Sun of Righteousness! Light and life to all He brings, Ris\'n with healing in His wings. Mild He lays His glory by, Born that man no more may die, Born to raise the sons of earth, Born to give them second birth. Hark! the herald angels sing, "Glory to the newborn King."'),
	(312, 'Be Exalted O God', 'Brent Chambers', '~Verse 1\r\nI will [G]give t[C]hanks to T[G]hee, O Lord a[C]mong the [G]people,\r\nI will s[Em]ing praises to [D]You a[C]mong the n[G]ations.[C][D]\r\nFor thy [G]steadfast l[C]ove is g[G]reat, Is great t[C]o the [G]heavens, \r\nAnd thy [Em]faithfulness, thy f[C]aithfulness to the c[D]louds[D7],\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C]Be [D]exa[G]lted O God, above the h[D]ea[Am7]vens[D], \r\nAnd let thy g[C]lory be [D]over all the e[G]arth,[CG]\r\n[C]Be [D]exa[G]lted O God, above the h[D]ea[Am7]vens[D],\r\nAnd let thy g[C]lory be [D]over all the e[G]arth,\r\nLet thy g[C]lo-r[D]y, Let thy g[Bm]lo-[Em]ry,\r\nLet thy g[C]lory be [D]over all the e[G]arth.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFor Thy steadfast love is great,\r\nIs great to the heavens,\r\nAnd Thy faithfulness, \r\nThy faithfulness to the clouds.\r\n', '', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/zHOX_UkDHqw', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/be-exalted-o-god/id285576148?i=285576165&uo=4" target="itunes_store">Be Exalted O God - Call to War, Pt. One</a>', 'I will give thanks to Thee, O Lord among the people, I will sing praises to You among the nations. For thy steadfast love is great, Is great to the heavens, And thy faithfulness, thy faithfulness to the clouds, Be exalted O God, above the heavens, And let thy glory be over all the earth, Be exalted O God, above the heavens, And let thy glory be over all the earth, Let thy glo-ry, Let thy glo-ry, Let thy glory be over all the earth. For Thy steadfast love is great, Is great to the heavens, And Thy faithfulness, Thy faithfulness to the clouds.'),
	(313, 'Shine Jesus Shine', 'Graham Kendrick', '~Chorus\r\n[A]Shine, [E/A]Jesus, [D/A]Shine,  fill this [Bm]land [Bm/A]with the [D/E]Fathe[E]r\'s [D/F#]glo - [E/G#]ry.\r\n[A]Blaze, [E/A]Spirit, [D/A]Blaze, set our [Bm]hearts [Bm/A]on    [G]fire.[Esus][E]\r\n[A]Flow, [E/A]river, [D/A]flow, flood the [Bm]nat[Bm/A]ions with [D/E]grace [E]and [D/F#]mer - [E/G#]cy.\r\n[A]Send [E/A]forth your [D/A]Word, Lord, and [Bm]let [Esus-E]there be l[A]ight.\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[A]Lord the [D/A]light of your [A]love is [E/A]shining [A]in the [D/A]midst of the [A]darkness [E/A]shining.\r\n[D]Jesus, [E/D]light of the [C#m7]world, shine u[F#m]pon us.\r\n[D]Set us [E/D]free by the [C#m7]Truth you now [F#m]bring us.\r\n[G]Shine on [E]me.  [G]Shine on [Esus]me. [D/E] [E] [D/F#]  [E/G#]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord I come to your awesome presence from the shadow into your radiance.\r\nBy the blood I can enter your brightness.\r\nSearch me, try me, consume all my darkness.  Shine on me.  Shine on me.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAs we gaze on your Kingly brightness, so our faces display your brightness.\r\nEver changing from glory to glory.  Mirrored here may our lives tell your story.\r\nShine on me.  Shine on me.\r\n', '', '1987 Make Way Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/gi1Ubff5XoY', '', 'Shine, Jesus, Shine,  fill this land with the Father\'s glo - ry. Blaze, Spirit, Blaze, set our hearts on    fire. Flow, river, flow, flood the nations with grace and mer - cy. Send forth your Word, Lord, and let there be light. Lord the light of your love is shining in the midst of the darkness shining. Jesus, light of the world, shine upon us. Set us free by the Truth you now bring us. Shine on me.  Shine on me. Lord I come to your awesome presence from the shadow into your radiance. By the blood I can enter your brightness. Search me, try me, consume all my darkness.  Shine on me.  Shine on me. As we gaze on your Kingly brightness, so our faces display your brightness. Ever changing from glory to glory.  Mirrored here may our lives tell your story. Shine on me.  Shine on me.'),
	(314, 'At Calvary', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYears I spent in vanity and pride,\r\nCaring not my Lord was crucified,\r\nKnowing not it was for me He died\r\n on Calvary.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBy God\'s Word at last my sin I learned-\r\nThen I trembled at the law I\'d spurned,\r\nTill my guilty soul imploring\r\nTurned to Calvary.  \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nNow I\'ve giv\'n to Jesus ev\'ry-thing,\r\nNow I gladly own Him as my King,\r\nNow my raptured soul can only sing\r\n	 Of Calvary.  \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nO the love that drew salvation\'s plan!\r\nO the grace that bro\'t it down to man!\r\nO the mighty gulf that God did span \r\n	 At Calvary.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nMercy there was great \r\nand grace was free,\r\nPardon there was multiplied to me,\r\nThere my burdened soul found liberty-\r\n	 At Calvary.   \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Years I spent in vanity and pride, Caring not my Lord was crucified, Knowing not it was for me He died on Calvary. By God\'s Word at last my sin I learned- Then I trembled at the law I\'d spurned, Till my guilty soul imploring Turned to Calvary. Now I\'ve giv\'n to Jesus ev\'ry-thing, Now I gladly own Him as my King, Now my raptured soul can only sing Of Calvary. O the love that drew salvation\'s plan! O the grace that bro\'t it down to man! O the mighty gulf that God did span At Calvary. Mercy there was great and grace was free, Pardon there was multiplied to me, There my burdened soul found liberty- At Calvary.'),
	(315, 'I Surrender All', 'Juson W. VandeVenter and Music by Winfield S. Weeden', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]All to Jesus [G]I surrender\r\n[F]All to Him I [G]freely [C]give\r\n[C]I will ever [G]love and trust Him\r\n[F]In His presence [G]daily [C]live.\r\n~Chorus\r\n[Am]I surrender [F]all\r\n[G]I surrender [C]all\r\n[C]All to Thee, my [C/E]blessed [F]Savior\r\n[G]I surrender [C]all.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAll to Jesus I surrender, Humbly at His feet I bow,\r\nWorldly pleasures all forsaken, Take me, Jesus, take me now.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll to Jesus I surrender, Make me, Savior, wholly Thine;\r\nMay Thy Holy Spirit fill me, May I know Thy pow\'r divine.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAll to Jesus I surrender, Lord, I give myself to Thee;\r\nFill me with Thy love and power, Let Thy blessing fall on me.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/7x2IpLSfqp8', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(All to Jesus I surrender All to Him I freely give I will ever love and trust Him In His presence daily live. I surrender all I surrender all All to Thee, my blessed Savior I surrender all. All to Jesus I surrender, Humbly at His feet I bow, Worldly pleasures all forsaken, Take me, Jesus, take me now. All to Jesus I surrender, Make me, Savior, wholly Thine; May Thy Holy Spirit fill me, May I know Thy pow\'r divine. All to Jesus I surrender, Lord, I give myself to Thee; Fill me with Thy love and power, Let Thy blessing fall on me.).'),
	(316, 'Lord Most High', 'Don Harris and Gary Sadler.', '~Verse 1\r\nFrom the ends of the earth\r\nFrom the ends of the earth\r\nFrom the depths of the sea\r\nFrom the depths of the sea\r\nFrom the heights of the heavens\r\n From the heights of the heavens\r\nYour name be praised.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFrom the hearts of the weak,\r\nFrom the hearts of the weak\r\nFrom the shouts of the strong\r\nFrom the shouts of the strong\r\nFrom the lips of all people \r\nFrom the lips of all people\r\nThis song we raise, Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThroughout the endless ages \r\nYou will be crowned with praises, \r\nLord Most High\r\nExalted in ev\'ry nation,\r\nSov\'reign of all creation,\r\nLord Most High, be magnified.\r\n', '', '1996 Integritys Music (Integrity Music, Inc.)', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/otNj-oCY-LM', '', 'From the ends of the earth From the ends of the earth From the depths of the sea From the depths of the sea From the heights of the heavens From the heights of the heavens Your name be praised. From the hearts of the weak, From the hearts of the weak From the shouts of the strong From the shouts of the strong From the lips of all people From the lips of all people This song we raise, Lord. Throughout the endless ages You will be crowned with praises, Lord Most High Exalted in ev\'ry nation, Sov\'reign of all creation, Lord Most High, be magnified.'),
	(317, 'Thank You,  Lord', 'Dennis Jernigan', '~Verse 1\r\nFor a[E]ll that You\'ve done I will [A]thank You,\r\nFor a[E]ll that You\'re going to [B]do,\r\nFor a[E]ll that You\'ve pr[E/G#]omised and al[A]l that You are\r\nAnd a[E]ll that has carried me th[B]rough, Jesus [A]I tha[E]nk You. \r\n~Chorus\r\nAnd I [A]thank You, thank [E]You, Lord (echo).\r\nAnd I [A]thank You, thank [E]You, Lord (echo). \r\n~Verse 2\r\nTh[E]ank You for lovin[E/G#]g and setting me free,\r\nTh[A]ank You for giving Your life just for me\r\nNow I [E]th[E/G#]ank Y[A]ou, Jesus [E]I [E/G#]than[A]k You,\r\nGratefully [E]th[E/G#]ank Y[A]ou,\r\nTh[A]ank Y[E]ou.\r\n', '', '1991 Shepherds Heart Music, Inc. (admin, by Word Music, Inc.)', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/2Xz3YvkaA5Q', '', 'For all that You\'ve done I will thank You, For all that You\'re going to do, For all that You\'ve promised and all that You are And all that has carried me through, Jesus I thank You. And I thank You, thank You, Lord (echo). And I thank You, thank You, Lord (echo). Thank You for loving and setting me free, Thank You for giving Your life just for me Now I thank You, Jesus I thank You, Gratefully thank You, Thank You.'),
	(319, 'God\'s Got An Army', 'Leroy Baker. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGod\'s got an army\r\nMarching through the land.\r\nDeliv\'rance is their song,\r\nWith healing in their hand.\r\nEverlasting joy and gladness in their heart,\r\nAnd in this army I\'ve got a part.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1972 Leroy Baker.', '', '', 'God\'s got an army Marching through the land. Deliv\'rance is their song, With healing in their hand. Everlasting joy and gladness in their heart, And in this army I\'ve got a part.'),
	(320, 'Amazing Grace', 'John Newton, John P. Rees, stanza 5 Music Traditional.', '~Verse 1\r\nAm[F]azing [F/A]grace, how swe[Bb]et the so[F]und\r\nThat saved a [Dm]wretch like me[F/C][C]\r\nI [F]once was [F/A]lost but no[Bb]w am fo[F]und\r\nWas [Dm]blind but no[F/C]w I[C] see[Bb][F]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\'Twas grace that taught my heart to fear\r\nAnd grace my fear relieved\r\nHow precious did that grace appear\r\nThe hour I first believed\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThrough many dangers, toils and snares\r\nI have already come\r\n\'Tis grace hath brought me safe thus far\r\nAnd grace will lead me home\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhen we\'ve been there ten thousand years\r\nBright shining as the sun\r\nWe\'ve no less days to sing God\'s praise\r\nThan when we\'ve first begun\r\n\r\n~Transition to key of G\r\n[Bb] [F/A] [Gm] [D/F#]\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/iT88jBAoVIM&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Amazing grace, how sweet the sound That saved a wretch like me I once was lost but now am found Was blind but now I see \'Twas grace that taught my heart to fear And grace my fear relieved How precious did that grace appear The hour I first believed Through many dangers, toils and snares I have already come \'Tis grace hath brought me safe thus far And grace will lead me home When we\'ve been there ten thousand years Bright shining as the sun We\'ve no less days to sing God\'s praise Than when we\'ve first begun'),
	(321, 'I Love Loving You', 'Dave Cumchal', '~Verse 1\r\nI love loving you, Lord Jesus\r\nI am walking in the truth\r\nI love loving you, Lord Jesus\r\nI will worship only you\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd with all my heart\r\nAnd with all my mind\r\nAnd with all my strength\r\nI will never cease in giving you\r\nAll of my praise\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will worship only you\r\nI will worship only you\r\nI love loving you, Lord Jesus.\r\n', '', '1997 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing', '', '', 'I love loving you, Lord Jesus I am walking in the truth I love loving you, Lord Jesus I will worship only you And with all my heart And with all my mind And with all my strength I will never cease in giving you All of my praise I will worship only you I will worship only you I love loving you, Lord Jesus.'),
	(322, 'Are You A Loser', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAn angel up on the tombstone said,\r\n"He is risen just as He said."\r\n"Quickly, now go tell His disciples\r\nThat Jesus Christ is no longer dead!"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJoy to the world, He is risen,\r\nAlleluia, is risen,\r\nAlleluia, is risen,\r\nAlleluia, Alleluia!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'An angel up on the tombstone said, "He is risen just as He said." "Quickly, now go tell His disciples That Jesus Christ is no longer dead!" Joy to the world, He is risen, Alleluia, is risen, Alleluia, is risen, Alleluia, Alleluia!'),
	(323, 'Lord I Come', 'Billy Funk', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, I come, take my life\r\nI offer it to You, a living sacrifice \r\nBy Your grace, by Your blood \r\nI come into the Holy of Holies.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll I want to do\r\nIs dwell in Your presence,\r\nAnd drink from the well\r\nThat never runs dry;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAll I want to see\r\nIs the light of Your glory,\r\nJust one glimpse, just one drink\r\nAnd my soul is satisfied.\r\n', '', '1997 Integritys Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/aQSflNNRrFw', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Lord, I come, take my life I offer it to You, a living sacrifice By Your grace, by Your blood I come into the Holy of Holies. All I want to do Is dwell in Your presence, And drink from the well That never runs dry; All I want to see Is the light of Your glory, Just one glimpse, just one drink And my soul is satisfied.).'),
	(324, 'With Our Hearts', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWith our hearts we believe,\r\nWith our mouths we confess\r\n"You are Lord, You are Lord"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFrom this day til the end\r\nWe will sing it again and again\r\n"You are Lord, You are Lord"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBy Your power You\'ve made us\r\nAnd by Your grace we\'re redeemed\r\nTo walk in the truth that You give us\r\nAnd minister life in Your Name.\r\n', '', '1991 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'With our hearts we believe, With our mouths we confess "You are Lord, You are Lord" From this day til the end We will sing it again and again "You are Lord, You are Lord" By Your power You\'ve made us And by Your grace we\'re redeemed To walk in the truth that You give us And minister life in Your Name.'),
	(326, 'Lift Up Your Heads (O You Gates)', 'Graham Kendrick.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLift up your heads, O you gates,\r\nSwing wide you everlasting doors.\r\nLift up your heads, O you gates,\r\nSwing wide you everlasting doors.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nUp from the dead He ascends\r\nThrough every rank of heavenly power\r\nLet heaven prepare the highest place,\r\nThrow wide the everlasting doors.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThat the King of Glory may come in,\r\nThat the King of Glory may come in.\r\n', '', ' 1991 Make Way Music (admin. in US & Canada by Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music),', '', '', 'Lift up your heads, O you gates, Swing wide you everlasting doors. Lift up your heads, O you gates, Swing wide you everlasting doors. Up from the dead He ascends Through every rank of heavenly power Let heaven prepare the highest place, Throw wide the everlasting doors. That the King of Glory may come in, That the King of Glory may come in.'),
	(327, 'Come Into His Presence Medley', 'Bruce Ballinger, Arr. by Mark Hayes', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome into His presence\r\nWith thanksgiving.\r\nCome into His courts\r\nWith a song of praise.\r\nGive Him all the glory\r\nFor He\'s worthy.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe\'s the great "I Am,"\r\nThe "Ancient of Days."\r\nFor He has made us,\r\nAnd not we ourselves,\r\nAnd He hath saved us \r\nFrom the gates of hell.\r\n', '', ' ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'Come into His presence With thanksgiving. Come into His courts With a song of praise. Give Him all the glory For He\'s worthy. He\'s the great "I Am," The "Ancient of Days." For He has made us, And not we ourselves, And He hath saved us From the gates of hell.'),
	(328, 'My Saviour\'s Love', 'Charles H. Gabriel Public Domain', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI stand amazed in the presence \r\nOf Jesus the Nazarene\r\nAnd wonder how He could love me,\r\nA sinner, condemned, unclean.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHow marvelous!\r\nHow wonderful!\r\nAnd my song shall ever be.\r\nHow marvelous!\r\nHow wonderful!\r\nIs my Saviour\'s love for me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor me it was in the garden He prayed,\r\n"Not My will, but Thine";\r\nHe had no tears for His own griefs,\r\nBut sweat drops of blood for mine.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe took my sins and my sorrows,\r\nHe made them His very own,\r\nHe bore the burden to Calv\'ry,\r\nAnd suffered and died alone.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhen with the ransomed in glory\r\nHis face I at last shall see;\r\n\'Twill be my joy thru the ages\r\nTo sing of His love for me.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I stand amazed in the presence Of Jesus the Nazarene And wonder how He could love me, A sinner, condemned, unclean. How marvelous! How wonderful! And my song shall ever be. How marvelous! How wonderful! Is my Saviour\'s love for me. For me it was in the garden He prayed, "Not My will, but Thine"; He had no tears for His own griefs, But sweat drops of blood for mine. He took my sins and my sorrows, He made them His very own, He bore the burden to Calv\'ry, And suffered and died alone. When with the ransomed in glory His face I at last shall see; \'Twill be my joy thru the ages To sing of His love for me.'),
	(329, 'Holy Is The Lord', 'Kelly Green', '~Chorus\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C]\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C]\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C]\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C][D]\r\n~Verse\r\n[Em]Righteousness[C] and [Em]mercy[C]\r\n[Em]Judgement[C] and [Em]grace[C][D]\r\n[Em]Faithfulness[C] and [Em]sovereignty[C]\r\n~Tag\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C]\r\n[Em]Holy [C]is the [Em]Lord [C]\r\n', '', '1983 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing', '', '', 'Holy is the Lord Holy is the Lord Holy is the Lord Holy is the Lord Righteousness and mercy Judgement and grace Faithfulness and sovereignty Holy is the Lord Holy is the Lord'),
	(330, 'My Reward (Paul Baloche)', 'Paul Baloche', '~Verse 1\r\nI want to hear You say the words to me,\r\n"Well done"\r\nI want to hear You say,\r\n"Good and faithful servant"\r\nI want to hear You say,\r\n"I\'ve prepared a place for You"\r\nLet all the treasures of this world fade away\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJesus, You are my reward\r\nTo hear Your voice on that day\r\nIs all I\'m living for\r\nJesus, You are my reward\r\nTo see Your face on that day\r\nIs all I\'m living for\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIn the twinkling of an eye\r\nWe\'ll all be changed\r\nWe\'ll meet You in the sky\r\nWe will see You face to face\r\n', '', '2003 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/ipo29gmQidg&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'I want to hear You say the words to me, \\"Well done\\" I want to hear You say, \\"Good and faithful servant\\" I want to hear You say, \\"I\\\'ve prepared a place for You\\" Let all the treasures of this world fade away Jesus, You are my reward To hear Your voice on that day Is all I\\\'m living for Jesus, You are my reward To see Your face on that day Is all I\\\'m living for In the twinkling of an eye We\\\'ll all be changed We\\\'ll meet You in the sky We will see You face to face'),
	(331, 'Your Love Is Deep', 'Susanna Bussey, Dan Collins & Jami Smith ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYour love is deeper than my view of grace\r\nHigher than this worldly place\r\nLonger than this road I travel\r\nWider than the gap You filled\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nDeeper than my view of grace\r\nHigher than this worldly place\r\nLonger than this road I travel\r\nWider than the gap You filled\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYour love is deep\r\nYour love is high\r\nYour love is long\r\nYour love is wide\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWho shall separate us\r\nWho shall separate us\r\nFrom Your love\r\nNothing can separate us\r\nNothing can separate us\r\nFrom Your love, \'cause\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nIt\'s deeper, it\'s higher, it\'s longer\r\nWider than the gap You filled\r\nIt\'s deeper, it\'s higher\r\nIt\'s longer than the road I travel\r\nWider than the gap you filled\r\n', '', ' 2001 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music c/o Integrity Music, Inc.  ', '', '', 'Your love is deeper than my view of grace Higher than this worldly place Longer than this road I travel Wider than the gap You filled Deeper than my view of grace Higher than this worldly place Longer than this road I travel Wider than the gap You filled Your love is deep Your love is high Your love is long Your love is wide Who shall separate us Who shall separate us From Your love Nothing can separate us Nothing can separate us From Your love, \'cause It\'s deeper, it\'s higher, it\'s longer Wider than the gap You filled It\'s deeper, it\'s higher It\'s longer than the road I travel Wider than the gap you filled'),
	(332, 'Gentle Shepherd', 'Gloria Gaither &andWilliam J. Gaither; music by William J. Gaither. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGentle Shepherd, come and lead us,\r\nFor we need You to help us find our way.\r\nGentle Shepherd, come and feed us,\r\nFor we need Your strength from day to day.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThere\'s no other we can turn to\r\nWho can help us face another day;\r\nGentle Shepherd, come and lead us,\r\nFor we need You to help us find our way.\r\n', '', ' 1974 by William J. Gaither (Gaither Music Company). ', '', '', 'Gentle Shepherd, come and lead us, For we need You to help us find our way. Gentle Shepherd, come and feed us, For we need Your strength from day to day. There\'s no other we can turn to Who can help us face another day; Gentle Shepherd, come and lead us, For we need You to help us find our way.'),
	(333, 'O Praise Him', 'David Crowder. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nTurn your ear to heaven\r\nAnd hear the noise inside\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe sound of angel\'s awe\r\nThe sound of angel\'s songs\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd all this for a King\r\nWe could join and sing\r\nAll to Christ the King\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAlleluia, Alleluia\r\nHe is holy\r\nHe is holy\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThe sound of rescued ones\r\nAnd all this for a King\r\nAngels join to sing \r\nAll for Christ the King\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHow constant, how divine\r\nThis song of ours will rise\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nO how constant, how divine\r\nThis love of ours will rise\r\nWill rise\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nTurn your gaze to heaven\r\nAnd raise a joyous noise\r\nThe sound of salvation come\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nHow infinite and sweet\r\nThis love so rescuing\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nO how infinitely sweet\r\nThis great love that has redeemed\r\nAs one we sing\r\n\r\n~Verse 12\r\nO praise Him  O praise Him\r\nHe is holy   He is holy\r\n', '', ' 2003 worshiptogether.com songs/sixsteps Music. ', '', '', 'Turn your ear to heaven And hear the noise inside The sound of angel\'s awe The sound of angel\'s songs And all this for a King We could join and sing All to Christ the King Alleluia, Alleluia He is holy He is holy The sound of rescued ones And all this for a King Angels join to sing All for Christ the King How constant, how divine This song of ours will rise O how constant, how divine This love of ours will rise Will rise Turn your gaze to heaven And raise a joyous noise The sound of salvation come How infinite and sweet This love so rescuing O how infinitely sweet This great love that has redeemed As one we sing O praise Him  O praise Him He is holy   He is holy'),
	(334, 'With All Of Our Heart', 'Don Moen & Martin J.Nystrom  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe Father is searching \r\nFor all who will worship \r\nIn Spirit and in truth;\r\nAnd He is discerning \r\nThe thoughts and the yearnings \r\nOf ev\'ry heart in this room.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWith all of our heart, mind, and strength\r\nWe give You honor, glory and praise;\r\nNot from afar, or just with our lips,\r\nBut all that we are, we offer in worship.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWith all of our heart, mind, and strength,\r\nJesus, we come to lift up Your name;\r\nWe give You glory, we give You praise,\r\nWith all of our heart,\r\n And our mind, and our strength.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nJesus we offer our lives on the altar,\r\nCleanse our hearts and thoughts;\r\nThat we may stand, holy,\r\nAnd we can come boldly\r\nBefore the throne of our God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nSo, let us determine\r\n That right at the start\r\nWe will worship the Father\r\n With all of our heart.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nFor we have determined \r\nThat right at the start\r\nWe will worship You, Jesus,\r\n With all of our heart.\r\n', '', '1996 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music c/o Integrity Music, Inc. PO Box 851622 Mobile, AL 36685-1622     ', '', '', 'The Father is searching For all who will worship In Spirit and in truth; And He is discerning The thoughts and the yearnings Of ev\'ry heart in this room. With all of our heart, mind, and strength We give You honor, glory and praise; Not from afar, or just with our lips, But all that we are, we offer in worship. With all of our heart, mind, and strength, Jesus, we come to lift up Your name; We give You glory, we give You praise, With all of our heart, And our mind, and our strength. Jesus we offer our lives on the altar, Cleanse our hearts and thoughts; That we may stand, holy, And we can come boldly Before the throne of our God. So, let us determine That right at the start We will worship the Father With all of our heart. For we have determined That right at the start We will worship You, Jesus, With all of our heart.'),
	(336, 'Praise Awaits You', 'Matt Redman. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPraise awaits You\r\nIn this place today, O Lord.\r\nWe are gathered, ready, God\r\nTo sing Your praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nReady to respond\r\nTo the glories of Your name,\r\nTo the wonders of Your heart,\r\nTo Your great love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSeasons come and seasons go,\r\nBut You remain;\r\nSo unchanging, all deserving\r\nOf our praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe\'re ready to respond\r\nTo the glories of Your name,\r\nTo the wonders of Your heart,\r\nTo Your great love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nPraise is waiting for You in this place.\r\nThere\'s a cry that our spirits will make\r\nAs we see Your glory.\r\nTo Your mercies our souls will awake,\r\nAnd we\'ll sing \'til the break of the day,\r\nBecause You are worthy, yes, Lord!\r\n', '', ' 2004 Thankyou Music. Administered', '', '', 'Praise awaits You In this place today, O Lord. We are gathered, ready, God To sing Your praise. Ready to respond To the glories of Your name, To the wonders of Your heart, To Your great love. Seasons come and seasons go, But You remain; So unchanging, all deserving Of our praise. We\'re ready to respond To the glories of Your name, To the wonders of Your heart, To Your great love. Praise is waiting for You in this place. There\'s a cry that our spirits will make As we see Your glory. To Your mercies our souls will awake, And we\'ll sing \'til the break of the day, Because You are worthy, yes, Lord!'),
	(337, 'Untitled', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe Creator\'s Love\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\nOur God, Creator of the heavens, \r\nearth and everything in between,\r\nEverything that can and cannot be seen,\r\nFrom the farthest reaches of the heavens, \r\nto the wind that blows...\r\nHe must know what He is doing, \r\nI suppose.\r\nThe earth and moon are in perfect balance because of the Word He spoke.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nMeasuring out the universe in a palm span.\r\nEverywhere you look, \r\nthe song of creation can be heard,\r\nIn the wind rustling through the trees \r\nand in the song of a bird.\r\nGod gave man life with His very own breath;\r\nThe Breath of life was not meant \r\nto experience death.\r\nHe created man in His image \r\nand woman out of man\'s bone;\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nWhat God has put into motion\r\n no one can revoke;\r\nAll things are held together \r\nby the power of His Word.\r\nWhen God called something \r\ninto existence, eternity heard.\r\nHe has measured the oceans \r\nin the hollow of His hand,\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nHe did all of this, \r\nso man would not have to be alone.\r\nThe same God, \r\nwho has created \r\nthe heavens and the earth, loves you.\r\nHe knows the desires of your heart, \r\nand what you will and will not do.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\nHe loves you so much; He knows the number of hairs on your head.\r\nHe has given you the capacity to learn, which is from above,\r\nNot just to live from day to day, \r\nbut to learn of His love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\n\r\nHe knows when you rise in the morning \r\nand when you go to bed.\r\nLook far and wide, high and low, \r\nyou will never find a love so great.\r\nLike a parent waiting for a stray child \r\nto come home, He will patiently wait\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'The Creator\'s Love Our God, Creator of the heavens, earth and everything in between, Everything that can and cannot be seen, From the farthest reaches of the heavens, to the wind that blows... He must know what He is doing, I suppose. The earth and moon are in perfect balance because of the Word He spoke. Measuring out the universe in a palm span. Everywhere you look, the song of creation can be heard, In the wind rustling through the trees and in the song of a bird. God gave man life with His very own breath; The Breath of life was not meant to experience death. He created man in His image and woman out of man\'s bone; What God has put into motion no one can revoke; All things are held together by the power of His Word. When God called something into existence, eternity heard. He has measured the oceans in the hollow of His hand, He did all of this, so man would not have to be alone. The same God, who has created the heavens and the earth, loves you. He knows the desires of your heart, and what you will and will not do. He loves you so much; He knows the number of hairs on your head. He has given you the capacity to learn, which is from above, Not just to live from day to day, but to learn of His love. He knows when you rise in the morning and when you go to bed. Look far and wide, high and low, you will never find a love so great. Like a parent waiting for a stray child to come home, He will patiently wait'),
	(338, 'My All In All', 'Frank Hernandez and Sherry Saunders. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are my strength, O God;\r\nYou are my help, O God;\r\nYou are the one on whom I call.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou are my shield, O God;\r\nMy life I yield, O God;\r\nFor You will ever be my all in all.\r\n', '', ' 1975', '', '', 'You are my strength, O God; You are my help, O God; You are the one on whom I call. You are my shield, O God; My life I yield, O God; For You will ever be my all in all.'),
	(339, 'The Servant King (From Heaven You Came)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFrom heav\'n You came, helpless Babe,\r\nEnter\'d our world, Your glory veiled;\r\nNot to be served, but to serve,\r\nAnd give Your life that we might live.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere in the garden of tears,\r\nMy heavy load He chose to bear;\r\nHis heart with sorrow was torn,\r\n"Yet not my will, but Yours," He said.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome, see His hands and His feet,\r\nThe scars that speak of sacrifice;\r\nHands that flung stars into space,\r\nTo cruel nails surrendered.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSo let us learn how to serve,\r\nAnd in our lives enthrone Him;\r\nEach other\'s needs to prefer,\r\nFor it is Christ we\'re serving.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThis is our God, the Servant King,\r\nHe calls us now to follow Him;\r\nTo bring our lives as a daily offering\r\nOf worship to the Servant King.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'From heav\'n You came, helpless Babe, Enter\'d our world, Your glory veiled; Not to be served, but to serve, And give Your life that we might live. There in the garden of tears, My heavy load He chose to bear; His heart with sorrow was torn, "Yet not my will, but Yours," He said. Come, see His hands and His feet, The scars that speak of sacrifice; Hands that flung stars into space, To cruel nails surrendered. So let us learn how to serve, And in our lives enthrone Him; Each other\'s needs to prefer, For it is Christ we\'re serving. This is our God, the Servant King, He calls us now to follow Him; To bring our lives as a daily offering Of worship to the Servant King.'),
	(340, 'The Power Of  Your Love (is Changing Me)', 'Gary Sadler', '~Verse 1\r\nYou\'ve drawn me to Your side\r\nAnd what else can I do\r\nMy heart is open wide\r\nMy hands reach up to you.\r\n\r\nWords & music by Gary Sadler. c. 1998 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music,\r\nc/o Integrity Media, Inc. ARR, UBP, CCLI #218004\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI\'m calling out for more,\r\nI\'m asking in Your name,\r\nThat by Your Spirit, Lord\r\nI will never be the same.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe power of Your love \r\nis changing me\r\nChanging me, \r\nO changing me, O Lord \r\nChange me by the power of Your love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI\'m singing out my praise\r\nI\'m pouring out my thanks\r\nFor the power of Your love \r\nis changing me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI\'m lifting up my voice\r\nI\'m dancing in the joy\r\nFor the power of Your love \r\nis changing me.\r\n', '', '1998 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/Cp0Fh5yPtPM', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(You\'ve drawn me to Your side And what else can I do My heart is open wide My hands reach up to you. Words & music by Gary Sadler. c. 1998 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Media, Inc. ARR, UBP, CCLI #218004 I\'m calling out for more, I\'m asking in Your name, That by Your Spirit, Lord I will never be the same. The power of Your love is changing me Changing me, O changing me, O Lord Change me by the power of Your love. I\'m singing out my praise I\'m pouring out my thanks For the power of Your love is changing me. I\'m lifting up my voice I\'m dancing in the joy For the power of Your love is changing me.).'),
	(341, 'Search Me O, God ', 'Kent Blanton.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSearch me O God and know my heart\r\nTest me and know my anxious thoughts\r\nAnd see if there be any wicked way in me\r\nAnd lead me in the way of life.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n    \r\n', '', ' 2006 Kent Blanton. ', '', '', 'Search me O God and know my heart Test me and know my anxious thoughts And see if there be any wicked way in me And lead me in the way of life.'),
	(342, 'We Are Strong In The Lord', 'Dennis Jernigan ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nStand firm, \r\nIn the armor of our God\r\nAnd pierce the darkness with light!\r\nAll praise,\r\nTo the overcoming God!\r\nLet us lift our sword and fight!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor we are strong in the Lord,\r\nIn the strength of His might!\r\nStrong in the Lord, we will stand and fight!\r\nStrong in the Lord as we stand and sing,\r\nStrong in the Lord \r\nas we praise the King of kings,\r\nLord Jesus Christ!\r\n', '', ' 1989 Shepherd\'s Heart Music ', '', '', 'Stand firm, In the armor of our God And pierce the darkness with light! All praise, To the overcoming God! Let us lift our sword and fight! For we are strong in the Lord, In the strength of His might! Strong in the Lord, we will stand and fight! Strong in the Lord as we stand and sing, Strong in the Lord as we praise the King of kings, Lord Jesus Christ!'),
	(343, 'Great Is The Lord (We Bow Down On Our Knees)', 'Steve McEwan. Psalm 48:1-2  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGreat is the Lord\r\nAnd most worthy of praise,\r\nIn the city of our God, the holy place,\r\nThe joy of the whole earth.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGreat is the Lord\r\nIn whom we have the victory,\r\nHe aids us against the enemy,\r\nWe bow down on our knees.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd Lord,\r\nWe want to lift Your name on high,\r\nAnd Lord, we want to thank You\r\nFor the works You\'ve done in our lives,\r\nAnd Lord, we trust in Your unfailing love,\r\nFor You alone are God eternal\r\nThroughout earth and heaven above.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Great is the Lord And most worthy of praise, In the city of our God, the holy place, The joy of the whole earth. Great is the Lord In whom we have the victory, He aids us against the enemy, We bow down on our knees. And Lord, We want to lift Your name on high, And Lord, we want to thank You For the works You\'ve done in our lives, And Lord, we trust in Your unfailing love, For You alone are God eternal Throughout earth and heaven above.'),
	(344, 'Whatever Is True', 'Brian Doerksen and Music by Craig Musseau; c. 1991 Langley Vineyard Music; ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]\r\nWhatever is [C]true  [D]\r\nWhatever is [G]right\r\nWhatever is [C]pure  [D]\r\nWhatever is [Gsus]love - [G]ly\r\nWe will [C]fix [D]our [Em7]thought[C]s on thes[D]e things\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJesus You\'re true\r\nJesus You\'re right\r\nJesus You\'re pure\r\nYou are loveley\r\nWe will fix our thoughts on You\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]Je - [C]sus ([G]Je - [C]sus), who is [G]like [C]You? (who is [G]like [C]You?)\r\n[G]Je - [C]sus ([G]Je - [C]sus), who is [G/D]like [D]You? (who is [G/D]like [D]You?)\r\n[G]Je - [C]sus ([G]Je - [C]sus), who is [G]like [C]You? (who is [G]like [C]You?)\r\n[G]Je - [C]sus ([G]Je - [C]sus), who is [G/D]like [D]You? (who is [G/D]like [D]You?)\r\nWho is [C6]like [C9]You?\r\n', '', ' 1991 Langley Vineyard Music; ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'Whatever is true Whatever is right Whatever is pure Whatever is love - ly We will fix our thoughts on these things Jesus You\'re true Jesus You\'re right Jesus You\'re pure You are loveley We will fix our thoughts on You Je - sus (Je - sus), who is like You? (who is like You?) Je - sus (Je - sus), who is like You? (who is like You?) Je - sus (Je - sus), who is like You? (who is like You?) Je - sus (Je - sus), who is like You? (who is like You?) Who is like You?'),
	(345, 'Lift Up Your Heads', 'Steven L. Fry. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLift up your heads to the coming King\r\nBow before Him and adore Him\r\nSing to His majesty\r\nLet your praises be pure and holy\r\nGiving glory to the King of Kings\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1974 Birdwing Music/', '', '', 'Lift up your heads to the coming King Bow before Him and adore Him Sing to His majesty Let your praises be pure and holy Giving glory to the King of Kings'),
	(346, 'Lead Us Lord (Dream Again)', 'Brian Doerksen', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHere we stand at a crossroads again\r\nLike you said, in time the seasons change\r\nLooking back, we recall the \r\nblessing and the pain\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBut now we turn our hearts toward \r\nwhat is still to come\r\nWe want to dream again\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou will lead us, Lord\r\nCome and lead us, Lord\r\nCome and lead us, Lord\r\nYou will lead us, Lord\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLead us, Lord into a life of fruitfulness\r\nPrepare our hearts to risk again\r\nAnd as we trust, \r\ntaking simple steps of obedience\r\nWe know that You will lead us, Lord\r\n', '', ' 2004 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'Here we stand at a crossroads again Like you said, in time the seasons change Looking back, we recall the blessing and the pain But now we turn our hearts toward what is still to come We want to dream again You will lead us, Lord Come and lead us, Lord Come and lead us, Lord You will lead us, Lord Lead us, Lord into a life of fruitfulness Prepare our hearts to risk again And as we trust, taking simple steps of obedience We know that You will lead us, Lord'),
	(347, 'Worthy Is The Lamb', 'Gerald W. Schlabach', '~Verse 1\r\nWorthy is the Lamb that was slain\r\nTo receive power and riches \r\nAnd wisdom and strength\r\nAnd honor and glory and blessing.\r\nWorthy is the Lamb\r\n', '', '1974 Integrity\'s Alleluia! Music', '', '', 'Worthy is the Lamb that was slain To receive power and riches And wisdom and strength And honor and glory and blessing. Worthy is the Lamb'),
	(348, 'Everlasting God', 'Brenton Brown and Ken Riley.', '~Verse\r\n[G]Strength will rise as we w[C2]ait upon the Lord\r\nWait upon the Lord\r\nAs we wait upon the Lord\r\n[G]Strength will rise as we w[C2]ait upon the Lord\r\nWait upon the Lord\r\nWe will wait upon the Lord\r\n[Em7]Our God You reign [C2]forev[D]er\r\n[C2]Our hope our strong [Em7]Delivero[D]r\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]You are the everlasting G[C2]od\r\nThe everlasting G[Em7]od\r\nYou do not faint and you w[C2]on\'t grow weary \r\n[G]You\'re the defender of the w[C2]eak\r\nYou comfort those in n[Em7]eed\r\nYou lift us up on wi[C2]ngs like eagle[G]s\r\n', '', ' 2005 Thankyou Music. ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/yubLGTOcm8c&hl=en&fs=1', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=152053320&id=152053191&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Brenton Brown - Everlasting God - Everlasting God" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Strength will rise as we wait upon the Lord Wait upon the Lord As we wait upon the Lord Strength will rise as we wait upon the Lord Wait upon the Lord We will wait upon the Lord Our God You reign forever Our hope our strong Deliveror You are the everlasting God The everlasting God You do not faint and you won\\\'t grow weary You\\\'re the defender of the weak You comfort those in need You lift us up on wings like eagles'),
	(349, 'Praise To The Lord, The Almighty', 'Joachim Neander', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Praise to the Lord, the Al[A]mighty, the [G]King of crea[A]ti[D]on!\r\n[D]O my soul, praise Him for [A]He is thy [G]health and salva[A]ti[D]on!\r\n[D]All ye who [G]hear, [D]now to His temple draw [A]near; \r\n[G]Join me in [Bm]glad ador[A]at[D]ion!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nPraise to the Lord, who o\'er all things so wondriously reigneth\r\nShelters Thee under His wings, yes, so gently sustaineth.\r\nHast Thou not seen how all Thy longings have been\r\nGranted in what He ordaineth?\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPraise to the Lord, Who doth prosper Thy work and defend Thee;\r\nSurely His goodness and mercy here daily attend Thee.\r\nPonder anew what the Almighty can do,\r\nIf with His love He befriend Thee.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nPraise to the Lord, O let all that is in me adore Him\r\nAll that hath life and breath, Come now with praises before Him,\r\nLet the Amen sound from His people again,\r\nGladly for aye we adore Him\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/JEh7Vt9sxmc', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Praise to the Lord, the Almighty, the King of creation! O my soul, praise Him for He is thy health and salvation! All ye who hear, now to His temple draw near; Join me in glad adoration! Praise to the Lord, who o\'er all things so wondriously reigneth Shelters Thee under His wings, yes, so gently sustaineth. Hast Thou not seen how all Thy longings have been Granted in what He ordaineth? Praise to the Lord, Who doth prosper Thy work and defend Thee; Surely His goodness and mercy here daily attend Thee. Ponder anew what the Almighty can do, If with His love He befriend Thee. Praise to the Lord, O let all that is in me adore Him All that hath life and breath, Come now with praises before Him, Let the Amen sound from His people again, Gladly for aye we adore Him).'),
	(350, 'We Gather Together', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe gather together\r\n to ask the Lord\'s blessing\r\nHe chastens and hastens \r\nHis will to make 	 known\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe wicked oppressing\r\n now cease from distressing;\r\nSing praises to his name:\r\nHe forgets not His own.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBeside us to guide us,\r\nOur God with us joining,\r\nOrdaining, maintaining \r\nHis kingdom divine;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSo from the beginning\r\n the fight we were winning:\r\nThou, Lord, wast at our side, \r\nall glory be Thine!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWe all do extol Thee,\r\nThou Leader triumphant,\r\nAnd pray that Thou still\r\n our Defender wilt be.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nLet Thy congregation escape tribulation:\r\nThy name be ever praised!\r\n O Lord, make us free!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nWe gather together in grateful rejoicing;\r\nOur song of thanksgiving\r\n to heaven we raise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nWe come to acknowledge \r\nthe gifts of the Father,\r\nAnd offer our lives as a tribute of praise.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1991 Word Music; ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'We gather together to ask the Lord\'s blessing He chastens and hastens His will to make 	 known The wicked oppressing now cease from distressing; Sing praises to his name: He forgets not His own. Beside us to guide us, Our God with us joining, Ordaining, maintaining His kingdom divine; So from the beginning the fight we were winning: Thou, Lord, wast at our side, all glory be Thine! We all do extol Thee, Thou Leader triumphant, And pray that Thou still our Defender wilt be. Let Thy congregation escape tribulation: Thy name be ever praised! O Lord, make us free! We gather together in grateful rejoicing; Our song of thanksgiving to heaven we raise. We come to acknowledge the gifts of the Father, And offer our lives as a tribute of praise.'),
	(351, 'More Love, More Power', 'Jude Del Hierro', '~Chorus 1\r\n[Em]More love, [C]More power,\r\n[Am]More of Y[D]ou in my l[Em]ife.\r\n[Em]More love, [C]More Power,\r\n[Am]More of Y[D]ou in my l[Em]ife.\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAnd I will worship y[C]ou\r\nwith a[D]ll of my h[Em]eart.\r\nAnd I will worship y[C]ou\r\nwith a[D]ll of my m[Bm]ind.  [Em]\r\nAnd I will worship y[C]ou\r\nwith a[D]ll of my s[Em]trength.\r\nFor you are my [Am]Lord.\r\nYou are my [Em]Lord.\r\n~Chorus 2\r\n[Em]More faith, [C]more passion, \r\n[Am]More of Y[D]ou in my life.\r\n[Em]More faith, [C]more passion, \r\n[Am]More of Y[D]ou in my life.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd I will seek Your f[C]ace\r\nwith a[D]ll of my h[Em]eart.\r\nAnd I will seek Your f[C]ace\r\nwith a[D]ll of my m[Bm]ind.  [Em]\r\nAnd I will seek Your f[C]ace\r\nwith a[D]ll of my st[Em]rength.\r\nFor you are my [Am]Lord.\r\nYou are my [Em]Lord.\r\n~Tag\r\nFor You are my [Em]Lord.\r\n', '', '1987 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/hhbyISg66q8&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'More love, More power, More of You in my life. More love, More Power, More of You in my life. And I will worship you with all of my heart. And I will worship you with all of my mind. And I will worship you with all of my strength. For you are my Lord. You are my Lord. More faith, more passion, More of You in my life. More faith, more passion, More of You in my life. And I will seek Your face with all of my heart. And I will seek Your face with all of my mind. And I will seek Your face with all of my strength. For you are my Lord. You are my Lord. For You are my Lord.'),
	(353, 'Better Is One Day', 'Matt Redman', '~Verse 1\r\nHow l[E]ovely is Your dwelling place,\r\n[A]oh Lord Alm[B]ighty\r\nM[E]y soul longs and even faints for Y[B]ou\r\nFor h[E]ere my heart is satisfied,\r\n[A]within Your pr[B]esence\r\nI s[E]ing beneath the shadow of Your w[B]ings\r\n~Chorus\r\nBetter is o[A]ne day in Your courts\r\nBetter is o[B]ne day in Your house\r\nBetter is o[A]ne day in Your courts\r\nThan thousands e[B]lsewhere\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOne th[E]ing I ask and I would seek,\r\n[A]to see Your be[B]auty\r\nTo f[E]ind You in the place Your glory dw[B]ells\r\n~Bridge\r\n[C#m7]My heart and flesh cry o[B]ut,\r\n[A]for You the living G[B]od\r\n[C#m7]Your spirit\'s water [B]to my s[A]oul[B]\r\n[C#m7]I\'ve tasted and I\'ve s[B]een,\r\n[A]come once again to me\r\n[E/G#]I will draw near to You\r\n[F#m7]I will draw near to [B]You\r\n', '', '1995 Thankyou Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/0VdUiKagWjU&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'How lovely is Your dwelling place, oh Lord Almighty My soul longs and even faints for You For here my heart is satisfied, within Your presence I sing beneath the shadow of Your wings Better is one day in Your courts Better is one day in Your house Better is one day in Your courts Than thousands elsewhere One thing I ask and I would seek, to see Your beauty To find You in the place Your glory dwells My heart and flesh cry out, for You the living God Your spirit\'s water to my soul I\'ve tasted and I\'ve seen, come once again to me I will draw near to You I will draw near to You'),
	(354, 'He Saved Us To Show His Glory', 'Tommy Walker. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSet apart to declare His glorious praise\r\nChosen to radiate His glory and His grace\r\nOnce without hope\r\nHis mercy we\'ve received\r\nSo let\'s show the world\r\nWhat it means to be redeemed\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSet apart to proclaim the glorious news\r\nThat all is forgiven now\r\nThe old can be made new\r\nOnce without hope\r\nHis mercy we\'ve received\r\nSo let\'s show the world\r\nWhat it means to be redeemed\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhy did He save you\r\nSo I could be a soul set free\r\nWhy did He save me\r\nSo you could be His child forgiven\r\nWhy did He save you\r\nSo we could show His grace and mercy\r\nWhy did He save me\r\nTo take His glory to the nations\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe saved us to show His glory\r\nHe saved us to show His love\r\nHe saved us to show\r\nHis glory and His love\r\n', '', ' 2000 Integrity\'s Praise! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'Set apart to declare His glorious praise Chosen to radiate His glory and His grace Once without hope His mercy we\'ve received So let\'s show the world What it means to be redeemed Set apart to proclaim the glorious news That all is forgiven now The old can be made new Once without hope His mercy we\'ve received So let\'s show the world What it means to be redeemed Why did He save you So I could be a soul set free Why did He save me So you could be His child forgiven Why did He save you So we could show His grace and mercy Why did He save me To take His glory to the nations He saved us to show His glory He saved us to show His love He saved us to show His glory and His love'),
	(355, 'We Are The Reason', 'David Meece. (c) 1980 Word Music. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAs little children\r\nWe would dream of Christmas morn\r\nAnd all the gifts and toys\r\nWe knew we\'d find\r\nBut we never realized\r\nA Baby born one blessed night\r\nGave us the greatest gift of our lives\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAs the years went by\r\nWe learned more about gifts\r\nThe giving of ourselves\r\nAnd what that means\r\nOn a dark and cloudy day\r\nA Man hung crying in the rain\r\nBecause of love, because of love\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe are the reason\r\nThat He gave His life\r\nWe are the reason\r\nThat He suffered and died\r\nTo a world that was lost\r\nHe gave all He could give\r\nTo show us the reason to live\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI finally found a reason for living\r\nIt\'s in giveing every part\r\nOf my heart to Him\r\nIn all that I do\r\nEvery word that I say\r\nI\'ll be giving my all just for Him, for Him\r\n', '', ' ', '', '', 'As little children We would dream of Christmas morn And all the gifts and toys We knew we\'d find But we never realized A Baby born one blessed night Gave us the greatest gift of our lives As the years went by We learned more about gifts The giving of ourselves And what that means On a dark and cloudy day A Man hung crying in the rain Because of love, because of love We are the reason That He gave His life We are the reason That He suffered and died To a world that was lost He gave all He could give To show us the reason to live I finally found a reason for living It\'s in giveing every part Of my heart to Him In all that I do Every word that I say I\'ll be giving my all just for Him, for Him'),
	(356, 'Come Worship The Lord (Psalm 95)', 'John Michael Talbot, c. 1980 Birdwing Music/Cherry Lane Pub., Co. (ASCAP), (a div. of Sparrow Corp.)', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n(PSALM 95)\r\nCome worship the Lord\r\nFor we are His people,\r\nThe flock that He shepherds,\r\nAlleluia, Alleluia.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1980 Birdwing Music/Cherry Lane Pub., Co. (ASCAP), (a div. of Sparrow Corp.); ', '', '', '(PSALM 95) Come worship the Lord For we are His people, The flock that He shepherds, Alleluia, Alleluia.'),
	(357, 'No One Like You', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAnd how could I ever deny\r\nThe love of my Savior\r\nYou are to me everything\r\nAll I need forever\r\nHow could You be so good to me?\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\nYou are more beautiful\r\nThan anyone ever\r\nEveryday You\'re the same\r\nYou never change, no never\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nEverywhere You are there\r\nEarth or air surrounding\r\nI\'m not alone, the heavens sing along\r\nMy God You\'re so astounding\r\nHow could You be so good?\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHow could You be so good to me?\r\nHow could You be so good to me?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere is no one like You\r\nThere has never ever been anyone like You\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThere is no one like You\r\nThere has never ever been anyone like You\r\nThere is no one like our God, yeah\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'And how could I ever deny The love of my Savior You are to me everything All I need forever How could You be so good to me? You are more beautiful Than anyone ever Everyday You\'re the same You never change, no never Everywhere You are there Earth or air surrounding I\'m not alone, the heavens sing along My God You\'re so astounding How could You be so good? How could You be so good to me? How could You be so good to me? There is no one like You There has never ever been anyone like You There is no one like You There has never ever been anyone like You There is no one like our God, yeah'),
	(359, 'Heal Their Land', 'Ron Kenoly', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIf my people, \r\nWho are called by My name,\r\nWill humble themselves and pray,\r\nAnd purpose to seek my face;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will hear from Heaven,\r\nI will hear from Heaven,\r\nI will hear from Heaven,\r\nI\'ll hear and I\'ll heal their land.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIf My people,\r\nWho are called by My name,\r\nWill humble themselves and pray,\r\nAnd turn from their wicked ways.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe will hear from Heaven,\r\nHe will hear from Heaven,\r\nHe will hear from Heaven,\r\nHe\'ll hear and He\'ll heal their land.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nIf God\'s people,\r\nWho are called by His name,\r\nWill humble themselves and pray,\r\nAnd purpose to seek His face;\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nIf God\'s people,\r\n Who are called by His name,\r\nWill humble themselves and pray,\r\nAnd turn from their wicked ways.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music  c/o Integrity Music, Inc.', '', '', 'If my people, Who are called by My name, Will humble themselves and pray, And purpose to seek my face; I will hear from Heaven, I will hear from Heaven, I will hear from Heaven, I\'ll hear and I\'ll heal their land. If My people, Who are called by My name, Will humble themselves and pray, And turn from their wicked ways. He will hear from Heaven, He will hear from Heaven, He will hear from Heaven, He\'ll hear and He\'ll heal their land. If God\'s people, Who are called by His name, Will humble themselves and pray, And purpose to seek His face; If God\'s people, Who are called by His name, Will humble themselves and pray, And turn from their wicked ways.'),
	(360, 'Sing A Song', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI want to sing a song for You, Lord.\r\nLord, for you, I want to sing a song.\r\nAnd I want to lift my voice to Heaven,\r\nand listen to the angels sing along.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI want to live my life for You, Lord.\r\nLord, for You, I want to live my life.\r\nI want to praise the name of Jesus\r\nand pray above all things \r\nYou\'re glorified.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nA song of Your faithfulness, \r\na song of Your grace,\r\nand of Your loving kindness,\r\nto the glory of Your Name.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd I sing about Your mercy\r\nand I sing about Your love;\r\nYour goodness, Lord, Your righteousness.\r\nI want to sing\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd we\'ll sing, "Holy, holy, holy."\r\nWe\'ll sing, "Holy, holy, holy."\r\nWe\'ll shout, "Holy, holy, \r\nare You, Lord God almighty !"\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWith ev\'rything that\'s in me, Lord,\r\nlisten to me say:\r\nI want to sing a song for You,\r\nI want to sing a song.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I want to sing a song for You, Lord. Lord, for you, I want to sing a song. And I want to lift my voice to Heaven, and listen to the angels sing along. I want to live my life for You, Lord. Lord, for You, I want to live my life. I want to praise the name of Jesus and pray above all things You\'re glorified. A song of Your faithfulness, a song of Your grace, and of Your loving kindness, to the glory of Your Name. And I sing about Your mercy and I sing about Your love; Your goodness, Lord, Your righteousness. I want to sing And we\'ll sing, "Holy, holy, holy." We\'ll sing, "Holy, holy, holy." We\'ll shout, "Holy, holy, are You, Lord God almighty !" With ev\'rything that\'s in me, Lord, listen to me say: I want to sing a song for You, I want to sing a song.'),
	(361, 'Hosanna (Open The Gates)', 'Chris Christensen and Thierry Ostrini', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe broken in spirit, \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe broken in spirit,\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nThe humble will hear it, \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThe humble will hear it;\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nHis invitation, \r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHis invitation\r\n~Verse 7\r\n\r\nTo join the celebration.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nOpen the gates, \r\nHere comes the King of Glory,\r\nLift up your voice and sing;\r\nLet us rejoice, \r\nOur God has come to save us,\r\nHosanna, hosanna, hosanna!\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nHis army assembles, \r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nHis army assembles,\r\n~Verse 12\r\n\r\nThe enemy trembles,\r\n\r\n~Verse 13\r\nThe enemy trembles;\r\n~Verse 14\r\n\r\nOur God is with us,\r\n\r\n~Verse 15\r\nOur God is with us,\r\n~Verse 16\r\n\r\nHis Word is victorious.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 17\r\nBefore His splendor, \r\n\r\n~Verse 18\r\nBefore His splendor,\r\n~Verse 19\r\n\r\nKings will surrender, \r\n\r\n~Verse 20\r\nKings will surrender;\r\n~Verse 21\r\n\r\nBow down before Him,\r\n\r\n~Verse 22\r\nBow down before Him,\r\n~Verse 23\r\n\r\nWorship and adore Him.\r\n\r\n~Verse 24\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 25\r\nHosanna, hosanna;\r\nHosanna, hosanna!\r\nHosanna, hosanna;\r\nHosanna, hosanna, hosanna!\r\n', '', ' 1995 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'The broken in spirit, The broken in spirit, The humble will hear it, The humble will hear it; His invitation, His invitation To join the celebration. Open the gates, Here comes the King of Glory, Lift up your voice and sing; Let us rejoice, Our God has come to save us, Hosanna, hosanna, hosanna! His army assembles, His army assembles, The enemy trembles, The enemy trembles; Our God is with us, Our God is with us, His Word is victorious. Before His splendor, Before His splendor, Kings will surrender, Kings will surrender; Bow down before Him, Bow down before Him, Worship and adore Him. Hosanna, hosanna; Hosanna, hosanna! Hosanna, hosanna; Hosanna, hosanna, hosanna!'),
	(362, 'I Heard The Bells On Christmas Day', '', '~Verse 1\r\nI heard the bells on Christmas day\r\nTheir old familiar carols play,\r\nAnd wild and sweet the words repeat\r\nOf peace on earth, good will to men.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI thought how, as the day had come,\r\nThe belfries of all Christendom\r\nHad rolled along th\'un-bro-ken song\r\nOf peace on earth, good will to men.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd in despair I bowed my head:\r\n"There is no peace on earth," I said,\r\n"For hate is strong, and mocks the song\r\nOf peace on earth, good will to men."\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYet pealed the bells more loud and deep:\r\n"God is not dead, nor doth He sleep;\r\nThe wrong shall fail, the right prevail,\r\nWith peace on earth, good will to men."\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThen ringing, singing on its way,\r\nThe world revolved from night to day -\r\nA voice, a chime, a chant sublime\r\nOf peace on earth, good will to men!\r\n', '', '1976 Manna Music Inc', '', '', 'I heard the bells on Christmas day Their old familiar carols play, And wild and sweet the words repeat Of peace on earth, good will to men. I thought how, as the day had come, The belfries of all Christendom Had rolled along th\\\'un-bro-ken song Of peace on earth, good will to men. And in despair I bowed my head: \\"There is no peace on earth,\\" I said, \\"For hate is strong, and mocks the song Of peace on earth, good will to men.\\" Yet pealed the bells more loud and deep: \\"God is not dead, nor doth He sleep; The wrong shall fail, the right prevail, With peace on earth, good will to men.\\" Then ringing, singing on its way, The world revolved from night to day - A voice, a chime, a chant sublime Of peace on earth, good will to men!'),
	(363, 'Give Me Jesus', 'Fernando Ortega', '~Intro\r\n[G] [Em9] [C6] [G]\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIn the [G]Morning, when I r[Em9]ise\r\nIn the [C6]Morning, when I ri[G]se\r\nIn the [Em9]morning, when I[A7sus] rise [C6]\r\nGive me [C6+9]Jesus[G]\r\n~Chorus\r\nGive me[Bm7] Jes[Em]us\r\nGive me [C6]Jes[G]us\r\nYou can [Em9]have all this [A7sus]world [C6]\r\nJust give me[C6+9] Jesu[G]s\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen [G]I am al[Em9]one\r\nWhen [C6]I am alo[G]ne\r\noh, w[Em9]hen I am[A7sus] alone[C6]\r\nGive me [C6+9]Jesus[G]\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhen [G]I come [Em9]to die\r\nwhen [C6]I come t[G]o die\r\noh, w[Em9]hen I co[A7sus]me to [C6]die\r\nGive me [C6+9]Jesus[G]\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/9Dca0P7w9ZQ&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/give-me-jesus/id201053345?i=201053401&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Jeremy Camp - Beyond Measure - Give Me Jesus" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'In the Morning, when I rise In the Morning, when I rise In the morning, when I rise Give me Jesus Give me Jesus Give me Jesus You can have all this world Just give me Jesus When I am alone When I am alone oh, when I am alone Give me Jesus When I come to die when I come to die oh, when I come to die Give me Jesus'),
