	(379, 'O Lord, You\'re Beautiful', 'Keith Green', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]O Lord, You\'re b[F]eau[C]tifu[G]l.  Your f[C]ace is a[F]ll [C]I s[G]eek.\r\nAnd wh[Am]en your e[E]yes are [Am]on th[G/B]is ch[C]ild, Your gr[F]ace abo[G]unds to [F-C]me.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO Lord, please light the fire that once burned bright and clear\r\nReplace the lamp of my first love that burned with holy zeal\r\n~Chorus\r\nI want to [F]take Your l[Dm]ove and sh[G]ine it all ar[C]ound\r\nBut first help me j[F]ust to l[G]ive it Lord.\r\nAnd if I\'m d[F]oin\' w[Dm]ell help me to n[G]ever seek a cr[C]own\r\nFor my r[Am]eward is giving g[Dm]lor[G]y to y[C]ou\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO Lord, You\'re merciful. Your love is all I need.\r\nAnd when your love Is on this child, Forgiveness I receive.\r\n', '', ' 1980 Birdwing Music/Cherry Lane Music Pub. Co. Inc. U.S.A.', '', '', 'O Lord, You\'re beautiful.  Your face is all I seek. And when your eyes are on this child, Your grace abounds to me. O Lord, please light the fire that once burned bright and clear Replace the lamp of my first love that burned with holy zeal I want to take Your love and shine it all around But first help me just to live it Lord. And if I\'m doin\' well help me to never seek a crown For my reward is giving glory to you O Lord, You\'re merciful. Your love is all I need. And when your love Is on this child, Forgiveness I receive.'),
