	(392, 'O Lord God Of Israel', 'Donna Atkins', '~Verse 1\r\nO Lord God of Israel\r\nThere is no god like Thee in the heav\'n\r\nThere is no god like Thee in the earth\r\nO Lord God of Israel.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThat keepest covenant and showeth mercy\r\nUnto Thy servants that walk before Thee\r\nWith all of their hearts.\r\n', '', '1976 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'O Lord God of Israel There is no god like Thee in the heav\\\'n There is no god like Thee in the earth O Lord God of Israel. That keepest covenant and showeth mercy Unto Thy servants that walk before Thee With all of their hearts.'),
	(394, 'Trust And Obey Changed (Hymn #349)', 'John H. Sammis and Music by Daniel B. Towner', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhen we walk with the Lord\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nin the light of His Word,\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhat a glory He sheds on our way!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhile we do His good will\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nNot a shadow can rise, \r\nnot a cloud in the skies,\r\nBut His smile quickly drives it away;\r\nNot a doubt nor a fear, not a sigh nor a tear,\r\nCan abide while we trust and obey.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHe abides with us still,\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nfor there\'s no other way\r\n	\r\n~Verse 8\r\nAnd with all who will trust and obey.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\n\r\nText by John H. Sammis and Music by Daniel B. Towner\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nNot a burden we bear, \r\nnot a sorrow we share,\r\nBut our toil He doth richly repay;\r\nNot a grief nor a loss,\r\n not a frown nor a cross,\r\nBut is blest if we trust and obey.\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nBut we never can prove, \r\nthe delights of His love\r\nUntil all on the altar we lay;\r\nFor the favor He shows\r\n and the joy He bestows\r\nAre for them who will trust and obey.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 12\r\nThen in fellowship sweet \r\nwe will sit at His feet,\r\nOr we\'ll walk by His side in the way;\r\nWhat He says He will do,\r\nWhere He sends we will go\r\nNever fear, only trust and obey.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 13\r\nTrust and obey, \r\n\r\n~Verse 14\r\nto be happy in Jesus,\r\n\r\n~Verse 15\r\nBut to trust and obey.\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'When we walk with the Lord in the light of His Word, What a glory He sheds on our way! While we do His good will Not a shadow can rise, not a cloud in the skies, But His smile quickly drives it away; Not a doubt nor a fear, not a sigh nor a tear, Can abide while we trust and obey. He abides with us still, for there\'s no other way And with all who will trust and obey. Text by John H. Sammis and Music by Daniel B. Towner Not a burden we bear, not a sorrow we share, But our toil He doth richly repay; Not a grief nor a loss, not a frown nor a cross, But is blest if we trust and obey. But we never can prove, the delights of His love Until all on the altar we lay; For the favor He shows and the joy He bestows Are for them who will trust and obey. Then in fellowship sweet we will sit at His feet, Or we\'ll walk by His side in the way; What He says He will do, Where He sends we will go Never fear, only trust and obey. Trust and obey, to be happy in Jesus, But to trust and obey.'),
	(396, 'Behold The  Lamb', 'Dottie Rambo', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBehold the Lamb, behold the Lamb,\r\nSlain from the foundation of the world.\r\nFor sinners crucified,\r\nO holy sacrifice, \r\nBehold the Lamb of God, \r\nBehold the Lamb.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCrown Him crown Him, \r\nWorthy is the Lamb.\r\nPraise Him, praise Him.\r\nHeav\'n and earth resound. \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Behold the Lamb, behold the Lamb, Slain from the foundation of the world. For sinners crucified, O holy sacrifice, Behold the Lamb of God, Behold the Lamb. Crown Him crown Him, Worthy is the Lamb. Praise Him, praise Him. Heav\'n and earth resound.'),
	(397, 'Now Thank We All Our God (Hymn #556)', '', '\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNow thank we all our God\r\nWith heart and hands and voices,\r\nWho wondrous things hath done,\r\nIn whom his world rejoices;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWho, from our mother\'s arms,\r\nHath blest us on our way\r\nWith countless gifts of love,\r\nAnd still is ours today.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO may this bounteous God\r\nThro\' all our life be near us,\r\nWith ever joyful hearts\r\nAnd blessed peace to cheer us;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAll praise and thanks to God\r\nThe Father now be given,\r\nThe Son, and Him who reigns\r\nWith them in highest heaven.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAnd keep us in His grace,\r\nAnd guide us when perplexed,\r\nAnd free us from all ills\r\nIn this world and the next.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nThe one eternal God,\r\nWhom earth and heav\'n adore;\r\nFor thus it was, is now,\r\nAnd shall be evermore.  Amen.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Now thank we all our God With heart and hands and voices, Who wondrous things hath done, In whom his world rejoices; Who, from our mother\'s arms, Hath blest us on our way With countless gifts of love, And still is ours today. O may this bounteous God Thro\' all our life be near us, With ever joyful hearts And blessed peace to cheer us; All praise and thanks to God The Father now be given, The Son, and Him who reigns With them in highest heaven. And keep us in His grace, And guide us when perplexed, And free us from all ills In this world and the next. The one eternal God, Whom earth and heav\'n adore; For thus it was, is now, And shall be evermore.  Amen.'),
	(398, 'He Lives', 'Alfred H. Achley.   c 1961 by The Rodeheaver Co.  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI serve a risen Savior,\r\nHe\'s in the world today;\r\nI know that He is living,\r\nWhatever men may say;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI see His hand of mercy,\r\nI hear His voice of cheer,\r\nAnd just the time I need Him\r\nHe\'s always near.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn all the world around me \r\nI see His loving care,\r\nAnd tho\' my heart grows weary,\r\nI never will despair;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe lives, He lives, \r\nChrist Jesus lives today!\r\nHe walks with me and talks with me \r\nAlong life\'s narrow way.\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHe lives, He lives, \r\nSalvation to impart!\r\nYou ask me how I know He lives?\r\nHe lives within my heart.\r\n~Verse 9\r\nRejoice, rejoice, O Christian, \r\nLift up your voice and sing\r\nEternal hallelujahs\r\n To Jesus Christ the King!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nThe Hope of all who seek Him,\r\nThe Help of all who find,\r\nNone other is so loving, \r\nSo good and kind.\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nI know that He is leading \r\nThro\' all the stormy blast,\r\nThe day of His appearing \r\nWill come at last.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I serve a risen Savior, He\'s in the world today; I know that He is living, Whatever men may say; I see His hand of mercy, I hear His voice of cheer, And just the time I need Him He\'s always near. In all the world around me I see His loving care, And tho\' my heart grows weary, I never will despair; He lives, He lives, Christ Jesus lives today! He walks with me and talks with me Along life\'s narrow way. He lives, He lives, Salvation to impart! You ask me how I know He lives? He lives within my heart. Rejoice, rejoice, O Christian, Lift up your voice and sing Eternal hallelujahs To Jesus Christ the King! The Hope of all who seek Him, The Help of all who find, None other is so loving, So good and kind. I know that He is leading Thro\' all the stormy blast, The day of His appearing Will come at last.'),
	(399, 'Sing A New Song To The Lord', 'Timothy Dudley-Smith', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSing a new song to the Lord\r\nHe to whom wonders belong!\r\nRejoice in His triumph and tell of His power.\r\nO sing to the Lord a new song!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNow to the ends of the earth\r\nSee his salvation is shown!\r\nAnd still He remembers His mercy and truth.\r\nUnchanging in love to His own.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSing a new song and rejoice\r\nPublish His praises abroad!\r\nLet voices in chorus with trumpet and horn\r\nResound for the joy of the Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nJoin with the hills and the sea\r\nThunders of praise to prolong!\r\nIn judgement and justice\r\nHe comes to the earth.\r\nO sing to the Lord a new song!\r\n', '', ' D.G. Wilson. ', '', '', 'Sing a new song to the Lord He to whom wonders belong! Rejoice in His triumph and tell of His power. O sing to the Lord a new song! Now to the ends of the earth See his salvation is shown! And still He remembers His mercy and truth. Unchanging in love to His own. Sing a new song and rejoice Publish His praises abroad! Let voices in chorus with trumpet and horn Resound for the joy of the Lord! Join with the hills and the sea Thunders of praise to prolong! In judgement and justice He comes to the earth. O sing to the Lord a new song!'),
	(400, 'Holy Is The Lord (we stand and lift up our hands)', 'Chris Tomlin & Louie Giglio', '~Verse 1\r\nWe stand and lift up\r\nour hands,\r\nFor the joy of the Lord\r\nis our strength.\r\nWe bow down\r\nand worship Him now.\r\nHow great,\r\nhow awesome is He.\r\nAnd together we sing\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHoly is the Lord\r\nGod Almighty.\r\nThe earth is filled\r\nwith His glory.\r\nHoly is the Lord\r\nGod Almighty.\r\nThe earth is filled\r\nwith His glory.\r\nThe earth is filled\r\nwith His glory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt\'s rising up all around.\r\nIt\'s the anthem of\r\nThe Lord\'s renown.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe stand and lift up\r\nour hands,\r\nFor the joy of the Lord\r\nis our strength.\r\nWe bow down\r\nand worship Him now.\r\nHow great,\r\nhow awesome is He.\r\nAnd together we sing\r\nEveryone sing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nIt\'s rising up all around.\r\nIt\'s the anthem of\r\nThe Lord\'s renown.\r\n  And together we sing,\r\nEveryone sing.\r\n\r\n', '', '2003 worshiptogether.com songs/sixsteps Music. ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/FIwMYktdBg8', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/holy-is-the-lord/id27672964?i=27672882&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Chris Tomlin - Arriving - Holy Is the Lord" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'We stand and lift up our hands, For the joy of the Lord is our strength. We bow down and worship Him now. How great, how awesome is He. And together we sing Holy is the Lord God Almighty. The earth is filled with His glory. Holy is the Lord God Almighty. The earth is filled with His glory. The earth is filled with His glory. It\'s rising up all around. It\'s the anthem of The Lord\'s renown. We stand and lift up our hands, For the joy of the Lord is our strength. We bow down and worship Him now. How great, how awesome is He. And together we sing Everyone sing. It\'s rising up all around. It\'s the anthem of The Lord\'s renown. And together we sing, Everyone sing.'),
	(401, 'I Stand Amazed In The Presence', '', '~Verse 1\r\nI stand amazed in the presence\r\nOf Jesus the Nazarene,\r\nAnd wonder how He could love me, \r\nA sinner condemned, unclean.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHow marvelous! How wonderful!\r\nAnd my song shall ever be:\r\nHow marvelous! How wonderful!\r\nIs my Saviours love for me!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor me it was in the garden\r\nHe prayed "not My will, but Thine"\r\nHe had no tears for His own griefs,\r\nBut sweat-drops of blood for mine.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn pity angels beheld Him,\r\nAnd came from the world of light\r\nTo comfort Him in the sorrows\r\nHe bore for my soul that night.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe took my sins and my sorrows,\r\nHe made them His very own;\r\nHe bore the burden to Calv\'ry,\r\nAnd suffered and died alone.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhen with the ransomed in glory\r\nHis face I at last shall see,\r\n\'Twill be my joy thru the ages \r\nTo sing of His love for me.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/hoV4koFy-Is', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I stand amazed in the presence Of Jesus the Nazarene, And wonder how He could love me, A sinner condemned, unclean. How marvelous! How wonderful! And my song shall ever be: How marvelous! How wonderful! Is my Saviours love for me! For me it was in the garden He prayed "not My will, but Thine" He had no tears for His own griefs, But sweat-drops of blood for mine. In pity angels beheld Him, And came from the world of light To comfort Him in the sorrows He bore for my soul that night. He took my sins and my sorrows, He made them His very own; He bore the burden to Calv\'ry, And suffered and died alone. When with the ransomed in glory His face I at last shall see, \'Twill be my joy thru the ages To sing of His love for me.).'),
	(402, 'I Will Sing Of The Mercies Of The Lord', 'J.H. Filmore, Public Domain', '~Verse 1\r\nI will s[D]ing of the mercies of the Lord forever\r\nI will s[Em]ing, I will si[D]ng\r\nI will sing of the mercies of the Lord forever\r\nI will s[Em7]ing of the m[A7]ercies of the Lord[D]\r\nWith my m[G]outh will I make kno[D]wn\r\nThy f[Em7]aithfulness, Thy fai[D]thfulness\r\nWith my m[G]outh will I make kno[D]wn\r\nThy f[A]aithfulness to all generat[A7]ions\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I will sing of the mercies of the Lord forever I will sing, I will sing I will sing of the mercies of the Lord forever I will sing of the mercies of the Lord With my mouth will I make known Thy faithfulness, Thy faithfulness With my mouth will I make known Thy faithfulness to all generations'),
	(403, 'Ancient Of Days', 'Gary Sadler & Jamie Harvill', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Blessing an[Em]d ho[D]nor, glory an[Em]d po[D]wer\r\n[D]Be unto the [A2]Ancient of [Bm]Days.[A2]\r\n[D]From every [Em]nat[D]ion, all of [Em]crea[D]tion\r\n[Bm7]Bow before the [A]Ancient of [D]Days.\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]Every tongue in [Em7]heaven and [A]earth shall dec[D/F#]lare Your glory.\r\n[G]Every knee shall [Em7]bow at Your [A]throne in [D/F#]worship[F#m7].\r\n[G]You will be e[Em7]xalted, O [A]God, \r\n[D/F#m]And Your [G]kingdom shall [Em7]not pass [A]away.\r\nO [G]Ancient of  [D]Days.[Dsus] [D][Dsus]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour [D]kingdom shall [Bm]reign over [A]all the [D]earth;\r\n[C]Sing un[G]to the [Am]Ancient [G]of [D]Days.\r\nFor [D]none can com[Bm]pare to Your [A]matchless [D]worth;\r\n[C]Sing un[G]to the [Am]Ancient [G]of [D]Days.[D/F#]\r\n', '', '1992 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/UOe5GpqFJrE', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Blessing and honor, glory and power Be unto the Ancient of Days. From every nation, all of creation Bow before the Ancient of Days. Every tongue in heaven and earth shall declare Your glory. Every knee shall bow at Your throne in worship. You will be exalted, O God, And Your kingdom shall not pass away. O Ancient of  Days. Your kingdom shall reign over all the earth; Sing unto the Ancient of Days. For none can compare to Your matchless worth; Sing unto the Ancient of Days.).'),
	(404, 'Revolution', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIf I\'m here all alone\r\nIf I\'m left behind \r\nIf they spit in my face\r\nIf they hate my kind\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen the world is at war \r\nWhen the grace is gone\r\nWhen the hungry lay dead\r\nWhile the rich live on\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will rise above\r\nI will live for love\r\nI will answer to the call\r\nFor the bond between\r\nFor a depth unseen\r\nFor my God forsake it all\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n(Here I stand)\r\nOpen hands\r\nWaiting for You\r\nI won\'t back down\r\nI\'ll live to speak Your truth\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\'Cause I\'m a fire\r\nI\'m a flood\r\nI\'m a revolution\r\nI am a war\r\nAlready won\r\nI\'m a revolution\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI will rise above\r\nI will live for love\r\nI will answer to the call\r\nFor the bond between\r\nFor the depth unseen\r\nFor my God forsake it all\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'If I\'m here all alone If I\'m left behind If they spit in my face If they hate my kind When the world is at war When the grace is gone When the hungry lay dead While the rich live on I will rise above I will live for love I will answer to the call For the bond between For a depth unseen For my God forsake it all (Here I stand) Open hands Waiting for You I won\'t back down I\'ll live to speak Your truth \'Cause I\'m a fire I\'m a flood I\'m a revolution I am a war Already won I\'m a revolution I will rise above I will live for love I will answer to the call For the bond between For the depth unseen For my God forsake it all'),
	(405, 'Psalm Of Thanks', 'Andy Park; c. 1992 Mercy Publishing; ARR; ICS; UBP; CC.LI#218004', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGive thanks unto the Lord, \r\n	 call on his name (2x)\r\nAnd sing to him, sing praise to him\r\nGlory in his holy name.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd rejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord.\r\nLet the hearts of those \r\nwho seek the Lord rejoice\r\nAnd rejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord.\r\nLet the hearts of those \r\nwho seek the Lord rejoice.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGive thanks unto the Lord \r\n	 for he is good (2x)\r\nAnd his love endures forever.\r\nCall upon his holy name.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTell all the nations what he has done (2x)\r\nTell of his mighty deeds,\r\n all his mighty deeds.\r\nGlory in his holy name.\r\n', '', ' 1992 Mercy Publishing; ARR; ICS; UBP; CC.LI#218004', '', '', 'Give thanks unto the Lord, call on his name (2x) And sing to him, sing praise to him Glory in his holy name. And rejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord. Let the hearts of those who seek the Lord rejoice And rejoice in the Lord, rejoice in the Lord. Let the hearts of those who seek the Lord rejoice. Give thanks unto the Lord for he is good (2x) And his love endures forever. Call upon his holy name. Tell all the nations what he has done (2x) Tell of his mighty deeds, all his mighty deeds. Glory in his holy name.'),
	(406, 'I Will Run To You', 'Darlene Zschech', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]Your e[C/G]ye is  [D/G]on the sp[G]arrow, \r\nAnd Your [C/G]hand, it [D/F#]comforts [Em]me [Em/D]\r\nFrom the [F/C]ends of the e[C]arth, \r\nTo the d[D]epths of  [D/F#]my  he[G]art, \r\nLet Your m[C]ercy and str[Am]ength be [Dsus]seen [D]\r\n~Verse 2 \r\nYou c[C]all me [C/D]to  Your p[G]urpose, [G/B]\r\nAs [C]angels [D]underst[Em]and [Em/D]\r\nFor Your [F/C]glo - [C]ry, \r\nMay You d[D]raw  [D/F#]all m[G]en, \r\n[G/B]As Your l[C]ove and gr[D]ace dem[G]ands \r\n~Chorus \r\nAnd I will [C/G]run  [D/G]to  Y[G]ou, to Your [D/F#]words  [B/D#]of  t[Em]ruth \r\nNot by m[Am7]ight, not by [G/B]power, \r\nBut by the Sp[C]ir - [A/C#]it of G[D]od \r\nY[G]es I will [C/G]run  [D/G]the r[G]ace, \'til I [D/F#]see   [B/D#]Your f[Em]ace \r\nOh let me [Am7]live in the g[G/B]lory  [Dsus]of  Your [Gsus]grace[G]\r\n', '', '1996 Darlene Zschech/Hillsongs Publishing.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/6mV3qtU7Wkc&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Your eye is  on the sparrow, And Your hand, it comforts me From the ends of the earth, To the depths of  my  heart, Let Your mercy and strength be seen You call me to  Your purpose, As angels understand For Your glo - ry, May You draw  all men, As Your love and grace demands And I will run  to  You, to Your words  of  truth Not by might, not by power, But by the Spir - it of God Yes I will run  the race, \'til I see   Your face Oh let me live in the glory  of  Your grace'),
	(407, 'Beloved, Let Us Love One Another', 'Dennis Ryder, c. 1974, Maranatha! Music,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBeloved, let us love one another,\r\nFor love is of God\r\nAnd everyone that loveth \r\nIs born of God and knoweth God,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe that loveth not,\r\nKnoweth not God,\r\nFor God is love,\r\nBeloved, let us love one another,\r\nFirst John 4:7 & 8\r\n', '', ' 1974, Maranatha! Music,', '', '', 'Beloved, let us love one another, For love is of God And everyone that loveth Is born of God and knoweth God, He that loveth not, Knoweth not God, For God is love, Beloved, let us love one another, First John 4:7 & 8'),
