	(410, 'The Greatest Thing', 'Mark Pendergrass', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life\r\n is knowing You.\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life \r\nis knowing You.\r\nI want to know You more; \r\nI want to know You more;\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life\r\n is knowing You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life\r\n is loving You.\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life\r\n is loving You.\r\nI want to love You more, \r\nI want to love You more.\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life \r\nis loving You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life \r\nis serving You.\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life\r\n is serving You.\r\nI want to serve You more, \r\nI want to serve You more.\r\nThe greatest thing in all my life \r\nis serving You.\r\n', '', ' 1977, Sparrow Song/Candle Co. Music,Cherry  River Music Co.(BMI)', '', '', 'The greatest thing in all my life is knowing You. The greatest thing in all my life is knowing You. I want to know You more; I want to know You more; The greatest thing in all my life is knowing You. The greatest thing in all my life is loving You. The greatest thing in all my life is loving You. I want to love You more, I want to love You more. The greatest thing in all my life is loving You. The greatest thing in all my life is serving You. The greatest thing in all my life is serving You. I want to serve You more, I want to serve You more. The greatest thing in all my life is serving You.'),
	(411, 'How Firm A Foundation', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHow firm a foundation,\r\nYe saints of the Lord,\r\nIs laid for your faith\r\nIn His excellent Word!\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhat more can He say\r\nThan to you He hath said,\r\nTo you who for refuge\r\nTo Jesus have fled?\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n"Fear not, I am with thee;\r\nO be not dismayed,\r\nFor I am thy God,\r\nAnd will still give thee aid;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI\'ll strengthen thee, help thee,\r\nAnd cause thee to stand,\r\nUpheld by My righteous\r\n Omnipotent hand.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n"When through fiery trials\r\n Thy pathway shall lie,\r\nMy grace all sufficient, \r\nShall be they supply:\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\n"The soul that on Jesus \r\nHath leaned for repose\r\nI will not, I will not desert to it\'s foes;\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nThat soul, though all hell\r\nShould endeavor to shake,\r\nI\'ll never, no, never, no, never forsake!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nThe flame shall not hurt thee;\r\n	 I only design Thy dross to consume\r\nAnd thy gold to refine.\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'How firm a foundation, Ye saints of the Lord, Is laid for your faith In His excellent Word! What more can He say Than to you He hath said, To you who for refuge To Jesus have fled? "Fear not, I am with thee; O be not dismayed, For I am thy God, And will still give thee aid; I\'ll strengthen thee, help thee, And cause thee to stand, Upheld by My righteous Omnipotent hand. "When through fiery trials Thy pathway shall lie, My grace all sufficient, Shall be they supply: "The soul that on Jesus Hath leaned for repose I will not, I will not desert to it\'s foes; That soul, though all hell Should endeavor to shake, I\'ll never, no, never, no, never forsake!" The flame shall not hurt thee; I only design Thy dross to consume And thy gold to refine.'),
	(412, 'I Will Never Be', '', '~Verse 1\r\nI will never be the same again,\r\n  I can never return, I\'ve closed the door;\r\n  I will walk the path, I\'ll run the race,\r\n  And I will never be the same again.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFall like fire, soak like rain,\r\n  Flow like mighty waters, \r\nagain and again;\r\n  Sweep away the darkness,\r\n  Burn away the chaff,\r\n  And let a flame burn \r\nto glorify your name.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere are higher heights,\r\n  There are deeper seas,\r\n  Whatever you need to do, \r\n  Lord do in me;\r\n  The glory of God fills my life,\r\n  And I will never be the same again.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Word Music ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/MU-6bB8XYYA', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I will never be the same again, I can never return, I\'ve closed the door; I will walk the path, I\'ll run the race, And I will never be the same again. Fall like fire, soak like rain, Flow like mighty waters, again and again; Sweep away the darkness, Burn away the chaff, And let a flame burn to glorify your name. There are higher heights, There are deeper seas, Whatever you need to do, Lord do in me; The glory of God fills my life, And I will never be the same again.).'),
	(414, 'Jesus Take Me As I Am', 'Dave Bryant', '~Verse 1\r\nJesus take me as I am\r\nI can come no other way\r\nTake me deeper into You\r\nMake my flesh life melt away\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMake me like a precious stone\r\nCrystal clear and finely honed\r\nLife of Jesus shining through\r\nGiving glory back to you.\r\n', '', '1978 Thankyou Music', '', '', 'Jesus take me as I am I can come no other way Take me deeper into You Make my flesh life melt away Make me like a precious stone Crystal clear and finely honed Life of Jesus shining through Giving glory back to you.'),
	(415, 'The Lord Is Come', 'Ric Marchi', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFor the Lord is come to Zion,\r\nHe will dwell in the midst of our praise;\r\nWe will magnify and exalt Him,\r\nLift Him up for all to see.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe Lord is come in glory and power,\r\nThe Lord is come, sing praise to His name;\r\nThe Lord is come, Hosanna, Hosanna,\r\nThe Lord is come, sing praise to His name.\r\n', '', '1987 Zion Song Music  (ASCAP)', '', '', 'For the Lord is come to Zion, He will dwell in the midst of our praise; We will magnify and exalt Him, Lift Him up for all to see. The Lord is come in glory and power, The Lord is come, sing praise to His name; The Lord is come, Hosanna, Hosanna, The Lord is come, sing praise to His name.'),
	(417, 'We Fall Down', 'Chris Tomlin.', '~Verse 1\r\n[E] [D/E] [E] [D]\r\n[E]We fall down\r\nWe [B]lay our [C#m]crowns\r\nAt the [A]feet of [F#m7]Jesus\r\nThe [E]greatness of [B]mercy and [C#m]love\r\nAt the [A]feet of [B]Jesus\r\n~Chorus\r\nAnd [E/G#]we cry, [A]"Holy, [E/G#]Holy, [F#m7]Holy"\r\nAnd [E/G#]we cry, [A]"Holy, [E/G#]Holy, [F#m7]Holy"\r\nAnd [C#m]we [B]cry, [A]"Holy, [C#m]Holy, [B9]Holy"\r\nIs the Lamb[E][D/E][E][D]\r\n', '', '1998 worshiptogether.com songs', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/wo69WR6IASg', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/we-fall-down/id262277972?i=262278159&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Chris Tomlin - I Will Celebrate - We Fall Down" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', '.mysql_real_escape_string(We fall down We lay our crowns At the feet of Jesus The greatness of mercy and love At the feet of Jesus And we cry, "Holy, Holy, Holy" And we cry, "Holy, Holy, Holy" And we cry, "Holy, Holy, Holy" Is the Lamb).'),
	(418, 'With All I Am', 'Reuben Morgan. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nInto Your hands I commit again\r\nAll I am for You Lord\r\nYou hold my world\r\nIn the palm of Your hand\r\nAnd I am Yours forever\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI\'ll walk with You wherever You go\r\nThrough tears and joy\r\nI\'ll trust in You\r\nAnd I will live in all of Your ways\r\nAnd Your promises forever\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus I believe in You\r\nJesus I belong to You\r\nYou\'re the reason that I live\r\nThe reason that I sing\r\nWith all I am\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI will worship\r\nI will worship You\r\nI will worship\r\nI will worship You\r\n', '', ' 2003 Hillsong Publishing.', '', '', 'Into Your hands I commit again All I am for You Lord You hold my world In the palm of Your hand And I am Yours forever I\'ll walk with You wherever You go Through tears and joy I\'ll trust in You And I will live in all of Your ways And Your promises forever Jesus I believe in You Jesus I belong to You You\'re the reason that I live The reason that I sing With all I am I will worship I will worship You I will worship I will worship You'),
	(419, 'The Gift And The Giver', 'Claire Cloninger and Gary Rhodes', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou\'ve given us songs \r\nto sing and to celebrate,\r\nGiven us joy to spread through the world.\r\nYou\'ve given us hope \r\nthat nothing\'s impossible,\r\nGiven us truth by the pow\'r of Your Word!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor You are the Gift and You are the Giver!\r\nYou are the Savior, come to deliver!\r\nYou are the Love that flows like a river \r\nInto our waiting hearts,\r\n into our waiting hearts.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou\'ve given us love to live as a family,\r\nGiven us peace to carry us through.\r\nYou\'ve given us grace \r\nto be all we need to be,\r\nMost of all, Lord, \r\n You\'ve given us You!\r\n', '', ' 1994 Word Music (a div. of WORD, INC) ', '', '', 'You\'ve given us songs to sing and to celebrate, Given us joy to spread through the world. You\'ve given us hope that nothing\'s impossible, Given us truth by the pow\'r of Your Word! For You are the Gift and You are the Giver! You are the Savior, come to deliver! You are the Love that flows like a river Into our waiting hearts, into our waiting hearts. You\'ve given us love to live as a family, Given us peace to carry us through. You\'ve given us grace to be all we need to be, Most of all, Lord, You\'ve given us You!'),
	(420, 'It Came Upon The Midnight Clear', 'Edmund H. Sears; music by Richard S. Wilis. Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIt came upon the midnight clear,\r\nThat glorious song of old,\r\nFrom angels bending near the earth\r\nTo touch their harps of gold:\r\n"Peace on the earth, goodwill to men,\r\nFrom heav\'n\'s all-gracous King!"\r\nThe world in solemn stillness lay\r\nTo hear the angels sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nStill thru the cloven skies they come\r\nWith peaceful wings unfurled,\r\nAnd still their hev\'nly music floats\r\nO\'er all the weary world:\r\nAbove its sad and lowly plains\r\nThey bend on hov\'ring wing,\r\nAnd ever o\'er its Babel sounds\r\nThe blessed angels sing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd ye, beneath life\'s crushing load,\r\nWhose forms are bending low,\r\nWho toil along the climbing way\r\nWith painful steps and slow,\r\nLook now! For glad and golden hours\r\nCome swiftly on the wing:\r\nO rest beside the weary road\r\nAnd hear the angels sing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor lo, the days are hast\'ning on,\r\nBy prophets seen of old,\r\nWhen with the ever circling years\r\nShall come the time foretold,\r\nWhen the new heav\'n and earth shall own\r\nThe prince of Peace their King,\r\nAnd the whole world send back the song\r\nWhich now the angels sing.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'It came upon the midnight clear, That glorious song of old, From angels bending near the earth To touch their harps of gold: "Peace on the earth, goodwill to men, From heav\'n\'s all-gracous King!" The world in solemn stillness lay To hear the angels sing. Still thru the cloven skies they come With peaceful wings unfurled, And still their hev\'nly music floats O\'er all the weary world: Above its sad and lowly plains They bend on hov\'ring wing, And ever o\'er its Babel sounds The blessed angels sing. And ye, beneath life\'s crushing load, Whose forms are bending low, Who toil along the climbing way With painful steps and slow, Look now! For glad and golden hours Come swiftly on the wing: O rest beside the weary road And hear the angels sing. For lo, the days are hast\'ning on, By prophets seen of old, When with the ever circling years Shall come the time foretold, When the new heav\'n and earth shall own The prince of Peace their King, And the whole world send back the song Which now the angels sing.'),
