	(426, 'Hallelujah What A Savior!', 'Philip P. Bliss', '~Verse 1\r\nMan of Sorrows, what a name \r\nFor the Son of God who came \r\nRuined sinners to reclaim,\r\nHallelujah, what a Savior!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBearing shame and scoffing rude,\r\nIn my place condemned He stood;\r\nSealed my pardon with His blood,\r\nHallelujah, what a Savior!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGuilty vile and helpless we,\r\nSpotless Lamb of God was He;\r\nFull atonement can it be,\r\nHallelujah, what a Savior!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLifted up was He to die,\r\n"It is finished!" was His cry;\r\nNow in heaven, exalted high,\r\nHallelujah, what a Savior!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhen He comes, our glorious King,\r\nAll His ransomed home to bring;\r\nThen anew this song we\'ll sing,\r\nHallelujah, what a Savior!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Man of Sorrows, what a name For the Son of God who came Ruined sinners to reclaim, Hallelujah, what a Savior! Bearing shame and scoffing rude, In my place condemned He stood; Sealed my pardon with His blood, Hallelujah, what a Savior! Guilty vile and helpless we, Spotless Lamb of God was He; Full atonement can it be, Hallelujah, what a Savior! Lifted up was He to die, "It is finished!" was His cry; Now in heaven, exalted high, Hallelujah, what a Savior! When He comes, our glorious King, All His ransomed home to bring; Then anew this song we\'ll sing, Hallelujah, what a Savior!'),
	(427, 'Great, So Great', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGreat, So great is Your Faithfulness\r\nNever changing, Never turning,\r\n You remain.\r\nAs You were in the begining, \r\nYou are today!\r\nGreat, so great is Your faithfulness.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGreat, so great is Your faithfulness;\r\nYou forgive me; \r\nlive within me all my days.\r\nStrength today, Hope for tomorrow; \r\nall blessings mine!\r\nGreat, so great is Your faithfulness.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor each morning with mercies new,\r\nwe cry, "Thank You! Thank You!"\r\nFor each dark night \r\nYou\'ve brought us through, \r\nwe cry "Thank You! Thank You!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe cry, "Thank You," \r\nwe cry, "Thank You" \r\nfor your faithfulness!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor Your strength and Your tenderness,\r\nFor Your grace that\'s delivered us, \r\nWe cry, "Thank You," \r\nWe cry, "Thank You" \r\nfor your faithfulness!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n  \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Great, So great is Your Faithfulness Never changing, Never turning, You remain. As You were in the begining, You are today! Great, so great is Your faithfulness. Great, so great is Your faithfulness; You forgive me; live within me all my days. Strength today, Hope for tomorrow; all blessings mine! Great, so great is Your faithfulness. For each morning with mercies new, we cry, "Thank You! Thank You!" For each dark night You\'ve brought us through, we cry "Thank You! Thank You!" We cry, "Thank You," we cry, "Thank You" for your faithfulness! For Your strength and Your tenderness, For Your grace that\'s delivered us, We cry, "Thank You," We cry, "Thank You" for your faithfulness!'),
	(429, 'I Will Enter His Gates With Thanksgiving', 'Leona Von Brethorst', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will enter His gates\r\n With thanksgiving in my heart,\r\nI will enter His courts with praise.\r\nI will say this is the day\r\n That the Lord has made.\r\nI will rejoice for He has made me glad.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe has made me glad,\r\n He has made me glad,\r\nI will rejoice\r\n For He has made me glad. \r\n', '', ' 1976 Maranatha! Music   A.R.R, I.C.S, ', '', '', 'I will enter His gates With thanksgiving in my heart, I will enter His courts with praise. I will say this is the day That the Lord has made. I will rejoice for He has made me glad. He has made me glad, He has made me glad, I will rejoice For He has made me glad.'),
	(430, 'Lord, Glorify Your Name', 'Robert Hartman', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord, glorify Your name\r\nAs we lift our hands in praise,\r\nBring Your pow\'r\r\nBring Your holiness\r\n   Bring Your glory to this place.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, glorify Your Name\r\nAs we lift our hands in praise\r\nCome in pow\'r\r\nCome in holiness\r\n   Come in glory to this place.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAs we sing to You,\r\nHallelujah!\r\nWe lift our voice to You,\r\nHallelujah!\r\nLord, we sing to You,\r\nHallelujah! Hallelujah!\r\n', '', '1989 Mercy Publishing  ', '', '', 'Lord, glorify Your name As we lift our hands in praise, Bring Your pow\'r Bring Your holiness Bring Your glory to this place. Lord, glorify Your Name As we lift our hands in praise Come in pow\'r Come in holiness Come in glory to this place. As we sing to You, Hallelujah! We lift our voice to You, Hallelujah! Lord, we sing to You, Hallelujah! Hallelujah!'),
	(431, 'We Will Meet You There', 'John Chisum and Jeff Slaughter. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou have called us to Your table,\r\nLove is waiting there;\r\nSpread before us heaven\'s table,\r\nTenderly prepared.\r\nBroken there the Bread of Life;\r\nFlowing there the Healing Wine.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAll are welcome at Your table,\r\nHope is waiting there;\r\nWhosoever to Your table,\r\nFind Your tender care.\r\nBroken there the Bread of Life;\r\nFlowing there the Healing Wine.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe will meet You there\r\nAnd we\'ll find grace to help in time of need;\r\nO, we will meet You there\r\nAnd seek Your face, bowing on our knees.\r\nAnd we\'ll cry, "Holy, holy, holy!"\r\nWe will meet You there.\r\n', '', ' 1994 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'You have called us to Your table, Love is waiting there; Spread before us heaven\'s table, Tenderly prepared. Broken there the Bread of Life; Flowing there the Healing Wine. All are welcome at Your table, Hope is waiting there; Whosoever to Your table, Find Your tender care. Broken there the Bread of Life; Flowing there the Healing Wine. We will meet You there And we\'ll find grace to help in time of need; O, we will meet You there And seek Your face, bowing on our knees. And we\'ll cry, "Holy, holy, holy!" We will meet You there.'),
