	(437, 'Teach Me Lord To Wait', 'Stuart Hamblen. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nTeach me, Lord, to wait,\r\nDown on my knees,\r\n\'Til in Your own good time,\r\nYou answer my pleas.\r\nTeach me not to rely on what others do,\r\nBut to wait in prayer for an answer from You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThey that wait upon the Lord\r\nShall renew their strength.\r\nThey shall mount up with wings as eagles.\r\nThey shall run and not be weary.\r\nThey shall walk and not faint.\r\nTeach me, Lord, teach me Lord, to wait.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nTeach me, Lord, to wait,\r\nWhile hearts are aflame.\r\nLet me humble my pride,\r\nAnd call on Your name.\r\nKeep my faith renewed my eyes on Thee;\r\nLet me be on this earth,\r\nWhat You want me to be.\r\n', '', ' 1953, renewed 1981 Hamblen Music Company. ', '', '', 'Teach me, Lord, to wait, Down on my knees, \'Til in Your own good time, You answer my pleas. Teach me not to rely on what others do, But to wait in prayer for an answer from You. They that wait upon the Lord Shall renew their strength. They shall mount up with wings as eagles. They shall run and not be weary. They shall walk and not faint. Teach me, Lord, teach me Lord, to wait. Teach me, Lord, to wait, While hearts are aflame. Let me humble my pride, And call on Your name. Keep my faith renewed my eyes on Thee; Let me be on this earth, What You want me to be.'),
	(438, 'I Love You Alone', 'Kim Anthony Gentes', '~Verse 1\r\nIn Your love, You\'re tender and kind\r\nI am Yours, and You are mine\r\nYou called me child,\r\nAnd I am Yours\r\nYou\'re my Father forevermore.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI love You,\r\nI love You,\r\nI love You, alone\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIn Your love I see You so clear\r\nMake me Yours, so holy and pure,\r\nYou called me child,\r\nSo make me like You\r\nCleanse my heart and make it true.\r\n', '', '1992 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing', '', '', 'In Your love, You\\\'re tender and kind I am Yours, and You are mine You called me child, And I am Yours You\\\'re my Father forevermore. I love You, I love You, I love You, alone In Your love I see You so clear Make me Yours, so holy and pure, You called me child, So make me like You Cleanse my heart and make it true.'),
