	(456, 'I Will Remember', 'Cameron Graham. Copyright Unknown.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe are gathered in this place\r\nWith broken hearts to say farewell.\r\nAnd everyone in their own way\r\nCan feel the tears begin to swell.\r\nFor the life we celebrate today\r\nLeft a mark on me that\'s here to stay,\r\nAnd I know I\'ll never be the same again.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI don\'t want to say goodbye\r\nThis parting\'s not forever.\r\nSome day I\'ll meet you in the sky\r\nAnd then we\'ll always be together.\r\nUntil then I\'ll remember\r\nWhen you were here in my arms,\r\nYes, I will remember\r\nWhen you were here in my arms.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou were always so strong,\r\nYou were always so brave.\r\nYou encouraged my heart,\r\nWith the love that you freely gave.\r\nFor everyone in your path\r\nEvery person you touched\r\nEvery life that you changed,\r\nWants to tell you how much.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe don\'t want to say goodbye.\r\nThis partings not forever.\r\nSome day we\'ll meet you in the sky\r\nAnd then we\'ll always be together.\r\nUntil then we\'ll remember\r\nWhen you were here in our arms\r\nAnd how you held us\r\nSafe from all earthly harm.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd what today we\'ve lost\r\nOn that day we\'ll find.\r\nAnd although now we cry,\r\nThis is not goodbye.\r\nFor by the grace of God,\r\nI\'ll see you in the sky.\r\nBy the grace of God,\r\nI\'ll see you in the sky.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'We are gathered in this place With broken hearts to say farewell. And everyone in their own way Can feel the tears begin to swell. For the life we celebrate today Left a mark on me that\'s here to stay, And I know I\'ll never be the same again. I don\'t want to say goodbye This parting\'s not forever. Some day I\'ll meet you in the sky And then we\'ll always be together. Until then I\'ll remember When you were here in my arms, Yes, I will remember When you were here in my arms. You were always so strong, You were always so brave. You encouraged my heart, With the love that you freely gave. For everyone in your path Every person you touched Every life that you changed, Wants to tell you how much. We don\'t want to say goodbye. This partings not forever. Some day we\'ll meet you in the sky And then we\'ll always be together. Until then we\'ll remember When you were here in our arms And how you held us Safe from all earthly harm. And what today we\'ve lost On that day we\'ll find. And although now we cry, This is not goodbye. For by the grace of God, I\'ll see you in the sky. By the grace of God, I\'ll see you in the sky.'),
	(457, 'Come Bless The Lord (All Ye Servants)', 'Phil Johnston. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome bless the Lord\r\nAll ye servants of the Lord\r\nWho stand by might in the house of the Lord.\r\nLift up your heads in the holy place\r\nAnd bless the Lord, and bless the Lord.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1975 Thankyou Music', '', '', 'Come bless the Lord All ye servants of the Lord Who stand by might in the house of the Lord. Lift up your heads in the holy place And bless the Lord, and bless the Lord.'),
	(458, 'Blessed Be The Lord God Almighty', 'Bob Fitts  C. 1986 Scripture in Song(Adm. by ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFather in heaven, how we love You\r\nWe lift Your name in all the earth\r\nMay Your kingdom be established \r\nIn our praises\r\nAs your people declare \r\nYour mighty works.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd I will lift Your name on high\r\nI choose to lift Your name on high\r\nI lift Your name like a banner in the sky\r\nI will lift Your name on high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBlessed be the Lord God Almighty\r\nWho was and is - and is to come\r\nBlessed be the Lord God Almighty\r\nWho reigns forever more\r\n', '', ' 1986 Scripture in Song(Adm. by ', '', '', 'Father in heaven, how we love You We lift Your name in all the earth May Your kingdom be established In our praises As your people declare Your mighty works. And I will lift Your name on high I choose to lift Your name on high I lift Your name like a banner in the sky I will lift Your name on high. Blessed be the Lord God Almighty Who was and is - and is to come Blessed be the Lord God Almighty Who reigns forever more'),
	(459, 'Song Of Surrender', 'Jeff Searles.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou died for me, Jesus you died for me\r\nYou died for me, Jesus my Lord,\r\n	 You died for me\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHow can it be\r\n That you\'ve called me your own\r\nSuch mercy and grace I have never known\r\nI\'ve lived a life of turning from you\r\nBut still you call me home again to you\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe rejoice in you, we know true joy in you\r\nJesus we rejoice in you\r\nOur hearts are filled with love\r\n And affection for you\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nYou live in me, Jesus you live in me\r\nYou live in me\r\nSuch wonderful love\r\n That you would live in me\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI love you Lord, \r\nI love you Lord,\r\nI love you Lord,\r\nThis is my song of surrender unto you\r\nLive in us today Lord and never go away.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Mercy/Vineyeard Publishing.  Words by Jeff Searles.', '', '', 'You died for me, Jesus you died for me You died for me, Jesus my Lord, You died for me How can it be That you\'ve called me your own Such mercy and grace I have never known I\'ve lived a life of turning from you But still you call me home again to you We rejoice in you, we know true joy in you Jesus we rejoice in you Our hearts are filled with love And affection for you You live in me, Jesus you live in me You live in me Such wonderful love That you would live in me I love you Lord, I love you Lord, I love you Lord, This is my song of surrender unto you Live in us today Lord and never go away.'),
