	(486, 'Once Again', 'Matt Redman', '~Intro\r\n[D] [A/D] [G/D] [D]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[D]Jesus [A]Christ, I thi[G]nk upon Your sacrific[D]e\r\n[G]You became no[D/F#]thing, po[G]ured out to death[A]\r\n[D]Many ti[A]mes I\'ve wo[G]ndered at Your gift [D]of life\r\nAnd [G]I\'m in that pl[A]ace once again[D]\r\n[G]I\'m in that pl[A]ace once again[D]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[D/F#]And once again I [G]look upon the [D/F#]cross where You died[A]\r\nI\'m h[D]umbled by Your mercy and I\'m br[G]oken inside[A]\r\n[Bm7]Once again I th[G]ank You\r\n[D/F#]Once again I p[A]our out my life[G] [Asus] [A]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[D]Now You [A]are exalted[G] to the highest [D]place\r\n[G]King of [D]the heavens, where [G]one day I\'ll [A]bow\r\n[D]But for [A]now, I ma[G]rvel at Your sa[D]ving grace\r\nAnd [G]I\'m full of pr[A]aise once again[D]\r\n[G]I\'m full of pra[A]ise once again[D]\r\n~Tag\r\n[G]Thank You for the cr[A]oss\r\n[D/F#]Thank You for the cr[D]oss\r\n[G]Thank You for the cr[A]oss, my Fr[D]iend\r\n\r\n', '', '1995 Kingsways ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/FkK4YHy-wNg', '', 'Jesus Christ, I think upon Your sacrifice You became nothing, poured out to death Many times I\'ve wondered at Your gift of life And I\'m in that place once again I\'m in that place once again And once again I look upon the cross where You died I\'m humbled by Your mercy and I\'m broken inside Once again I thank You Once again I pour out my life Now You are exalted to the highest place King of the heavens, where one day I\'ll bow But for now, I marvel at Your saving grace And I\'m full of praise once again I\'m full of praise once again Thank You for the cross Thank You for the cross Thank You for the cross, my Friend'),
	(487, 'We Want To See Jesus Lifted High', 'Doug Horley ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe want to see Jesus lifted high,\r\nA banner that flies across this land,\r\nThat all men might see the truth \r\nand know\r\nHe is the way to heaven.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe\'re gonna see, we\'re gonna see,\r\nWe\'re gonna see Jesus lifted high.\r\nWe\'re gonna see, we\'re gonna see,\r\nWe\'re gonna see Jesus lifted high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe want to see, we want to see, \r\nwe want to see Jesus lifted high.\r\nWe want to see, we want to see, \r\nwe want to see Jesus lifted high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nStep by step we\'re moving forward,\r\nLittle by little we\'re taking ground\r\nEvery prayer a powerful weapon, \r\nStrongholds come tumbling down,\r\n and down, and down, and down.\r\n', '', ' 1993 Kingsway\'s Thankyou Music/Administered in N.A. by EMI Christian Music Publishing/P.O. Box 5085', '', '', 'We want to see Jesus lifted high, A banner that flies across this land, That all men might see the truth and know He is the way to heaven. We\'re gonna see, we\'re gonna see, We\'re gonna see Jesus lifted high. We\'re gonna see, we\'re gonna see, We\'re gonna see Jesus lifted high. We want to see, we want to see, we want to see Jesus lifted high. We want to see, we want to see, we want to see Jesus lifted high. Step by step we\'re moving forward, Little by little we\'re taking ground Every prayer a powerful weapon, Strongholds come tumbling down, and down, and down, and down.'),
	(488, 'Let The Heavens Rejoice', 'Don Harris and Martin J. Nystrom', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAll of creation is boldly proclaiming\r\nThe wonderful things He has done;\r\nLet\'s join with all nations\r\nIn one declaration,\r\nProclaiming the goodness of God.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet the heavens rejoice\r\nAnd the earth be glad,\r\nLet the seas resound\r\nWith a mighty roar;\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe heavens above\r\nAre declaring His splendor,\r\nHis power cannot be denied;\r\nFor all of creation is loudly confessing\r\nThat Jesus, our Lord, is alive.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLet the trees of the forest\r\nClap their hands,\r\nLet the earth be filled\r\nWith the glory of the Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1993 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music  ', '', '', 'All of creation is boldly proclaiming The wonderful things He has done; Let\'s join with all nations In one declaration, Proclaiming the goodness of God. Let the heavens rejoice And the earth be glad, Let the seas resound With a mighty roar; The heavens above Are declaring His splendor, His power cannot be denied; For all of creation is loudly confessing That Jesus, our Lord, is alive. Let the trees of the forest Clap their hands, Let the earth be filled With the glory of the Lord.'),
	(489, 'O For A Thousand Tongues (Hymn #76)', '', '~Verse 1\r\nO [D]for a [A]thousand [D]tongues to sing my great re[G]deemers [A]praise,\r\nThe [D]glories of my [G]God and King, the [D]triumphs of [A]His [D]grace.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[D]My gracious [A]master [D]and my God assist me [G]to procl[A]aim,\r\nTo [D]spread thro\' all the [G]earth abroad the [D]honors of [A]thy [D]name.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus the name that charms our fears, that bids our sorrows cease,\r\n\'Tis music to the sinner\'s ear, \'tis life and health and peace.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe breaks the power of canceled sin, He sets the prisoner free,\r\nHis blood can make the foulest clean, His blood availed for me.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHear Him ye deaf, His praise ye dumb, your loosened tongues employ,\r\nYe blind behold your Savior come, and leap ye lame for joy.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'O for a thousand tongues to sing my great redeemers praise, The glories of my God and King, the triumphs of His grace. My gracious master and my God assist me to proclaim, To spread thro\' all the earth abroad the honors of thy name. Jesus the name that charms our fears, that bids our sorrows cease, \'Tis music to the sinner\'s ear, \'tis life and health and peace. He breaks the power of canceled sin, He sets the prisoner free, His blood can make the foulest clean, His blood availed for me. Hear Him ye deaf, His praise ye dumb, your loosened tongues employ, Ye blind behold your Savior come, and leap ye lame for joy.'),
	(490, 'Today (As For Me And My House)', 'Brian Doerksen & Sandra Gage', '~Verse\r\nToday I choose to follow You\r\nToday I choose to give my \'yes\' to You\r\nToday I choose to hear \r\nYour voice and live\r\nToday I choose to follow You\r\n~Chorus\r\nAs for me and my house\r\nWe will serve You\r\nAs for me and my house\r\nWe will spend our lives on You today\r\n~Bridge\r\nWonderful Counselor\r\nEverlasting Father\r\nEternal King, Lord of Hosts\r\nWillingly we follow\r\n\r\n   \r\n', '', '2003 Integrity\'s Hosanna!', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/rSOQQVvHwJI', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Today I choose to follow You Today I choose to give my \'yes\' to You Today I choose to hear Your voice and live Today I choose to follow You As for me and my house We will serve You As for me and my house We will spend our lives on You today Wonderful Counselor Everlasting Father Eternal King, Lord of Hosts Willingly we follow).'),
	(491, 'I Will Celebrate (with My Heart Rejoicing)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWith my heart rejoicing within\r\nWith my mind focused on Him\r\nWith my hands raised to the heavens\r\nAll I am worshipping Him.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will celebrate, sing unto the Lord\r\nSing to the Lord a new song\r\nI will celebrate, sing unto the Lord\r\nSing to the Lord a new song.\r\n', '', ' 1990 And This Arr. C. 1997', '', '', 'With my heart rejoicing within With my mind focused on Him With my hands raised to the heavens All I am worshipping Him. I will celebrate, sing unto the Lord Sing to the Lord a new song I will celebrate, sing unto the Lord Sing to the Lord a new song.'),
	(492, 'While Shepherds Watched Their Flocks By Night', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n"Fear not!" said he; for mighty dread\r\nHad seized their troubled mind,\r\n"Glad tidings of great joy I bring\r\nTo you and all man-kind,\r\nTo you and all man-kind."\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhile shepherds watched\r\nTheir flocks by night,\r\nAll seated on the ground,\r\nThe angel of the Lord came down,\r\nAnd glory shone around,\r\nAnd glory shone around.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n"To you, in David\'s town this day,\r\nIs born of David\'s line,\r\nThe Savior who is Christ the Lord,\r\nAnd this shall be the sign:\r\nAnd this shall be the sign."\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n"The heav\'nly Babe you there shall find\r\nTo human view displayed,\r\nAll meanly wrapped in swathing bands,\r\nAnd in a manger laid;\r\n   And in a manger laid."\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n"All glory be to God on high,\r\nAnd to the earth be peace:\r\nGood will henceforth from heav\'n to men,\r\nBegin and never cease,\r\nBegin and never cease."\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', '"Fear not!" said he; for mighty dread Had seized their troubled mind, "Glad tidings of great joy I bring To you and all man-kind, To you and all man-kind." While shepherds watched Their flocks by night, All seated on the ground, The angel of the Lord came down, And glory shone around, And glory shone around. "To you, in David\'s town this day, Is born of David\'s line, The Savior who is Christ the Lord, And this shall be the sign: And this shall be the sign." "The heav\'nly Babe you there shall find To human view displayed, All meanly wrapped in swathing bands, And in a manger laid; And in a manger laid." "All glory be to God on high, And to the earth be peace: Good will henceforth from heav\'n to men, Begin and never cease, Begin and never cease."'),
	(493, 'O Little Town Of Bethlehem (Hymn #141)', '', '~Verse 1\r\nO [F]little [Fdim]town of [C]Bethle[Gm]hem, how [F]still we [C7]see Thee [F]lie!\r\nA[F]bove thy [D7]deep and [Gm]dreamless sleep the [F]silent [C7]stars go [F]by.\r\nYet [F]in thy [Gm]dark streets [A]shineth the [Dm]everlasting [A]light;\r\nThe [F]hopes and [Fdim]fears of [C]all the [Gm]years are [F]met in [C7]Thee t[F]onight.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFor Christ is born of Mary; and gathered all above,\r\nWhile mortals sleep, the angels keep their watch of wondering love.\r\nO morning stars together proclaim the holy birth,\r\nand praises sing to God the King, and peace to men on earth.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHow silently, how silently the wondrous gift is given!\r\nSo God imparts to human hearts the blessings of His heaven.\r\nNo ear may hear His coming but in this world of sin,\r\nWhere meek souls will receive him still, the dear Christ enters in.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO holy child of Bethlehem, descend to us, we pray;\r\nCast out our sin and enter in, be born in us today.\r\nWe hear the Christmas angels, the great glad tiding tell,\r\nO come to us, abide with us, our Lord Emmanuel.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'O little town of Bethlehem, how still we see Thee lie! Above thy deep and dreamless sleep the silent stars go by. Yet in thy dark streets shineth the everlasting light; The hopes and fears of all the years are met in Thee tonight. For Christ is born of Mary; and gathered all above, While mortals sleep, the angels keep their watch of wondering love. O morning stars together proclaim the holy birth, and praises sing to God the King, and peace to men on earth. How silently, how silently the wondrous gift is given! So God imparts to human hearts the blessings of His heaven. No ear may hear His coming but in this world of sin, Where meek souls will receive him still, the dear Christ enters in. O holy child of Bethlehem, descend to us, we pray; Cast out our sin and enter in, be born in us today. We hear the Christmas angels, the great glad tiding tell, O come to us, abide with us, our Lord Emmanuel.'),
	(494, 'They That Wait Upon The Lord', 'Stuart Hamblen', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThey that wait upon the Lord \r\nShall renew their strength;\r\nThey shall mount up with wings like eagles;\r\nThey shall run and not be weary; \r\nThey shall walk and not faint.\r\nTeach me Lord; teach me Lord, to wait.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'They that wait upon the Lord Shall renew their strength; They shall mount up with wings like eagles; They shall run and not be weary; They shall walk and not faint. Teach me Lord; teach me Lord, to wait.'),
	(495, 'Glory In The Highest', 'Chris Tomlin, Ed Cash, Matt Redman, Jesse Reeves and Daniel Carson. ', '~Verse 1\r\nYou are the first, You go before,\r\nYou are the last, Lord You\'re the encore.\r\nYour name\'s in lights for all to see,\r\nThe starry host declare Your glory.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nApart from You there is no God,\r\nLight of the world,\r\nThe bright and morning star.\r\nYour name will shine for all to see,\r\nYou are the one, You are my glory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlory in the highest,\r\nGlory in the highest,\r\nGlory in the highest.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd no one else could ever compare\r\nTo You, Lord\r\nAll the earth together declare:\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGlory in the highest,\r\nGlory in the highest,\r\nGlory in the highest,\r\nTo You Lord, to You Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAll the earth will sing Your praise,\r\nThe moon and stars, the sun and rain.\r\nEvery nation will proclaim,\r\nThat You are God and You will ransom.\r\nGlory, glory Hallelujah,\r\nGlory, glory to You Lord.\r\nGlory, glory Hallelujah, Hallelujah.\r\n', '', ' 2006 sixsteps Music/worshiptogether.com Songs (admin. by EMI CMG Publishing) (ASCAP)/Alletrop Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/C8X6trgQtIo', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=208528708&id=208528692&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Chris Tomlin - Double Take: Chris Tomlin - Glory In the Highest" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', '.mysql_real_escape_string(You are the first, You go before, You are the last, Lord You\'re the encore. Your name\'s in lights for all to see, The starry host declare Your glory. Apart from You there is no God, Light of the world, The bright and morning star. Your name will shine for all to see, You are the one, You are my glory. Glory in the highest, Glory in the highest, Glory in the highest. And no one else could ever compare To You, Lord All the earth together declare: Glory in the highest, Glory in the hig