	(504, 'Angels From The Realms Of Glory', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAngels, from the realms of glory,\r\nWing your flight o\'er all the earth;\r\nYe who sang creation\'s story,\r\nNow proclaim Messiah\'s birth:\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nShepherds, in the fields abiding,\r\nWatching o\'er your flocks by night,\r\nGod with man is now residing,\r\nYonder shines the infant Light:\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSages, leave your contemplations,\r\nBrighter visions beam afar;\r\nSeek the great Desire of nations,\r\nYe have seen His natal star:\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSaints before the altar bending,\r\nWatching long in hope and fear,\r\nSuddenly the Lord, descending,\r\nIn His temple shall appear:\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCome and worship, \r\nCome and worship,\r\nWorship Christ, the newborn King.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Angels, from the realms of glory, Wing your flight o\'er all the earth; Ye who sang creation\'s story, Now proclaim Messiah\'s birth: Shepherds, in the fields abiding, Watching o\'er your flocks by night, God with man is now residing, Yonder shines the infant Light: Sages, leave your contemplations, Brighter visions beam afar; Seek the great Desire of nations, Ye have seen His natal star: Saints before the altar bending, Watching long in hope and fear, Suddenly the Lord, descending, In His temple shall appear: Come and worship, Come and worship, Worship Christ, the newborn King.'),
	(505, 'I Bow Down', 'Joel Engle', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, I stand in Your presence\r\nBroken before You\r\nAnd my heart\'s desire\r\nIs to love and adore You\r\nWith all of my heart,\r\nWith all of my soul forever\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI bow down at Your feet\r\nI bow down at Your feet\r\nBow down and worship You, Jesus\r\nMy Savior, my King\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, I fall at Your altar\r\nIn sweet surrender\r\nAnd I\'ve never known \r\na mercy so tender\r\nIt\'s healing my heart,\r\nIt\'s healing my soul forever\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBow down and worship You, Jesus\r\nBow down and worship You, Jesus\r\nI bow down, I bow down\r\nLord, I bow down\r\nBow down to worship You, Jesus           \r\n', '', '1998 Spin Sixty-Three Music', '', '', 'Lord, I stand in Your presence Broken before You And my heart\\\'s desire Is to love and adore You With all of my heart, With all of my soul forever I bow down at Your feet I bow down at Your feet Bow down and worship You, Jesus My Savior, my King Lord, I fall at Your altar In sweet surrender And I\\\'ve never known a mercy so tender It\\\'s healing my heart, It\\\'s healing my soul forever Bow down and worship You, Jesus Bow down and worship You, Jesus I bow down, I bow down Lord, I bow down Bow down to worship You, Jesus'),
	(506, 'Hosanna (Praise is rising)', 'Paul Baloche', '~Intro\r\n[G5]                                    \r\n\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[G5]Praise is rising, eyes are turning to Y[C2]ou, we turn to Yo[G5]u\r\nHope is stirring, hearts are yearning for Yo[C2]u, we long for You[G5]\r\n\'Cause when we se[D(add4)]e You, we find strengt[C]h to face the da[G5]y\r\nIn Your Pre[D(add4)]s-ence all our fears [C]are washed awa[G5]y, washed awa[Dsus]y\r\n~Chorus:\r\nH[Gsus]o--san[G]--[Em7]na, ho[C2]--sanna\r\nYou are the Go[G5]d Who saves us,[Dsus] worthy of al[Em7]l our prai[C2]ses\r\nH[Gsus]o--san[G]--[Em7]na, ho[C2]--sanna\r\nCome have Your wa[G5]y among u[Dsus]s\r\nWe welcome You her[Em7]e, Lord Jesu[C2]s\r\n', '', '2006 Integrity\'s', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/TY4BWbvxEXQ&hl=en&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/hosanna/id294954575?i=294954781&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Paul Baloche - A Greater Song - Hosanna" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Praise is rising, eyes are turning to You, we turn to You Hope is stirring, hearts are yearning for You, we long for You \\\'Cause when we see You, we find strength to face the day In Your Pres-ence all our fears are washed away, washed away Ho--san--na, ho--sanna You are the God Who saves us, worthy of all our praises Ho--san--na, ho--sanna Come have Your way among us We welcome You here, Lord Jesus'),
	(508, 'You Are Holy', 'Scott Wesley Brown; c. 1995 Integrity\'s ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are holy, O Lord, so holy;\r\nYou are holy, O Lord, so holy.\r\nWhat a privilege and an honor\r\n to worship at Your throne;\r\nTo be called into Your presence \r\n	 as Your own.\r\n\r\nWords and Music by Scott Wesley Brown; c. 1995 Integrity\'s \r\nHosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc., P.O. Box 851622, \r\nMobile, AL  36685-1622; ARR, ICS; UBP; CCLI#218004103\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou are worthy, O Lord,  so worthy\r\nYou are worthy, O Lord,  so worthy\r\nWhat a privilege and an honor\r\n to worship at Your throne;\r\nTo be called into Your presence \r\n	 as Your own.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are faithful, O Lord, so faithful\r\nYou are faithful, O Lord, so faithful\r\nWhat a privilege and an honor\r\n to worship at Your throne;\r\nTo be called into Your presence \r\n	 as Your own.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Integrity\'s ', '', '', 'You are holy, O Lord, so holy; You are holy, O Lord, so holy. What a privilege and an honor to worship at Your throne; To be called into Your presence as Your own. Words and Music by Scott Wesley Brown; c. 1995 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc., P.O. Box 851622, Mobile, AL  36685-1622; ARR, ICS; UBP; CCLI#218004103 You are worthy, O Lord,  so worthy You are worthy, O Lord,  so worthy What a privilege and an honor to worship at Your throne; To be called into Your presence as Your own. You are faithful, O Lord, so faithful You are faithful, O Lord, so faithful What a privilege and an honor to worship at Your throne; To be called into Your presence as Your own.'),
