	(510, 'Come Ye Sinners Poor And Needy', 'Joseph Hart; refrain, source unknown', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, ye sinners, poor and needy,\r\nWeak and wounded, sick and sore;\r\nJesus ready stands to save you,\r\nFull of pity, love and power.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nCome, ye thirsty, come and welcome,\r\nGod\'s free bounty glorify;\r\nTrue belief and true repentance,\r\nEvery grace that brings you nigh.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet not conscience make you linger,\r\nNor of fitness fondly dream;\r\nAll the fitness He requireth\r\nIs to feel your need of Him.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome, ye weary, heavy laden,\r\nLost and ruined by the fall;\r\nIf you tarry till you\'re better,\r\nYou will never come at all.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI will arise and go to Jesus,\r\nHe will embrace me in His arms;\r\nIn the arms of my dear Savior,\r\nO, there are ten thousand charms.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, ye sinners, poor and needy, Weak and wounded, sick and sore; Jesus ready stands to save you, Full of pity, love and power. Come, ye thirsty, come and welcome, God\'s free bounty glorify; True belief and true repentance, Every grace that brings you nigh. Let not conscience make you linger, Nor of fitness fondly dream; All the fitness He requireth Is to feel your need of Him. Come, ye weary, heavy laden, Lost and ruined by the fall; If you tarry till you\'re better, You will never come at all. I will arise and go to Jesus, He will embrace me in His arms; In the arms of my dear Savior, O, there are ten thousand charms.'),
	(512, 'Jesus Your Name', 'Morris Chapman and Claire Cloninger.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus, Your name is power,\r\nJesus, Your name is might.\r\nJesus, Your name\r\nWill break every stronghold;\r\nJesus, Your name is life.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJesus, Your name is healing,\r\nJesus, Your name gives sight.\r\nJesus, Your name will free every captive;\r\nJesus, Your name is life.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, Your name is holy,\r\nJesus, Your name brings light.\r\nJesus, Your name above every other;\r\nJesus, Your name is life.\r\n', '', ' 1990 Maranatha Praise, Inc./Word Music, LLC. ', '', '', 'Jesus, Your name is power, Jesus, Your name is might. Jesus, Your name Will break every stronghold; Jesus, Your name is life. Jesus, Your name is healing, Jesus, Your name gives sight. Jesus, Your name will free every captive; Jesus, Your name is life. Jesus, Your name is holy, Jesus, Your name brings light. Jesus, Your name above every other; Jesus, Your name is life.'),
	(513, 'In Moments Like These', 'David Graham', '~Verse\r\nIn [D]moments like [Bm]these\r\nI [G]sing out a [A]song\r\nI [G]sing out a [A]song to [D]Je-[A]sus\r\nIn [D]moments like [Bm]these\r\nI [G]lift up my [A]hands\r\nI [G]lift up my [A]hands to the [D]Lord\r\n~Chorus\r\nSinging, [G]I  [A]love You [D]Lord\r\nSinging, [G]I  [A]love You [D]Lord\r\nSinging, [G]I  [F#m]love [Bm]You  [G]Lord\r\nOh, [D]I  [A]love You [D]Lord\r\n~Tag\r\nSinging, [G]I  [F#m]love [Bm]You  [G]Lord\r\nO, [D]I  [A]love You [D]Lord\r\n', '', 'A. Music USA  (A div. of Christian Artist Corp.)', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/sDOM6mxyXik&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'In moments like these I sing out a song I sing out a song to Je-sus In moments like these I lift up my hands I lift up my hands to the Lord Singing, I  love You Lord Singing, I  love You Lord Singing, I  love You  Lord Oh, I  love You Lord Singing, I  love You  Lord O, I  love You Lord'),
	(514, 'I Surrender All (Harlos)', 'Kim Harlos. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus, I\'m waiting\r\nTo hear Your voice calling me\r\nJesus, I\'m waiting\r\nTo take Your hand to be guided\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd Jesus, You\'re probably waiting for\r\nme to hear Your voice calling me\r\nAnd Jesus, You\'re probably waiting for\r\nme to take Your hand to be guided\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI surrender all of me\r\nI believe that You gave your life for me\r\nI will live my life for You\r\nO, I surrender all\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThank you, Lord, for waiting patiently\r\nFor me to respond, hear Your voice\r\nThank you, Lord, for waiting patiently\r\nFor me to respond, take Your hand\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHallelujah to the King of kings\r\nI praise You, Lord, and give You everything\r\nI lift my hands up to heaven\'s skies\r\nAnd pray that You are glorified\r\n', '', ' 2007 Kim Harlos.', '', '', 'Jesus, I\'m waiting To hear Your voice calling me Jesus, I\'m waiting To take Your hand to be guided And Jesus, You\'re probably waiting for me to hear Your voice calling me And Jesus, You\'re probably waiting for me to take Your hand to be guided I surrender all of me I believe that You gave your life for me I will live my life for You O, I surrender all Thank you, Lord, for waiting patiently For me to respond, hear Your voice Thank you, Lord, for waiting patiently For me to respond, take Your hand Hallelujah to the King of kings I praise You, Lord, and give You everything I lift my hands up to heaven\'s skies And pray that You are glorified'),
	(515, 'Transformed By Your Love', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAs I look into Your face\r\nI behold Your precious love for me.\r\nAs I gaze into Your eyes\r\nI understand now that You died for me.\r\nAnd You speak with words filled with grace,\r\nAs I worship You on my face.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThings that used to catch my eye\r\nDon\'t attract me anymore,\r\nLife goals have changed.\r\nMy heart that once lay cold\r\nIs warming as I feel Your love for me.\r\nAnd as I ponder Calvary\'s tree,\r\nAnd think that "You died for me!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI\'m being transfored by Your love,\r\nIt\'s renewing every part of my soul.\r\nI\'m being transformed by Your love,\r\nNever to be the same,\r\nMy heart is being changed by Your love.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'As I look into Your face I behold Your precious love for me. As I gaze into Your eyes I understand now that You died for me. And You speak with words filled with grace, As I worship You on my face. Things that used to catch my eye Don\'t attract me anymore, Life goals have changed. My heart that once lay cold Is warming as I feel Your love for me. And as I ponder Calvary\'s tree, And think that "You died for me!" I\'m being transfored by Your love, It\'s renewing every part of my soul. I\'m being transformed by Your love, Never to be the same, My heart is being changed by Your love.'),
	(516, 'I Will Sing I Will Sing', 'Max Dyer', '~Verse 1\r\nI will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord.\r\nI will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord.\r\nI will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord.\r\nAlleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe will come,\r\nWe will come as one before the Lord.\r\nWe will come,\r\nWe will come as one before the Lord.\r\nWe will come,\r\nWe will come as one before the Lord.\r\nAlleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIf the Son, if the Son shall make you free,\r\nIf the Son, if the Son shall make you free,\r\nIf the Son, if the Son shall make you free,\r\nYou shall be free indeed.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThey that sow in tears shall reep in joy.\r\nThey that sow in tears shall reep in joy.\r\nThey that sow in tears shall reep in joy.\r\nAlleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nEvery knee shall bow\r\nAnd every tongue confess\r\nEvery knee shall bow\r\nAnd every tongue confess\r\nEvery knee shall bow\r\nAnd every tongue confess\r\nThat Jesus Christ is Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nIn His name,\r\nIn His name we have the victory.\r\nIn His name,\r\nIn His name we have the victory.\r\nIn His name,\r\nIn His name we have the victory.\r\nAlleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAllelu, alleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\nAllelu, alleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\nAllelu, alleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\nAlleluia, glory to the Lord.\r\n', '', '1974, 1975 Celebration', '', '', 'I will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord. I will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord. I will sing, I will sing a song unto the Lord. Alleluia, glory to the Lord. We will come, We will come as one before the Lord. We will come, We will come as one before the Lord. We will come, We will come as one before the Lord. Alleluia, glory to the Lord. If the Son, if the Son shall make you free, If the Son, if the Son shall make you free, If the Son, if the Son shall make you free, You shall be free indeed. They that sow in tears shall reep in joy.