	(523, 'The Joy Of The Lord', 'Allience G. Vale', '~Verse 1\r\nThe joy of the Lord is my strength;\r\n(repeat 3x)\r\nThe joy of the Lord is my strength.\r\nHe gives me living water \r\nand I thirst no more;\r\n(repeat 3x)\r\nThe joy of the Lord is my strength.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe fills my mouth with laughter,\r\nHa, ha, ha, ha, ha  (repeat 3x)\r\nThe joy of the Lord is my strength.\r\n', '', '1971 His Eye Music', '', '', 'The joy of the Lord is my strength; (repeat 3x) The joy of the Lord is my strength. He gives me living water and I thirst no more; (repeat 3x) The joy of the Lord is my strength. He fills my mouth with laughter, Ha, ha, ha, ha, ha  (repeat 3x) The joy of the Lord is my strength.'),
	(524, 'First Love', ' Paul Baloche and Gary Sadler', '~Verse 1\r\nLike a candle st[G]ir the flame         [G]\r\nLet the sword of[G] Your word tears my heart again                   [C9]\r\nHoly Spirit movi[G]ng me             [Em]\r\n[C9]Draw me close to your heart\r\n[D]Where I need to be\r\n~Chorus\r\nFirst love [G]Jesus m[C9]y Savior\r\n[G]My one d[D]esire to love You more\r\nFirst love [G]Lord ma[C9]ke me faithful\r\n[Em]I want You always to be my first [D]love....', '', ' 1998, Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music ', '', '', 'Like a candle stir the flame Let the sword of Your word tears my heart again Holy Spirit moving me Draw me close to your heart Where I need to be First love Jesus my Savior My one desire to love You more First love Lord make me faithful I want You always to be my first love....'),
	(525, 'Glory, Glory Lord', 'Bob Fitts', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou who go down to the sea,\r\nYou who live in the islands;\r\nIf you live in the city,\r\nLift your voice and sing out.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nWe give You glory, Lord;\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSing to the Lord a new song;\r\nSing His praise to the ends of the earth;\r\nLet ev\'ry nation tell it,\r\nTill ev\'ry man has heard.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nWe give You glory, Lord;\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\nYou are the living God,\r\nYou are the only God,\r\nYou are the mighty God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nNa-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah,\r\nI Nou Ka-na-ni le-jo-vah;\r\nNa-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah,\r\nKe A-Ku-a-Ma-na Lo-a.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nVi-i-a, Vi-i-a le atu-a,\r\nMa-tou te vi-ia oe le atu-a;\r\nVi-i-a, vi-i-a le atu-a O\r\nOele Atu-a ma-ta-u-ti-a.\r\n', '', ' 1990 Scripture in Song/Adm. Maranatha! Music', '', '', 'You who go down to the sea, You who live in the islands; If you live in the city, Lift your voice and sing out. Glory, glory Lord, We give You glory, Lord; Glory, glory Lord, You are the mighty God, You are the mighty God, Sing to the Lord a new song; Sing His praise to the ends of the earth; Let ev\'ry nation tell it, Till ev\'ry man has heard. Glory, glory Lord, We give You glory, Lord; Glory, glory Lord, You are the mighty God, You are the living God, You are the only God, You are the mighty God. Na-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah, I Nou Ka-na-ni le-jo-vah; Na-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah, Ke A-Ku-a-Ma-na Lo-a. Vi-i-a, Vi-i-a le atu-a, Ma-tou te vi-ia oe le atu-a; Vi-i-a, vi-i-a le atu-a O Oele Atu-a ma-ta-u-ti-a.'),
	(526, 'Unending Love', 'John Barnett  ', '~Verse 1\r\n[E]Father, I come to you, lifting up my hands,\r\n[E/A]In the name of Jesus, [E]by your grace I stand.\r\n[B7]Just because you love me, [C#m7]and I l[B6]ove your [A]Son,\r\nI know your [E]favor[A]--un[B]ending l[E]ove.\r\n[A]Une[B]nding [C#m]love, [G#m]  your [A]une[B]nding l[E]ove.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[E]I receive your favor--your unending love;\r\n[E/A]Not because I\'ve earned it, [E]not for what I\'ve done;\r\n[B7]Just because you love me, [C#m7]and I l[B6]ove your S[A]on,\r\nI know your [E]favor[A]--une[B]nding l[E]ove.\r\n[A]Une[B]nding [C#m]love, [G#m]  your [A]une[B]nding l[E]ove.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt\'s the p[E]resence of your kingdom as your glory fills this place,\r\nAnd I [E/A]see how much you love me as I l[E]ook into your face.\r\n[B7]Nothing could be better, there\'s [C#m7]nothing [B6]I would [A]trade\r\nFor your [E]favor[A]--une[B]nding l[E]ove.\r\n[A]Une[B]nding [C#m]love, [G#m]  your [A]une[B]nding l[E]ove.\r\n', '', '1989 Mercy  Publishing', '', '', 'Father, I come to you, lifting up my hands, In the name of Jesus, by your grace I stand. Just because you love me, and I love your Son, I know your favor--unending love. Unending love,   your unending love. I receive your favor--your unending love; Not because I\'ve earned it, not for what I\'ve done; Just because you love me, and I love your Son, I know your favor--unending love. Unending love,   your unending love. It\'s the presence of your kingdom as your glory fills this place, And I see how much you love me as I look into your face. Nothing could be better, there\'s nothing I would trade For your favor--unending love. Unending love,   your unending love.'),
	(527, 'This Is The Day That The Lord Hath Made', 'Les Garrett. ', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]This is the day, this is the day\r\nThat the [D]Lord hath made, that the Lord hath made.\r\nWe will rejoice, we will rejoice\r\nand be [G]glad in it, and be glad in it.\r\n[C]This is the day that the [G]Lord hath made,\r\n[C]We will rejoice and be [G]glad in it,\r\n~Chorus\r\nThis is the day, this is the day that the Lord has made,\r\nThat the Lord [D7]hath [G]made.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThis is the day, this is the day\r\nWhen He rose again, when He rose again;\r\nWe will rejoice, we will rejoice\r\nand be glad in it, and be glad in it.\r\nThis is the day when He rose again,\r\nWe will rejoice and be glad in it.\r\nThis is the day, this is the day\r\nWhen He rose again.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThis is the day, this is the day\r\nWhen the Spirit came, when the Spirit came.\r\nWe will rejoice, we will rejoice\r\nand be glad in it, and be glad in it.\r\nThis is the day when the Spirit came,\r\nWe will rejoice and be glad in it.\r\nThis is the day, this is the day\r\nWhen the Spirit came.', '', '1967', '', '', 'This is the day, this is the day That the Lord hath made, that the Lord hath made. We will rejoice, we will rejoice and be glad in it, and be glad in it. This is the day that the Lord hath made, We will rejoice and be glad in it, This is the day, this is the day that the Lord has made, That the Lord hath made. This is the day, this is the day When He rose again, when He rose again; We will rejoice, we will rejoice and be glad in it, and be glad in it. This is the day when He rose again, We will rejoice and be glad in it. This is the day, this is the day When He rose again. This is the day, this is the day When the Spirit came, when the Spirit came. We will rejoice, we will rejoice and be glad in it, and be glad in it. This is the day when the Spirit came, We will rejoice and be glad in it. This is the day, this is the day When the Spirit came.'),
	(528, 'You\'re Good Lord', 'Kathryn Scott. (c) 2003 Vertical Worship Songs,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYour mercy overwhelms me\r\nMore amazing every day\r\nThis kindness straight from Heaven\r\nIs relentless like the waves\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour mercy overtakes me\r\nEven when my feet have strayed\r\nAnd though I don\'t deserve it\r\nYou surround me with Your grace\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou\'re good Lord\r\nYou\'re wonderful to me\r\nYou\'re good Lord\r\nSo wonderful to me\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou\'re good Lord\r\nYou\'re good Lord\r\nSo good Lord\r\nSo good Lord\r\n', '', ' ', '', '', 'Your mercy overwhelms me More amazing every day This kindness straight from Heaven Is relentless like the waves Your mercy overtakes me Even when my feet have strayed And though I don\'t deserve it You surround me with Your grace You\'re good Lord You\'re wonderful to me You\'re good Lord So wonderful to me You\'re good Lord You\'re good Lord So good Lord So good Lord'),
	(529, 'Beautiful One', 'Tim Hughes', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]Wonderful, so [B]wonderful, is [E]your unfailing love\r\nYour [A]cross has spoken [B]mercy over [C#m]me.\r\n[A]No eye can see, no [B]ear has heard, no [E]heart can fully know.\r\nHow [A]glorious, how [B]beautiful you are[E].\r\n~Chorus\r\nBeautiful [A]One, I [B]love (you), Beautiful [A]One, I [B]adore,\r\nBeautiful [A]One, my [B]soul must [E]sing.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[A]Powerful, so [B]powerful, your [E]glory fills the skies,\r\nYour [A]mighty works dis[B]played for all to [C#m]see.\r\nThe [A]beauty of your [B]majesty a[E]wakes my heart to sing.\r\nHow [A]marvelous, how [B]wonderful you ar[E]e.\r\n~Bridge\r\nYou\'ve [A]opened my eyes to your [B]wonders anew,\r\nYou [A]captured my heart with this [B]love.\r\nCause n[A]othing on earth is as b[B]eautiful as [C#m]you.\r\n(Cause n[A]othing on earth is as b[B]eautiful as [E]you.)\r\n', '', '2002 Thankyou Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/rIZ77NormVI', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/beautiful-one/id6042265?i=6042228&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Tim Hughes - Here I Am to Worship - Beautiful One" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Wonderful, so wonderful, is your unfailing love Your cross has spoken mercy over me. No eye can see, no ear has heard, no heart can fully know. How glorious, how beautiful you are. Beautiful One, I love (you), Beautiful One, I adore, Beautiful One, my soul must sing. Powerful, so powerful, your glory fills the skies, Your mighty works displayed for all to see. The beauty of your majesty awakes my heart to sing. How marvelous, how wonderful you are. You\\\'ve opened my eyes to your wonders anew, You captured my heart with this love. Cause nothing on earth is as beautiful as you. (Cause nothing on earth is as beautiful as you.)'),
	(531, 'As High As The Heavens', 'Don Harris & Martin J. Nystom', '~Verse 1\r\nFor His anger lasts only a moment,\r\nBut His favor lasts for a life time;\r\nWeeping may remain for a night\r\nBut rejoicing comes, \r\nIt comes in the morning.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAs high as the heavens are above the earth\r\nSo great is the Father\'s love;\r\nAs far as the east is from the west;\r\nSo far has He taken our sin from us.\r\n', '', ' 1993 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music  ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/D06zgk-ILSI', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(For His anger lasts only a moment, But His favor lasts for a life time; Weeping may remain for a night But rejoicing comes, It comes in the morning. As high as the heavens are above the earth So great is the Father\'s love; As far as the east is from the west; So far has He taken our sin from us.).'),
	(532, 'Rock Of Refuge', 'Gary Sadler ', '~Verse 1\r\n\r\nYou\'re my Rock of Refuge,\r\nthe shelter of my life,\r\nmy merciful companion,\r\nmy comfort in the night;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nAnd I run to You,\r\nand You hold me close,\r\nYou hide me under Your shadow.\r\nYes, I run to You, \r\nIt\'s so good to know,\r\nO Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nThough my heart falls hard,\r\nstill Your love stands guard,\r\nO Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nYou\'re my Rock of Refuge,\r\nthe calm within my storm,\r\na secret place of safety,\r\nmy barrier from harm;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\nWhen my eyes are tears,\r\nthrough my worst of fears,\r\nO Lord, You are my rock of Refuge.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\n\r\nYes I run to You,\r\nit\'s so good to know,\r\nO Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge.\r\nO Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge.\r\n', '', ' 2000 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/dhTOnvleNwM', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(You\'re my Rock of Refuge, the shelter of my life, my merciful companion, my comfort in the night; And I run to You, and You hold me close, You hide me under Your shadow. Yes, I run to You, It\'s so good to know, O Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge. Though my heart falls hard, still Your love stands guard, O Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge. You\'re my Rock of Refuge, the calm within my storm, a secret place of safety, my barrier from harm; When my eyes are tears, through my worst of fears, O Lord, You are my rock of Refuge. Yes I run to You, it\'s so good to know, O Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge. O Lord, You are my Rock of Refuge.).'),
	(533, 'Good Christian Men Rejoice - Hymn #151', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGood Christian men, rejoice\r\nWith heart and soul and voice;\r\nGive ye heed to what we say:\r\nNews! News! Jesus Christ is born today!\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGood Christian men, rejoice\r\nWith heart and soul and voice;\r\nNow ye hear of endless bliss:\r\nJoy! Joy! Christ is born for this!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGood Christian men, rejoice\r\nWith heart and soul and voice;\r\nNow ye need not fear the grave:\r\nPeace! Peace! \r\nJesus Christ was born to save!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nOx and ass before Him bow,\r\nAnd He is in the manger now:\r\nChrist is born today! \r\nChrist is born today!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHe has opened heaven\'s door,\r\nAnd man is blessed evermore:\r\nChrist was born for this! \r\nChrist was born for this!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nCalls you one and calls you all\r\nTo gain His everlasting hall:\r\nChrist was born to save! \r\nChrist was born to save!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Good Christian men, rejoice With heart and soul and voice; Give ye heed to what we say: News! News! Jesus Christ is born today! Good Christian men, rejoice With heart and soul and voice; Now ye hear of endless bliss: Joy! Joy! Christ is born for this! Good Christian men, rejoice With heart and soul and voice; Now ye need not fear the grave: Peace! Peace! Jesus Christ was born to save! Ox and ass before Him bow, And He is in the manger now: Christ is born today! Christ is born today! He has opened heaven\'s door, And man is blessed evermore: Christ was born for this! Christ was born for this! Calls you one and calls you all To gain His everlasting hall: Christ was born to save! Christ was born to save!'),
	(534, 'Stand Up And Bless The Lord (Hymn #21)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nStand up and bless the Lord,\r\nYe people of His choice;\r\nStand up and bless the Lord your God\r\nWith heart and soul and voice.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThough high above all praise,\r\nAbove all blessing high,\r\nWho would not fear His holy name,\r\nAnd laud and magnify?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO for the living flame,\r\nFrom His own altar brought,\r\nTo touch our lips, our minds inspire,\r\nAnd wing to heav\'n our thought.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGod is our strength and song,\r\nAnd His salvation ours;\r\nThen be His love in Christ proclaim\'d\r\nWith all our ransomed pow\'rs.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nStand up and bless the Lord,\r\nThe Lord your God adore;\r\nStand up and bless His glorious name\r\nHenceforth forevermore.  Amen.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Stand up and bless the Lord, Ye people of His choice; Stand up and bless the Lord your God With heart and soul and voice. Though high above all praise, Above all blessing high, Who would not fear His holy name, And laud and magnify? O for the living flame, From His own altar brought, To touch our lips, our minds inspire, And wing to heav\'n our thought. God is our strength and song, And His salvation ours; Then be His love in Christ proclaim\'d With all our ransomed pow\'rs. Stand up and bless the Lord, The Lord your God adore; Stand up and bless His glorious name Henceforth forevermore.  Amen.'),
	(535, 'In The Secret', 'Andy Park', '~Verse 1\r\n[G][C][Em][D][C]\r\n[G] In the secret, in the quiet pla[C]ce\r\n[Em] In the stillness [D]you are th[C]ere\r\n[G] In the secret\r\n In the quiet[C] hour I wait only for you\r\n[Em] \'Cause I want to k[D]now you m[C]ore\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G] I want to [D]know you\r\n[Em] I want to [C]hear your voice\r\n[G] I want to [D]know you [C]more\r\n[G] I want to [D]touch you\r\n[Em] I want to [C]see your face\r\n[G] I want to [D]know you [C]more\r\n~Verse 2\r\n I am reaching for the highest goal\r\n That I might receive the prize\r\n Pressing onward\r\n Pushing every hinderance aside, out of my way\r\n \'Cause I want to know you more\r\n', '', '1995 Mercy / Vineyard Publishing', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/YV9qD0Z0WuM', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(In the secret, in the quiet place In the stillness you are there In the secret In the quiet hour I wait only for you \'Cause I want to know you more I want to know you I want to hear your voice I want to know you more I want to touch you I want to see your face I want to know you more I am reaching for the highest goal That I might receive the prize Pressing onward Pushing every hinderance aside, out of my way \'Cause I want to know you more).'),
	(536, 'What Kind Of Love Is This', 'Bryn and Sally Haworth; Spirit of Praise', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhat kind of love is this?\r\nThat gave itself for me\r\nI am the guilty one\r\nYet I go free.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhat kind of love is this?\r\nA love I\'ve never known\r\nI didn\'t even \r\nKnow His name,\r\nWhat kind of love is this?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhat kind of man is this,\r\nThat died in agony?\r\nHe who had \r\nDone no wrong\r\nWas crucified for me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhat kind of man is this,\r\nWho laid aside His throne?\r\nThat I may know \r\nThe love of God\r\nWhat kind of man is this?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nBy grace I have been saved,\r\nIt is the gift of God.\r\nHe destined me\r\n To be His son,\r\nSuch is His love.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nNo eye has ever seen,\r\nNo ear has ever heard,\r\nNor has the heart \r\nOf man conceived,\r\nWhat kind of love is this?\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'What kind of love is this? That gave itself for me I am the guilty one Yet I go free. What kind of love is this? A love I\'ve never known I didn\'t even Know His name, What kind of love is this? What kind of man is this, That died in agony? He who had Done no wrong Was crucified for me. What kind of man is this, Who laid aside His throne? That I may know The love of God What kind of man is this? By grace I have been saved, It is the gift of God. He destined me To be His son, Such is His love. No eye has ever seen, No ear has ever heard, Nor has the heart Of man conceived, What kind of love is this?'),
	(537, 'Be Bold, Be Strong', 'Morris Chapman ', '~Verse 1\r\nBe bold!\r\nBe bold!\r\nBe strong!\r\nBe strong!\r\nFor the Lord your God is with you;\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI am not afraid, I am not dismayed,\r\n\'Cause I\'m walkin\' in faith and victory.\r\nCome on and walk in faith and victory,\r\nFor the Lord, your God, is with you.\r\n', '', ' 1984 ', '', '', 'Be bold! Be bold! Be strong! Be strong! For the Lord your God is with you; I am not afraid, I am not dismayed, \'Cause I\'m walkin\' in faith and victory. Come on and walk in faith and victory, For the Lord, your God, is with you.'),
	(857, 'My Saviour Lives', 'New Life Worship', '~Verse1\r\nOur God wil reign forever\r\nAnd all the world will know His name\r\nEveryone together sing the song of the redeemed\r\n~Chorus\r\nI know that my redeemer lives\r\nAnd now I stand on what He did\r\nMy Saviour, my Saviour lives\r\nEvery day a brand new chance to say\r\nJesus, You are the only way\r\nMy Saviour, my Saviour lives\r\n~Verse2\r\nThe King has come from Heaven\r\nAnd darkness trembles at His name\r\nVictory forever is the song of the redeemed\r\n~Bridge\r\nMy Saviour lives, My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives\r\nMy Saviour lives, My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives\r\n', '', '2006 Vertical Worship Songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/aZLqd07IEo0', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=209341233&id=209341220&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="New Life Worship - My Savior Lives - My Savior Lives" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Our God wil reign forever And all the world will know His name Everyone together sing the song of the redeemed I know that my redeemer lives And now I stand on what He did My Saviour, my Saviour lives Every day a brand new chance to say Jesus, You are the only way My Saviour, my Saviour lives The King has come from Heaven And darkness trembles at His name Victory forever is the song of the redeemed My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives, My Saviour lives'),
	(538, 'For The Beauty Of The Earth', 'Conrad Kocker; Arranged by William H. Monk', '~Verse 1\r\nFor the beauty of the earth,\r\nFor the glory of the skies;\r\nFor the love which from our birth;\r\nOver and around us lies.\r\nLord of all, to Thee we raise,\r\nThis our hymn of grateful praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor the wonder of each hour\r\nOf the day and of the night;\r\nHill and vale and tree and flower,\r\nSun and moon and stars of light;\r\nLord of all, to Thee we raise,\r\nThis our hymn of grateful praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor the joy of human love,\r\nBrother, sister, parent, child;\r\nFriends on earth and friends above,\r\nFor all gentle thought and mild;\r\nLord of all, to Thee we raise,\r\nThis our hymn of grateful praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor Thy church that evermore,\r\nLifteth holy hands above;\r\nOffering up on every shore,\r\nHer pure sacrifice of love;\r\nLord of all, to Thee we raise,\r\nThis our hymn of grateful praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nFor Thy self, best gift divine,\r\nTo our race so freely given;\r\nFor that great, great love of Thine,\r\nPeace on earth and joy in heaven;\r\nLord of all, to Thee we raise,\r\nThis our hymn of grateful praise.\r\n', '', '', '', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(For the beauty of the earth, For the glory of the skies; For the love which from our birth; Over and around us lies. Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise. For the wonder of each hour Of the day and of the night; Hill and vale and tree and flower, Sun and moon and stars of light; Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise. For the joy of human love, Brother, sister, parent, child; Friends on earth and friends above, For all gentle thought and mild; Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise. For Thy church that evermore, Lifteth holy hands above; Offering up on every shore, Her pure sacrifice of love; Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise. For Thy self, best gift divine, To our race so freely given; For that great, great love of Thine, Peace on earth and joy in heaven; Lord of all, to Thee we raise, This our hymn of grateful praise.).'),
	(539, 'I Will Love Thee', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will love Thee,\r\nI will love Thee,\r\nI will trust Thee,\r\nI will trust Thee,\r\nI will love Thee,\r\nI will love Thee,\r\nI will call upon the Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1981 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'I will love Thee, I will love Thee, I will trust Thee, I will trust Thee, I will love Thee, I will love Thee, I will call upon the Lord.'),
	(540, 'Be Thou My Vision', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Be thou my [Bm]vision, O [D]Lord of [A]my [D]heart.\r\n[A]Naught be all else to me, [Bm]save that thou [A]art.\r\n[G]Thou my best [D]thought by [Bm]day or by [G-A]night.\r\n[D]Waking or [Bm]sleeping, thy [Em]presence [A]my [D]light.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBe thou my Wisdom and thou my true Word,\r\nI ever with Thee and thou with me, Lord; \r\nThou my great Father, I thy true son,\r\nThou in me dwelling and I with Thee one.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nRiches I heed not nor man\'s empty praise,\r\nThou mine inheritance now and always.\r\nThou and Thou only, first in my heart,\r\nHigh King of Heaven, my Treasure Thou art.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHigh King of heaven my victory won,\r\nMay I reach heaven\'s joys, O bright Heaven\'s Son!\r\nHeart of my own heart, whatever befall,\r\nStill be my vision, O ruler of all.', '', '1986 Word Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/IQxHvBtR7hs&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Be thou my vision, O Lord of my heart. Naught be all else to me, save that thou art. Thou my best thought by day or by night. Waking or sleeping, thy presence my light. Be thou my Wisdom and thou my true Word, I ever with Thee and thou with me, Lord; Thou my great Father, I thy true son, Thou in me dwelling and I with Thee one. Riches I heed not nor man\\\'s empty praise, Thou mine inheritance now and always. Thou and Thou only, first in my heart, High King of Heaven, my Treasure Thou art. High King of heaven my victory won, May I reach heaven\\\'s joys, O bright Heaven\\\'s Son! Heart of my own heart, whatever befall, Still be my vision, O ruler of all.'),
	(541, 'What A Friend We Have In Jesus', 'Joseph M. Scriven; Music by Charles C. Converse', '~Verse 1\r\nWhat a friend we have in Jesus,\r\nAll our sins and griefs to bear!\r\nWhat a privilege to carry\r\nEverything to God in prayer!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO what peace we often forfeit,\r\nO what needless pain we bear,\r\nAll because we do not carry\r\nEverything to God in prayer!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHave we trials and temptations?\r\nIs there trouble anywhere?\r\n We should never be discouraged\r\nTake it to the Lord in prayer!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nCan we find a friend so faithful\r\nWho will all our sorrows share?\r\nJesus knows our every weakness,\r\nTake it to the Lord in prayer!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAre we weak and heavy laden,\r\nCumbered with a load of care?\r\nPrecious Savior, still our Refuge\r\nTake it to the Lord in prayer.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nDo thy friends despise, forsake thee?\r\nTake it to the Lord in prayer,\r\nIn His arms He\'ll take and shield thee,\r\nThou wilt find a solace there.\r\n', '', ' Converse', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/8SCorW9r_Is', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(What a friend we have in Jesus, All our sins and griefs to bear! What a privilege to carry Everything to God in prayer! O what peace we often forfeit, O what needless pain we bear, All because we do not carry Everything to God in prayer! Have we trials and temptations? Is there trouble anywhere? We should never be discouraged Take it to the Lord in prayer! Can we find a friend so faithful Who will all our sorrows share? Jesus knows our every weakness, Take it to the Lord in prayer! Are we weak and heavy laden, Cumbered with a load of care? Precious Savior, still our Refuge Take it to the Lord in prayer. Do thy friends despise, forsake thee? Take it to the Lord in prayer, In His arms He\'ll take and shield thee, Thou wilt find a solace there.).'),
	(542, 'El Shaddai', '', '~Chorus\r\nEl Sh[Dm]addai, El Sha[G]ddai,\r\nEl-El[C]yon na Ado[F]nia,\r\nAge to [Bb]age You\'re still the [E/D]same,\r\nBy the [Am]power of the n[A]ame.\r\nEl Sh[Dm]addai[G], El Shaddai,\r\nErkam[C]ka na Ado[F]nai,\r\nWe will p[Bb]raise and l[E/D]ift You high,\r\nEl Sh[C]addai.\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThroug[Dm]h your love a[G]nd through the ram,\r\nYou saved the s[C]on of Abra[F]ham;\r\nThrou[Bb]gh the power [E/D]of your hand,\r\nTur[Am]ned th[A]e sea into dry land.\r\n[Dm]To the o[G]utcast on her knees,\r\nYou we[C]re the [F]God who really sees,\r\nAnd by Your m[Bb]ight,\r\nYou set[E/D] Your ch[C]ildren free.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThrough the y[Dm]ears [G]You\'ve made it clear,\r\nTh[C]at the time[F] of Christ was near,\r\nThoug[Bb]h the [E/D]people couldn\'t see\r\nWhat Me[Am]ssiah ought to [A]be.\r\nThough Your W[Dm]ord[G] contained the plan,\r\nThey just co[C]uld n[F]ot understand\r\nYour[Bb] most a[E/D]wesome work was done\r\nThroug[Am]h the f[A]railty of Your Son.\r\n', '', '1982, Whole Armor Pub. Co.; ARR; ICS; ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/DuXB1a3NBCw&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'El Shaddai, El Shaddai, El-Elyon na Adonia, Age to age You\'re still the same, By the power of the name. El Shaddai, El Shaddai, Erkamka na Adonai, We will praise and lift You high, El Shaddai. Through your love and through the ram, You saved the son of Abraham; Through the power of your hand, Turned the sea into dry land. To the outcast on her knees, You were the God who really sees, And by Your might, You set Your children free. Through the years You\'ve made it clear, That the time of Christ was near, Though the people couldn\'t see What Messiah ought to be. Though Your Word contained the plan, They just could not understand Your most awesome work was done Through the frailty of Your Son.'),
	(543, 'Break Thou The Bread Of Life', 'Mary A. Lathbury & William F. Sherwin. Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBreak Thou the bread of life,\r\nDear Lord, to me,\r\nAs Thou didst break\r\nThe loaves beside the sea\r\nBeyond the sacred page I seek Thee, Lord;\r\nMy spirit pants for Thee, O Living Word!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBreak Thou the truth,\r\nDear Lord, to me, to me,\r\nAs Thou didst bless the bread by Galilee;\r\nThen shall all bondage cease, all fetters fall,\r\nAnd I shall find my peace, my All in All.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTeach me to live, dear Lord, only for Thee,\r\nAs Thy disciples lived in Galilee;\r\nThen, all my struggles o\'er, then, vict\'ry won,\r\nI shall behold Thee, Lord, the Living One.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Break Thou the bread of life, Dear Lord, to me, As Thou didst break The loaves beside the sea Beyond the sacred page I seek Thee, Lord; My spirit pants for Thee, O Living Word! Break Thou the truth, Dear Lord, to me, to me, As Thou didst bless the bread by Galilee; Then shall all bondage cease, all fetters fall, And I shall find my peace, my All in All. Teach me to live, dear Lord, only for Thee, As Thy disciples lived in Galilee; Then, all my struggles o\'er, then, vict\'ry won, I shall behold Thee, Lord, the Living One.'),
	(544, 'We Need To Worship', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe need to worship, we need to hear\r\nWe need to know You Lord\r\nPlease draw near\r\nWe need to listen, we need to know\r\nThat You\'re here in our presence\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord, come right now and bring a fresh wind\r\nBring a fresh wind\r\nLet Your Spirit draw near to refresh and fill\r\nBring a fresh wind, bring a fresh wind\r\nLet Your spirit draw near us Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe come to worship, we come to hear\r\nWe come to know You Lord\r\nPlease draw near\r\nWe come to listen, we come to know\r\nThat You\'re here in our presence\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLord, come right now and bring a fresh wind\r\nBring a fresh wind\r\nLet Your Spirit draw near to refresh and fill\r\nBring a fresh wind, bring a fresh wind\r\nLet Your spirit draw near us Lord.\r\n', '', ' Crossworld Music. ', '', '', 'We need to worship, we need to hear We need to know You Lord Please draw near We need to listen, we need to know That You\'re here in our presence Lord, come right now and bring a fresh wind Bring a fresh wind Let Your Spirit draw near to refresh and fill Bring a fresh wind, bring a fresh wind Let Your spirit draw near us Lord. We come to worship, we come to hear We come to know You Lord Please draw near We come to listen, we come to know That You\'re here in our presence Lord, come right now and bring a fresh wind Bring a fresh wind Let Your Spirit draw near to refresh and fill Bring a fresh wind, bring a fresh wind Let Your spirit draw near us Lord.'),
	(545, 'Jesus Is My Lord', 'Norman Manzon  ', '~Verse 1\r\nJesus is my Lord, my Master, My Savior\r\nJesus is my Lord, my Master, My Savior\r\nNow and forever more, Hallelujah\r\nNow and forever more.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nPraise you Jesus, Son of God\r\nAnd the blood of the Lamb\r\nKing of Kings, and Lord of Lords\r\nGod of Abraham, Hallelujah\r\nGod of Abraham.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus is the one who delivers me daily\r\nJesus is the one who delivers me daily\r\nFrom my sin & shame, Hallelujah\r\nFrom my sin & shame.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nJesus You\'re my Lord, my Master, \r\n	 my Saviour...\r\nJesus You\'re my Lord, my Master, \r\n	 my Saviour...\r\nNow and forever more, Hallelujah\r\nNow and forever more.\r\n', '', '1985 Paragon Music Corp./ASCAP', '', '', 'Jesus is my Lord, my Master, My Savior Jesus is my Lord, my Master, My Savior Now and forever more, Hallelujah Now and forever more. Praise you Jesus, Son of God And the blood of the Lamb King of Kings, and Lord of Lords God of Abraham, Hallelujah God of Abraham. Jesus is the one who delivers me daily Jesus is the one who delivers me daily From my sin & shame, Hallelujah From my sin & shame. Jesus You\\\'re my Lord, my Master, my Saviour... Jesus You\\\'re my Lord, my Master, my Saviour... Now and forever more, Hallelujah Now and forever more.'),
	(546, 'The Bond Of Love', 'Otis Skillings. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe are one in the bond of love\r\nWe are one in the bond of love\r\nWe have joined our spirits\r\nWith the Spirit of God\r\nWe are one in the bond of love\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet us praise Jesus Christ the Son\r\nPraise Him now for the work begun\r\nLet us join our hands\r\nThat the world may know\r\nWe are one in the bond of love\r\n', '', ' 1971 Lillenas Publishing Co.', '', '', 'We are one in the bond of love We are one in the bond of love We have joined our spirits With the Spirit of God We are one in the bond of love Let us praise Jesus Christ the Son Praise Him now for the work begun Let us join our hands That the world may know We are one in the bond of love'),
	(548, 'As The Deer ', 'Martin Nystrom', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]As the [A/C#]deer panteth [Bm]for the [Bm/A]water\r\nSo my [G]soul longs [A]after [D]you[G-A]\r\n[D]You [A/C#]alone are my [Bm]heart\'s [Bm/A]desire\r\nAnd I [G]long to [A]worship [D]you\r\n~Chorus:\r\n[Bm]You a[Bm/A]lone are my [G]strength my s[D]hield \r\n[G]To you alone may my [Em7]spirit [F#sus-F#]yield\r\n[D]You a[A/C#]lone are my hear[Bm]t\'s de[A/Bm]sire\r\nAnd I [G]long to [A]worship [D]you\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[D]I want [A/C#]you more than [Bm]gold or [Bm/A]silver\r\nOnly [G]you can [A]satis[D]fy[G-A]\r\n[D]You a[A/C#]lone are the [Bm]real joy [Bm/A]giver\r\nAnd the [G]apple of [A]my [D]eye\r\n~Verse 3\r\n[D]You\'re my [A/C#]friend and You [Bm]are my [Bm/A]brother\r\nEven [G]though You [A]are a [D]Kin[G-A]g\r\n[D]I love [A/C#]You more than [Bm]any [Bm/A]other\r\nSo much [G]more than [A]any[D]thing\r\n', '', '1984 Maranatha! Music ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/y8PSfmsrQ3c&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'As the deer panteth for the water So my soul longs after you You alone are my heart\'s desire And I long to worship you You alone are my strength my shield To you alone may my spirit yield You alone are my heart\'s desire And I long to worship you I want you more than gold or silver Only you can satisfy You alone are the real joy giver And the apple of my eye You\'re my friend and You are my brother Even though You are a King I love You more than any other So much more than anything'),
	(549, 'Exalt The Lord', 'Rick Founds. ', '[Em7]       Exalt [D] the Lord our [Em7]God (Exalt [D] the Lord our [Em7]God)\r\nAnd wor[D]ship at His [Em7]feet (And wor[D]ship at His [Em7]feet)\r\n\r\nFor he (for [D]he) is hol[G]y\r\n\r\nFor the [G]Lord our [Em7]God, He is* [C]ho[D]ly\r\nFor the [G]Lord our [Em7]God, He is [C]ho[D]ly\r\nFor the [G]Lord our [Em7]God, He is [C]ho[D]ly\r\nYes the [G]Lord our [Em7]God, He is [C]ho[D]ly     [G]\r\n', '', ' 1977 Scripture in song', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/kCYgkqbX-fQ', '', 'Exalt  the Lord our God (Exalt  the Lord our God) And worship at His feet (And worship at His feet) For he (for he) is holy For the Lord our God, He is* holy For the Lord our God, He is holy For the Lord our God, He is holy Yes the Lord our God, He is holy'),
	(550, 'There Is A Place', 'Dennis L. Jernigan;', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere is a place that calls you home.\r\nThere is a King upon a throne.\r\nHe offers hope \r\nwhere hope is just not known.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe is the King of Kings!\r\nLord over ev\'rything!\r\nLord God Almighty!\r\nLord of Lords and King of Kings!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe is the hope of ev\'ry nation!\r\nSaviour of all who will believe!\r\nWhen we have questions He is the \r\n	 Answer that we need!\r\nIsn\'t it good to know that Jesus is the King?\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nIf you need love there is a way out\r\nOf the games the world will play.\r\nCry out to Jesus!  He is the only way!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWhere do you go when doubts prevail,\r\nWorries arise and fears assail?\r\nWho offers love that simply will not fail?\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nWho heals your hurt when your heart\'s torn?\r\nWhen your heart\'s cold who makes it warm?\r\nCome unto Jesus the Calmer of the storm!\r\n', '', ' 1989 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, c/o Northstar Ltd., 2904 Parklawn Dr., ', '', '', 'There is a place that calls you home. There is a King upon a throne. He offers hope where hope is just not known. He is the King of Kings! Lord over ev\'rything! Lord God Almighty! Lord of Lords and King of Kings! He is the hope of ev\'ry nation! Saviour of all who will believe! When we have questions He is the Answer that we need! Isn\'t it good to know that Jesus is the King? If you need love there is a way out Of the games the world will play. Cry out to Jesus!  He is the only way! Where do you go when doubts prevail, Worries arise and fears assail? Who offers love that simply will not fail? Who heals your hurt when your heart\'s torn? When your heart\'s cold who makes it warm? Come unto Jesus the Calmer of the storm!'),
	(551, 'God Is With Us', 'Chris Springer & Alicia Williamson.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMade a way in the wilderness,\r\nCalmed the raging sea;\r\nThe Lily of the Valley \r\nIs always there for me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSee, where can I go from\r\nYour presence, Lord?\r\nThere\'s nothing You don\'t know\r\nNothing You don\'t know\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGod is with us,\r\nGod is with us,\r\nEmmanuel our God is with us;\r\nNo matter where we go,\r\nThere\'s one thing we know,\r\nEmmanuel, our God is with us.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGod is with us,\r\nGod is with us,\r\nEmmanuel our God is with us;\r\nNo matter where we go,\r\nThere\'s one thing we know,\r\nEmmanuel, our God is with us.\r\nGod is with us.\r\nThe Lord Jehovah, God Almighty is with us!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nEven in the shadow of death,\r\nThere\'s no need to fear;\r\nFor Emmanuel our God\r\nIs always standing near.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nDarkness cannot hide us\r\nYour light always shines through\r\nFor Emmanuel our God\r\nIs with us in all we do\r\n', '', ' 1994 Integrity\'s Praise! Music & Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music/', '', '', 'Made a way in the wilderness, Calmed the raging sea; The Lily of the Valley Is always there for me. See, where can I go from Your presence, Lord? There\'s nothing You don\'t know Nothing You don\'t know God is with us, God is with us, Emmanuel our God is with us; No matter where we go, There\'s one thing we know, Emmanuel, our God is with us. God is with us, God is with us, Emmanuel our God is with us; No matter where we go, There\'s one thing we know, Emmanuel, our God is with us. God is with us. The Lord Jehovah, God Almighty is with us! Even in the shadow of death, There\'s no need to fear; For Emmanuel our God Is always standing near. Darkness cannot hide us Your light always shines through For Emmanuel our God Is with us in all we do'),
	(552, 'Victory Song (Through Our God)', 'Dale Garratt', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThrough our God we shall do valiantly\r\nIt is He who will tread down the enemy\r\nWe\'ll sing and shout His victory\r\nChrist is King.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor God has won the victory\r\nAnd set His people free\r\nHis Word has slain the enemy\r\nThe earth shall stand & see\r\nThat through our God....   \r\n', '', ' 1979 Scripture in Song  (Admin. by Maranatha Music)', '', '', 'Through our God we shall do valiantly It is He who will tread down the enemy We\'ll sing and shout His victory Christ is King. For God has won the victory And set His people free His Word has slain the enemy The earth shall stand & see That through our God....'),
	(553, 'I Want To Be Where You Are', 'Don Moen', '~Verse 1\r\nI just want to be where You are\r\nDwelling daily in Your presence.\r\nI don\'t want to worship from afar\r\nDraw me near \r\nto where You are.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI want to be where You are\r\nDwelling in Your presence.\r\nFeasting at Your table\r\nSurrounded by Your glory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIn Your presence - \r\n  That\'s where I always want to be\r\nI just want to be,\r\n I just want to be with You\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI just want to be where You are\r\nIn Your dwelling place forever.\r\nTake me to the place \r\nwhere You are.\r\nI just want to be with You.\r\n', '', '1989 Integrity Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/NWxnqvaZmKg', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I just want to be where You are Dwelling daily in Your presence. I don\'t want to worship from afar Draw me near to where You are. I want to be where You are Dwelling in Your presence. Feasting at Your table Surrounded by Your glory. In Your presence - That\'s where I always want to be I just want to be, I just want to be with You I just want to be where You are In Your dwelling place forever. Take me to the place where You are. I just want to be with You.).'),
	(554, 'Spirit Fall On Us', 'Jeff Nelson. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe need Your power,\r\nWe need Your grace.\r\nLord, let your healing fill this place.\r\nWe need Your mercy;\r\nWe need Your love.\r\nO Spirit, fall on us, fall on us.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSpirit fall on us;\r\nSpirit fall on us.\r\nO draw our hearts into Your holy passion.\r\nSpirit, fall on us.\r\n', '', ' 1999 WholeHearted Worship.', '', '', 'We need Your power, We need Your grace. Lord, let your healing fill this place. We need Your mercy; We need Your love. O Spirit, fall on us, fall on us. Spirit fall on us; Spirit fall on us. O draw our hearts into Your holy passion. Spirit, fall on us.'),
	(555, 'Singing Hallelujah', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSinging Hallelujah!\r\nLamb upon the throne,\r\nWe worship and adore you,\r\nYou\'ve made Your glories known.\r\nHallelujah, glory to the King!\r\nYou\'re more than a conqueror,\r\nAnd You\'re Lord of everything.\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Singing Hallelujah! Lamb upon the throne, We worship and adore you, You\'ve made Your glories known. Hallelujah, glory to the King! You\'re more than a conqueror, And You\'re Lord of everything.'),
	(556, 'Spirit Of The Living God', 'Daniel Iverson', '~Verse 1\r\nSpirit of the living God, fall fresh on me;\r\nSpirit of the living God, fall fresh on me.\r\nBreak me! Melt me! Mould me! Fill me!\r\nSpirit of the living God, fall fresh on me.\r\n\r\n', '', '1935, 1963, Moody Press', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/BagH-zTfnsQ', '', 'Spirit of the living God, fall fresh on me; Spirit of the living God, fall fresh on me. Break me! Melt me! Mould me! Fill me! Spirit of the living God, fall fresh on me.'),
	(557, 'Fear Not, For I Have Redeemed You', 'Jodi Clark', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhen you pass through the waters\r\n I will be with you;\r\nAnd through rivers,\r\n They will not overwhelm you.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFear not, for I have redeemed you;\r\nI have called you by name.\r\nI have called you by name.\r\nYou are mine.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhen you walk through the fire\r\n You will not 	 be burned;\r\nThe flames shall not consume you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBecause you are precious and I love you,\r\nYou whom I formed for my glory,\r\nYou whom I called by my Name,\r\nI will gather together.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nYou are my witnesses; I have chosen You\r\nThat you may know and believe me.\r\nYou are my servants for the world to see\r\nI am the Lord, I\'m among you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nIt\'s time now to lay aside the former things;\r\nA new day has dawned, do you see it?\r\nI\'m making a way in the wilderness, \r\nAnd rivers to flow in the desert.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nThe rivers that flow in the desert\r\nGive drink to my chosen people;\r\nTo quench their thirst \r\nAnd to strengthen them,\r\nThat they might show forth my praise.\r\n', '', ' Celebration Services (International) Ltd., 1975; ARR; UBP; ', '', '', 'When you pass through the waters I will be with you; And through rivers, They will not overwhelm you. Fear not, for I have redeemed you; I have called you by name. I have called you by name. You are mine. When you walk through the fire You will not 	 be burned; The flames shall not consume you. Because you are precious and I love you, You whom I formed for my glory, You whom I called by my Name, I will gather together. You are my witnesses; I have chosen You That you may know and believe me. You are my servants for the world to see I am the Lord, I\'m among you. It\'s time now to lay aside the former things; A new day has dawned, do you see it? I\'m making a way in the wilderness, And rivers to flow in the desert. The rivers that flow in the desert Give drink to my chosen people; To quench their thirst And to strengthen them, That they might show forth my praise.'),
	(558, 'Psalm 100', 'Andy Park', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nShout to the Lord for joy;  All the earth\r\nWorship the Lord with gladness\r\nAnd joyful songs; \r\n Know that the Lord is good\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt is He who has made us\r\nEnter His gates with thanks\r\nCome into His courts with praise\r\nCome into His courts with praise\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor the Lord is good; \r\nAnd His love endures forever\r\nHis faithfulness shall be forevermore\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor the Lord is good; \r\nAnd His love endures forever\r\nHis faithfulness shall be forevermore\r\nFor the Lord is good.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Shout to the Lord for joy;  All the earth Worship the Lord with gladness And joyful songs; Know that the Lord is good It is He who has made us Enter His gates with thanks Come into His courts with praise Come into His courts with praise For the Lord is good; And His love endures forever His faithfulness shall be forevermore For the Lord is good; And His love endures forever His faithfulness shall be forevermore For the Lord is good.'),
	(559, 'Peacemaker', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n\r\nPeace Maker,  Fear Taker      \r\n    Soul Soother,  Storm Soother.\r\n   Light Shiner,  Lost Finder\r\n     Cloud Lifter,  Deliverer.\r\nHeart Toucher,  Truth Lover\r\nWho Other could be...\r\n             Fear Taker, Peace Maker \r\nto me.        \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\nMind Clearer, Sigh hearer,\r\nHand Holder, Consoler.\r\n           Wound Binder, Tear Drier,\r\n              Strength giver,  Provider.\r\nHeart Healer, Kind Father, \r\nWho other could be,\r\n              My Savior Peace Maker\r\nto me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet Your Peace rule in my heart,         \r\nLet Your Kindness fill my thoughts.\r\n    Let Your Strength secure my soul,\r\n        Let Your Peace take hold in me.   \r\nLet Your Wisdom guild my will,          \r\n Your Compassion fill this place,  \r\n              Let my Anxious thoughts be still,           \r\n                    Let Your Peace rule in my heart,  \r\nI need You, I need You, I need You,\r\nIn My Life, Lord I Trust You,\r\nBelieve You, I need You, \r\nIn My Life, I Know!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Peace Maker,  Fear Taker Soul Soother,  Storm Soother. Light Shiner,  Lost Finder Cloud Lifter,  Deliverer. Heart Toucher,  Truth Lover Who Other could be... Fear Taker, Peace Maker to me. Mind Clearer, Sigh hearer, Hand Holder, Consoler. Wound Binder, Tear Drier, Strength giver,  Provider. Heart Healer, Kind Father, Who other could be, My Savior Peace Maker to me. Let Your Peace rule in my heart, Let Your Kindness fill my thoughts. Let Your Strength secure my soul, Let Your Peace take hold in me. Let Your Wisdom guild my will, Your Compassion fill this place, Let my Anxious thoughts be still, Let Your Peace rule in my heart, I need You, I need You, I need You, In My Life, Lord I Trust You, Believe You, I need You, In My Life, I Know!'),
	(560, 'Hope Of The Nations', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]Jesus [D]hope of the nations \r\n[A]Jesus [D]comfort for all who [F#m]mourn \r\nYou [E]are the source of [D]Heaven\'s hope on [E]earth \r\n[A]Jesus [D/A]light in the darkness \r\n[A]Jesus [D]truth in each [F#m]circumstance \r\nYou [E]are the source of [D]Heaven\'s light on [E]earth \r\n~Pre-Chorus\r\nIn [D]history You [A/C#]lived and died \r\nYou [Bm7]broke the chains You [E]rose to life \r\n~Chorus\r\nYou are the [A]hope living in [D]us \r\nYou are the [E]rock in Whom we [A]trust \r\nYou are the [F#m]light \r\nShining for [D]all the world to [E]see  [D/F#]\r\nYou rose from the [A]dead conquering [D]fear \r\nOur Prince of [E]Peace drawing us [A]near \r\nJesus our [F#m]hope living for [Bm7]all who will [E]receive [D]\r\nLord we be[A]lieve[D]\r\n', '', '2002 Integrity', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/37NYEIo7sEI&hl=en&fs=1&rel=0&color1=0x3a3a3a&color2=0x999999', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/hope-nations/id293249177?i=293249195&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Brian Doerksen - It&#39;s Time - Hope of the Nations" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Jesus hope of the nations Jesus comfort for all who mourn You are the source of Heaven\\\'s hope on earth Jesus light in the darkness Jesus truth in each circumstance You are the source of Heaven\\\'s light on earth In history You lived and died You broke the chains You rose to life You are the hope living in us You are the rock in Whom we trust You are the light Shining for all the world to see You rose from the dead conquering fear Our Prince of Peace drawing us near Jesus our hope living for all who will receive Lord we believe'),
	(561, 'Psalm 121', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse\r\n[C]   I lift my [F]eyes up [C] to the [F]mountains\r\n[C]   Where does my [F]help [C]come [G]from?\r\n[C]   My help comes [F]from You, [C] Maker of [F]Heaven\r\n[C]   Creator [F]of [C]the [G]earth\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C/E]   O how I [F]need You Lord, [C/E] You are my [F]only hope\r\n[C/E]   You\'re my [F]on[C]ly [G]prayer\r\n[C/E]   So I will [F]wait for You [C/E] to come and [F]rescue me\r\n[C/E]   Come and [F]give [C]me [G]life\r\n', '', '1990 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/dwdi3pnQ4aQ&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'I lift my eyes up  to the mountains Where does my help come from? My help comes from You,  Maker of Heaven Creator of the earth O how I need You Lord,  You are my only hope You\\\'re my only prayer So I will wait for You  to come and rescue me Come and give me life'),
	(562, 'My Life Is In You, Lord', 'Daniel Gardner ', '~Verse 1\r\nI will praise You \r\nWith all of my life,\r\nI will praise You\r\n  With all of my strength,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMy Life is in You, Lord,\r\nMy strength is in You, Lord,\r\nMy hope is in You, Lord\r\nIn You, it\'s in You; \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWith all of my life, \r\nWith all of my strength.\r\nAll of my hope is in You.\r\n', '', ' 1986 Integrity\'s Hosanna Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/pyNiYHfj3qs', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I will praise You With all of my life, I will praise You With all of my strength, My Life is in You, Lord, My strength is in You, Lord, My hope is in You, Lord In You, it\'s in You; With all of my life, With all of my strength. All of my hope is in You.).'),
	(563, 'I Will Praise Your Name', 'Bob Fitts', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will praise Your name,\r\nI will praise Your name,\r\nI will praise Your name and extol You;\r\nI will praise Your name,\r\nI will praise Your name\r\nI will praise Your name as I behold You;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will magnify, I will glorify,\r\nI will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus,\r\nI will magnify, I will glorify,\r\nI will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI will praise Your name,\r\nI will praise Your name,\r\nI will praise Your name and extol You;\r\nI will magnify, I will glorify,\r\nI will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor Your love is never ending\r\nAnd Your mercy ever true;\r\nI will bless Your name, Lord Jesus,\r\nFor my heart belongs to You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI will praise Your name\r\n', '', ' 1993 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'I will praise Your name, I will praise Your name, I will praise Your name and extol You; I will praise Your name, I will praise Your name I will praise Your name as I behold You; I will magnify, I will glorify, I will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus, I will magnify, I will glorify, I will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus. I will praise Your name, I will praise Your name, I will praise Your name and extol You; I will magnify, I will glorify, I will lift on high Your name, Lord Jesus. For Your love is never ending And Your mercy ever true; I will bless Your name, Lord Jesus, For my heart belongs to You. I will praise Your name'),
	(564, 'The River', 'Brian Doerksen, Michael Hansen & Brian Thiessen', '~Verse 1\r\nTo the river I am going\r\nBringing sins I cannot bear\r\nCome and cleanse me,\r\nCome forgive me\r\nLord, I need to meet You there\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIn these waters,\r\nHealing mercy flows\r\nWith freedom from despair\r\nI am going to that river\r\nLord, I need to meet You there\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPrecious Jesus, I am ready\r\nTo surrender every care\r\nTake my hand now, \r\nLead me closer\r\nLord, I need to meet You there\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome and join us in the river\r\nCome find life beyond compare\r\nHe is calling, He is waiting\r\nJesus longs to meet you there\r\nHe is calling, He is waiting\r\nJesus longs to meet you there\r\n', '', ' 2004 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Media Inc.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/RGRCjWNwAg0&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'To the river I am going Bringing sins I cannot bear Come and cleanse me, Come forgive me Lord, I need to meet You there In these waters, Healing mercy flows With freedom from despair I am going to that river Lord, I need to meet You there Precious Jesus, I am ready To surrender every care Take my hand now, Lead me closer Lord, I need to meet You there Come and join us in the river Come find life beyond compare He is calling, He is waiting Jesus longs to meet you there He is calling, He is waiting Jesus longs to meet you there'),
	(565, 'Blessed Jesus', 'Joey Holder', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBlessed Jesus, come to me\r\nSoothe my soul with songs of peace.\r\nAs I look to You alone\r\nFill me with Your love.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMountains high and valleys low,\r\nYou will never let me go.\r\nBy Your fountain let me drink,\r\nFill my thirsty soul.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlorious, marvelous,\r\nGrace that rescued me!\r\nHoly, worthy is the Lamb\r\nWho died for me!\r\n', '', ' 1987 Far Lane Music Publishing.', '', '', 'Blessed Jesus, come to me Soothe my soul with songs of peace. As I look to You alone Fill me with Your love. Mountains high and valleys low, You will never let me go. By Your fountain let me drink, Fill my thirsty soul. Glorious, marvelous, Grace that rescued me! Holy, worthy is the Lamb Who died for me!'),
	(566, 'I Will Come And Bow Down', 'Martin Nystrom', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will come and bow down\r\nAt Your feet, Lord Jesus.\r\nIn Your presence if fullness of joy.\r\nThere is nothing, there is no one\r\nWho compares with You.\r\nI take pleasure in worshiping You, Lord.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1984 Integrity\'s', '', '', 'I will come and bow down At Your feet, Lord Jesus. In Your presence if fullness of joy. There is nothing, there is no one Who compares with You. I take pleasure in worshiping You, Lord.'),
	(567, 'Count Your Blessings', 'Johnson Oatman, Jr.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhen upon life\'s billows\r\nYou are tempest tossed,\r\nWhen you are discouraged,\r\nThinking all is lost,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nName them one by one,\r\nAnd it will surprise you\r\nWhat the Lord hath done.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAre you ever burdened\r\nWith a load of care?\r\nDoes the cross seem heavy\r\nYou are called to bear?\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nEvery doubt will fly,\r\nAnd you will be singing\r\nAs the days go by.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhen you look at others\r\nWith their lands and gold,\r\nThink that Christ has promised you\r\nHis wealth untold;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nMoney cannot buy\r\nYour reward in heaven,\r\nNor your home on high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nSo, amid the conflict,\r\nWhether great or small,\r\nDo not be discouraged,\r\nGod is over all;\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nAngels will attend,\r\nHelp and comfort give you\r\nTo your journey\'s end.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nCount your blessings,\r\nName them one by one\r\nCount your blessings\r\nSee what God hath done;\r\nCount your blessings,\r\nName them one by one\r\nCount your blessings\r\nSee what God hath done.\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nName them one by one;\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nSee what God hath done;\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nName them one by one;\r\nCount your many blessings,\r\nSee what God hath done.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'When upon life\'s billows You are tempest tossed, When you are discouraged, Thinking all is lost, Count your many blessings, Name them one by one, And it will surprise you What the Lord hath done. Are you ever burdened With a load of care? Does the cross seem heavy You are called to bear? Count your many blessings, Every doubt will fly, And you will be singing As the days go by. When you look at others With their lands and gold, Think that Christ has promised you His wealth untold; Count your many blessings, Money cannot buy Your reward in heaven, Nor your home on high. So, amid the conflict, Whether great or small, Do not be discouraged, God is over all; Count your many blessings, Angels will attend, Help and comfort give you To your journey\'s end. Count your blessings, Name them one by one Count your blessings See what God hath done; Count your blessings, Name them one by one Count your blessings See what God hath done. Count your many blessings, Name them one by one; Count your many blessings, See what God hath done; Count your many blessings, Name them one by one; Count your many blessings, See what God hath done.'),
	(568, 'I Delight', 'Graham Kendrick', '~Verse 1\r\nFilthy rags He changed for riches\r\nGave me honor for my shame,\r\nDressed me in His strength and splendor\r\nI will glorify His name.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI delight greatly in the Lord,\r\nIn Him is all my happiness;\r\nFor He has made me beautiful and bright,\r\nIn robes of righteousness.\r\nI delight greatly in the Lord.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHearts so full of celebration,\r\nLike a bride upon her wedding day,\r\nDressed like priests with His salvation,\r\nWe will ever sing for joy.\r\n~Tag\r\nI delight greatly in the Lord,\r\nI delight greatly in the Lord.\r\nHEY!!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Filthy rags He changed for riches Gave me honor for my shame, Dressed me in His strength and splendor I will glorify His name. I delight greatly in the Lord, In Him is all my happiness; For He has made me beautiful and bright, In robes of righteousness. I delight greatly in the Lord. Hearts so full of celebration, Like a bride upon her wedding day, Dressed like priests with His salvation, We will ever sing for joy. I delight greatly in the Lord, I delight greatly in the Lord. HEY!!'),
	(569, 'In Thanksgiving Let Us Praise Him', 'Clair Clininger', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFrom the first bright light of morning,\r\nTo the last warm glow of dusk;\r\nEvery breath we take is sacred,\r\nFor it is God\'s gift to us.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIn thanksgiving, let us praise Him;\r\nIn thanksgiving let us sing\r\nSongs of praise and adoration\r\nTo our gracious Lord, and King.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn the season of our plenty,\r\nIn the season of our need;\r\nWe will find His grace sufficient,\r\nWe will find His love complete.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSafe within His hand that guides us,\r\nHidden in His healing wings;\r\nDay by day His love provides us\r\nEvery good and perfect thing.\r\n', '', ' 1986 Word Music ', '', '', 'From the first bright light of morning, To the last warm glow of dusk; Every breath we take is sacred, For it is God\'s gift to us. In thanksgiving, let us praise Him; In thanksgiving let us sing Songs of praise and adoration To our gracious Lord, and King. In the season of our plenty, In the season of our need; We will find His grace sufficient, We will find His love complete. Safe within His hand that guides us, Hidden in His healing wings; Day by day His love provides us Every good and perfect thing.'),
	(570, 'Praise The Lord, Ye Heav\'ns Adore Him', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPraise the Lord! Ye Heav\'ns adore Him;\r\nPraise Him angels in the height,\r\nSun and moon, rejoice before Him,\r\nPraise Him, all ye stars of light;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPraise the Lord! For He hath spoken,\r\nWorlds His mighty voice obeyed;\r\nLaws which never shall be broken,\r\nFor their guidance He hath made.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nPraise the Lord! For He is glorious,\r\nNever shall His promise fail;\r\nGod hath made His saints victorious,\r\nSin and death shall not prevail;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nPraise the God of our salvation!\r\nHosts on high, His pow\'r proclaim;\r\nHeav\'n and earth and all creation,\r\nLaud and magnify His name.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWorship, honor, glory, blessing,\r\nLord, we offer unto Thee;\r\nYoung and old, Thy praise expressing\r\nIn glad homage bend the knee;\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAll the saints in heav\'n adore Thee;\r\nWe would bow before Thy throne;\r\nAs Thine angels serve before Thee,\r\nSo on earth Thy will be done.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Praise the Lord! Ye Heav\'ns adore Him; Praise Him angels in the height, Sun and moon, rejoice before Him, Praise Him, all ye stars of light; Praise the Lord! For He hath spoken, Worlds His mighty voice obeyed; Laws which never shall be broken, For their guidance He hath made. Praise the Lord! For He is glorious, Never shall His promise fail; God hath made His saints victorious, Sin and death shall not prevail; Praise the God of our salvation! Hosts on high, His pow\'r proclaim; Heav\'n and earth and all creation, Laud and magnify His name. Worship, honor, glory, blessing, Lord, we offer unto Thee; Young and old, Thy praise expressing In glad homage bend the knee; All the saints in heav\'n adore Thee; We would bow before Thy throne; As Thine angels serve before Thee, So on earth Thy will be done.'),
	(571, 'Holy Lord', 'Steve and Vikki Cook ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHoly Lord, most holy Lord, \r\nYou alone are worthy of my praise;\r\nO holy Lord, most holy Lord,\r\nWith all of my heart I sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGreat are You, Lord, \r\nWorthy of praise\r\nHoly and true, \r\nGreat are You Lord,\r\nMost holy Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1984 Marantha Music  ', '', '', 'Holy Lord, most holy Lord, You alone are worthy of my praise; O holy Lord, most holy Lord, With all of my heart I sing. Great are You, Lord, Worthy of praise Holy and true, Great are You Lord, Most holy Lord.'),
	(572, 'Mary Did You Know', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMary did you know, that your baby boy\r\nwould one day walk on water?\r\nMary did you know, that your baby boy\r\nwould save our sons and daughters?\r\nDid you know that your baby boy\r\nhas come to make you new;\r\nthis child that you deliver\r\nwill soon deliver you?\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMary did you know, that your baby boy\r\nwill give sight to the blind man?\r\nMary did you know that your baby boy\r\nwould calm a storm with His hand?\r\nDid you know that your baby boy, \r\nhas walked where angels trod,\r\nand when you kiss your little baby,\r\nyou\'ve kissed the face of God?\r\n\r\nO Mary did you know?\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMary did you know, that your baby boy\r\nis the Lord of all creation?\r\nMary did you know that your baby boy\r\nwill one day rule the nations?\r\nDid you know that your baby boy\r\nwas heavens perfect Lamb,\r\nand the sleeping Child you\'re holding\r\nis the great I am.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThe blind will see, \r\nthe deaf will hear,\r\nthe dead will live again\r\n\r\nthe lame will leap \r\nthe dumb will speak\r\nthe praises of the Lamb\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Mary did you know, that your baby boy would one day walk on water? Mary did you know, that your baby boy would save our sons and daughters? Did you know that your baby boy has come to make you new; this child that you deliver will soon deliver you? Mary did you know, that your baby boy will give sight to the blind man? Mary did you know that your baby boy would calm a storm with His hand? Did you know that your baby boy, has walked where angels trod, and when you kiss your little baby, you\'ve kissed the face of God? O Mary did you know? Mary did you know, that your baby boy is the Lord of all creation? Mary did you know that your baby boy will one day rule the nations? Did you know that your baby boy was heavens perfect Lamb, and the sleeping Child you\'re holding is the great I am. The blind will see, the deaf will hear, the dead will live again the lame will leap the dumb will speak the praises of the Lamb'),
	(573, 'Away In A Manager (Hymn 158)', 'William J. Kirkpatrick', '~Verse 1\r\nA[F(D)]way in a manger, no [Bb(G)]crib for a [F(D)]bed, \r\nthe [C7(A7)]little Lord Jesus laid [F(D)]down His sweet head; \r\nThe [F(D)]stars in the bright sky looked [Bb(G)]down where He [F(D)]lay, \r\nthe [C7(A7)]lit-tle Lord [F(D)]Jesus, a[Bb(G)]sleep on [C7]the [F(A7]hay.[D)]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe cattle are lowing, the Baby awakes, \r\nBut little Lord Jesus, no crying He makes; \r\nI love Thee, Lord Jesus! Look down from the sky, \r\nand stay by my cradle, till morning is nigh.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBe near me, Lord Jesus, I ask Thee to stay \r\nclose by me forever, and love me, I pray; \r\nBless all the dear children in Thy tender care, \r\nand fit us for heaven, to live with Thee there. \r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/FnVorT14i4I', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Away in a manger, no crib for a bed, the little Lord Jesus laid down His sweet head; The stars in the bright sky looked down where He lay, the lit-tle Lord Jesus, asleep on the hay. The cattle are lowing, the Baby awakes, But little Lord Jesus, no crying He makes; I love Thee, Lord Jesus! Look down from the sky, and stay by my cradle, till morning is nigh. Be near me, Lord Jesus, I ask Thee to stay close by me forever, and love me, I pray; Bless all the dear children in Thy tender care, and fit us for heaven, to live with Thee there.).'),
	(574, 'Father I Want You To Hold Me', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\nFather, I want You to hold me, \r\nI want to rest in Your arms today.\r\nFather, I want You to show me,\r\nHow much You care for me in ev\'ry way.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFather, I know You will hold me.\r\nI know I am Your child, Your own.\r\nFather, I know You will show me,\r\nI feel Your arms holding me, \r\nI\'m not alone.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI bring all my fears,\r\nAnd I lay them at Your feet.\r\nYou are always here\r\n And You love me as I am.\r\nYes You love me as I am.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI bring all my cares,\r\nAnd I lay them at Your feet.\r\nYou are always there \r\nAnd You love me as I am.\r\nYes You love me as I am.\r\n', '', '1989 Mercy Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/FIVFgYEeQQI&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Father, I want You to hold me, I want to rest in Your arms today. Father, I want You to show me, How much You care for me in ev\\\'ry way. Father, I know You will hold me. I know I am Your child, Your own. Father, I know You will show me, I feel Your arms holding me, I\\\'m not alone. I bring all my fears, And I lay them at Your feet. You are always here And You love me as I am. Yes You love me as I am. I bring all my cares, And I lay them at Your feet. You are always there And You love me as I am. Yes You love me as I am.'),
	(575, 'Rock Of Ages (There Is No Rock)', 'Rita Baloche', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]There is no [A4]rock\r\n[A]There is no [A4]god like [A]our Go[A4]d    [A]   [A4]\r\n[D]No other [D4]name\r\n[D]Worthy of [D4]all our [A]prais[A4]e   [A]   [A4]\r\nThe [E]rock of salv[E4]ation tha[E]t cannot [E4]be moved\r\nHe\'s [F#m]proven Himself to be f[D]aithful and true\r\n[B4]There is no rock\r\n[D]There is no God like [A]our[A4]s   [A]   [A4]\r\n~Chorus\r\nRock [F#m]of a--[D]ges, [A]Jesus is the [E]rock\r\nRock [F#m]of a--[D]ges, [A]Jesus is the [E]rock\r\nRock [F#m]of a--[D]ges, [A]Jesus is the [E]rock\r\n[G4]There is no rock\r\n[D]There is no God like ours  [A]\r\n~Tag\r\n[A]Rock of Ages (repeat till Jesus comes)', '', '1997 Maranatha! Music ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/fqZOMGLjKds', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=251965614&id=251963532&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Rita Baloche - Top 25 - Praise Songs Updated - Rock of Ages" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'There is no rock There is no god like our God No other name Worthy of all our praise The rock of salvation that cannot be moved He\\\'s proven Himself to be faithful and true There is no rock There is no God like ours Rock of a--ges, Jesus is the rock Rock of a--ges, Jesus is the rock Rock of a--ges, Jesus is the rock There is no rock There is no God like ours Rock of Ages (repeat till Jesus comes)'),
	(576, 'Behold What Manner Of Love', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBehold, what manner of love\r\nThe Father has given unto us,\r\nBehold, what manner of love\r\nThe Father has given unto us.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThat we should be called\r\nThe sons of God,\r\nThat we should be called\r\nThe sons of God.\r\n', '', ' 1978, Maranatha! Music, USA; ', '', '', 'Behold, what manner of love The Father has given unto us, Behold, what manner of love The Father has given unto us. That we should be called The sons of God, That we should be called The sons of God.'),
	(577, 'All Hail The Power Of Jesus\' Name (Diadem)', 'Edward Perronet, adapted by John Rippon, music by James Ellor. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAll hail the pow\'r of Jesus\' name!\r\nLet angels prostrate fall, \r\nLet angels prostrate fall;\r\nBring forth the royal diadem,\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYe chosen seed of Israel\'s race\r\nYe ransomed from the fall,\r\nYe ransomed from the fall;\r\nHail Him who saves you by His grace,\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet ev\'ry kindred, ev\'ry tribe,\r\nOn this terrestrial ball,\r\nOn this terrestrial ball;\r\nTo Him all majesty ascribe,\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO that with yonder sacred throng,\r\nWe at His feet may fall,\r\nWe at His feet may fall!\r\nWe\'ll join the everlasting song,\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAnd crown Him, crown Him,\r\n crown Him, crown Him, \r\nAnd crown Him Lord of all.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'All hail the pow\'r of Jesus\' name! Let angels prostrate fall, Let angels prostrate fall; Bring forth the royal diadem, Ye chosen seed of Israel\'s race Ye ransomed from the fall, Ye ransomed from the fall; Hail Him who saves you by His grace, Let ev\'ry kindred, ev\'ry tribe, On this terrestrial ball, On this terrestrial ball; To Him all majesty ascribe, O that with yonder sacred throng, We at His feet may fall, We at His feet may fall! We\'ll join the everlasting song, And crown Him, crown Him, crown Him, crown Him, And crown Him Lord of all.'),
	(579, 'Blessed Be The Name (All Praise To Him)', 'William H. Clark; (refrain by Ralph E. Hudson)', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAll praise to Him who reigns above\r\nIn majesty supreme\r\nWho gave His Son for man to die,\r\nThat He might man redeem\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHis name above all names shall stand\r\nExalted more and more,\r\nAt God the Father\'s own right hand,\r\nWhere angel hosts adore.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHis name shall be the Counsellor\r\nThe mighty Prince of Peace.\r\nOf all the earth\'s Kingdoms Conqueror\r\nWhose reign shall never cease.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBlessed be the name\r\nBlessed be the name\r\nBlessed be the name of the Lord\r\nBlessed be the name\r\nBlessed be the name\r\nBlessed be the name of the Lord\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nRedeemer, Savior, Friend of Man,\r\nOnce ruined by the fall,\r\nThou has devised salvation\'s plan,\r\nFor Thou hast died for all.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAlpha and Omega, \r\nEverlasting Father, \r\nMighty, Mighty God\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'All praise to Him who reigns above In majesty supreme Who gave His Son for man to die, That He might man redeem His name above all names shall stand Exalted more and more, At God the Father\'s own right hand, Where angel hosts adore. His name shall be the Counsellor The mighty Prince of Peace. Of all the earth\'s Kingdoms Conqueror Whose reign shall never cease. Blessed be the name Blessed be the name Blessed be the name of the Lord Blessed be the name Blessed be the name Blessed be the name of the Lord Redeemer, Savior, Friend of Man, Once ruined by the fall, Thou has devised salvation\'s plan, For Thou hast died for all. Alpha and Omega, Everlasting Father, Mighty, Mighty God'),
	(580, 'I Will Celebrate', 'Linda Duvall & Daniel Amstuz', '~Verse 1\r\nI will celebrate, sing unto the Lord,\r\n I will sing to Him a new song. \r\nI will celebrate, sing unto the Lord,\r\n I will sing to Him a new song.\r\n~Chorus\r\nHallelujah, hallelujah,\r\n Hallelujah, hallelujah,\r\n   Hallelu, hallelujah  \r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will praise Him,\r\n I will sing to Him a new song.\r\nI will praise Him,\r\n I will sing to Him a new song.\r\n', '', '1982 Grace Fellowship/Maranatha Music', '', '', 'I will celebrate, sing unto the Lord, I will sing to Him a new song. I will celebrate, sing unto the Lord, I will sing to Him a new song. Hallelujah, hallelujah, Hallelujah, hallelujah, Hallelu, hallelujah I will praise Him, I will sing to Him a new song. I will praise Him, I will sing to Him a new song.'),
	(581, 'You Are My Hiding Place', 'Michael Ledner. ', '[Am]You are my h[Dm]iding place, [G7]You always f[C]ill my heart with s[F]ongs of del[Dm]iverance;\r\nW[Esus]henever I am af[E]raid, I will trust in [Am]you.\r\n(round)\r\n~\r\n[Dm]I will trust in [G7]you.  [C] Let the weak say\r\n[F]"I am st[Dm]rong in the str[Esus]ength of the L[E]ord."[Am]\r\n', '', ' 1981', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/ElVC6rfX3Z8', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(You are my hiding place, You always fill my heart with songs of deliverance; Whenever I am afraid, I will trust in you. (round) I will trust in you.   Let the weak say "I am strong in the strength of the Lord.").'),
	(582, 'The Trees Of The Field', 'Stuart Dauermann.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou shall go out with joy\r\nAnd be led forth with peace.\r\nThe mountains and the hills\r\nWill break forth before you;\r\nThere\'ll be shouts of joy,\r\nAnd all the trees of the field\r\nWill clap, will clap their hands.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAnd all the trees of the field\r\nWill clap their hands,\r\nThe trees of the field will clap their hands.\r\nThe trees of the field will clap their hands,\r\nWhile you go out with joy.\r\n', '', ' 1975 Lillenas Publishing Company. ', '', '', 'You shall go out with joy And be led forth with peace. The mountains and the hills Will break forth before you; There\'ll be shouts of joy, And all the trees of the field Will clap, will clap their hands. And all the trees of the field Will clap their hands, The trees of the field will clap their hands. The trees of the field will clap their hands, While you go out with joy.'),
