	(587, 'Come Ye Thankful People Come', 'Henry Alford, music by George J. Elvey.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, ye thankful people, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home;\r\nAll is safely gathered in\r\nEre the winter storms begin.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGod, our Maker, doth provide\r\nFor our wants to be supplied;\r\nCome to God\'s own temple, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll the world is God\'s own field,\r\nFruit unto His praise to yield;\r\nWheat and tares together sown,\r\nUnto joy or sorrow grown.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFirst the blade and then the ear,\r\nThen the full corn shall appear;\r\nLord of harvest, grant that we\r\nWholesome grain and pure may be.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFor the Lord our God shall come\r\nAnd shall take His harvest-home;\r\nFrom His field shall in that day\r\nAll offenses purge away.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nGive His angels charge at last\r\nIn the fire the tares to cast,\r\nBut the fruitful ears to store\r\nIn His garner evermore.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nEven so, Lord, quickly come\r\nTo Thy final harvest-home;\r\nGather Thou Thy people in,\r\nFree from sorrow, free from sin.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nThere, forever purified,\r\nIn Thy presence to abide;\r\nCome, with all Thine angels, come\r\nRaise the glorious harvest-home. Amen.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, ye thankful people, come Raise the song of harvest-home; All is safely gathered in Ere the winter storms begin. God, our Maker, doth provide For our wants to be supplied; Come to God\'s own temple, come Raise the song of harvest-home. All the world is God\'s own field, Fruit unto His praise to yield; Wheat and tares together sown, Unto joy or sorrow grown. First the blade and then the ear, Then the full corn shall appear; Lord of harvest, grant that we Wholesome grain and pure may be. For the Lord our God shall come And shall take His harvest-home; From His field shall in that day All offenses purge away. Give His angels charge at last In the fire the tares to cast, But the fruitful ears to store In His garner evermore. Even so, Lord, quickly come To Thy final harvest-home; Gather Thou Thy people in, Free from sorrow, free from sin. There, forever purified, In Thy presence to abide; Come, with all Thine angels, come Raise the glorious harvest-home. Amen.'),
	(588, 'Come Into The King\'s Chambers', 'Daniel Gardner.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO come into the King\'s chambers\r\nAnd worship before His throne.\r\nO come into the King\'s chambers\r\nAnd His glory shall be shown.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO come into His holy presence\r\nAnd magnify His name.\r\nO come into the King\'s chambers,\r\nYou will never be the same.\r\n', '', ' 1981 Daniel Gardner Music, c/o Tempo Music Publishing.', '', '', 'O come into the King\'s chambers And worship before His throne. O come into the King\'s chambers And His glory shall be shown. O come into His holy presence And magnify His name. O come into the King\'s chambers, You will never be the same.'),
