	(628, 'Unto You', 'Gerrit Gustafson', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe bring unto You our gratitude,\r\nWe lift up to You our praise;\r\nWe offer our lives in sacrifice\r\nAs tokens our hands we raise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nUnto You, we minister - unto You;\r\nYou gave us beautiful garments of praise;\r\nSo we minister unto You;\r\nWe minister unto You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe sing unto You with songs of joy,\r\nIn garments of white we stand;\r\nThe prayers of the saints ascend to You\r\nWe come by the blood of the Lamb.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'We bring unto You our gratitude, We lift up to You our praise; We offer our lives in sacrifice As tokens our hands we raise. Unto You, we minister - unto You; You gave us beautiful garments of praise; So we minister unto You; We minister unto You. We sing unto You with songs of joy, In garments of white we stand; The prayers of the saints ascend to You We come by the blood of the Lamb.'),
	(629, 'Consuming Fire', 'Tim Hughes.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere must be more than this.\r\nO breath of God, \r\nCome breathe within.\r\nThere must be more than this.\r\nSpirit of God, we wait for You.\r\nFill us anew, we pray.\r\nFill us anew, we pray.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nCome like a rushing wind.\r\nClothe us with power \r\nfrom on high.\r\nNow set the captives free.\r\nLeave us abandoned \r\nto Your praise.\r\nLord, let Your glory fall.\r\nLord, let Your glory fall.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nConsuming Fire, fan into flame\r\nA passion for Your name.\r\nSpirit of God, fall in this place.\r\nLord, have Your way.\r\nLord, have Your way with us.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFill us anew, we pray.\r\nFill us anew, we pray.\r\n', '', ' 2002 Thankyou Music. ', '', '', 'There must be more than this. O breath of God, Come breathe within. There must be more than this. Spirit of God, we wait for You. Fill us anew, we pray. Fill us anew, we pray. Come like a rushing wind. Clothe us with power from on high. Now set the captives free. Leave us abandoned to Your praise. Lord, let Your glory fall. Lord, let Your glory fall. Consuming Fire, fan into flame A passion for Your name. Spirit of God, fall in this place. Lord, have Your way. Lord, have Your way with us. Fill us anew, we pray. Fill us anew, we pray.'),
	(630, 'O Worship The King', 'Robert Grant', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]O, worship the [Bm]King all [G]glorious a[A]bove\r\nand [D]gratefully [Bm]sing His [G]wonder[A]ful [D]love.\r\nOur [A]Shield and Defender, the [A7]Ancient of Days, \r\nPa[D]villioned in [D/F#]splendor and [G]girded [A]with [D]praise.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO, tell of His might and sing of His grace,\r\nWhose robe is the light, whose canopy space.\r\nHis chariots of wrath the deep thunderclouds form,\r\nand dark is His path on the wings of the storm.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThy bountiful care, what tongue can recite,\r\nIt breathes in the air, it shines in the light,\r\nIt streams from the hills, it descends from the plain,\r\nand sweetly distills in the dew and the rain.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFrail children of dust and feeble as frail,\r\nIn Thee do we trust, nor find Thee to fail.\r\nThy mercies how tender, how firm to the end,\r\nOur Maker, Defender, Redeemer and Friend.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'O, worship the King all glorious above and gratefully sing His wonderful love. Our Shield and Defender, the Ancient of Days, Pavillioned in splendor and girded with praise. O, tell of His might and sing of His grace, Whose robe is the light, whose canopy space. His chariots of wrath the deep thunderclouds form, and dark is His path on the wings of the storm. Thy bountiful care, what tongue can recite, It breathes in the air, it shines in the light, It streams from the hills, it descends from the plain, and sweetly distills in the dew and the rain. Frail children of dust and feeble as frail, In Thee do we trust, nor find Thee to fail. Thy mercies how tender, how firm to the end, Our Maker, Defender, Redeemer and Friend.'),
	(631, 'Rise Up, O Church Of God', 'William P. Merrill, altered, Music by Aaron Williams', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRise up, O church of God;\r\nHave done with lesser things;\r\nGive heart and mind and soul and strength\r\nTo serve the King of Kings.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nRise up! Rise up!\r\nAs followers of the Son of Man,\r\nRise up,O church of God,\r\nRise up, O church of God.\r\nRise up, rise up, rise up.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nRise up, O church of God!\r\nHis kingdom tarries long;\r\nBring in the day of brotherhood\r\nAnd end the night of wrong.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nRise up, O sons of God!\r\nThe church for you doth wait,\r\nHer strength unequal to her task,\r\nRise up, and make her great.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nLift high the cross of Christ!\r\nTread where His feet have trod;\r\nAs foll\'wers of the Son of Man,\r\nRise up, O Church of God!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Rise up, O church of God; Have done with lesser things; Give heart and mind and soul and strength To serve the King of Kings. Rise up! Rise up! As followers of the Son of Man, Rise up,O church of God, Rise up, O church of God. Rise up, rise up, rise up. Rise up, O church of God! His kingdom tarries long; Bring in the day of brotherhood And end the night of wrong. Rise up, O sons of God! The church for you doth wait, Her strength unequal to her task, Rise up, and make her great. Lift high the cross of Christ! Tread where His feet have trod; As foll\'wers of the Son of Man, Rise up, O Church of God!'),
	(632, 'Psalm 63', 'Andy Park', '~Verse 1\r\nGod, You are my God,\r\nAnd I will seek You with all my heart;\r\nMy soul is thirsty for You,\r\nTo know Your love with all my heart.\r\n~Chorus\r\nAbba Father, I receive Your love. (x2)\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour love is better than life\r\nYou satisfy my desire;\r\nI will lift up my hands\r\nTo worship You for all my life.\r\nI will worship You with all my heart.\r\nI will worship You with all my heart.\r\n', '', '1989 Mercy Publishing  ', '', '', 'God, You are my God, And I will seek You with all my heart; My soul is thirsty for You, To know Your love with all my heart. Abba Father, I receive Your love. (x2) Your love is better than life You satisfy my desire; I will lift up my hands To worship You for all my life. I will worship You with all my heart. I will worship You with all my heart.'),
	(633, 'There\'s A River Of Life', 'L. Casebolt. Copyright unknown.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI\'ve got a river of life flowing out of me;\r\nMakes the lame to walk and the blind to see;\r\nOpens prison doors,\r\nSets those captives free.\r\nI\'ve got a river of life flowing out of me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSpring up, O well, within my soul.\r\nSpring up, O well, and make me whole.\r\nSpring up, O well, and give to me\r\nThat life abundantly.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I\'ve got a river of life flowing out of me; Makes the lame to walk and the blind to see; Opens prison doors, Sets those captives free. I\'ve got a river of life flowing out of me. Spring up, O well, within my soul. Spring up, O well, and make me whole. Spring up, O well, and give to me That life abundantly.'),
	(634, 'That\'s What We Came Here For', 'Russell Fragar and Darlene Zschech.', '~Verse 1\r\nWe come into Your presence with singing,\r\nCome into Your presence with praise.\r\nAnd enter Your gates with thankful hearts,\r\nWe are going to celebrate.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou deserve the highest praise \r\nThat we can give and more.\r\nLord, we give You our praise, \r\nThat\'s what we came here for. \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll of heaven\'s waiting,\r\nPow\'r is on it\'s way.\r\nSo we shout "Hallelujah", \r\nLifting to You a mighty roar of praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nEverything within me reaches out to You.\r\nYour power and majesty, \r\nGrace, and mercy too.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere\'ll be singing, and dancing.\r\nHearts and voices raised.\r\nYou have set Your people free, \r\nNow the house is filled with praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nYou deserve the highest praise.\r\nYou deserve the highest praise.\r\n', '', ' 1997 Russell Fragar and Darlene Zschech/Hillsong Publishing.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/UXSTcNuxvC4', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(We come into Your presence with singing, Come into Your presence with praise. And enter Your gates with thankful hearts, We are going to celebrate. You deserve the highest praise That we can give and more. Lord, we give You our praise, That\'s what we came here for. All of heaven\'s waiting, Pow\'r is on it\'s way. So we shout "Hallelujah", Lifting to You a mighty roar of praise. Everything within me reaches out to You. Your power and majesty, Grace, and mercy too. There\'ll be singing, and dancing. Hearts and voices raised. You have set Your people free, Now the house is filled with praise. You deserve the highest praise. You deserve the highest praise.).'),
	(635, 'Alleluia! Alleluia!', 'Christopher Wordsworth, altered music by Ludwig van Beethoven,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAlleluia! Alleluia!\r\nHearts to heav\'n and voices raise;\r\nSing to God a hymn of gladness,\r\nSing to God a hymn of praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe who on the cross as Savior \r\nFor the world\'s salvation bled,\r\nJesus Christ, the King of Glory, \r\nNow is risen from the dead.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nNow the iron bars are broken,\r\nChrist from death to life is born,\r\nGlorious life, and life immortal,\r\nOn this resurrection morn;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nChrist has triumphed, and we conquer\r\nBy His mighty enterprise,\r\nWe with Him to life eternal \r\nBy His resurrection rise.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Alleluia! Alleluia! Hearts to heav\'n and voices raise; Sing to God a hymn of gladness, Sing to God a hymn of praise. He who on the cross as Savior For the world\'s salvation bled, Jesus Christ, the King of Glory, Now is risen from the dead. Now the iron bars are broken, Christ from death to life is born, Glorious life, and life immortal, On this resurrection morn; Christ has triumphed, and we conquer By His mighty enterprise, We with Him to life eternal By His resurrection rise.'),
	(636, 'Jesus Lover Of My Soul', 'John Ezzy, Daniel Grul and Stephen McPherson', '~Verse 1\r\nJesus, lover of my soul,\r\nJesus, I will never let You go;\r\nYou\'ve taken me from the miry clay,\r\nYou\'ve set my feet upon the Rock\r\nAnd now I know.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI love You, I need You,\r\nThough my world will fall,\r\nI\'ll never let You go.\r\nMy Saviour, my closest Friend,\r\nI will worship You until the very end.\r\n', '', '1992 Hillsongs Australia (adm. in U.S. and Canada by Integrity Hosanna! ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/C5jxwHjC6Xk', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Jesus, lover of my soul, Jesus, I will never let You go; You\'ve taken me from the miry clay, You\'ve set my feet upon the Rock And now I know. I love You, I need You, Though my world will fall, I\'ll never let You go. My Saviour, my closest Friend, I will worship You until the very end.).'),
	(637, 'We\'ll Understand It Better By And By', 'Charles A. Tindley', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nTrials dark on ev\'ry hand\r\nAnd we cannot understand\r\nAll the ways that God would lead us to that 	 blessed Promised Land;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBut He\'ll guide us with His eye,\r\nAnd we\'ll follow till we die;\r\nWe will understand it better by and by.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nOft our cherished plans have failed,\r\nDisappointments have prevailed,\r\nAnd we\'ve wandered in the darkness,\r\nHeavy-hearted and alone;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBut we\'re trusting in the Lord,\r\nAnd, according to His Word,\r\nWe will understand it better by and by.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nBy and by, when the morning comes,\r\nWhen the saints of God are gathered home,\r\nWe will tell the story how we\'ve overcome;\r\nWe will understand it better by and by.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Trials dark on ev\'ry hand And we cannot understand All the ways that God would lead us to that 	 blessed Promised Land; But He\'ll guide us with His eye, And we\'ll follow till we die; We will understand it better by and by. Oft our cherished plans have failed, Disappointments have prevailed, And we\'ve wandered in the darkness, Heavy-hearted and alone; But we\'re trusting in the Lord, And, according to His Word, We will understand it better by and by. By and by, when the morning comes, When the saints of God are gathered home, We will tell the story how we\'ve overcome; We will understand it better by and by.'),
	(638, 'O How I Love Jesus', 'Frederick Whitfield; music: Traditional American melody. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere is a name I love to hear,\r\nI love to sing its worth;\r\nIt sounds like music in my ear,\r\nThe sweetest name on earth.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIt tells me of a Savior\'s love,\r\nWho died to set me free;\r\nIt tells me of His precious blood,\r\nThe sinner\'s perfect plea.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIt tells me what my Father hath\r\nIn store for ev\'ry day,\r\nAnd, tho I tread a darksome path,\r\nYields sunshine all the way.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIt tells of One whose loving heart\r\nCan feel my deepest woe,\r\nWho in each sorrow bears a part\r\nThat none can bear below.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nO, how I love Jesus,\r\nO, how I love Jesus,\r\nO, how I love Jesus\r\nBecause He first loved me!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'There is a name I love to hear, I love to sing its worth; It sounds like music in my ear, The sweetest name on earth. It tells me of a Savior\'s love, Who died to set me free; It tells me of His precious blood, The sinner\'s perfect plea. It tells me what my Father hath In store for ev\'ry day, And, tho I tread a darksome path, Yields sunshine all the way. It tells of One whose loving heart Can feel my deepest woe, Who in each sorrow bears a part That none can bear below. O, how I love Jesus, O, how I love Jesus, O, how I love Jesus Because He first loved me!'),
	(639, 'Pass Me Not', 'Fanny J. Crosby, music by William H. Doan. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPass me not, O gentle Savior\r\nHear my humble cry!\r\nWhile on others Thou art calling\r\nDo not pass me by.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLet me at a throne of mercy\r\nFind a sweet relief;\r\nKneeling there in deep contrition\r\nHelp my unbelief.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTrusting only in Thy merit,\r\nWould I seek Thy face;\r\nHeal my wounded, broken spirit,\r\nSave me by Thy grace.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThou the spring of all my comfort,\r\nMore than life to me!\r\nWhom have I on earth beside Thee?\r\nWhom in heav\'n but Thee?\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSavior, Savior,\r\nHear my humble cry!\r\nWhile on others Thou art calling,\r\nDo not pass me by.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Pass me not, O gentle Savior Hear my humble cry! While on others Thou art calling Do not pass me by. Let me at a throne of mercy Find a sweet relief; Kneeling there in deep contrition Help my unbelief. Trusting only in Thy merit, Would I seek Thy face; Heal my wounded, broken spirit, Save me by Thy grace. Thou the spring of all my comfort, More than life to me! Whom have I on earth beside Thee? Whom in heav\'n but Thee? Savior, Savior, Hear my humble cry! While on others Thou art calling, Do not pass me by.'),
	(640, 'Come Thou Almighty King', '', '{t:Come, Thou Almighty King}\r\nCome, Thou almighty King,\r\nHelp us Thy Name to sing, help us to praise!\r\nFather all glorious, over all victorious,\r\nCome and reign over us, Ancient of Days!\r\n\r\nCome, Thou incarnate Word,\r\nGird on Thy mighty sword, our prayer attend!\r\nCome, and Thy people bless, and give Thy Word success,\r\nSpirit of holiness, on us descend!\r\n\r\nCome, holy Comforter,\r\nThy sacred witness bear in this glad hour.\r\nThou Who almighty art, now rule in every heart,\r\nAnd ne\'er from us depart, Spirit of power!\r\n\r\nTo Thee, great One in Three,\r\nEternal praises be, hence, evermore.\r\nThy sovereign majesty may we in glory see,\r\nAnd to eternity love and adore!\r\n\r\n{c:Text: Anonymous, or Charles Wesley, 1757}\r\n{c:Tune: Felice de Giardini}\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/0qYp23aupLc', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Come, Thou almighty King, Help us Thy Name to sing, help us to praise! Father all glorious, over all victorious, Come and reign over us, Ancient of Days! Come, Thou incarnate Word, Gird on Thy mighty sword, our prayer attend! Come, and Thy people bless, and give Thy Word success, Spirit of holiness, on us descend! Come, holy Comforter, Thy sacred witness bear in this glad hour. Thou Who almighty art, now rule in every heart, And ne\'er from us depart, Spirit of power! To Thee, great One in Three, Eternal praises be, hence, evermore. Thy sovereign majesty may we in glory see, And to eternity love and adore!).'),
	(641, 'All Heaven Declares', 'Noel & Tricia Richards, ', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]All heav\'n [D]declares [Esus4]\r\nThe [E]glory of the [D/A]risen [A]Lord\r\nWho can com[D]pare [Esus4]\r\n[E]With the beauty [D/A]of the [A]Lord?\r\nForever he will [D]be [E]\r\nThe Lamb upon the [A]throne [E/G#][F#m7]\r\nI gladly bow my [D]knee [E7]\r\nAnd worship him [A]alone [D/A][A]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will proclaim\r\nThe glory of the risen Lord\r\nWho once was slain\r\nTo reconcile us to God\r\nForever you will be\r\nThe Lamb upon the throne\r\nI gladly bow my knee\r\nAnd worship you alone\r\n', '', '1987 Kingsway\'s Thankyou Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/FXnvckvpBxU', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(All heav\'n declares The glory of the risen Lord Who can compare With the beauty of the Lord? Forever he will be The Lamb upon the throne I gladly bow my knee And worship him alone I will proclaim The glory of the risen Lord Who once was slain To reconcile us to God Forever you will be The Lamb upon the throne I gladly bow my knee And worship you alone).'),
	(642, 'Blessing And Honour', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBlessing and honor\r\nGlory and power\r\nRiches and wisdom and strength\r\n(repeat)\r\n	 	 	 \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBe unto You unto You\r\nWho sits at the right hand of God\r\nBe unto You unto You\r\nWho sits at the right hand of God\r\nUnto You\r\n\r\n', '', ' 2000 TMMI Music (Admin. by Music Services) ', '', '', 'Blessing and honor Glory and power Riches and wisdom and strength (repeat) Be unto You unto You Who sits at the right hand of God Be unto You unto You Who sits at the right hand of God Unto You'),
	(643, 'One Way', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\n\r\nI lay my life down at Your feet\r\nYou\'re the only One I need\r\nI turn to You and You are always there\r\nIn troubled times it\'s You I seek\r\nI put You first that\'s all I need\r\nI humble all I am all to You\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou are always\r\nAlways there\r\nEvery how and every where\r\nYour grace abounds so deeply within me\r\nYou will never ever change\r\nYesterday today the same\r\nForever \'til forever meets no end\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nOne way Jesus\r\nYou\'re the only One that I could live for\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nYou are the Way\r\nThe Truth and the Life\r\nWe live by faith and not by sight\r\nFor You\r\nWe\'re living all for You\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'I lay my life down at Your feet You\'re the only One I need I turn to You and You are always there In troubled times it\'s You I seek I put You first that\'s all I need I humble all I am all to You You are always Always there Every how and every where Your grace abounds so deeply within me You will never ever change Yesterday today the same Forever \'til forever meets no end One way Jesus You\'re the only One that I could live for You are the Way The Truth and the Life We live by faith and not by sight For You We\'re living all for You'),
	(644, 'Praise Him', 'Rob Rife', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGive thanks to the Lord\r\nFor He is good and His mercies unending\r\nSing praise to the Lord for He is good.\r\nPraise to the Lord most high.\r\nPraise Him!  (repeat)\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSing to the Lord a new song\r\nSing praise to the Lord now. \r\n', '', '1991 Rob Rife. ', '', '', 'Give thanks to the Lord For He is good and His mercies unending Sing praise to the Lord for He is good. Praise to the Lord most high. Praise Him!  (repeat) Sing to the Lord a new song Sing praise to the Lord now.'),
	(645, 'Rock Of Ages', 'Augustus M. Toplady; Music by Thomas Hastings.  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRock of Ages, cleft for me,\r\nLet me hide myself in Thee;\r\nLet the water and the blood, \r\nFrom Thy riven side which flowed,\r\nBe of sin the double cure, \r\nCleanse me from its guilt and pow\'r.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nNot the labours of my hands \r\nCan fulfill Thy law\'s demands;\r\nCould my zeal no respite know, \r\nCould my tears forever Flow,\r\nAll for sin could not atone; \r\nThou must save and thou alone.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nNothing in my hand I bring, \r\nSimply to Thy cross I cling;\r\nNaked, come to thee for dress, \r\nHelpless, look to Thee for grace; \r\nFoul, I to the fountain fly, \r\nWash me Saviour or I die!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhile I draw this fleeting breath,\r\nWhen my eyes shall close in death,\r\nWhen I soar to worlds unknown, \r\nSee Thee on Thy judgement throne,\r\nRock of ages, cleft for me,\r\nLet me hide myself in Thee.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Rock of Ages, cleft for me, Let me hide myself in Thee; Let the water and the blood, From Thy riven side which flowed, Be of sin the double cure, Cleanse me from its guilt and pow\'r. Not the labours of my hands Can fulfill Thy law\'s demands; Could my zeal no respite know, Could my tears forever Flow, All for sin could not atone; Thou must save and thou alone. Nothing in my hand I bring, Simply to Thy cross I cling; Naked, come to thee for dress, Helpless, look to Thee for grace; Foul, I to the fountain fly, Wash me Saviour or I die! While I draw this fleeting breath, When my eyes shall close in death, When I soar to worlds unknown, See Thee on Thy judgement throne, Rock of ages, cleft for me, Let me hide myself in Thee.'),
	(646, 'I Will Magnify', 'Russell L. Lowe. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI will magnify\r\nYour name, O Lord.\r\nI will exalt You forever more.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFor You are King of kings\r\n And Lord of lords\r\nAnd You reign in majesty;\r\nOmnipotent Father\r\nCreator of all things.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1989 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music,', '', '', 'I will magnify Your name, O Lord. I will exalt You forever more. For You are King of kings And Lord of lords And You reign in majesty; Omnipotent Father Creator of all things.'),
	(647, 'I Will Sing Unto The Lord As Long As I Live', 'Donya Brockway', '~Verse 1\r\nI will sing unto the Lord as long as I live\r\nI will sing praise to my God\r\n While I have my being.\r\nMy meditation of Him shall be sweet,\r\nI will be glad, I will be glad in the Lord.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBless thou the Lord, O my soul,\r\nPraise ye the Lord.\r\n\r\n', '', '1972', '', '', 'I will sing unto the Lord as long as I live I will sing praise to my God While I have my being. My meditation of Him shall be sweet, I will be glad, I will be glad in the Lord. Bless thou the Lord, O my soul, Praise ye the Lord.'),
	(648, 'Angels We Have Heard On High', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[F]Angels we[Am] have heard on [C]high [F]\r\nS[F]weetly s[C]ingin[F] o\'er th[F]e pl[C]ain[F]s\r\na[F]nd the m[Am]ountains in re[C]ply [F]\r\nech[F]o ba[C]ck[F] thei[F]r joy[F]ous strain[F]s\r\n~Chorus\r\nGlo-ria,\r\n In excelsis De-o,\r\nGlo-ria,\r\n In excelsis De-o.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[F]Shepherds[Am], why this Jubi[C]lee[F]?\r\nW[F]hy your [C]joyou[F]s strain[F]s pr[C]olong[F]?\r\ns[F]ay what [Am]may the tidings be[C],    [F]\r\nWhi[F]ch i[C]ns[F]pire [F]your [F]heavenly  so[F]ng?\r\n~Verse 3\r\n[F]Come to B[Am]ethlehem an[C]d s[F]ee\r\nH[F]im whose[C] birt[F]h the an[F]gels[C] sing[F];\r\nC[F]ome, ado[Am]re on bended knee [C]     [F]\r\nChr[F]ist,[C] the[F] Lord[F], the[F] newborn kin[F]g)\r\n~Verse 4\r\n[F]See him i[Am]n a manger[C] la[F]id.\r\nJ[F]esus Lor[C]d of [F]heaven a[F]nd e[C]arth [F]\r\nM[F]ary,Jose[Am]ph lend your a[C]id   [F]\r\nCel[F]ebra[C]te[F]s our[F] Savi[F]or\'s bir[F]ht\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Angels we have heard on high Sweetly singin o\'er the plains and the mountains in reply echo back their joyous strains Glo-ria, In excelsis De-o, Glo-ria, In excelsis De-o. Shepherds, why this Jubilee? Why your joyous strains prolong? say what may the tidings be, Which inspire your heavenly  song? Come to Bethlehem and see Him whose birth the angels sing; Come, adore on bended knee Christ, the Lord, the newborn king) See him in a manger laid. Jesus Lord of heaven and earth Mary,Joseph lend your aid Celebrates our Savior\'s birht'),
	(649, 'As I Abide In You', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou make my joy complete\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAs I abide in You\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nYou fill my ev\'ry need\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAs I abide in You.\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nI will remain in You for all of my days.\r\nYou will shelter me as I give You praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nYou answer ev\'ry prayer,\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nAs I abide in You\r\n~Verse 9\r\n\r\nI feel Your love and care\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nAs I abide in You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nI will remain in You for all of my days.\r\nYou will shelter me as I give You praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 13\r\n\r\n\r\nI will sing of Your love.\r\nI will bring all of my love.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'You make my joy complete As I abide in You You fill my ev\'ry need As I abide in You. I will remain in You for all of my days. You will shelter me as I give You praise. You answer ev\'ry prayer, As I abide in You I feel Your love and care As I abide in You. I will remain in You for all of my days. You will shelter me as I give You praise. I will sing of Your love. I will bring all of my love.'),
	(650, 'Come Let Us Offer', 'Marlene Bigley', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome let us offer the sacrifice of praise.\r\nCome let us offer the sacrifice of praise\r\nThe fruit of our lips giving thanks,\r\nThe fruit of our lips giving thanks.\r\nCome and offer sacrifices,\r\nCome and offer praise unto the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1985 Tempo Music Publications, Inc. International C secured.', '', '', 'Come let us offer the sacrifice of praise. Come let us offer the sacrifice of praise The fruit of our lips giving thanks, The fruit of our lips giving thanks. Come and offer sacrifices, Come and offer praise unto the Lord.'),
	(651, 'He Hideth My Soul', 'Fanny J. Crosby; music by William J. Kirkpatrick.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nA wonderful Savior is Jesus my Lord,\r\nA wonderful Savior to me;\r\nHe hideth my soul in the cleft of the rock,\r\nWhere rivers of pleasure I see.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nA wonderful Savior is Jesus my Lord\r\nHe taketh my burden away;\r\nHe hgoldeth me up and I shall not be moved,\r\nHe giveth me strength as my day.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWith numberless blessings\r\nEach moment He crowns,\r\nAnd filled with His fullness devine,\r\nI sing in my rapture, "O glory to God\r\nFor such a Redeemer as mine!"\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhen clothed in His brightness\r\nTransported I rise,\r\nTo meet Him in clouds of the sky,\r\nHis perfect salvation, His wonderful love,\r\nI\'ll shout with the millions on high.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHe hideth my soul in the cleft of the rock\r\nThat shadows a dry, thirsty land\'\r\nHe hideth my life in the depths of His love,\r\nAnd covers me there with His hand,\r\nAnd covers me there with His hand.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'A wonderful Savior is Jesus my Lord, A wonderful Savior to me; He hideth my soul in the cleft of the rock, Where rivers of pleasure I see. A wonderful Savior is Jesus my Lord He taketh my burden away; He hgoldeth me up and I shall not be moved, He giveth me strength as my day. With numberless blessings Each moment He crowns, And filled with His fullness devine, I sing in my rapture, "O glory to God For such a Redeemer as mine!" When clothed in His brightness Transported I rise, To meet Him in clouds of the sky, His perfect salvation, His wonderful love, I\'ll shout with the millions on high. He hideth my soul in the cleft of the rock That shadows a dry, thirsty land\' He hideth my life in the depths of His love, And covers me there with His hand, And covers me there with His hand.'),
	(652, 'Celebrate Jesus', 'Gary Oliver', '~Verse 1\r\n[F]Celebr[Bb]ate [C]Jesus, [F]Celebrate[Bb],[C]\r\n[F]Celebr[Bb]ate [C]Jesus, [Gm]Celebrat[F]e;[C][D]\r\n[F]Celebr[Bb]ate [C]Jesus, [F]Celebrate[Bb],[C]\r\n[F]Celebr[Bb]ate [C]Jesus, [Gm]Celebrat[F]e.\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[F]He is [C]ris-en, He is [Dm]ris-en,\r\nand He [C]lives forev[Dm]ermore;\r\n[Bb]He is [C]ris-en, He is [Dm]ris-en,\r\ncome on and [C]celebrate_\r\nthe resurr[Bb]ection [C]of our [F]Lord.\r\n', '', '1988 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/XV15GBkgJgs&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'Celebrate Jesus, Celebrate, Celebrate Jesus, Celebrate; Celebrate Jesus, Celebrate, Celebrate Jesus, Celebrate. He is ris-en, He is ris-en, and He lives forevermore; He is ris-en, He is ris-en, come on and celebrate_ the resurrection of our Lord.'),
	(653, 'That\'s Why We Praise Him', 'Tommy Walker', '~Verse 1\r\nHe came to live, live a perfect life;\r\nHe came to be - the living word, our light.\r\nHe came to die so we\'d be reconciled.\r\nHe came to rise\r\n To show His pow\'r and might,\r\n~Chorus\r\nThat\'s why we praise Him; \r\nThat\'s why we sing.\r\nThat\'s why we offer Him our ev\'rything.\r\nThat\'s why we bow down\r\n And worship this King,\r\nCause He gave His ev\'rything, \r\nCause He gave His ev\'rything.\r\n~Bridge\r\nHalle, hallelujah! Halle, hallelujah!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe came to live; live again in us.\r\nHe came to be \r\n Our con-q\'ring King - our friend.\r\nHe came to heal \r\nAnd show the lost ones His love.\r\nHe came to go - prepare a place for us,', '', '1998 WeMobile Music / BMI', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/G2Fjad3asbo&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'He came to live, live a perfect life; He came to be - the living word, our light. He came to die so we\\\'d be reconciled. He came to rise To show His pow\\\'r and might, That\\\'s why we praise Him; That\\\'s why we sing. That\\\'s why we offer Him our ev\\\'rything. That\\\'s why we bow down And worship this King, Cause He gave His ev\\\'rything, Cause He gave His ev\\\'rything. Halle, hallelujah! Halle, hallelujah! He came to live; live again in us. He came to be Our con-q\\\'ring King - our friend. He came to heal And show the lost ones His love. He came to go - prepare a place for us,'),
	(654, 'Heavenly Father', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHeavenly Father, give grace to me,\r\nYour righteousness I will ever be.\r\nHeavenly Father, give grace to me -\r\nWith you I will ever be.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHeavenly Father, give light to me,\r\nThat once blind eyes may ever see.\r\nHeavenly Father, give light to me -\r\nIn darkness I will never be.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHeavenly Father, give love to me,\r\nYour arm of tenderness I will ever be.\r\nHeavenly Father, give love to me -\r\nIn hatred I will never be.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd when I falter I will lift up my head,\r\nI\'ll lift my eyes to God and pray\r\nYes, when I falter I will lift up my head,\r\nI\'ll lift my hands to God and say ...\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHeavenly Father, give hope to me,\r\nThat dark despair I may never see.\r\nHeavenly Father , give hope to me -\r\nAlone I will never be.\r\n', '', ' 1993 Robert A.Rife  ARR. UBP  ', '', '', 'Heavenly Father, give grace to me, Your righteousness I will ever be. Heavenly Father, give grace to me - With you I will ever be. Heavenly Father, give light to me, That once blind eyes may ever see. Heavenly Father, give light to me - In darkness I will never be. Heavenly Father, give love to me, Your arm of tenderness I will ever be. Heavenly Father, give love to me - In hatred I will never be. And when I falter I will lift up my head, I\'ll lift my eyes to God and pray Yes, when I falter I will lift up my head, I\'ll lift my hands to God and say ... Heavenly Father, give hope to me, That dark despair I may never see. Heavenly Father , give hope to me - Alone I will never be.'),
	(655, 'Take My Life And Let It Be', 'Frances Ridley Havergal', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Take my life and [A7]let it [D]be\r\nConse[Em7]crated[D], Lord[A7], t[D]o Thee;\r\n[D]Take my [A]moments and my [D]days,\r\nLet them [Em]flow in [D]ceaseless [A]praise,\r\n[G]Let them [Bm]flow in [G]cease[A]less [D]praise.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nTake my hands and let them move\r\nAt the impulse of Thy love;\r\nTake my feet and let them be\r\nSwift and beautiful for Thee,\r\nSwift and beautiful for Thee.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTake my voice and let me sing\r\nAlways, only, for my King;\r\nTake my lips and let them be\r\nFilled with messages from Thee,\r\nFilled with messages from Thee.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nTake my silver and my gold\r\nNot a mite would I withhold;\r\nTake my intellect and use\r\nEv\'ry pow\'r as Thou shalt choose,\r\nEv\'ry pow\'r as Thou shalt choose.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nTake my will and make it Thine\r\nIt shall be no longer mine,\r\nTake my heart it is Thine own,\r\nIt shall be Thy royal throne,\r\nIt shall be Thy royal throne.\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTake my love my Lord, I pour\r\nAt Thy feet its treasure store;\r\nTake myself and I will be\r\nEver, only, all for Thee,\r\nEver, only, all for Thee.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/lQ93HVuYd5Y', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Take my life and let it be Consecrated, Lord, to Thee; Take my moments and my days, Let them flow in ceaseless praise, Let them flow in ceaseless praise. Take my hands and let them move At the impulse of Thy love; Take my feet and let them be Swift and beautiful for Thee, Swift and beautiful for Thee. Take my voice and let me sing Always, only, for my King; Take my lips and let them be Filled with messages from Thee, Filled with messages from Thee. Take my silver and my gold Not a mite would I withhold; Take my intellect and use Ev\'ry pow\'r as Thou shalt choose, Ev\'ry pow\'r as Thou shalt choose. Take my will and make it Thine It shall be no longer mine, Take my heart it is Thine own, It shall be Thy royal throne, It shall be Thy royal throne. Take my love my Lord, I pour At Thy feet its treasure store; Take myself and I will be Ever, only, all for Thee, Ever, only, all for Thee.).'),
	(656, 'Every Move I Make', 'David Ruis', '[G]Every move I m[C]ake, I make in yo[D]u\r\nYou make me [C]move (Jesus)\r\n[G]Every breath I [C]take, I breathe in [D]you   [C]\r\n\r\n[G]Every step I [C]take, I take in [D]you\r\nYou are my wa[C]y (Jesus)\r\n[G]Every breath I t[C]ake, I breathe in y[D]ou\r\n\r\n[G]La la la la la l[C]a, la la la la l[D]a la la la\r\n[G]La la la la la l[C]a, la la la la l[D]a la la la\r\n\r\n[G]Waves of m[Am7]ercy, w[Bm]aves of g[C]rac[D]e\r\n[G]Everywhe[Am7]re I look,[Bm] I see[C] your[D] face\r\n[G]Your love[Am7] has cap[Bm]tured [C]me [D]\r\n[G]O my God[Am7], this lo[Bm]ve, how can[C] it[D] be? [G][C][D][C]\r\n{eoc}\r\n\r\n{c:David Ruis}\r\n{c:(c)1996 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing}\r\n', '', '1996 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing (ASCAP)', '<iframe width="420" height="315" src="//www.youtube.com/v/UuSy1ny2D8Q" frameborder="0" allowfullscreen></iframe>', '', 'Every move I make, I make in you You make me move (Jesus) Every breath I take, I breathe in you Every step I take, I take in you You are my way (Jesus) Every breath I take, I breathe in you La la la la la la, la la la la la la la la La la la la la la, la la la la la la la la Waves of mercy, waves of grace Everywhere I look, I see your face Your love has captured me O my God, this love, how can it be?'),
	(657, 'I Will Bow To You', 'Peter Episcopo', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, I will bow to You\r\nTo no other God\r\nBut You alone\r\nLord, I will worship You\r\nNothing hands have made\r\nBut You alone\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will lay down my idols\r\nThrones I have made\r\nAll that has taken my heart\r\nLord, I will bow to You\r\nTo no other God\r\nBut You alone\r\n', '', '2001 Integrity\'s Praise! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/gmQ4l7PWLi0', '', 'Lord, I will bow to You To no other God But You alone Lord, I will worship You Nothing hands have made But You alone I will lay down my idols Thrones I have made All that has taken my heart Lord, I will bow to You To no other God But You alone'),
	(658, 'I Offer My Life', 'Claire Cloninger and Don Moen', '~Verse 1\r\nAll that I am, all that I have,\r\nI lay them down before You, O Lord;\r\nAll my regrets, all my acclaim, \r\nThe joy and the pain, \r\nI\'m making them Yours.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord, I offer my life to You,\r\nEv\'rything I\'ve been through,\r\nUse it for Your glory;\r\nLord, I offer my days to You,\r\nLifting my praise to You\r\nAs a pleasing sacrifice,\r\nLord, I offer You my life.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThings in the past,\r\nThings yet unseen,\r\nWishes and dreams\r\nThat are yet to come true,\r\nAll of my hopes, all of my plans,\r\nMy heart and my hands\r\nAre lifted to You.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhat can we give\r\nThat You have not given;\r\nAnd what do we have\r\nThat is not already Yours?\r\nAll we possess \r\nare these lives we\'re living,\r\nAnd that\'s what we give to You, Lord.\r\n', '', '1994 Juniper Landing Music (admin. by Word Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/t-JJg-8qPso', '<a href="https://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/i-offer-my-life/id626456799?i=626457212&uo=4" target="itunes_store">I Offer My Life - God Will Make a Way: The Best of Don Moen</a>', 'All that I am, all that I have, I lay them down before You, O Lord; All my regrets, all my acclaim, The joy and the pain, I\'m making them Yours. Lord, I offer my life to You, Ev\'rything I\'ve been through, Use it for Your glory; Lord, I offer my days to You, Lifting my praise to You As a pleasing sacrifice, Lord, I offer You my life. Things in the past, Things yet unseen, Wishes and dreams That are yet to come true, All of my hopes, all of my plans, My heart and my hands Are lifted to You. What can we give That You have not given; And what do we have That is not already Yours? All we possess are these lives we\'re living, And that\'s what we give to You, Lord.'),
	(659, 'We Wish You A Merry Christmas', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGood tidings to you wherever you are\r\nGood tidings for Christmas\r\n and a Happy New Year\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe wish you a Merry Christmas\r\nWe wish you a Merry Christmas\r\nWe wish you a Merry Christmas\r\nAnd a happy New Year!\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Good tidings to you wherever you are Good tidings for Christmas and a Happy New Year We wish you a Merry Christmas We wish you a Merry Christmas We wish you a Merry Christmas And a happy New Year!'),
	(660, 'Turn Your Eyes Upon Jesus', 'Helen Lemmel', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]Turn your [A]eyes upon [Bm]Jesus,\r\nLook [G]full in His wonderful [A]face[A7],\r\nand the [D]things of [D7]earth will grow [G]strangly [Gm]dim\r\nIn the [D]light of His [Em]glory [A]and g[D]race.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nKeep your eyes upon Jesus,\r\nAnd others will not take His place,\r\nBut through every hour,\r\n He will give you power,\r\n\'Til at last you have run the straight race.\r\n', '', '1922, Renewal 1950, by H.H. Lemmel', '', '', 'Turn your eyes upon Jesus, Look full in His wonderful face, and the things of earth will grow strangly dim In the light of His glory and grace. Keep your eyes upon Jesus, And others will not take His place, But through every hour, He will give you power, \'Til at last you have run the straight race.'),
	(661, 'Only A God Like You', 'Tommy Walker. ', '~Verse 1\r\nFor the praises of man \r\nI will never ever stand,\r\nFor the kingdoms of this world\r\nI\'ll never give my heart away\r\nOr shout my praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOnly a God like You \r\nCould be worthy of my praise \r\nAnd all my hope and faith\r\nTo only a King of all kings\r\nDo I bow my knee and sing\r\nGive my everything \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTo only my Maker, \r\nMy Father, my Savior\r\nRedeemer, Restorer, \r\nRebuilder, Rewarder\r\nTo only a God like You \r\nDo I give my praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nMy allegiance and devotion\r\nMy heart\'s desire and all emotion \r\nGo to serve the Man \r\nWho died upon that tree.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nOnly a God like You\r\nOnly a God like You\r\nOnly a God like You\r\nOnly a God like You\r\n', '', '2000 Integrity\'s Praise Music/BMI.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/-6O8blhOpQY', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(For the praises of man I will never ever stand, For the kingdoms of this world I\'ll never give my heart away Or shout my praise. Only a God like You Could be worthy of my praise And all my hope and faith To only a King of all kings Do I bow my knee and sing Give my everything To only my Maker, My Father, my Savior Redeemer, Restorer, Rebuilder, Rewarder To only a God like You Do I give my praise. My allegiance and devotion My heart\'s desire and all emotion Go to serve the Man Who died upon that tree. Only a God like You Only a God like You Only a God like You Only a God like You).'),
	(662, 'Sing Hallelujah To The Lord', 'Linda Stassen', '~Verse 1\r\nSing Hallelujah to the Lord,\r\nSing Hallelujah to the Lord,\r\nSing Hallelujah, Sing Hallelujah,\r\nSing Hallelujah to the Lord!\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1974, New Song Ministries', '', '', 'Sing Hallelujah to the Lord, Sing Hallelujah to the Lord, Sing Hallelujah, Sing Hallelujah, Sing Hallelujah to the Lord!'),
	(663, 'Lamb Of God', 'Twila Paris ', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]Your only Son, no sin to hide\r\nBut You [G/B]have [Am]sent Him from Your [Gsus4]side [G]\r\nTo [C/E]walk up[Am]on this guilty [Fmaj7]sod\r\nAnd to be[C/G]come the Lamb [G]of [C]God\r\n~Chorus\r\nO Lamb [G/B]of [Am]God, sweet Lamb of [C]God\r\nI love the [Am]holy Lamb of [Gsus4]God [G]\r\nO [C/E]wash me [Am]in Your [Em]precious [Fmaj7]blood\r\nMy Jesus [C/G]Christ the [Gsus4]Lamb [G]of [C]God\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour gift of love they crucified\r\nThey laughed and scorned Him as He died\r\nThe humble King they named a fraud\r\nAnd sacrificed the Lamb of God\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI was so lost, I should have died\r\nBut You have brought me to Your side\r\nTo be led by Your staff and rod\r\nAnd to be called a lamb of God\r\n', '', '1986 Straightway Music/Admin. By Gaither Copyright Management   ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/x_-flIpeAsc?fs=1&hl=en_US', '', 'Your only Son, no sin to hide But You have sent Him from Your side To walk upon this guilty sod And to become the Lamb of God O Lamb of God, sweet Lamb of God I love the holy Lamb of God O wash me in Your precious blood My Jesus Christ the Lamb of God Your gift of love they crucified They laughed and scorned Him as He died The humble King they named a fraud And sacrificed the Lamb of God I was so lost, I should have died But You have brought me to Your side To be led by Your staff and rod And to be called a lamb of God'),
	(664, 'What A Mighty God We Serve', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]What a mighty God [G]we [D]serve, \r\nWhat a mighty God we [A]serve.\r\n[D]Angels bow before Him,\r\n[]Heaven and earth adore Him,\r\n[D]What a mighty [A]God [A7]we [D]serve.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe is the King of Kings\r\nHe is the Lord of Lords\r\nHis name is \r\nJesus, Jesus, Jesus, Jesus\r\nOh, He is the King. \r\nOh, He is the King. \r\n', '', '', '', '', 'What a mighty God we serve, What a mighty God we serve. Angels bow before Him, Heaven and earth adore Him, What a mighty God we serve. He is the King of Kings He is the Lord of Lords His name is Jesus, Jesus, Jesus, Jesus Oh, He is the King. Oh, He is the King.'),
	(665, 'You Are My God (You Are My King)', 'Macon Delavan, ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are my God; You are my King\r\nYou are my Master,  my everything\r\nYou are my Lord, that\'s why I sing to You.\r\nA-le-lu-ia! A-le-lu-ia!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '1984 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music,   A.R.R,I.C.S,U.B.P, ', '', '', 'You are my God; You are my King You are my Master,  my everything You are my Lord, that\'s why I sing to You. A-le-lu-ia! A-le-lu-ia!'),
	(666, 'Hungry', 'Kathryn Scott. ', '{t:Hungry}\n{su:Falling On My Knees}\n[C]Hungry, I come t[Am7]o You for I kn[G]ow You satis[F]fy\n[C]I am empty, b[Am7]ut I know Your lo[G]ve does not run d[F]ry\nAnd so I [G]wait for Y[F/A]ou so I [G/B]wait for Yo[F]u\n\n{soc}\nI\'m [C]falling on my kn[Fmaj7]ees\nOff[C]ering all of [Fmaj7]me\nJes[C]us, You\'re all this [Fmaj7]heart is living for[C]\n{eoc}\n\nBroken, I run to You for Your arms are open wide\nI am weary, but I know Your touch restores my life\nAnd so I wait for You so I wait for You\n\n{c:Kathryn Scott}\n{c:(c)1999 Vineyard Songs (UK/Eire)}\n', '', ' 1999 Vineyard Songs.', '', '', 'Hungry, I come to You for I know You satisfy I am empty, but I know Your love does not run dry And so I wait for You so I wait for You  I\'m falling on my knees Offering all of me Jesus, You\'re all this heart is living for  Broken, I run to You for Your arms are open wide I am weary, but I know Your touch restores my life And so I wait for You so I wait for You'),
	(667, 'Jesus What A Wonder You Are', 'Dave Bolton.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus, what a wonder You are,\r\nYou are so gentle, so pure and so kind.\r\nYou shine like the morning star.\r\nJesus, what a wonder You are.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1975 Dawn Treader Music. ', '', '', 'Jesus, what a wonder You are, You are so gentle, so pure and so kind. You shine like the morning star. Jesus, what a wonder You are.'),
	(668, 'This Is The Time', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThis is the time\r\nWhen true worshippers will worship Him\r\nThese are the days\r\nWhen my Father\'s ways \r\nwill be known to men\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHoly holy holy is Your name\r\nWorthy worthy let all the earth proclaim\r\nMighty mighty there is no God like You\r\nAnd we worship You in spirit and in truth\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThis is the hour\r\nWhen the Spirit\'s pow\'r will move again\r\nAs we worship Him in spirit and in truth\r\n', '', ' 2000 TMMI Music (Admin. by Music Services) ', '', '', 'This is the time When true worshippers will worship Him These are the days When my Father\'s ways will be known to men Holy holy holy is Your name Worthy worthy let all the earth proclaim Mighty mighty there is no God like You And we worship You in spirit and in truth This is the hour When the Spirit\'s pow\'r will move again As we worship Him in spirit and in truth'),
	(669, 'Joy Is A Flag', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJoy is a flag flown high,\r\nFrom the castle of my heart\r\nFrom the castle of my heart\r\nFrom the castle of my heart\r\nJoy is a flag flown high\r\nFrom the castle of my heart\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor the King is in residence there.\r\nOh, let it fly in the sky\r\nLet the whole world know\r\nLet the whole world know\r\nLet the whole world know\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nOh, let it fly in the sky\r\nLet the whole world know\r\nThat the King is in residence there.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Joy is a flag flown high, From the castle of my heart From the castle of my heart From the castle of my heart Joy is a flag flown high From the castle of my heart For the King is in residence there. Oh, let it fly in the sky Let the whole world know Let the whole world know Let the whole world know Oh, let it fly in the sky Let the whole world know That the King is in residence there.'),
	(670, 'Thanksgiving Medley', 'Henry Alford, music by George J. Elvey.Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, ye thankful people, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home:\r\nAll is safely gathered in\r\nEre the winter storms begin.\r\nGod, our Maker, doth provide\r\nFor our wants to be supplied:\r\nCome to God\'s own temple, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGod is so good, God is so good,God is so good, He\'s so good to me!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome and praise the Lord our King,\r\nLift your voice and with us sing,\r\nChrist was born in Bethlehem,\r\nSon of God and Son of Man,\r\nHe grew up an earthly child,\r\nIn the world, but undefiled,\r\nJesus died at Calvary,\r\nRose again triumphantly.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHe saved my soul, He saved my soul,He saved my soul, He\'s so good to me!\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nHe has conquered death and sin,\r\nGreat His triumph glorious win,\r\nNow He rules from heav\'n above,\r\nKing of mercy, King of love,\r\nWe will live with Him some day,\r\nAnd forever with Him stay,\r\nCome to God\'s own temple, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nHe answers prayer, He answers prayer,\r\nHe answers prayer, He\'s so good to me!\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nCome, ye thankful people, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home:\r\nAll is safely gathered in\r\nEre the winter storms begin.\r\nGod, our Maker, doth provide\r\nFor our wants to be supplied:\r\nCome to God\'s own temple, come\r\nRaise the song of harvest-home.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 12\r\n\r\n    \r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, ye thankful people, come Raise the song of harvest-home: All is safely gathered in Ere the winter storms begin. God, our Maker, doth provide For our wants to be supplied: Come to God\'s own temple, come Raise the song of harvest-home. God is so good, God is so good,God is so good, He\'s so good to me! Come and praise the Lord our King, Lift your voice and with us sing, Christ was born in Bethlehem, Son of God and Son of Man, He grew up an earthly child, In the world, but undefiled, Jesus died at Calvary, Rose again triumphantly. He saved my soul, He saved my soul,He saved my soul, He\'s so good to me! He has conquered death and sin, Great His triumph glorious win, Now He rules from heav\'n above, King of mercy, King of love, We will live with Him some day, And forever with Him stay, Come to God\'s own temple, come Raise the song of harvest-home. He answers prayer, He answers prayer, He answers prayer, He\'s so good to me! Come, ye thankful people, come Raise the song of harvest-home: All is safely gathered in Ere the winter storms begin. God, our Maker, doth provide For our wants to be supplied: Come to God\'s own temple, come Raise the song of harvest-home.'),
	(671, 'Blessed Be Your Name', 'Matt and Beth Redman', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]Blessed be[E] Your name in the [F#m7]land that is p[D]lentiful\r\nWhere Your [A]streams of a[E]bundance flow\r\nBlessed[D] be Your name\r\n[A]And blessed be[E] Your name when I\'m [F#m7]found in the [D]desert place\r\nThough I [A]walk through the [E]wilderness\r\nBlessed[D] be Your name\r\n[A] Every blessing [E]You pour out I\'ll\r\n[F#m7] turn back to[D] praise\r\n[A] And when the darkness[E] closes in, Lord\r\n[F#m7] Still I will [D]say\r\n~Chorus\r\nBlessed be the [A]name of the Lord[E]\r\nBlessed be Your [F#m7]name[D]\r\nBlessed be the [A]name of the Lord[E]\r\nBlessed be Your [F#m7]glorious [D]name\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[A]Blessed be[E] Your name when the [F#m7]sun\'s shining d[D]own on me\r\nWhen the [A]world\'s "all as i[E]t should be"\r\nBlessed[D] be Your name\r\n[A]And blessed be[E] Your name on the [F#m7]road marked with [D]suffering\r\nThough there\'s [A]pain in the [E]offering\r\nBlessed[D] be Your name\r\n[A] Every blessing [E]You pour out I\'ll\r\n[F#m7] turn back to[D] praise\r\n[A] And when the darkness[E] closes in, Lord\r\n[F#m7] Still I will [D]say\r\n~Bridge\r\nYou [A]give and take a[E]way\r\nYou [F#m7]give and take a[D]way\r\nMy [A]heart will choose to [E]say\r\nLord, [F#m7]blessed be Your [D]name\r\n', '', '2002 Thankyou Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/F6xo5KogzaI&fs=1', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/blessed-be-your-name/id6042265?i=6042251&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Matt Redman - Here I Am to Worship - Blessed Be Your Name" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Blessed be Your name in the land that is plentiful Where Your streams of abundance flow Blessed be Your name And blessed be Your name when I\\\'m found in the desert place Though I walk through the wilderness Blessed be Your name Every blessing You pour out I\\\'ll turn back to praise And when the darkness closes in, Lord Still I will say Blessed be the name of the Lord Blessed be Your name Blessed be the name of the Lord Blessed be Your glorious name Blessed be Your name when the sun\\\'s shining down on me When the world\\\'s \\"all as it should be\\" Blessed be Your name And blessed be Your name on the road marked with suffering Though there\\\'s pain in the offering Blessed be Your name Every blessing You pour out I\\\'ll turn back to praise And when the darkness closes in, Lord Still I will say You give and take away You give and take away My heart will choose to say Lord, blessed be Your name'),
	(672, 'On Jordan\'s Stormy Banks', 'Samuel Stennett,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nOn Jordan\'s stormy banks\r\nI stand,\r\nAnd cast a wishful eye\r\nTo Canaan\'s fair\r\nAnd happy land,\r\nWhere my possessions lie.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI am bound for\r\nThe promised land,\r\nI am bound for\r\nThe promised land,\r\nWho will come\r\nAnd go with me?\r\nI am bound for\r\nThe promised land.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAll o\'er those wide\r\nExtended plains\r\nShines one eternal day;\r\nThere God the Son\r\nForever reigns\r\nAnd scatters night away.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nNo chilling winds\r\nNor pois\'nous breath\r\nCan reach that healthful shore;\r\nSickness and sorrow,\r\nPain and death\r\nAre felt and feared no more.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhen shall I reach\r\nThat happy place,\r\nAnd be forever blest?\r\nWhen shall I see\r\nMy Father\'s face,\r\nAnd in His bosom rest?\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'On Jordan\'s stormy banks I stand, And cast a wishful eye To Canaan\'s fair And happy land, Where my possessions lie. I am bound for The promised land, I am bound for The promised land, Who will come And go with me? I am bound for The promised land. All o\'er those wide Extended plains Shines one eternal day; There God the Son Forever reigns And scatters night away. No chilling winds Nor pois\'nous breath Can reach that healthful shore; Sickness and sorrow, Pain and death Are felt and feared no more. When shall I reach That happy place, And be forever blest? When shall I see My Father\'s face, And in His bosom rest?'),
	(674, 'The Old Rugged Cross', 'George Bennard; ', '~Verse 1\r\nOn a hill far away stood an old rugged cross,\r\nThe emblem of suff\'ring and shame,\r\nAnd I love that old cross\r\nwhere the dearest and 	 best,\r\nFor a world of lost sinners was slain.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO that old rugged cross \r\nso despised by the world,\r\nHas a wondrous attraction for me;\r\nFor the dear Lamb of God \r\nleft His glory above,\r\nTo bear it to dark Calvary.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSo I\'ll cherish the old rugged cross,\r\nTill my trophies at last I lay down;\r\nI will cling to the old rugged cross,\r\nAnd exchange it some day for a crown.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nIn the old rugged cross, \r\nstained with blood so divine,\r\nA wondrous beauty I see;\r\nFor \'twas on that old cross\r\nJesus suffered and died,\r\nTo pardon and sanctify me.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTo the old rugged cross I will ever be true,\r\nIts shame and reproach gladly bear,\r\nThen He\'ll call me some day\r\nTo my home far away,\r\nWhere His glory forever I\'ll share.\r\n', '', ' 1941 The Rodeheaver Co. (Word Inc.); ARR; ICS; ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/CltrLsjsQl0', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(On a hill far away stood an old rugged cross, The emblem of suff\'ring and shame, And I love that old cross where the dearest and 	 best, For a world of lost sinners was slain. O that old rugged cross so despised by the world, Has a wondrous attraction for me; For the dear Lamb of God left His glory above, To bear it to dark Calvary. So I\'ll cherish the old rugged cross, Till my trophies at last I lay down; I will cling to the old rugged cross, And exchange it some day for a crown. In the old rugged cross, stained with blood so divine, A wondrous beauty I see; For \'twas on that old cross Jesus suffered and died, To pardon and sanctify me. To the old rugged cross I will ever be true, Its shame and reproach gladly bear, Then He\'ll call me some day To my home far away, Where His glory forever I\'ll share.).'),
	(675, 'A Mighty Fortress Is Our God', 'Martin Luther', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]A mighty F[G]ortr[Em]ess [Am]is o[D]ur G[G]od,\r\n[Am]A B[Em]ulwark nev[Am]er [Dm]fai[G7]lin[C]g;\r\n[C]Our Helper [G]He [Em]am[Am]idst t[D]he fl[G]ood\r\n[Am]Of m[Em]ortal ills [Am]pre[Dm]vai[G7]lin[C]g:\r\nF[C]or still o[D]ur ancient f[G]oe\r\nDoth s[C]eek to w[G]ork us w[Am]oe;\r\nH[E]is c[Am]raft and p[D7]ow\'r are gr[G]eat,\r\nAnd a[F]rmed w[C]ith c[Dm]ruel h[E]ate,\r\n[Am]On e[Em]arth is not [Am]his [Dm]e - [G7]qu[C]al.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nDid we in our own strength confide,\r\nOur striving would be losing;\r\nWere not the right Man on our side,\r\nThe Man of God\'s own choosing:\r\nDost ask who that may be?\r\nChrist Jesus, it is He;\r\nLord Saboath His Name,\r\nFrom age to age the same,\r\nAnd He must win the battle.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd though this world, with devils filled,\r\nShould threaten to undo us;\r\nWe will not fear, for God hath willed\r\nHis truth to triumph through us:\r\nThe prince of darkness grim,\r\nWe tremble not for him;\r\nHis rage we can endure,\r\nFor lo, his doom is sure,\r\nOne little word shall fell him.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThat word above all earthly pow\'rs,\r\nNo thanks to them a - bideth;\r\nThe Spirit and the gifts are ours\r\nThrough Him Who with us sideth:\r\nLet goods and kindred go,\r\nThis mortal life also;\r\nThe body they may kill;\r\nGod\'s truth abideth still,\r\nHis Kingdom is forever.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'A mighty Fortress is our God, A Bulwark never failing; Our Helper He amidst the flood Of mortal ills prevailing: For still our ancient foe Doth seek to work us woe; His craft and pow\\\'r are great, And armed with cruel hate, On earth is not his e - qual. Did we in our own strength confide, Our striving would be losing; Were not the right Man on our side, The Man of God\\\'s own choosing: Dost ask who that may be? Christ Jesus, it is He; Lord Saboath His Name, From age to age the same, And He must win the battle. And though this world, with devils filled, Should threaten to undo us; We will not fear, for God hath willed His truth to triumph through us: The prince of darkness grim, We tremble not for him; His rage we can endure, For lo, his doom is sure, One little word shall fell him. That word above all earthly pow\\\'rs, No thanks to them a - bideth; The Spirit and the gifts are ours Through Him Who with us sideth: Let goods and kindred go, This mortal life also; The body they may kill; God\\\'s truth abideth still, His Kingdom is forever.'),
	(676, 'Restore Us', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRestore us O Lord God Almighty.\r\nMake Your face shine upon us,\r\nThat we may be saved\r\nThat we may be saved\r\nMake Your face shine upon us.\r\nMake Your face shine upon us.\r\nMake Your face shine upon us.\r\nRestore us O Lord God Almighty we pray.\r\nWe pray.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Restore us O Lord God Almighty. Make Your face shine upon us, That we may be saved That we may be saved Make Your face shine upon us. Make Your face shine upon us. Make Your face shine upon us. Restore us O Lord God Almighty we pray. We pray.'),
	(677, 'Come Just As You Are', 'Joseph Sabolick. c. 1994', '~Verse 1\r\nCome just as you are,\r\nHear the Spirit call.\r\nCome just as you are.\r\nCome and see, come receive.\r\nCome and live forever.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLife everlasting,\r\nAnd strength for today;\r\nTaste the Living Water,\r\nAnd never thirst again.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome just as you are,\r\nHear the Spirit call.\r\nCome just as you are.\r\nCome receive, Christ, the King\r\nCome and live forever more.\r\n', '', ' 1994', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/veQvv7Gw9UU', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Come just as you are, Hear the Spirit call. Come just as you are. Come and see, come receive. Come and live forever. Life everlasting, And strength for today; Taste the Living Water, And never thirst again. Come just as you are, Hear the Spirit call. Come just as you are. Come receive, Christ, the King Come and live forever more.).'),
	(678, 'One Thing Is Needful', 'Kirk Dearman', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nOne thing is needful, O my Father,\r\nOne thing is needful, O my God,\r\nThat I sit at Your feet and pour out my love;\r\nThis thing is needful, O my Lord!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI sit and worship You, my Father,\r\nI sit and worship You, my God;\r\nLord, I sit at Your feet and pour out my love,\r\nI sit and worship You, my King.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI lift my hands to You, my Father,\r\nI lift my hands to You, my God;\r\nLord, I sit at Your feet and pour out my love,\r\nI lift my hands to You, my Lord.\r\n', '', '1981, 1983 Maranatha! Music;  ', '', '', 'One thing is needful, O my Father, One thing is needful, O my God, That I sit at Your feet and pour out my love; This thing is needful, O my Lord! I sit and worship You, my Father, I sit and worship You, my God; Lord, I sit at Your feet and pour out my love, I sit and worship You, my King. I lift my hands to You, my Father, I lift my hands to You, my God; Lord, I sit at Your feet and pour out my love, I lift my hands to You, my Lord.'),
	(679, 'I Have Come To Love You', 'Martin Cooper and Paul Oakley.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI have come to love You\r\nFor You have won my heart\r\nWhen You revealed Your love to me\r\nMy life will be a witness\r\nOf such love and such forgiveness\r\nFor You have given me Your peace\r\nAnd You\'re everything I need\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYou have come to love me\r\nAnd heal my broken heart\r\nNow I am reaching out to You\r\nYour strength is in my weakness\r\nI\'m clinging to Your promise\r\nSo let Your work in me shine through\r\nIn everything I do\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI love to sing Your name\r\nTo speak about Your fame\r\nYou\'re worthy of my praise\r\nI long to worship You\r\nIn spirit and in truth\r\nIt\'s all I want to do\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAs I come before You now\r\nLet Your Spirit touch me\r\nI will make this gospel known\r\nFill me with Your love and power\r\nAnd Your compassion\r\nThrough me let Your kingdom come\r\n', '', ' 1999 Thankyou Music. ', '', '', 'I have come to love You For You have won my heart When You revealed Your love to me My life will be a witness Of such love and such forgiveness For You have given me Your peace And You\'re everything I need You have come to love me And heal my broken heart Now I am reaching out to You Your strength is in my weakness I\'m clinging to Your promise So let Your work in me shine through In everything I do I love to sing Your name To speak about Your fame You\'re worthy of my praise I long to worship You In spirit and in truth It\'s all I want to do As I come before You now Let Your Spirit touch me I will make this gospel known Fill me with Your love and power And Your compassion Through me let Your kingdom come'),
	(680, 'Holy Moses', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHoly Moses,\r\nthe Lord chose his\r\nfaith to lead His people\r\nto the Promised land.\r\n\r\nHoly Moses,\r\nHis life shows us\r\nHow to walk with God and\r\nFollow His commands.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe was not holy as a kid.\r\nHe did stuff most kids did.\r\nBut when God chose him for a task,\r\nMoses did what God asked.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe learned of God\'s love as a lad,\r\nBut he had more than lads had.\r\nThough in the palace he was raised,\r\nIn the desert, he was saved.\r\n \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe had a lisp or a stutter;\r\nat the least, Moses muttered.\r\nBut there was not another humble as he,\r\nIn all the \r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHoly Moses!\r\nHoly Moses!\r\nHoly Moses!\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Holy Moses, the Lord chose his faith to lead His people to the Promised land. Holy Moses, His life shows us How to walk with God and Follow His commands. He was not holy as a kid. He did stuff most kids did. But when God chose him for a task, Moses did what God asked. He learned of God\'s love as a lad, But he had more than lads had. Though in the palace he was raised, In the desert, he was saved. He had a lisp or a stutter; at the least, Moses muttered. But there was not another humble as he, In all the Holy Moses! Holy Moses! Holy Moses!'),
	(681, 'I Was Created', 'Billy Funk and Daryn Funk ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI was created to live in Your presence,\r\nTo fellowship with You,\r\nTo walk in Your love \r\nAnd be led by Your Spirit.\r\nI live to worship You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMy heart\'s only desire is to worship You.\r\nMy life, freely I give You.\r\nMake it holy, pure and true;\r\nMy eyes see with Your Spirit \r\nWhen I fellowship with You;\r\nI was created to live \r\nIn Your presence, Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSurely goodness and mercy\r\nFollow me all the days of my life,\r\nAs I learn to yield my heart to You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nMy life is changed by Your love \r\nAnd Your mercy;\r\nYour Spirit has made me new;\r\nNow I can feel the joy of Your presence,\r\nYour light in me shines through.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI was created\r\nTto live in Your presence, Lord.\r\nI was created\r\n To live in Your presence, Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1999 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music ', '', '', 'I was created to live in Your presence, To fellowship with You, To walk in Your love And be led by Your Spirit. I live to worship You. My heart\'s only desire is to worship You. My life, freely I give You. Make it holy, pure and true; My eyes see with Your Spirit When I fellowship with You; I was created to live In Your presence, Lord. Surely goodness and mercy Follow me all the days of my life, As I learn to yield my heart to You. My life is changed by Your love And Your mercy; Your Spirit has made me new; Now I can feel the joy of Your presence, Your light in me shines through. I was created Tto live in Your presence, Lord. I was created To live in Your presence, Lord.'),
	(682, 'Spoken For', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nTake this world from me\r\nI don\'t need it anymore\r\nFor I am finally free\r\nMy heart is spoken for\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNow I have a peace\r\n       That I\'ve never known before\r\nI find myself complete\r\nMy heart is spoken for\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nOh and I praise You\r\nOh and I worship You\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCovered by a love divine\r\nChild of the risen Lord\r\nTo hear You say, \r\n"This one\'s mine"\r\nMy heart is spoken for.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nBy the power of the cross\r\nYou\'ve taken what was lost\r\nAnd made it fully yours\r\nAnd I have been redeemed\r\nBy you who spoke to me\r\nNow I am spoken for\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTake this world from me\r\nI don\'t need it anymore\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Take this world from me I don\'t need it anymore For I am finally free My heart is spoken for Now I have a peace That I\'ve never known before I find myself complete My heart is spoken for Oh and I praise You Oh and I worship You Covered by a love divine Child of the risen Lord To hear You say, "This one\'s mine" My heart is spoken for. By the power of the cross You\'ve taken what was lost And made it fully yours And I have been redeemed By you who spoke to me Now I am spoken for Take this world from me I don\'t need it anymore'),
	(683, 'Send It On Down', 'Geron Davis', '~Verse 1\r\nLord, we\'re Your children \r\nand we are asking\r\n for You to send the fire;\r\nOur hearts are hungry, \r\nour spirits are thirsty,\r\n	 we need to feel Your pow\'r.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSend it on down, Send it on down,\r\nLord, let the Holy Ghost \r\ncome on down;\r\nSend it on down, \r\nSend it on down,\r\nLord, let the Holy Ghost \r\ncome on down.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJust like the prophet \r\nsaid it would be,\r\nIn the last days \r\nAn outpouring we\'d see;\r\nYes we are waiting, anticipating.\r\n Lord, won\'t You send \r\nThe Holy Ghost down?\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHeavenly Father, hear our call\r\nLet Your Holy Spirit fall;\r\nSend down the power, \r\nlet it fall like rain,\r\nAs we lift our praises \r\nto your name.\r\n', '', '1994', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/EQ3jNCsUqag', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Lord, we\'re Your children and we are asking for You to send the fire; Our hearts are hungry, our spirits are thirsty, we need to feel Your pow\'r. Send it on down, Send it on down, Lord, let the Holy Ghost come on down; Send it on down, Send it on down, Lord, let the Holy Ghost come on down. Just like the prophet said it would be, In the last days An outpouring we\'d see; Yes we are waiting, anticipating. Lord, won\'t You send The Holy Ghost down? Heavenly Father, hear our call Let Your Holy Spirit fall; Send down the power, let it fall like rain, As we lift our praises to your name.).'),
	(684, 'Salvation Is Here', 'Joel Houston. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGod above all the world in motion\r\nGod above all my hopes and fears\r\nAnd I don\'t care\r\nWhat the world throws at me now\r\nI\'m gonna be alright\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHear the sound of the generations\r\nMaking loud their freedom song\r\nAll in all that the world\r\nWould know Your Name\r\nWe\'re gonna be alright\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\'Cause I know my God saved the day\r\nAnd I know His Word never fails\r\nAnd I know my God made a way for me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSalvation is here\r\nSalvation is here and He lives in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\nSalvation that died just to set me free\r\nSalvation is here\r\nSalvation is here and He lives in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\'Cause You are alive and You live in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\nSalvation is here and He lives in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n\'Cause You are alive and You live in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\n\r\nSalvation is here and He lives in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n\'Cause You are alive and You live in me\r\nSalvation is here\r\n', '', ' 2004 Hillsong Publishing.', '', '', 'God above all the world in motion God above all my hopes and fears And I don\'t care What the world throws at me now I\'m gonna be alright Hear the sound of the generations Making loud their freedom song All in all that the world Would know Your Name We\'re gonna be alright \'Cause I know my God saved the day And I know His Word never fails And I know my God made a way for me Salvation is here Salvation is here Salvation is here and He lives in me Salvation is here Salvation that died just to set me free Salvation is here Salvation is here and He lives in me Salvation is here \'Cause You are alive and You live in me Salvation is here Salvation is here and He lives in me Salvation is here \'Cause You are alive and You live in me Salvation is here Salvation is here and He lives in me Salvation is here \'Cause You are alive and You live in me Salvation is here'),
