	(686, 'O Come O Come, Emmanuel', '', '~Verse1\r\nO [Em]Come, o come, E[Am-Bm]mma--nu[Em]el, \r\nand [G]ransome [C]captive [Am-Bm]I.....sr[Em]ael,\r\nWho [Am]mourns in lonely [Em]exile [D]here\r\nUn[G]til the Son of [Am-D]God  ap[Em]pears.\r\n~Chorus\r\nRe[D]joice! Re[G]joice! Em[Am-Bm]ma..nu[Em]el\r\nShall [G]come to [C]thee, O [Am-Bm]I.....sr[Em]ael.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO come, thou Day Spring, come and cheer\r\nOur spirits by thine advent here;\r\nDisperse the gloomy clouds of night,\r\nand death\'s dark shadows put to flight.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO come, Desire of Nations, come, \r\nand bind in one the hearts of all mankind;\r\nBid thou our sad divisions cease,\r\nand be thyself our King of peace.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'O Come, o come, Emma--nuel, and ransome captive I.....srael, Who mourns in lonely exile here Until the Son of God  appears. Rejoice! Rejoice! Emma..nuel Shall come to thee, O I.....srael. O come, thou Day Spring, come and cheer Our spirits by thine advent here; Disperse the gloomy clouds of night, and death\'s dark shadows put to flight. O come, Desire of Nations, come, and bind in one the hearts of all mankind; Bid thou our sad divisions cease, and be thyself our King of peace.'),
	(687, 'Your Grace Still Amazes Me', 'Connie Harrington and Shawn Craig.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy faithful Father, enduring Friend\r\nYour tender mercy\'s like a river with no end\r\nIt overwhelms me, covers my sin\r\nEach time I come into Your presence\r\nI stand in wonder once again\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nO patient Savior, You make me whole\r\nYou are the Author and the Healer of my soul\r\nWhat can I give You Lord, what can I say\r\nI know there\'s no way to repay You\r\nOnly to offer You my praise\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\nYour live is still a mystery\r\nEach day I fall on my knees\r\n\'Cause Your grace still amazes me\r\nYour grace still amazes me\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIt\'s deeper, it\'s wider\r\nIt\'s stronger, it\'s higher\r\nIt\'s deeper, it\'s wider\r\nIt\'s stronger, it\'s higher\r\nThan anything my eyes can see\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAmazing grace\r\n', '', ' Ariose Music/PraiseSong Press/EMI April Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'My faithful Father, enduring Friend Your tender mercy\'s like a river with no end It overwhelms me, covers my sin Each time I come into Your presence I stand in wonder once again O patient Savior, You make me whole You are the Author and the Healer of my soul What can I give You Lord, what can I say I know there\'s no way to repay You Only to offer You my praise Your grace still amazes me Your live is still a mystery Each day I fall on my knees \'Cause Your grace still amazes me Your grace still amazes me It\'s deeper, it\'s wider It\'s stronger, it\'s higher It\'s deeper, it\'s wider It\'s stronger, it\'s higher Than anything my eyes can see Amazing grace'),
	(689, 'There Is None Like You', 'Lenny LeBlanc.', '~Verse 1\r\nMercy flows like a river wide and\r\nHealing comes from Your hands;\r\nSuffering children are safe in Your arms,\r\nThere is none like You.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThere is none like You,\r\nNo one else can touch \r\nmy heart like You do;\r\nI could search for all eternity long and find\r\nThere is none like You.\r\n', '', ' 1991 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music,  c/o Integrity Music, Inc.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/EP0Wwn53ZgI', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Mercy flows like a river wide and Healing comes from Your hands; Suffering children are safe in Your arms, There is none like You. There is none like You, No one else can touch my heart like You do; I could search for all eternity long and find There is none like You.).'),
	(690, 'Praise Him! Praise Him! (Hymn #106)', 'Fanny J. Crosby  Music by Chester G. Allen', '~Verse 1\r\nPraise Him! Praise Him!\r\nJesus, our blessed Redeemer!\r\nSing O earth, His wonderful love proclaim!\r\nHail Him! Hail Him! \r\nHighest archangels in glory,\r\nStrength and honor give to His holy name!\r\n~Chorus\r\nPraise Him! Praise Him!\r\nTell of His excellent greatness,\r\nPraise Him! Praise Him! \r\n Ever in joyful song!\r\nLike a shepherd, \r\nJesus will guard His children,\r\nIn His arms He carries them all day long:\r\n~Verse 2\r\nPraise Him! Praise Him!\r\nJesus, our blessed Redeemer!\r\nFor our sins He suffered, and bled and died;\r\nHe our Rock, our Hope of eternal salvation,\r\nHail Him! Hail Him! Jesus, the Crucified!\r\nSound His praises; \r\nJesus who bore our sorrows;\r\nLove unbounded,\r\n wonderful deep and strong.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPraise Him! Praise Him!\r\nJesus, our blessed Redeemer!\r\nHeav\'nly portals loud with hosannas ring!\r\nJesus, Saviour, reigneth forever and ever;\r\nCrown Him! Crown Him!\r\nProphet, and Priest and King!\r\nChrist is coming!\r\n over the world victorious;\r\nPow\'r and glory \r\nunto the Lord belong:\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Praise Him! Praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer! Sing O earth, His wonderful love proclaim! Hail Him! Hail Him! Highest archangels in glory, Strength and honor give to His holy name! Praise Him! Praise Him! Tell of His excellent greatness, Praise Him! Praise Him! Ever in joyful song! Like a shepherd, Jesus will guard His children, In His arms He carries them all day long: Praise Him! Praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer! For our sins He suffered, and bled and died; He our Rock, our Hope of eternal salvation, Hail Him! Hail Him! Jesus, the Crucified! Sound His praises; Jesus who bore our sorrows; Love unbounded, wonderful deep and strong. Praise Him! Praise Him! Jesus, our blessed Redeemer! Heav\\\'nly portals loud with hosannas ring! Jesus, Saviour, reigneth forever and ever; Crown Him! Crown Him! Prophet, and Priest and King! Christ is coming! over the world victorious; Pow\\\'r and glory unto the Lord belong:'),
	(691, 'O Holy Night (Hymn #148)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO holy night! The stars are brightly shining,\r\nIt is the night of the dear Savior\'s birth;\r\nLong lay the world in sin and error pining,\r\nTill He appeared and the soul felt its worth.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nA thrill of hope the weary world rejoices,\r\nFor yonder breaks a new and glorious morn;\r\nFall on your knees,\r\n Oh, hear the angel voices!\r\nO night divine, O night \r\nWhen Christ was born!\r\nO night, O holy night, O night divine!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLed by the light of faith serenely beaming,\r\nWith glowing hearts by His cradle we stand\r\nSo led by light of a star sweetly gleaming,\r\nHere came the wise men from Orient land,\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThe King of kings lay thus in lowly manger,\r\nIn all our trials born to be our Friend;\r\nHe knows our need,\r\nTo our weakness is no stranger.\r\nBehold your King, before Him lowly bend!\r\nBehold your King, before Him lowly bend!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTruly He taught us to love one another;\r\nHis law is love and His gospel is peace;\r\nChains shall He break,\r\n For the slave is our brother,\r\nAnd in His name all oppression shall cease.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nSweet hymns of joy\r\n In grateful chorus raise we,\r\nLet all within us praise His holy name;\r\nChrist is the Lord,\r\n Oh, praise His name forever!\r\nHis pow\'r and glory evermore proclaim!\r\nHis pow\'r and glory evermore proclaim.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'O holy night! The stars are brightly shining, It is the night of the dear Savior\'s birth; Long lay the world in sin and error pining, Till He appeared and the soul felt its worth. A thrill of hope the weary world rejoices, For yonder breaks a new and glorious morn; Fall on your knees, Oh, hear the angel voices! O night divine, O night When Christ was born! O night, O holy night, O night divine! Led by the light of faith serenely beaming, With glowing hearts by His cradle we stand So led by light of a star sweetly gleaming, Here came the wise men from Orient land, The King of kings lay thus in lowly manger, In all our trials born to be our Friend; He knows our need, To our weakness is no stranger. Behold your King, before Him lowly bend! Behold your King, before Him lowly bend! Truly He taught us to love one another; His law is love and His gospel is peace; Chains shall He break, For the slave is our brother, And in His name all oppression shall cease. Sweet hymns of joy In grateful chorus raise we, Let all within us praise His holy name; Christ is the Lord, Oh, praise His name forever! His pow\'r and glory evermore proclaim! His pow\'r and glory evermore proclaim.'),
	(692, 'The Love Of God', 'Frederick M. Lehman. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe love of God is greater far\r\nThan tongue or pen can ever tell,\r\nIt goes beyond the highest star\r\nAnd reaches to the lowest hell;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThe guilty pair, bowed down with care,\r\nGod gave His Son to win:\r\nHis erring child He reconciled\r\nAnd pardoned from his sin.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhen years of time shall pass away\r\nAnd earthly thrones and kingdoms fall,\r\nWhen men, who here refuse to pray,\r\nOn rocks and hills and mountains call,\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGod\'s love so sure shall still endure,\r\nAll measureless and strong:\r\nRedeeming grace to Adam\'s race\r\nThe saints\' and angels\' song.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nCould we with ink the ocean fill\r\nAnd were the skies of parchment made,\r\nWere ev\'ry stalk on earth a quill\r\nAnd ev\'ry man a scribe by trade,\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nTo write the love of God above\r\nWould drain the ocean dry,\r\nNor could the scroll contain the whole\r\nTho stretched from sky to sky.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nO love of God, how rich and pure!\r\nHow measureless and strong!\r\nIt shall forevermore endure\r\nThe saints\' and angels\' song.\r\n', '', ' 1917 renewed 1945 by Nazarene Publishing House. ', '', '', 'The love of God is greater far Than tongue or pen can ever tell, It goes beyond the highest star And reaches to the lowest hell; The guilty pair, bowed down with care, God gave His Son to win: His erring child He reconciled And pardoned from his sin. When years of time shall pass away And earthly thrones and kingdoms fall, When men, who here refuse to pray, On rocks and hills and mountains call, God\'s love so sure shall still endure, All measureless and strong: Redeeming grace to Adam\'s race The saints\' and angels\' song. Could we with ink the ocean fill And were the skies of parchment made, Were ev\'ry stalk on earth a quill And ev\'ry man a scribe by trade, To write the love of God above Would drain the ocean dry, Nor could the scroll contain the whole Tho stretched from sky to sky. O love of God, how rich and pure! How measureless and strong! It shall forevermore endure The saints\' and angels\' song.'),
	(693, 'Good To Me', 'Craig Musseau', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]I cry [C]out\r\nfor your [Em]hand of [D]mercy to [C]heal me\r\n[G]I am [C]weak\r\nI [Em]need your [D]love to [C]free me\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOh [G/B]Lord, my [C]rock\r\nMy [G/B]strength in [C]weakness,\r\nCome [Em]rescue [Bm7]me oh [C2]Lord\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYou are my [D]hope,\r\nyour [G/B]promise [C]never [Dsus]fails [D/F#]     [G]me\r\nAnd my [D]desire\r\nIs to [G/B]follow [C]you for [Dsus]- e - [D/F#]ver.[G]\r\n~Chorus\r\nFor you are [C]good\r\nFor you are [G/B]good\r\nFor you are [Am7]good [G]to [D/F#]me\r\n[D]For you are [C]good\r\nFor you are [G/B]good\r\nFor you are [Am7]good [G]to [D/F#]me.\r\n', '', ' 1989 Langley Vineyard Music,', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/qIvqwvgfoE0&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '', 'I cry out for your hand of mercy to heal me I am weak I need your love to free me Oh Lord, my rock My strength in weakness, Come rescue me oh Lord You are my hope, your promise never fails      me And my desire Is to follow you for - e - ver. For you are good For you are good For you are good to me For you are good For you are good For you are good to me.'),
	(694, 'We Declare That The Kingdom Of God Is Here', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe blind see, the deaf hear, \r\nthe lame men are walking,\r\nSicknesses flee at His voice;\r\nThe dead live again \r\nand the poor hear the good news.\r\nJesus is King, so rejoice.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe declare that the kingdom of God is here,  \r\n(echo)  \r\nWe declare that the kingdom of God is here\r\n(echo)\r\nAmong you   (Among you)\r\nAmong you  (Among you).\r\n', '', ' 1986 Make Way Music & Thankyou Music/Admin. by Maranatha! Music; ', '', '', 'The blind see, the deaf hear, the lame men are walking, Sicknesses flee at His voice; The dead live again and the poor hear the good news. Jesus is King, so rejoice. We declare that the kingdom of God is here, (echo) We declare that the kingdom of God is here (echo) Among you   (Among you) Among you  (Among you).'),
	(695, 'Open Our Eyes', 'Robert Cull', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]Op[(G)]en our eyes [Fmaj7(C)]Lord,  w[G]e [(D)]want to see J[F]esu[C]s,[Am][(C][G][Em)]\r\nTo reach out and to[Dm(Am)]uch Him,  a[G]nd [(D)]say that we lo[F(C)]ve Hi[C]m.[(G)]\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[C]Op[(G)]en our ears [Fmaj7(C)]Lord,    [G]an[(D)]d help us to l[F]iste[C]n.[Am(C][G][Em)]\r\nOpen our e[Dm(Am)]yes Lord,  [G]we [(D)]want to see Je[F]sus[C(C].[G)]\r\n', '', '1976, Maranatha! Music', '', '', 'Open our eyes Lord,  we want to see Jesus, To reach out and touch Him,  and say that we love Him. Open our ears Lord,    and help us to listen. Open our eyes Lord,  we want to see Jesus.'),
	(697, 'At The Cross (I know a place)', 'Randy Butler & Terry Butler', '~Verse 1\r\n[E]I know a p[Bm7]lace\r\nA w[A]onderful p[E]lace\r\nWhere accused and con[Bm7]demned\r\nFind m[A]ercy and g[E]race\r\nWhere the w[E]rongs we have [Bm7]done\r\nAnd the w[A]rongs done to u[E]s\r\nWere nailed there with h[Bm7]im \r\nT[A]here on the c[E]ross\r\n\r\n~Chorus\r\nAt the [D]cross [A]\r\nHe [G]died for our [E]sins\r\nAt the [D]cross [A]\r\nHe [G]gave us life [E]again\r\n', '', '1993 Mercy Publishing', '', '', 'I know a place A wonderful place Where accused and condemned Find mercy and grace Where the wrongs we have done And the wrongs done to us Were nailed there with him There on the cross At the cross He died for our sins At the cross He gave us life again'),
	(698, 'Come Heal This Land', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLet the exile come,\r\nLet the stranger come,\r\nLet the weary come find rest;\r\nAll you homeless sons,\r\nAll you widowed ones,\r\nAll you poor and dispossessed;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor a table waits in your Father\'s house,\r\nThere the meek can come and eat;\r\nThere\'s a place of rest\r\nAt your Father\'s breast,\r\nWhere His mercy is complete.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nDoes a cry ring out from a broken nation,\r\nFrom a people who have been brought low;\r\nWas pride in our hearts,\r\nDid we grieve Your Spirit,\r\nHave we blocked\r\nThe ancient wells that flowed;\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHere is our covenant prayer,\r\nWho call upon Your name;\r\nWe humble ourselves before You,\r\nWe humble ourselves.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCome heal this land\r\nCome heal this land\r\nCome heal this land\r\nCome heal this land\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nDo the tears of One\r\nWho gave all things for us,\r\nDo they fall from Heaven\r\nStill because of us;\r\nFor we have tasted grace\r\nAnd we have known Your mercy,\r\nBut we have not shown this grace to men;\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nHere is our covenant prayer,\r\nWho call upon Your name;\r\nWe humble ourselves before You,\r\nWe humble ourselves.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nMay this land we love be a place of safety,\r\nBe a light for all the nations of this earth;\r\nMay Your streams of love,\r\nMay they flow here freely,\r\nHere where every stranger finds a home;\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nHere is our covenant prayer,\r\nWho call upon Your name;\r\nWe humble ourselves before You,\r\nWe humble ourselves.\r\n', '', ' 2001 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'Let the exile come, Let the stranger come, Let the weary come find rest; All you homeless sons, All you widowed ones, All you poor and dispossessed; For a table waits in your Father\'s house, There the meek can come and eat; There\'s a place of rest At your Father\'s breast, Where His mercy is complete. Does a cry ring out from a broken nation, From a people who have been brought low; Was pride in our hearts, Did we grieve Your Spirit, Have we blocked The ancient wells that flowed; Here is our covenant prayer, Who call upon Your name; We humble ourselves before You, We humble ourselves. Come heal this land Come heal this land Come heal this land Come heal this land Do the tears of One Who gave all things for us, Do they fall from Heaven Still because of us; For we have tasted grace And we have known Your mercy, But we have not shown this grace to men; Here is our covenant prayer, Who call upon Your name; We humble ourselves before You, We humble ourselves. May this land we love be a place of safety, Be a light for all the nations of this earth; May Your streams of love, May they flow here freely, Here where every stranger finds a home; Here is our covenant prayer, Who call upon Your name; We humble ourselves before You, We humble ourselves.'),
	(699, 'Jehovah - Jireh', 'Merla Watson ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy God shall supply all my needs\r\nAccording to His riches in glory.\r\nHe will give His angels charge over me,\r\nJehovah Jireh cares for me, for me, for me.\r\nJehovah Jireh cares for me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJehovah Jireh, my Provider,\r\nHis Grace is sufficient for me, for me, for me.\r\nJehovah, Jireh, my Provider,\r\nHis Grace is sufficient for me.\r\n', '', '1974 Catacombs Productions, Ltd.;  ', '', '', 'My God shall supply all my needs According to His riches in glory. He will give His angels charge over me, Jehovah Jireh cares for me, for me, for me. Jehovah Jireh cares for me. Jehovah Jireh, my Provider, His Grace is sufficient for me, for me, for me. Jehovah, Jireh, my Provider, His Grace is sufficient for me.'),
	(700, 'We Will Dance On Streets That Are Golden', 'David Ruis. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSing a song of celebration \r\nLift up a shout of praise\r\nFor the bridegroom will come, \r\nthe glorious one\r\nAnd oh, we will look on His face\r\nWe\'ll go to a much better place.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe will dance on streets that are golden\r\nThe glorious bride and the great Son of man\r\nAnd every tongue and tribe and nation,\r\nwill join in the song of the Lamb.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nDance with all your might\r\nLift up your hands and clap for joy\r\nThe time\'s drawing near\r\n when He will appear\r\nAnd oh, we will stand by His side\r\nA strong and pure spotless bride.\r\n', '', ' 1993 Mercy Publishing.', '', '', 'Sing a song of celebration Lift up a shout of praise For the bridegroom will come, the glorious one And oh, we will look on His face We\'ll go to a much better place. We will dance on streets that are golden The glorious bride and the great Son of man And every tongue and tribe and nation, will join in the song of the Lamb. Dance with all your might Lift up your hands and clap for joy The time\'s drawing near when He will appear And oh, we will stand by His side A strong and pure spotless bride.'),
	(701, 'When We All Get To Heaven', 'Eliza E. Hewitt and Music by Emily D. Wilson', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nSing the wondrous love of Jesus,\r\nSing His mercy and His grace;\r\nIn the mansions bright and blessed\r\nHe\'ll prepare for us a place.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhen we all get to heaven,\r\nWhat a day of rejoicing that will be!\r\nWhen we all see Jesus,\r\nWe\'ll sing and shout the victory.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nOnward to the prize before us!\r\nSoon His beauty we\'ll behold;\r\nSoon the pearly gates will open,\r\nWe shall tread the streets of gold.\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Sing the wondrous love of Jesus, Sing His mercy and His grace; In the mansions bright and blessed He\'ll prepare for us a place. When we all get to heaven, What a day of rejoicing that will be! When we all see Jesus, We\'ll sing and shout the victory. Onward to the prize before us! Soon His beauty we\'ll behold; Soon the pearly gates will open, We shall tread the streets of gold.'),
	(702, 'His Banner Over Me Is Love', 'Kevin Prosch - Song of Songs 2:4', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe brought me to His banqueting table\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe brought me to His banqueting table\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\nHe brought me to His banqueting table \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe brought me to His banqueting table\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nAnd His banner over me is love.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nI am my beloved\'s and He is mine\r\nI am my beloved\'s and He is mine \r\nI am my beloved\'s and He is mine\r\nI am my beloved\'s and He is mine\r\nAnd His banner over me is love\r\nYes, His banner over me is love. \r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nWe can feel the love of God in this place\r\nWe believe Your goodness, \r\nWe receive Your grace\r\nWe delight ourselves at Your table, oh God\r\nYou do all things well, \r\njust look at our lives.\r\n', '', 'S.; ', '', '', 'He brought me to His banqueting table He brought me to His banqueting table He brought me to His banqueting table He brought me to His banqueting table And His banner over me is love. I am my beloved\'s and He is mine I am my beloved\'s and He is mine I am my beloved\'s and He is mine I am my beloved\'s and He is mine And His banner over me is love Yes, His banner over me is love. We can feel the love of God in this place We believe Your goodness, We receive Your grace We delight ourselves at Your table, oh God You do all things well, just look at our lives.'),
	(703, 'Glory Glory Lord', 'Bob Fitts.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou who go down to the sea,\r\nYou who live in the islands;\r\nIf you live in the city,\r\nLift your voice and sing out.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nWe give You glory, Lord;\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSing to the Lord a new song;\r\nSing His praise to the ends of the earth;\r\nLet ev\'ry nation tell it,\r\nTill ev\'ry man has heard.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nWe give You glory, Lord;\r\nGlory, glory Lord,\r\nYou are the mighty God,\r\nYou are the living God,\r\nYou are the only God,\r\nYou are the mighty God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nNa-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah,\r\nI Nou Ka-na-ni le-jo-vah;\r\nNa-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah,\r\nKe A-Ku-a-Ma-na Lo-a.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nVi-i-a, Vi-i-a le atu-a,\r\nMa-tou te vi-ia oe le atu-a;\r\nVi-i-a, vi-i-a le atu-a O\r\nOele Atu-a ma-ta-u-ti-a.\r\n', '', ' 1990 Scripture in Song (adm. by Maranatha! Music).', '', '', 'You who go down to the sea, You who live in the islands; If you live in the city, Lift your voice and sing out. Glory, glory Lord, We give You glory, Lord; Glory, glory Lord, You are the mighty God, You are the mighty God, Sing to the Lord a new song; Sing His praise to the ends of the earth; Let ev\'ry nation tell it, Till ev\'ry man has heard. Glory, glory Lord, We give You glory, Lord; Glory, glory Lord, You are the mighty God, You are the living God, You are the only God, You are the mighty God. Na-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah, I Nou Ka-na-ni le-jo-vah; Na-ni, Na-ni le-jo-vah, Ke A-Ku-a-Ma-na Lo-a. Vi-i-a, Vi-i-a le atu-a, Ma-tou te vi-ia oe le atu-a; Vi-i-a, vi-i-a le atu-a O Oele Atu-a ma-ta-u-ti-a.'),
	(704, 'Waiting For You', 'Kent Blanton. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome to the table, a feast is prepared,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\nThere\'s nothing more to be done,\r\nSo come, for I\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nCleansing from sin, healing and wholeness,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\nStrength for today and hope everlasting,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCome and dine,\r\nFeast on the bread and the wine.\r\nStrength for today and hope everlasting,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome believe,\r\nCome and my grace now receive\r\nCome and rest,\r\nCome and forever be blessed.\r\nStrength for today and hope everlasting,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nCome and dine,\r\nFeast on the bread and the wine.\r\nI died for you, oh won\'t you listen, yes\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nCome believe,\r\nCome and my grace now receive\r\nCome and rest,\r\nCome and forever be blessed.\r\nCome believe,\r\nCome and my grace now receive\r\nCome and rest,\r\nCome and forever be blessed.\r\nStrength for today and hope everlasting\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nMy one desire - that you\'d be with me,\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\nI died for you, oh won\'t you listen\r\nI\'m here waiting for you.\r\n', '', ' 2005 Kent Blanton.', '', '', 'Come to the table, a feast is prepared, I\'m here waiting for you. There\'s nothing more to be done, So come, for I\'m here waiting for you. Cleansing from sin, healing and wholeness, I\'m here waiting for you. Strength for today and hope everlasting, I\'m here waiting for you. Come and dine, Feast on the bread and the wine. Strength for today and hope everlasting, I\'m here waiting for you. Come believe, Come and my grace now receive Come and rest, Come and forever be blessed. Strength for today and hope everlasting, I\'m here waiting for you. Come and dine, Feast on the bread and the wine. I died for you, oh won\'t you listen, yes I\'m here waiting for you. Come believe, Come and my grace now receive Come and rest, Come and forever be blessed. Come believe, Come and my grace now receive Come and rest, Come and forever be blessed. Strength for today and hope everlasting I\'m here waiting for you. I\'m here waiting for you. I\'m here waiting for you. My one desire - that you\'d be with me, I\'m here waiting for you. I died for you, oh won\'t you listen I\'m here waiting for you.'),
	(705, 'Go, Tell It On The Mountain (Hymn #138)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWhile shepherds kept their watching\r\nO\'er silent flocks by night,\r\nBehold throughout the heavens\r\nThere shone a holy light.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe shepherds feared and trembled\r\nWhen, lo above the earth\r\nRang out the angel chorus \r\nThat hailed our Savior\'s birth.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nGo tell it on the mountain\r\nOver the hills and ev\'rywhere;\r\nGo tell it on the mountain\r\nThat Jesus Christ is born.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nDown in a lowly manger\r\nThe humble Christ was born.\r\nAnd God sent us salvation\r\nThat blessed Christmas morn.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'While shepherds kept their watching O\'er silent flocks by night, Behold throughout the heavens There shone a holy light. The shepherds feared and trembled When, lo above the earth Rang out the angel chorus That hailed our Savior\'s birth. Go tell it on the mountain Over the hills and ev\'rywhere; Go tell it on the mountain That Jesus Christ is born. Down in a lowly manger The humble Christ was born. And God sent us salvation That blessed Christmas morn.'),
	(706, 'I Will Rejoice', 'Don Moen and Claire Cloninger', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nEvery step I take\r\n I feel Your love around me,\r\nI cannot escape Your grace;\r\nI cannot explain \r\nThe blessings that surround me,\r\nI can only sing Your praise.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI will rejoice,\r\n I\'m gonna lift my voice	 and worship You,\r\nAnd glorify Your name among the nations; \r\n O---\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI have made a choice,\r\n To offer up thanksgiving, \r\nLifting up Your holy name;\r\nI will lift my voice\r\nAnd come before You, singing\r\nWith a sacrifice of praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI will rejoice, \r\nIn everything I will give thanks to You,\r\nFor You have been my help\r\n	 And my salvation.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music  ', '', '', 'Every step I take I feel Your love around me, I cannot escape Your grace; I cannot explain The blessings that surround me, I can only sing Your praise. I will rejoice, I\'m gonna lift my voice	 and worship You, And glorify Your name among the nations; O--- I have made a choice, To offer up thanksgiving, Lifting up Your holy name; I will lift my voice And come before You, singing With a sacrifice of praise. I will rejoice, In everything I will give thanks to You, For You have been my help And my salvation.'),
	(707, 'Great Is The Lord', 'Deborah Smith, Michael W. Smith.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGreat is the Lord; He is holy and just;\r\nBy His power we trust in His love.\r\nGreat is the Lord; He is faithful and true;\r\nBy His mercy He proves He is love.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGreat is the Lord and worthy of glory,\r\nGreat is the Lord and worthy of praise.\r\nGreat is the Lord, I lift up my voice,\r\nI lift up my voice, Great is the Lord,\r\nGreat is the Lord.\r\n', '', ' 1982 Meadowgreen Music Co. ', '', '', 'Great is the Lord; He is holy and just; By His power we trust in His love. Great is the Lord; He is faithful and true; By His mercy He proves He is love. Great is the Lord and worthy of glory, Great is the Lord and worthy of praise. Great is the Lord, I lift up my voice, I lift up my voice, Great is the Lord, Great is the Lord.'),
	(708, 'Awesome Is The Lord Most High', 'Chris Tomlin', '~Intro\r\n[G]   [D]   [Em7]     [C2]                         \r\n~Verse 1\r\n[G]Great are You, Lord, Mighty in st[D]rength\r\n[C2]You are faithful, You will ever be[G]\r\n[G]We will praise You all of our [D]days\r\n[C2]It\'s for Your glory We offer every[Em7]thing [D/F#]\r\n~Chorus\r\nRaise Your [G]hands all you nations\r\nShout to [D/F#]God all creation\r\nHow [Em7]awesome is the Lord most [C2]high  (1st time to verse 2)\r\nWe will [G]praise You together\r\nFor [D/F#]now and forever\r\nHow [Em7]awesome is the Lord most [C2]high\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhere You send us, God we will go\r\nYou\'re the answer, we want the world to know\r\nWe will trust You, when You call our name\r\nWhere You lead us, we\'ll follow all the way\r\n~Bridge\r\n[G]Hallelujah, [D]Hallelujah\r\nHow [Em7]awesome is the Lord most [C2]High\r\n[G]Hallelujah, [D]Hallelujah\r\nHow [Em7]awesome is the Lord most [C2]High', '', ' 2006', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/8T2Z69I4j6Y', '', 'Great are You, Lord, Mighty in strength You are faithful, You will ever be We will praise You all of our days It\\\'s for Your glory We offer everything Raise Your hands all you nations Shout to God all creation How awesome is the Lord most high  (1st time to verse 2) We will praise You together For now and forever How awesome is the Lord most high Where You send us, God we will go You\\\'re the answer, we want the world to know We will trust You, when You call our name Where You lead us, we\\\'ll follow all the way Hallelujah, Hallelujah How awesome is the Lord most High Hallelujah, Hallelujah How awesome is the Lord most High'),
	(709, 'He Is Our Peace', 'Kandela Groves, c. 1986 Marantha! Music,', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe is our peace\r\nWho has broken down ev\'ry wall,\r\nHe is our peace,\r\nHe is our peace.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCast all your cares on Him\r\nFor He cares for you;\r\nHe is our peace, \r\nHe is our peace.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou are my peace\r\nWho has broken down ev\'ry wall,\r\nYou are my peace,\r\nYou are my peace.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI cast all my cares on You\r\nFor You care for me;\r\nYou are my peace,\r\nYou are my peace.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1986 Marantha! Music,', '', '', 'He is our peace Who has broken down ev\'ry wall, He is our peace, He is our peace. Cast all your cares on Him For He cares for you; He is our peace, He is our peace. You are my peace Who has broken down ev\'ry wall, You are my peace, You are my peace. I cast all my cares on You For You care for me; You are my peace, You are my peace.'),
	(710, 'These Hands', 'Susan Pagenkopf. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThese hands that I am holding out,\r\nI raise to offer my life to You.\r\nAs I open them to You\r\nPlease accept my sacrifice.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYour hands are guiding me day and night.\r\nTake mine to help me walk in the Light.\r\nWhat my hands will do for You,\r\nThey will do with all their might.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThese hands were made to serve You,\r\nTo bring Your healing to this world.\r\nThese hands were made to worship,\r\nTo be obedient to Your Word.\r\nAnd my hands are reaching out\r\nTo grab hold of Your love.\r\n', '', ' 1997 Susan Pagenkopf.', '', '', 'These hands that I am holding out, I raise to offer my life to You. As I open them to You Please accept my sacrifice. Your hands are guiding me day and night. Take mine to help me walk in the Light. What my hands will do for You, They will do with all their might. These hands were made to serve You, To bring Your healing to this world. These hands were made to worship, To be obedient to Your Word. And my hands are reaching out To grab hold of Your love.'),
	(711, 'Alleluia (Jesus, I Love You)', 'Jude Del Hierro.  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nJesus, I love You, \r\nI bow down before You\r\nPraises and worship to our King\r\nAlleluia, alleluia,\r\n Alleluia, allelu.\r\n', '', ' 1985 Mercy Publishing.  ', '', '', 'Jesus, I love You, I bow down before You Praises and worship to our King Alleluia, alleluia, Alleluia, allelu.'),
	(713, 'At The Cross(Hillsong)', 'Reuben Morgan and Darlene Zschech', '~Intro:\r\n[A]  [E/G#]  [A]   [B]\r\n~Verse 1\r\n[E/G#]   Oh [A2]Lord You\'ve [B]searched [C#m7]me,\r\n[E/G#]   You [A2]know my [B]way;[-]\r\n[E/G#]   Even [A2]when I [B]fail [C#m7]You,\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me.\r\n[E/G#]   Your [A2]holy [B]pre[C#m7]sence\r\n[E/G#]    Sur[A2]rounding [B]me[-]\r\n[E/G#]   In [A2]every [B]sea[C#m7]son,\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me;\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me.\r\n~Chorus\r\n[E] At the cross I bow my [C#m]knee,\r\nWhere Your blood was [E/G#]shed for [A]me,\r\nThere\'s no greater love than [B]this.\r\n[E] You have overcome the [C#m]grave,\r\nYour glory fills the [E/G#]highest [A]place,\r\nWhat can separate me [B]now?\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[E/G#]   You [A2]go be[B]fore [C#m7]me,\r\n[E/G#]   You [A2]shield my [B]way,[-]\r\n[E/G#]   Your [A2]hand up[B]holds [C#m7]me;\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me.\r\n[E/G#]   And [A2]when the [B]earth [C#m7]fades,\r\n[E/G#]   Falls [A2]from my e[B]yes,[-]\r\n[E/G#]   And You [A2]stand be[B]fore [C#m7]me,\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me;\r\n[A2]I know You [Bsus]love [B]me.\r\n~Bridge\r\nYou tore the [A2]veil, [B]You made a [C#m7]way\r\nWhen You [A]said that [C#m7]it is [B]done.\r\n', '', '2006 Hillsong Publishing. ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/eOY0mjjmx8Y&hl=en&fs=1', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=159406854&id=159406811&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Hillsong - Mighty to Save - At the Cross" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'Oh Lord You\\\'ve searched me, You know my way; Even when I fail You, I know You love me. Your holy presence Surrounding me In every season, I know You love me; I know You love me. At the cross I bow my knee, Where Your blood was shed for me, There\\\'s no greater love than this. You have overcome the grave, Your glory fills the highest place, What can separate me now? You go before me, You shield my way, Your hand upholds me; I know You love me. And when the earth fades, Falls from my eyes, And You stand before me, I know You love me; I know You love me. You tore the veil, You made a way When You said that it is done.'),
	(714, 'Highest Place', 'Ramon Pink. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe place You on the highest place, \r\nFor You are the great High Priest;\r\nWe place You high above all else,\r\nAnd we come to You\r\nAnd worship at Your feet.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1983 Scripture In Song,', '', '', 'We place You on the highest place, For You are the great High Priest; We place You high above all else, And we come to You And worship at Your feet.'),
	(715, 'Holy Spirit, Living In Me', 'Carol McHardy  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHoly Spirit, \r\nI know you are living in me.\r\nJust as You promised\r\nJust like Jesus said it would be.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTeach me of God\'s glory,\r\nTeach me how to be set free;\r\nPrecious Holy Spirit, \r\nRoot out all the evil in me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI\'ve come to sit at the feet of the Father\r\nTo gaze at the face of the Living One.\r\nI\'ve come to relinquish self on the alter\r\nTo receive all the love of the Son.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHoly Spirit, \r\nI know you are living in me.\r\nYou are living water, \r\nWelling in the depths of me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCleanse me now and make me\r\nWholly undivided for Thee,\r\nWash me in the water,\r\nFlood out my iniquity.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Holy Spirit, I know you are living in me. Just as You promised Just like Jesus said it would be. Teach me of God\'s glory, Teach me how to be set free; Precious Holy Spirit, Root out all the evil in me. I\'ve come to sit at the feet of the Father To gaze at the face of the Living One. I\'ve come to relinquish self on the alter To receive all the love of the Son. Holy Spirit, I know you are living in me. You are living water, Welling in the depths of me. Cleanse me now and make me Wholly undivided for Thee, Wash me in the water, Flood out my iniquity.'),
	(716, 'Portugues Song Translation', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFor everything you have done,\r\nfor everything you will done,\r\nfor your promises, and for all I am\r\nI want to thank you with all my being.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMen: I thank you, my Lord\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\nI thank you for delivering me and for saving\r\nFor dying in my place\r\nI thank you, Jesus, I thank you.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'For everything you have done, for everything you will done, for your promises, and for all I am I want to thank you with all my being. Men: I thank you, my Lord I thank you for delivering me and for saving For dying in my place I thank you, Jesus, I thank you.'),
	(717, 'Give Glory To Jesus', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nGive glory to Jesus\r\nGive glory to God\r\nGive glory to Jesus\r\nGive glory to God\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSing praise to His name\r\nHallelujah\r\nSing praise to His name\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Give glory to Jesus Give glory to God Give glory to Jesus Give glory to God Sing praise to His name Hallelujah Sing praise to His name'),
	(718, 'This Is The Day', 'Bob Fitts ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe goes before me,\r\n He walks beside me,\r\nHe lives within me,\r\n He\'s the Lover of my soul;\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThis is the day\r\nthat the Lord has made, \r\nI will rejoice and celebrate;\r\nThis is the day\r\nthat the Lord has made,\r\nI will rejoice, \r\nI will rejoice and celebrate.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe\'s my defender,\r\n He\'s my provider,\r\nHis overflowing mercies\r\n are brand new every day.\r\n', '', '1996 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'He goes before me, He walks beside me, He lives within me, He\'s the Lover of my soul; This is the day that the Lord has made, I will rejoice and celebrate; This is the day that the Lord has made, I will rejoice, I will rejoice and celebrate. He\'s my defender, He\'s my provider, His overflowing mercies are brand new every day.'),
	(719, 'Hand In Hand', 'Dennis L. Jernigan; c. 1995 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, Inc. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLike a star in the heavens, \r\nLike a flower in the spring,\r\nLike a bluebird in the forest \r\nWith a joyous song to sing,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHand in hand, dear Jesus,\r\nAll along the way.\r\nHand in hand, dear Jesus, \r\nEach and ev\'ry day.\r\nHand in hand, dear Jesus, \r\nI love to hear You say,\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n"Child, I want to wipe away your ev\'ry tear!\r\nChild, I want to take away your ev\'ry fear!\r\nChild, I love you so,\r\nI want to hold you near!"\r\nWe belong together in a perfect way:\r\nJesus, my Lord and me!\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nLike valleys in the mountains,\r\nLike waves upon the sea,\r\nThey belong together in a perfect way\r\nJust like my Lord and me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nLike a sunrise in the morning, \r\nLike a sunset ends the day,\r\nLike a mother and a baby, \r\nLike a potter and the clay,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nLike light\'ning and the thunder,\r\nLike a river and the sea,\r\nThey belong together in a perfect way\r\nJust like my Lord and me.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Shepherd\'s Heart Music, Inc. ', '', '', 'Like a star in the heavens, Like a flower in the spring, Like a bluebird in the forest With a joyous song to sing, Hand in hand, dear Jesus, All along the way. Hand in hand, dear Jesus, Each and ev\'ry day. Hand in hand, dear Jesus, I love to hear You say, "Child, I want to wipe away your ev\'ry tear! Child, I want to take away your ev\'ry fear! Child, I love you so, I want to hold you near!" We belong together in a perfect way: Jesus, my Lord and me! Like valleys in the mountains, Like waves upon the sea, They belong together in a perfect way Just like my Lord and me. Like a sunrise in the morning, Like a sunset ends the day, Like a mother and a baby, Like a potter and the clay, Like light\'ning and the thunder, Like a river and the sea, They belong together in a perfect way Just like my Lord and me.'),
	(720, 'Rejoice The Lord Is King (Hymn #228)', 'Charles Wesley & John Darwall', '~Verse 1\r\nRejoice, the Lord is King!\r\nYour Lord and King adore!\r\nRejoice, give thanks, and sing,\r\nAnd triumph ev-er-more:\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLift up your heart,\r\n lift up your voice!\r\nRejoice, again I say, \r\nI say rejoice! Amen.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThe Lord, our Savior, reigns,\r\nThe God of truth and love;\r\nWhen He had purged our stains,\r\nHe took His seat above:\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nHis kingdom cannot fail,\r\nHe rules o\'er earth and heav\'n:\r\nThe keys of death and hell\r\nAre to our Jesus giv\'n:\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nRejoice in glorious hope!\r\nOur Lord the Judge shall come\r\nAnd take His servants up\r\nTo their eternal home:\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/2N0iVysrykU', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Rejoice, the Lord is King! Your Lord and King adore! Rejoice, give thanks, and sing, And triumph ev-er-more: Lift up your heart, lift up your voice! Rejoice, again I say, I say rejoice! Amen. The Lord, our Savior, reigns, The God of truth and love; When He had purged our stains, He took His seat above: His kingdom cannot fail, He rules o\'er earth and heav\'n: The keys of death and hell Are to our Jesus giv\'n: Rejoice in glorious hope! Our Lord the Judge shall come And take His servants up To their eternal home:).'),
	(721, 'Open The Gates', 'Graham Kkenrick;', '\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOpen the gates for the King of kings.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWomen echo\r\n~Verse 6\r\nOpen the gates for the King of kings.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nWomen echo\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nPrepare the way of the Lord.\r\n\r\n~Verse 12\r\n	 Women echo\r\n~Verse 15\r\nPrepare the way of the Lord.\r\n	\r\n~Verse 16\r\nWomen echo\r\n~Verse 19\r\nHosanna!  \r\n\r\n~Verse 20\r\nWomen echo\r\n~Verse 23\r\nHosanna!  \r\n\r\n~Verse 24\r\nWomen echo\r\n~Verse 27\r\nHosanna!\r\n', '', ' 1991 Make Way Music/ Adm. by Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music in U.S. and Canada.  ', '', '', 'Open the gates for the King of kings. Women echo Open the gates for the King of kings. Women echo Prepare the way of the Lord. Women echo Prepare the way of the Lord. Women echo Hosanna! Women echo Hosanna! Women echo Hosanna!'),
	(722, 'Lord Reign In Me', 'Brenton Brown', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]Over [G]all the ea[F]rth, you r[G]eign on [C]high\r\nEvery m[G]ountain stre[F]am, every s[G]unset sk[Am7]y\r\nBut my [G]one requ[F]est, Lord, my [G]only ai[Dm7]m\r\nIs that you\'d [F]reign in [G]me again\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C]Lord, [G]reign in m[F]e, reign i[G]n your pow[C]er\r\nOver a[G]ll my dre[F]ams, in my [G]darkest ho[Am7]ur\r\nYou a[G]re the Lo[F]rd of [G]all I a[Dm7]m\r\nSo won\'t you [F]reign in [G]me agai[C]n[G][F][Am7][G][F]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nOver every thought, over every word\r\nMay my life reflect the beauty of my Lord\r\n\'Cause you mean more to me than any earthly thing\r\nSo won\'t you reign in me again\r\n', '', '1998 Vineyard Songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/ZzEkhTwiODc', '', 'Over all the earth, you reign on high Every mountain stream, every sunset sky But my one request, Lord, my only aim Is that you\'d reign in me again Lord, reign in me, reign in your power Over all my dreams, in my darkest hour You are the Lord of all I am So won\'t you reign in me again Over every thought, over every word May my life reflect the beauty of my Lord \'Cause you mean more to me than any earthly thing So won\'t you reign in me again'),
	(723, 'Make A Joyful Noise', 'Jimmy Owens', '~Verse 1\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord,\r\n All the earth!\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord!\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord,\r\n All the earth!\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord!\r\nMake a loud noise and rejoice! \r\n Sing praises!\r\nMake a joyful noise unto the Lord!\r\nMake a loud noise and rejoice! \r\n Sing praises!\r\n\r\n', '', '1974 by Lexicon Music, Inc.', '', '', 'Make a joyful noise unto the Lord, All the earth! Make a joyful noise unto the Lord! Make a joyful noise unto the Lord, All the earth! Make a joyful noise unto the Lord! Make a joyful noise unto the Lord! Make a loud noise and rejoice! Sing praises! Make a joyful noise unto the Lord! Make a loud noise and rejoice! Sing praises!'),
	(724, 'I Lift My Eyes Up (Psalm 121)', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse\r\n[C]   I lift my [F]eyes up [C] to the [F]mountains\r\n[C]   Where does my [F]help [C]come [G]from?\r\n[C]   My help comes [F]from You, [C] Maker of [F]Heaven\r\n[C]   Creator [F]of [C]the [G]earth\r\n~Chorus\r\n[C/E]   O how I [F]need You Lord, [C/E] You are my [F]only hope\r\n[C/E]   You\'re my [F]on[C]ly [G]prayer\r\n[C/E]   So I will [F]wait for You [C/E] to come and [F]rescue me\r\n[C/E]   Come and [F]give [C]me [G]life\r\n', '', '1989 Langley Vineyard Music;   ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/dwdi3pnQ4aQ&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'I lift my eyes up  to the mountains Where does my help come from? My help comes from You,  Maker of Heaven Creator of the earth O how I need You Lord,  You are my only hope You\\\'re my only prayer So I will wait for You  to come and rescue me Come and give me life'),
	(725, 'Fire', 'Paul Oakley', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAnd I will run with all of the passion\r\nYou\'ve put in me.\r\nI will spread\r\nThe seed of the gospel\r\nEverywhere.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFire, there\'s a fire, \r\nSweet fire burning in my heart.\r\nFire, there\'s a fire, \r\nSweet fire burning in my heart.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd I can feel the power of Your hand \r\nUpon me.\r\nNow I know\r\nI\'ll never be the same again.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLet me feel Your tongues of fire \r\nResting upon me.\r\nLet me hear\r\nThe sound of Your mighty rushing wind.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nLet my life\r\nBe like an offering of worship.\r\nLet me be\r\nA living sacrifice of praise.\r\n', '', ' 1995 Kingsway\'s Thankyou Music/Administered in North America by EMI Christian Music Publishing/ P.O', '', '', 'And I will run with all of the passion You\'ve put in me. I will spread The seed of the gospel Everywhere. Fire, there\'s a fire, Sweet fire burning in my heart. Fire, there\'s a fire, Sweet fire burning in my heart. And I can feel the power of Your hand Upon me. Now I know I\'ll never be the same again. Let me feel Your tongues of fire Resting upon me. Let me hear The sound of Your mighty rushing wind. Let my life Be like an offering of worship. Let me be A living sacrifice of praise.'),
	(726, 'We Need Your Presence', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord, we need Your presence here with us,\r\nCome, inhabit our lives;\r\nLord, we seek Your Spirit in our midst,\r\nChanging our hearts, filling our minds.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, we need Your presence\r\n	 here with us today,\r\nFill us with Your Spirit,\r\nConsume us with Your praise;\r\nShow Your mighty power,\r\nReveal Your truth and love,\r\nLord, we need Your presence with us.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Lord, we need Your presence here with us, Come, inhabit our lives; Lord, we seek Your Spirit in our midst, Changing our hearts, filling our minds. Lord, we need Your presence here with us today, Fill us with Your Spirit, Consume us with Your praise; Show Your mighty power, Reveal Your truth and love, Lord, we need Your presence with us.'),
	(728, 'That\'s Why I\'m Here', 'Lenny LeBlanc', '~Verse 1\r\nI didn\'t come here to sing about the Devil,\r\nI came to praise the name of the Lord.\r\nI\'m here to tell you, once I was a rebel,\r\nI\'ve been delivered \r\nby the power of His Word.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nTo sing worthy is the Lord\r\nWho is my rock\r\nJesus the only Son of God.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThat\'s why I\'m here, to lift up His name,\r\nTell the whole world\r\n I\'m the reason He came;\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThat\'s why I\'m here, to glorify Him.\r\nHe\'s the only One who deserves my praise,\r\nGonna live for Him all the rest of my days;\r\nThat\'s why I\'m here;\r\nThat\'s why I\'m here.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI didn\'t come here to talk about the weather,\r\nI came to hear about the blood of the Lamb.\r\nI wanna stand up and worship my Savior,\r\nShout hallelujah and say amen.\r\n', '', '1999 Integrity Hosanna! Music & LenSongs Publishing & Breneddie Music ', '', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewAlbum?i=272607982&id=272607913&s=143455&uo=6"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Lenny LeBlanc - Above All - That&#39;s Why I&#39;m Here" src="http://ax.itunes.apple.com/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'I didn\\\'t come here to sing about the Devil, I came to praise the name of the Lord. I\\\'m here to tell you, once I was a rebel, I\\\'ve been delivered by the power of His Word. To sing worthy is the Lord Who is my rock Jesus the only Son of God. That\\\'s why I\\\'m here, to lift up His name, Tell the whole world I\\\'m the reason He came; That\\\'s why I\\\'m here, to glorify Him. He\\\'s the only One who deserves my praise, Gonna live for Him all the rest of my days; That\\\'s why I\\\'m here; That\\\'s why I\\\'m here. I didn\\\'t come here to talk about the weather, I came to hear about the blood of the Lamb. I wanna stand up and worship my Savior, Shout hallelujah and say amen.'),
	(729, 'Rejoice In The Lord Always', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nRejoice in the Lord always,\r\n	 again I say rejoice!\r\nRejoice in the Lord always,\r\n	 again I say rejoice!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nRejoice, rejoice \r\nagain I say rejoice\r\nRejoice, rejoice\r\nagain I say rejoice\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Rejoice in the Lord always, again I say rejoice! Rejoice in the Lord always, again I say rejoice! Rejoice, rejoice again I say rejoice Rejoice, rejoice again I say rejoice'),
	(730, 'I Long For The Day', 'Dennis Jernigan. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI long for the day\r\nWhen my Lord come to take me away\r\nWhether by death,\r\nOr if You come for me on a horse of white.\r\nAny way You come will be alright with me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI long to just hear You say, "Now is the time!\r\nChild won\'t you come away?"\r\nThen I\'ll take Your hand,\r\nSurrendering completely to You that day.\r\nO, I can\'t contain the joy that day will bring!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO, Lord while I wait\r\nI will cling to each word that You say!\r\nSpeak to my heart\r\nYour voice is live to me be it night or day!\r\nAnything You say will be alright with me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou see, my heart\'s greatest need,\r\nYou and me walking intimately.\r\nYou\'re my All in All\r\nAnd I am waiting patiently for Your call,\r\nWhen You call me to Your side eternally!\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nForever with You, no crying there.\r\nForever with You no burdens,\r\nNo more worldly cares.\r\nMy heart is anticipating\r\nEternally with You, celebrating You!\r\nForever with You I long to be.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nForever worshiping,\r\nKnowing You intimately!\r\nWhen You say, "Child, no more waiting!\r\nI\'ll spend forever just celebrating too!"\r\nForever Lord, I\'ll be celebrating You!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nI\'ll see all my loved ones gone before.\r\nI\'ll get to be with them,\r\nLaugh with them, hold them once more!\r\nThere\'ll be no more separating!\r\nTogether we will be celebrating You!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nTogether we\'ll worship You\r\nAnd sing forever praising\r\nLord Jesus our Savior and King!\r\nWhen you say, "Child, no more waiting!\r\nEnter your rest and start celebrating too!"\r\nForever Lord, I\'ll be celebrating You!\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nWhen I get to see You face to face,\r\nWhen I can finally put sight\r\nTo the voice I\'ve embraced!\r\nIt will be worth all the waiting\r\nFor that one moment of celebrating You!\r\n\r\n~Verse 11\r\nWhen I get to feel Your hand in mine,\r\nWhen I can finally be free\r\nFrom this prison called time!\r\nWhen You say, Child, I\'ve been waiting\r\nFor this one moment of celebrating too!\r\nFor this one moment of celebrating You!"\r\n', '', ' 1993 Shepherd\'s', '', '', 'I long for the day When my Lord come to take me away Whether by death, Or if You come for me on a horse of white. Any way You come will be alright with me. I long to just hear You say, "Now is the time! Child won\'t you come away?" Then I\'ll take Your hand, Surrendering completely to You that day. O, I can\'t contain the joy that day will bring! O, Lord while I wait I will cling to each word that You say! Speak to my heart Your voice is live to me be it night or day! Anything You say will be alright with me. You see, my heart\'s greatest need, You and me walking intimately. You\'re my All in All And I am waiting patiently for Your call, When You call me to Your side eternally! Forever with You, no crying there. Forever with You no burdens, No more worldly cares. My heart is anticipating Eternally with You, celebrating You! Forever with You I long to be. Forever worshiping, Knowing You intimately! When You say, "Child, no more waiting! I\'ll spend forever just celebrating too!" Forever Lord, I\'ll be celebrating You! I\'ll see all my loved ones gone before. I\'ll get to be with them, Laugh with them, hold them once more! There\'ll be no more separating! Together we will be celebrating You! Together we\'ll worship You And sing forever praising Lord Jesus our Savior and King! When you say, "Child, no more waiting! Enter your rest and start celebrating too!" Forever Lord, I\'ll be celebrating You! When I get to see You face to face, When I can finally put sight To the voice I\'ve embraced! It will be worth all the waiting For that one moment of celebrating You! When I get to feel Your hand in mine, When I can finally be free From this prison called time! When You say, Child, I\'ve been waiting For this one moment of celebrating too! For this one moment of celebrating You!"'),
	(731, 'To Him Who Sits On The Throne', 'Debbye Grasfsma ', '~Verse 1\r\nTo Him who sits on the Throne \r\nAnd unto the Lamb\r\nTo Him who sits on the Throne\r\nAnd unto the Lamb\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nBe blessing and honor and\r\nGlory and power forever\r\nBe blessing and honor and\r\nGlory and power forever\r\n', '', ' 1984 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music ', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/qgECtWyBZA0&hl=en_US&fs=1&', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/to-him-who-sits-on-the-throne/id298143099?i=298143146&uo=6" target="itunes_store"><img height="15" width="61" alt="Carlton Pearson - Azusa Praise - Jubilee! - To Him Who Sits On the Throne" src="http://ax.phobos.apple.com.edgesuite.net/images/badgeitunes61x15dark.gif" /></a>', 'To Him who sits on the Throne And unto the Lamb To Him who sits on the Throne And unto the Lamb Be blessing and honor and Glory and power forever Be blessing and honor and Glory and power forever'),
	(732, 'My Jesus I Love Thee', 'William R. Featherston and music by Adoniram J. Gordon. Public Domain, ', '~Verse 1\r\nMy Jesus, I love Thee, \r\nI know Thou art mine-\r\nFor Thee all the follies \r\nOf sin I resign;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI love Thee because \r\nThou hast first loved me.\r\nAnd purchased my pardon\r\n On Calvary\'s tree;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI\'ll love Thee in life, \r\nI will love Thee in death,\r\nAnd praise Thee as long as \r\nThou lendest me breath;\r\n   \r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nIn mansions of glory \r\nAnd endless delight,\r\nI\'ll ever adore Thee \r\nIn heaven so bright;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nI\'ll sing with the glittering\r\n Crown on my brow,\r\n"If ever I loved Thee, \r\nMy Jesus, \'tis now."\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nAnd say when the death-dew\r\n Lies cold on my brow,\r\n"If ever I loved, Thee,\r\n My Jesus, \'tis now."\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nI love Thee for wearing \r\nThe thorns on Thy brow:\r\nIf ever I loved Thee, \r\nMy Jesus, \'tis now.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nMy gracious Redeemer, \r\nMy Savior art Thou;\r\nIf ever I loved Thee, \r\nMy Jesus, \'tis now.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/lqFOsOPj9uk', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(My Jesus, I love Thee, I know Thou art mine- For Thee all the follies Of sin I resign; I love Thee because Thou hast first loved me. And purchased my pardon On Calvary\'s tree; I\'ll love Thee in life, I will love Thee in death, And praise Thee as long as Thou lendest me breath; In mansions of glory And endless delight, I\'ll ever adore Thee In heaven so bright; I\'ll sing with the glittering Crown on my brow, "If ever I loved Thee, My Jesus, \'tis now." And say when the death-dew Lies cold on my brow, "If ever I loved, Thee, My Jesus, \'tis now." I love Thee for wearing The thorns on Thy brow: If ever I loved Thee, My Jesus, \'tis now. My gracious Redeemer, My Savior art Thou; If ever I loved Thee, My Jesus, \'tis now.).'),
	(733, 'We Bring The Sacrifice Of Praise', 'Kirk Dearman', '[D]We bring a [F#m]sacrifice of [D7]praise into the [G]house of the [A7]Lord.\r\n[D]We bring a [Em]sacrifice of [F#m]praise into the [G]house of [A]the [D]Lord.\r\nAnd we [G]offer up to [D]You the sacri[A]fices of [D]thanksgiv[D7]ing.\r\nAnd we [G]offer up to [F#m]You the sacri[Em]fices [A]of [D]joy.\r\n\r\n', '', '1984 John T. Benson Pub. Co.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/h2OmaKsVfxs', '', 'We bring a sacrifice of praise into the house of the Lord. We bring a sacrifice of praise into the house of the Lord. And we offer up to You the sacrifices of thanksgiving. And we offer up to You the sacrifices of joy.'),
	(734, 'Jesus Paid It All', 'Elvina M. Hall; Music by John T. Grape', '~Verse 1\r\nI hear the Savior say, \r\n"Thy strength indeed is small!\r\nChild of weakness, watch and pray,\r\nFind in Me thine all in all."\r\n~Verse 2\r\nJesus paid it all, \r\nAll to Him I owe;\r\nSin had left a crimson stain\r\nHe washed it white as snow.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLord, now indeed I find\r\nThy pow\'r, and Thine alone,\r\nCan change the leper\'s spots\r\nAnd melt the heart of stone.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor nothing good have I\r\nWhereby Thy grace to claim,\r\nI\'ll wash my garments white\r\nIn the blood of Calv\'ry\'s Lamb.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd when before the throne\r\nI stand in Him complete,\r\n"Jesus died my soul to save,"\r\nMy lips shall still repeat.\r\n', '', '', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/iaZbqDd33Yw', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I hear the Savior say, "Thy strength indeed is small! Child of weakness, watch and pray, Find in Me thine all in all." Jesus paid it all, All to Him I owe; Sin had left a crimson stain He washed it white as snow. Lord, now indeed I find Thy pow\'r, and Thine alone, Can change the leper\'s spots And melt the heart of stone. For nothing good have I Whereby Thy grace to claim, I\'ll wash my garments white In the blood of Calv\'ry\'s Lamb. And when before the throne I stand in Him complete, "Jesus died my soul to save," My lips shall still repeat.).'),
	(735, 'Beauty For Ashes', '', '~Verse 1\r\nHe gave me beauty for ashes\r\nThe oil of joy for mourning\r\nThe garment of praise\r\nFor the spirit of heaviness\r\nThat we might be trees of righteousness\r\nThe planting of the Lord\r\nThat He might be glorified\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1976, 1979, 1983 Maranatha! Music (admin. by Music Services).', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/0q5k6uPMxv4', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(He gave me beauty for ashes The oil of joy for mourning The garment of praise For the spirit of heaviness That we might be trees of righteousness The planting of the Lord That He might be glorified).'),
	(736, 'Praise Song', 'John Wimber', '~Verse 1\r\nSon of God, this is our praise song,\r\nJesus, my Lord, I sing to You\r\nCome now, Spirit of God,\r\nBreathe life into these words of love\r\nAngels join from above\r\n as we sing our praise song.\r\n~Chorus\r\nWe praise You, we praise You\r\nWe praise You, we praise You.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSon of God, this is our love song.\r\nJesus, my Lord, I sing to You;\r\nCome now, Spirit of God\r\nBreathe life into these words of love\r\nAngels join from above\r\n as we sing our praise song.\r\n~Chorus 2\r\nWe love You, We love You,\r\nWe love You, We worship You.\r\n', '', '1981 Mercy Pbul. (Admin. by Marantha! Music)', '', '', 'Son of God, this is our praise song, Jesus, my Lord, I sing to You Come now, Spirit of God, Breathe life into these words of love Angels join from above as we sing our praise song. We praise You, we praise You We praise You, we praise You. Son of God, this is our love song. Jesus, my Lord, I sing to You; Come now, Spirit of God Breathe life into these words of love Angels join from above as we sing our praise song. We love You, We love You, We love You, We worship You.'),
	(737, 'I Lift Your Name', 'David Ruis', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]Lord, my heart can [Bm]grow, so [E]far away and [A]cold;\r\n[A]And yet for me Your [Bm]love is still the [E]same\r\n[A]Lord, I bend my [Bm]knee in [E]awe and fear of [A]Thee\r\n[A]My head bowed down in [Bm]rev\'rence to Your [E]name.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI l[A]ift Your n[D]ame, Your Ho[E]ly n[C#m]ame,\r\n[F#m]Jehovah [D]God, E[E]lohim\r\nThe Gr[A]eat I [D]Am, the Ri[E]sen [C#m]Lamb\r\nMy [F#m]Comfor[D]ter [E]and [A]King.  	\r\n~Verse 2\r\nLord, my heart\'s desire is to be filled with the Spirit Fire,\r\nMy purpose is to worship You alone.\r\nOpen up my soul to worship and adore,\r\nTo be a fragrane offered to Your throne.\r\n', '', '1989 Maranatha Praise, Inc.', '', '', 'Lord, my heart can grow, so far away and cold; And yet for me Your love is still the same Lord, I bend my knee in awe and fear of Thee My head bowed down in rev\'rence to Your name. I lift Your name, Your Holy name, Jehovah God, Elohim The Great I Am, the Risen Lamb My Comforter and King. Lord, my heart\'s desire is to be filled with the Spirit Fire, My purpose is to worship You alone. Open up my soul to worship and adore, To be a fragrane offered to Your throne.'),
	(738, 'Your Great Love', 'Chris Christensen', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHeavenly Father, Son, and Holy Spirit,\r\nWe\'re here to bless You \r\nand give You praise;\r\nSpirits rejoice and hearts overflow \r\n	 just to know Your love.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nCovenant Keeper, we are Yours forever, \r\nFriend and Redeemer, we will not go free;\r\nWe\'re bound by Your mercy, \r\n	 held by Your grace,\r\nCaptives of Your great love. \r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYour great love\r\n is stronger than the mountains,\r\nYour great love is deeper than the oceans; \r\nYour great love \r\nis higher than the heavens up above, \r\nYour great love.\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Heavenly Father, Son, and Holy Spirit, We\'re here to bless You and give You praise; Spirits rejoice and hearts overflow just to know Your love. Covenant Keeper, we are Yours forever, Friend and Redeemer, we will not go free; We\'re bound by Your mercy, held by Your grace, Captives of Your great love. Your great love is stronger than the mountains, Your great love is deeper than the oceans; Your great love is higher than the heavens up above, Your great love.'),
	(739, 'Make Us One', 'Paul Johnson', '~Verse 1\r\nFor You have chosen \r\nThat together we should be\r\nA reflection of \r\nYour love and unity.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMake us one, Father God,\r\n Make us one,\r\nThat the world may know \r\nYou gave Your only Son.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFill us with the love \r\nYou\'ve given us to share,\r\nAnd protect us from\r\n The evil ev\'rywhere.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSend us in the world \r\nTo be a channel of \r\nAll the glorious riches\r\nOf your love.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAnd we\'ll tell the world \r\nThe truth of how You feel,\r\nThat the world may know\r\n Your love for us is real.\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCleanse us from \r\nOur old nature of sin, \r\nThat the world may know \r\nThat Jesus\' love is real.\r\n', '', '1973 by New One-Way Pub.', '', '', 'For You have chosen That together we should be A reflection of Your love and unity. Make us one, Father God, Make us one, That the world may know You gave Your only Son. Fill us with the love You\\\'ve given us to share, And protect us from The evil ev\\\'rywhere. Send us in the world To be a channel of All the glorious riches Of your love. And we\\\'ll tell the world The truth of how You feel, That the world may know Your love for us is real. Cleanse us from Our old nature of sin, That the world may know That Jesus\\\' love is real.'),
	(740, 'And They Overcame Him', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nAnd they overcame him\r\nBy the blood of the Lamb\r\nAnd the word of their testimony;\r\nAnd they loved not their lives\r\nUnto the death,\r\nAnd they loved not their lives \r\nUnto death\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'And they overcame him By the blood of the Lamb And the word of their testimony; And they loved not their lives Unto the death, And they loved not their lives Unto death'),
	(741, 'Trading My Sorrows', 'Darrell Evans', '{t:Trading My Sorrows}\r\n{key:A}\r\n{gc:Intro:}\r\n[A][D][F#m][Esus4][E]\r\n\r\n[A]I\'m [D]trading my [F#m]sor[Esus4]rows,[E]\r\nI\'m trading my shame.\r\n[A]I\'m [D]laying them [F#m]down for the [E]joy of the Lord[A][D][F#m][Esus4][E]\r\nI\'m trading my sickness,\r\nI\'m trading my pain,\r\nI\'m laying them down for the joy of the Lord.\r\n\r\n{soc}\r\n[A]Yes, Lord, [D]yes, Lord. [F#m]Yes, yes, [Esus4]Lord.[E]\r\nYes, Lord, yes, Lord. Yes, yes, Lord.\r\nYes, Lord, yes, Lord. Yes, yes, Lord. Amen! \r\n{eoc}\r\n\r\nI am pressed but not crushed,\r\nPersecuted not abandoned,\r\nStruck down but not destroyed.\r\nI am blessed beyond the curse,\r\nFor His promise will endure\r\nThat His joy\'s gonna be my strength.\r\n\r\n{gc:Bridge:}\r\n[E] Though the sorrow may [A/E]last for the [E]night,\r\nHis [Gadd9]joy comes with the morning.\r\n\r\n{c:Darrell Evans}\r\n{c:(c)1998 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music / ASCAP (Administered by Integrity Music, Inc).}\r\n\r\n', '', '1998 Integrity Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/2KsfwvpcQhY', '<a href="http://itunes.apple.com/ca/album/trading-my-sorrows/id467739228?i=467740342&uo=4" target="itunes_store">Trading My Sorrows - Top 50 Praise Songs</a>', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I\'m trading my sorrows, I\'m trading my shame. I\'m laying them down for the joy of the Lord I\'m trading my sickness, I\'m trading my pain, I\'m laying them down for the joy of the Lord. Yes, Lord, yes, Lord. Yes, yes, Lord. Yes, Lord, yes, Lord. Yes, yes, Lord. Yes, Lord, yes, Lord. Yes, yes, Lord. Amen! I am pressed but not crushed, Persecuted not abandoned, Struck down but not destroyed. I am blessed beyond the curse, For His promise will endure That His joy\'s gonna be my strength. Though the sorrow may last for the night, His joy comes with the morning.).'),
	(742, 'More Love To Thee', 'Elizabeth P. Prentiss and Music by William H. Doane', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMore love to Thee, O Christ,\r\nMore love to Thee!\r\nHear Thou the prayer I make\r\nOn bended knee;\r\nThis is my earnest plea:\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMore love, O Christ to Thee\r\nMore love to Thee,\r\nMore love to Thee.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThen shall my latest breath\r\nWhisper Thy praise;\r\nThis be the parting cry\r\nMy heart shall raise;\r\nThis still my prayer shall be:\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nOnce earthly joy I craved,\r\nSought peace and rest;\r\nNow Thee alone I seek,\r\nGive what is best;\r\nThis all my prayer shall be:\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'More love to Thee, O Christ, More love to Thee! Hear Thou the prayer I make On bended knee; This is my earnest plea: More love, O Christ to Thee More love to Thee, More love to Thee. Then shall my latest breath Whisper Thy praise; This be the parting cry My heart shall raise; This still my prayer shall be: Once earthly joy I craved, Sought peace and rest; Now Thee alone I seek, Give what is best; This all my prayer shall be:'),
	(743, 'More Of  You', 'Kent Blanton', '~Verse 1\r\nMore of You, I want more of You!\r\nIn my heart Lord I cry, \r\n"I want more of You!"\r\nMore of You, I want more of You!\r\nIn my heart Lord I cry,\r\n"I want more of You!"\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAll of me, I give You all of me!\r\nIn my heart Lord I choose\r\nTo give You all of me! \r\nAll of me, I give You all of me!\r\nIn my heart Lord I choose\r\nTo give You all of me! \r\n~Chorus\r\nYou are my God,\r\nYou are my King,\r\nYou are my Lord, My everything.\r\nYou are my hope,\r\nYou are my destiny,\r\nYou are my joy, \r\nYou are the God of me.\r\n', '', '1995 Kent Blanton', '', '', 'More of You, I want more of You! In my heart Lord I cry, \\"I want more of You!\\" More of You, I want more of You! In my heart Lord I cry, \\"I want more of You!\\" All of me, I give You all of me! In my heart Lord I choose To give You all of me! All of me, I give You all of me! In my heart Lord I choose To give You all of me! You are my God, You are my King, You are my Lord, My everything. You are my hope, You are my destiny, You are my joy, You are the God of me.'),
	(744, 'Love Lifted Me', 'James Rowe; Music by Howard E. Smith ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI was walking in sin,\r\nFar from the peaceful shore;\r\nVery deeply stained within\r\nSinking to rise no more;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLove lifted me!\r\nLove lifted me!\r\nWhen nothing else could help,\r\nLove lifted me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBut the Master of the sea\r\nHeard my despairing cry\r\nFrom the waters lifted me,\r\nNow safe am I.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nAll my heart to Him I give\r\nEver to Him I\'ll cling\r\nIn His blessed presence live\r\nEver His praises sing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nSouls in danger, look above,\r\nJesus completely saves;\r\nHe will lift you by His love\r\nOut of the angry waves.\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nLove so mighty and so true\r\nMerits my soul\'s best songs;\r\nFaithful, loving service too,\r\nTo Him belongs.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nHe\'s the Master of the sea,\r\nBillows His will obey;\r\nHe your Savior wants to be,\r\nBe saved to day.\r\n', '', ' 1912 Renewal 1940 by Mrs. Howard Smith Assigned  ', '', '', 'I was walking in sin, Far from the peaceful shore; Very deeply stained within Sinking to rise no more; Love lifted me! Love lifted me! When nothing else could help, Love lifted me. But the Master of the sea Heard my despairing cry From the waters lifted me, Now safe am I. All my heart to Him I give Ever to Him I\'ll cling In His blessed presence live Ever His praises sing. Souls in danger, look above, Jesus completely saves; He will lift you by His love Out of the angry waves. Love so mighty and so true Merits my soul\'s best songs; Faithful, loving service too, To Him belongs. He\'s the Master of the sea, Billows His will obey; He your Savior wants to be, Be saved to day.'),
	(745, 'Every Knee Will Bow', 'Jerry Proppe.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThough You are God\r\nYou laid aside your crown\r\nYou became nothing\r\nFrom glory you came down\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThough You are God\r\nYou gave Your life for me\r\nYou became a servant\r\nHung Your life upon a tree\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThat\'s why the Father lifts you up\r\nFor all the world to see\r\nThat at the name of Jesus Christ\r\nFor all eternity ev\'ry knee will bow\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThat\'s why the Father lifts you up\r\nFor all the world to see\r\nThat at the name of Jesus Christ\r\nFor all eternity\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nEv\'ry knee will bow\r\nEv\'ry tongue confess\r\nTo the glory of the Father\r\nTo the son of righteousness\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nEv\'ry voice in heav\'n\r\nEv\'ry one upon the Earth\r\nWill join the ancient chorus\r\nWill join the universe\r\nYou are Lord, You are Lord\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nHallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah\r\nSing hallelujah\r\nHallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah\r\nSing hallelujah\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nYou are Lord, You\'re my Lord\r\n', '', ' 2007 / SOCAN / ', '', '', 'Though You are God You laid aside your crown You became nothing From glory you came down Though You are God You gave Your life for me You became a servant Hung Your life upon a tree That\'s why the Father lifts you up For all the world to see That at the name of Jesus Christ For all eternity ev\'ry knee will bow That\'s why the Father lifts you up For all the world to see That at the name of Jesus Christ For all eternity Ev\'ry knee will bow Ev\'ry tongue confess To the glory of the Father To the son of righteousness Ev\'ry voice in heav\'n Ev\'ry one upon the Earth Will join the ancient chorus Will join the universe You are Lord, You are Lord Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah Sing hallelujah Hallelujah, Hallelujah, Hallelujah Sing hallelujah You are Lord, You\'re my Lord'),
	(746, 'All Hail The Power Of Jesus\' Name', '', '~Verse 1\r\nAll [A]hail the pow\'r of [E]Jesus\' name! \r\nLet angels prostrate [A]fall.\r\nBring [A]forth the royal diadem, \r\nAnd [A]crown [E/G#]Him   [F#m]Lord [B]of [Esus]all,[E]\r\nBring [A]forth the royal [E]diadem,\r\nAnd [A/C#]crown [D]Him [A/E]Lord   [E] of [A]all.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nYe chosen seed of Israel\'s race, \r\nYe ransomed from the fall,\r\nHail Him who saves you by His grace, \r\nAnd crown Him Lord of all (x2)\r\n~Verse 3\r\nLet every kindred, every tribe\r\nOn this terrestrial ball\r\nTo Him all majesty ascribe,\r\nAnd crown Him Lord of all (x2)\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO that with yonder sacred throng, \r\nWe at His feet may fall!\r\nWe\'ll join the everlasting song, \r\nAnd crown Him Lord of all (x2)\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'All hail the pow\'r of Jesus\' name! Let angels prostrate fall. Bring forth the royal diadem, And crown Him   Lord of all, Bring forth the royal diadem, And crown Him Lord    of all. Ye chosen seed of Israel\'s race, Ye ransomed from the fall, Hail Him who saves you by His grace, And crown Him Lord of all (x2) Let every kindred, every tribe On this terrestrial ball To Him all majesty ascribe, And crown Him Lord of all (x2) O that with yonder sacred throng, We at His feet may fall! We\'ll join the everlasting song, And crown Him Lord of all (x2)');
