	(747, 'My Redeemer Lives', 'Hillsong', '~Verse 1\r\n[E7]I know He [A7]Rescued my soul\r\n[E7]His Blood [A7]covered my sin\r\nI be[E7]lieve[A7]  I be[E7]lieve[A7]\r\n[E7]My shame He\'s [A7]taken away\r\n[E7]My pain is [A7]healed in His name\r\nI be[E7]lieve[A7]  I be[E7]lieve[A7]\r\n~Pre-Chorus\r\n[B]I\'ll raise a banner\r\n[A]\'Cause my Lord has conquered the [B]grave\r\n~Chorus\r\nMy Re[E]deemer [A]lives my Re[C#m]deemer [Bsus4]lives\r\nMy Re[E]deemer [A]lives my Re[C#m]deemer [Bsus4]lives\r\nMy Re[E]deemer [A]lives my Re[C#m]deemer [Bsus4]lives\r\nMy Re[E]deemer [A]lives my Re[C#m]deemer [Bsus4]lives\r\n~Bridge\r\n[D]You lift my burdens\r\n[A/C#]I\'ll rise with You\r\nI\'m [E/G#]dancing on this [F#m7]mountain top\r\nTo [E/G#]see Your Kingdom [Bsus4]come', '', '1998 Reuben Morgan/Hillsongs Publishing', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/IBbSyig8vQ0&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'I know He Rescued my soul His Blood covered my sin I believe  I believe My shame He\\\'s taken away My pain is healed in His name I believe  I believe I\\\'ll raise a banner \\\'Cause my Lord has conquered the grave My Redeemer lives my Redeemer lives My Redeemer lives my Redeemer lives My Redeemer lives my Redeemer lives My Redeemer lives my Redeemer lives You lift my burdens I\\\'ll rise with You I\\\'m dancing on this mountain top To see Your Kingdom come'),
	(748, 'The Potter\'s Hand', ' Darlene Zschech', '~Verse 1\r\nBeautiful Lord wonderful Savior\r\nI know for sure all of my days are\r\nHeld in Your hand\r\nCrafted into Your perfect plan\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nTake me, mold me\r\nUse me, fill me\r\nI give my life to the Potter\'s hand\r\nCall me, guide me\r\nLead me, walk beside me\r\nI give my life to the Potter\'s hand.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nYou gently call me into Your presence\r\nGuiding me by Your Holy Spirit\r\nTeach me dear Lord\r\nTo live all of my life through Your eyes.\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI\'m captured by Your holy calling\r\nSet me apart\r\nI know You\'re drawing me to Yourself\r\nLead me Lord I pray.\r\n', '', '1997 Darlene Zschech/Hillsongs Australia', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/xDAITgJXO1I', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Beautiful Lord wonderful Savior I know for sure all of my days are Held in Your hand Crafted into Your perfect plan Take me, mold me Use me, fill me I give my life to the Potter\'s hand Call me, guide me Lead me, walk beside me I give my life to the Potter\'s hand. You gently call me into Your presence Guiding me by Your Holy Spirit Teach me dear Lord To live all of my life through Your eyes. I\'m captured by Your holy calling Set me apart I know You\'re drawing me to Yourself Lead me Lord I pray.).'),
	(749, 'Be Still And Know', '', '~Verse 1\r\nBe still and know that I Am God,\r\nBe still and know that I Am God,\r\nBe still and know that I Am God.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI Am the Lord that healeth thee,\r\nI Am the Lord that healeth thee,\r\nI Am the Lord that healeth thee.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn You, O Lord, I put my trust,\r\nIn You, O Lord, I put my trust,\r\nIn You, O Lord, I put my trust.\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Be still and know that I Am God, Be still and know that I Am God, Be still and know that I Am God. I Am the Lord that healeth thee, I Am the Lord that healeth thee, I Am the Lord that healeth thee. In You, O Lord, I put my trust, In You, O Lord, I put my trust, In You, O Lord, I put my trust.'),
	(750, 'I Belong To Jesus', 'Dennis Jernigan ', '~Verse 1\r\nHe was lifted up!\r\nHe was lifted up!\r\nHe paid a costly price!\r\nHe paid a costly price!\r\nHe bought me with the blood\r\nHe bought me with the blood\r\nOf His own life!\r\nOf His own life!\r\n~Chorus\r\nI belong to Jesus! I belong to Him!\r\nI belong to Jesus! Free from sin!\r\nI belong to Jesus! I belong to Him!\r\nI belong to Jesus! Free from sin!\r\n~Verse 2\r\nChrist the King now reigning!\r\nChrist the King now reigning!\r\nHe wears the Victor\'s crown!\r\nHe wears the Victor\'s crown!\r\nSatan was defeated\r\nSatan was defeated\r\nWhen the blood flowed down!\r\nWhen the blood flowed down!\r\n', '', '1993 Shepherd\'s Heart Music', '', '', 'He was lifted up! He was lifted up! He paid a costly price! He paid a costly price! He bought me with the blood He bought me with the blood Of His own life! Of His own life! I belong to Jesus! I belong to Him! I belong to Jesus! Free from sin! I belong to Jesus! I belong to Him! I belong to Jesus! Free from sin! Christ the King now reigning! Christ the King now reigning! He wears the Victor\\\'s crown! He wears the Victor\\\'s crown! Satan was defeated Satan was defeated When the blood flowed down! When the blood flowed down!'),
	(751, 'Nothing But The Blood', 'Robert Lowry', '~Verse 1\r\n[E]What can [A/E]wash [B/E]a - [E]way my sin?\r\n[C#m]Nothing but the blood of [F#m]Jesus[E].\r\n[E]What can m[A/E]ake [B/E]me  w[E]hole again?\r\n[C#m]Nothing but the blood of [F#m]Jesu[(/B)]s.[E]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[E]Oh, p[F#m7]recious [G#m]is the f[C#m]low t[F#m]hat m[E/G#]akes me [F#m/A-B-]white as [C#m-B6/C#]snow.[A/B]\r\n[E]No [F#m7]other f[G#m]ount I [C#m]know.  N[A]othing but the blo[C#m]od of [F#m]Jesu[(/B)]s.[E]\r\n[C#m]Nothing but the blood of [F#m]Jesu[(/B)]s.[E]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nNothing can for sin atone\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus;\r\nNaught of good that I have done\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThis is all my hope and peace\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus;\r\nThis is all my righteousness\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor my pardon this I see\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus;\r\nFor my cleansing, this my plea\r\nNothing but the blood of Jesus.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'What can wash a - way my sin? Nothing but the blood of Jesus. What can make me  whole again? Nothing but the blood of Jesus. Oh, precious is the flow that makes me white as snow. No other fount I know.  Nothing but the blood of Jesus. Nothing but the blood of Jesus. Nothing can for sin atone Nothing but the blood of Jesus; Naught of good that I have done Nothing but the blood of Jesus. This is all my hope and peace Nothing but the blood of Jesus; This is all my righteousness Nothing but the blood of Jesus. For my pardon this I see Nothing but the blood of Jesus; For my cleansing, this my plea Nothing but the blood of Jesus.'),
	(752, 'Saved Saved', 'Jack P. Scholfield. Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI\'ve found a Friend who is all to me,\r\nHis love is ever true;\r\nI love to tell how He lifted me,\r\nAnd what His grace can do for you.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe saves me from every sin and harm,\r\nSecures my soul each day;\r\nI\'m leaning strong on His mighty arm;\r\nI know He\'ll guide me all the way.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhen poor and needy and all alone,\r\nIn love He said to me,\r\n"Come unto Me and I\'ll lead you home,\r\nTo live with Me eternally."\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nSaved by His pow\'r divine,\r\nSaved to new life sub-lime!\r\nLife now is sweet and my joy is complete,\r\nFor I\'m saved, saved, saved!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I\'ve found a Friend who is all to me, His love is ever true; I love to tell how He lifted me, And what His grace can do for you. He saves me from every sin and harm, Secures my soul each day; I\'m leaning strong on His mighty arm; I know He\'ll guide me all the way. When poor and needy and all alone, In love He said to me, "Come unto Me and I\'ll lead you home, To live with Me eternally." Saved by His pow\'r divine, Saved to new life sub-lime! Life now is sweet and my joy is complete, For I\'m saved, saved, saved!'),
	(753, 'My Eyes Are Dry', 'Keith Green', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy eyes are dry,\r\nMy faith is old,\r\nMy heart is hard,\r\nMy prayers are cold.\r\nAnd I know how I ought to be:\r\nAlive to You, and dead to me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nOh, what can be done\r\nFor an old heart like mine?\r\nSoften it up, with oil and wine.\r\nThe oil is You, \r\nYour spirit of love.\r\nPlease wash me anew\r\nIn the wine of Your blood.\r\n', '', '  (Admin. by BMG)', '', '', 'My eyes are dry, My faith is old, My heart is hard, My prayers are cold. And I know how I ought to be: Alive to You, and dead to me. Oh, what can be done For an old heart like mine? Soften it up, with oil and wine. The oil is You, Your spirit of love. Please wash me anew In the wine of Your blood.'),
	(754, 'Spirit Song', 'John Wimber', '~Verse 1\r\nOh let the Son of God enfold you,\r\nWith His Spirit and His love,\r\nLet Him fill your heart and satisfy your soul.\r\nOh let Him have the things that hold you,\r\nAnd His Spirit like a dove,\r\nWill descend upon your life,\r\nAnd make you whole.\r\n~Chorus\r\nJesus, Oh Jesus, \r\ncome and fill your lambs.\r\nJesus, Oh Jesus, \r\ncome and fill your lambs.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nO come and sing this song with gladness,\r\nAs your hearts are filled with joy,\r\nLift your hands in sweet surrender to His name.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nOh give Him all your tears and sadness, \r\nGive Him all your years of pain,\r\nAnd you\'ll enter into life in Jesus\' name.\r\n', '', '1979 Mercy Publishing', '', '', 'Oh let the Son of God enfold you, With His Spirit and His love, Let Him fill your heart and satisfy your soul. Oh let Him have the things that hold you, And His Spirit like a dove, Will descend upon your life, And make you whole. Jesus, Oh Jesus, come and fill your lambs. Jesus, Oh Jesus, come and fill your lambs. O come and sing this song with gladness, As your hearts are filled with joy, Lift your hands in sweet surrender to His name. Oh give Him all your tears and sadness, Give Him all your years of pain, And you\'ll enter into life in Jesus\' name.'),
	(755, 'Bind Us Together', 'Bob Gillman', '~Verse 1\r\nBind us together, Lord, \r\nBind us together \r\nWith chords that cannot be broken\r\nBind us together, Lord, \r\nBind us together, Lord, \r\nBind us together with love.\r\n', '', '1977 Thank You Music (admin. in US by StraightWay Music)', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/NEH38evSbME', '', 'Bind us together, Lord, Bind us together With chords that cannot be broken Bind us together, Lord, Bind us together, Lord, Bind us together with love.'),
