	(759, 'All I Need', 'Brian Thiessen', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]All [B]the [E]beauty [A]I can s[B]ee\r\n[A]If [B]it [E]could bel[A]ong to m[B]e\r\n[F#m]I would [E]give it [A]all f[B]or [E]You\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[A]Any [B]grea[E]tness I [A]achiev[B]e\r\n[A]Ever[B]y [E]praise I ma[A]y recei[B]ve\r\n[F#m]I would [E]give it [A]all f[B]or [E]You\r\n~Chorus\r\n[A]All [B]I nee[E]d You are al[E]l I [A]need\r\nI have [C#m]found [B]it tr[A]ue\r\nLife comes only fro[A]m Yo[B]u[E]\r\n[A]All [B]I nee[E]d you are al[E]l I [A]need\r\nNothing e[C#m]lse wi[B]ll do[A]\r\nNo one [A]else [B]but Y[F#m]ou [E] [A] [Bsus] [B]\r\n~Verse 3\r\n[A]If I[B]\'m g[E]iven co[A]mfort h[B]ere\r\n[A]Offe[B]re[E]d what the [A]world h[B]olds dear\r\n[F#m]I would [E]give it [A]all f[B]or [E]You\r\n', '', ' 2001 Vineyard Songs (Canada)', '', '', 'All the beauty I can see If it could belong to me I would give it all for You Any greatness I achieve Every praise I may receive I would give it all for You All I need You are all I need I have found it true Life comes only from You All I need you are all I need Nothing else will do No one else but You If I\'m given comfort here Offered what the world holds dear I would give it all for You'),
	(760, 'Sweet Wind', 'David Ruis', '~Verse 1\r\n[D]There\'s a wi[Dsus]nd a-blow[D]in\',\r\nall acr[Dsus]oss the l[D]and\r\n[D]A fragrant [Dsus]breeze of \r\nhe[D]aven, blowin\' [Dsus]once a[D]gain\r\n~Verse 2\r\n[G]Don\'t know wh[C]ere it [G]comes from,\r\ndon\'t know wh[C]ere it go[G]es\r\n[G]But let it blow over [D]me\r\n[A]Oh, oh, oh, sweet [G]wind\r\nCome and blow over [D]me\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThere\'s a rain a-pourin\',\r\nshowers from above\r\nMercy drops are comin\',\r\nmercy drops of love\r\n~Verse 4\r\nTurn your face to heaven,\r\nlet the water pour\r\nWell let it pour over me\r\nOh, oh, oh, sweet rain\r\nCome and pour over me\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThere\'s a fire burning,\r\nfalling from the sky\r\nAwesome tongues of fire,\r\nconsuming you and I\r\n~Verse 6\r\nCan you feel it burnin\',\r\nburn the sacrifice\r\nWell let it burn over me\r\nOh, oh, oh, sweet fire\r\nCome and burn over me', '', '', '', '', 'There\\\'s a wind a-blowin\\\', all across the land A fragrant breeze of heaven, blowin\\\' once again Don\\\'t know where it comes from, don\\\'t know where it goes But let it blow over me Oh, oh, oh, sweet wind Come and blow over me There\\\'s a rain a-pourin\\\', showers from above Mercy drops are comin\\\', mercy drops of love Turn your face to heaven, let the water pour Well let it pour over me Oh, oh, oh, sweet rain Come and pour over me There\\\'s a fire burning, falling from the sky Awesome tongues of fire, consuming you and I Can you feel it burnin\\\', burn the sacrifice Well let it burn over me Oh, oh, oh, sweet fire Come and burn over me'),
	(761, 'We Come To Humble Ourselves', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\nFather, we come to seek You.\r\nGod of life, we want to see Your glory.\r\nWe bow down before Your throne of grace\r\nWe come to humble ourselves.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFather, we come to love You.\r\nGod of life, We want to soften our hearts.\r\nWe bow down before Your throne of grace.\r\nWe come to humble ourselves.\r\n', '', '1989 Langley Vineyard Music', '', '', 'Father, we come to seek You. God of life, we want to see Your glory. We bow down before Your throne of grace We come to humble ourselves. Father, we come to love You. God of life, We want to soften our hearts. We bow down before Your throne of grace. We come to humble ourselves.'),
	(762, 'Made To Worship', 'Chris Tomlin, Stephan Sharp and Ed Cash. ', '~Verse 1\r\nBefo[G]re the day\r\nBefo[G/F#]re the light\r\nBefo[Em]re the world revolved around the sun      [C]\r\n[G]God on high stepped down into tim[G/F#]e\r\nAnd wrot[Em]e the story of His love for everyone  [C]\r\n~Pre-chorus\r\n[C]   He has filled our hearts w[D]ith wonder\r\n[C]  So that we al-way[D]s remember  [C]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[G]You and I are made to worship you\r\n[C]You and I are called to love\r\n[Am7]You and I are forgiven and free   [D]\r\n[G]You and I embrace surrender\r\n[C]You and I choose to believe\r\nThen you [Am7]and I will see    [D]\r\nWho we were meant to be      [G]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAll we are and all we have\r\nIs all a gift from God that we receive\r\nBrought to life we open up our eyes\r\nTo see the majesty and glory of the King\r\n~Bridge\r\n[Am7]     Even the rocks cry out [G/B]\r\nEven the heavens shout    [C]\r\nAt the sound of His Holy name  [D]\r\n[Am7]    So let every voice sing out [G/B]\r\nLet every knee bow down    [C]\r\nHe\'s worthy of all our pra[D]ise\r\n', '', ' 2006 worshiptogether.com Songs (ASCAP)/sixsteps Music (admin. by EMI CMG Publishing)/ Alletrop Mujs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/Z7VEcNqb-P8&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Before the day Before the light Before the world revolved around the sun God on high stepped down into time And wrote the story of His love for everyone He has filled our hearts with wonder So that we al-ways remember You and I are made to worship you You and I are called to love You and I are forgiven and free You and I embrace surrender You and I choose to believe Then you and I will see Who we were meant to be All we are and all we have Is all a gift from God that we receive Brought to life we open up our eyes To see the majesty and glory of the King Even the rocks cry out Even the heavens shout At the sound of His Holy name So let every voice sing out Let every knee bow down He\'s worthy of all our praise'),
	(763, 'I Worship You Almighty God', 'Sondra Corbett', '~Verse 1\r\nI worship You, Almighty God, \r\nThere is none like You.\r\nI worship You, O Prince Of Peace,\r\nThat is what I want to do.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI give You praise, \r\nFor You are my righteousness,\r\nI worship You, Almighty God, \r\nThere is none like You.\r\n', '', '1983 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/evbA09mwpos', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(I worship You, Almighty God, There is none like You. I worship You, O Prince Of Peace, That is what I want to do. I give You praise, For You are my righteousness, I worship You, Almighty God, There is none like You.).'),
	(764, 'All Because Of You', 'Kent Blanton', '~Verse 1\r\nWhy do we come to church\r\nEach and every week\r\nWhy do we kneel and pray\r\nAnd our God intently seek\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhy do we laugh and shout\r\nTell each other what He\'s done\r\nWhy do we lift our hands\r\nAnd revel in the vict\'ry\r\n that\'s been won\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhy do we sing these songs\r\nPraise our Lord from deep within\r\nWhy do we share our thanks\r\nAnd humbly confess our sin\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhy do we read God\'s word\r\nSeek to understand and grow\r\nWhy do we give our offerings\r\nSo that others, too, may know\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAnd all this is for You, Jesus\r\nTo celebrate the life \r\nYou give to us\r\nWe praise You for Your \r\nprecious gift\r\nAnd give You all our love\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nIt\'s all because of You, Jesus\r\nAll because of great and \r\nawesome love\r\nYou showed us \r\nthrough Your sacrifice\r\nBy the shedding of Your blood\r\n', '', '2004 Kent Blanton. ', '', '', 'Why do we come to church Each and every week Why do we kneel and pray And our God intently seek Why do we laugh and shout Tell each other what He\'s done Why do we lift our hands And revel in the vict\'ry that\'s been won Why do we sing these songs Praise our Lord from deep within Why do we share our thanks And humbly confess our sin Why do we read God\'s word Seek to understand and grow Why do we give our offerings So that others, too, may know And all this is for You, Jesus To celebrate the life You give to us We praise You for Your precious gift And give You all our love It\'s all because of You, Jesus All because of great and awesome love You showed us through Your sacrifice By the shedding of Your blood'),
	(765, 'Great God', 'Andrew Smith ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou deliver me from evil\r\nYou show your righteousness\r\nYou save me from the darkness\r\nYou bring your truth and light\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHe\'s a great\r\n He\'s a great\r\nHe\'s a great God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nMy God is a great God\r\nMy God is a great God\r\nMy God is a great God\r\nHe\'s a great God\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nIn your house are many strangers\r\nAt your door you heal the sick\r\nBlessed are the poor in spirit\r\nFor they shall be made new\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nWho is there in all the earth\r\nIn whom I can put my trust\r\nWho can move these mighty mountains\r\nWhose voice can calm these seas\r\n', '', ' 1996 Mercy/Vineyard Publishing.', '', '', 'You deliver me from evil You show your righteousness You save me from the darkness You bring your truth and light He\'s a great He\'s a great He\'s a great God. My God is a great God My God is a great God My God is a great God He\'s a great God In your house are many strangers At your door you heal the sick Blessed are the poor in spirit For they shall be made new Who is there in all the earth In whom I can put my trust Who can move these mighty mountains Whose voice can calm these seas'),
	(766, 'Thanks', 'Carroll McGruder', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThank You, Lord for the strength\r\n	 You give to simply carry on,\r\nThrough life\'s toils and tests,\r\n	 the worst and best, never left alone;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\n(W.L.) Thanks, (Cong.) Thanks,\r\n(W.L.) Thanks, (Cong.) Thanks,\r\n(All)  I give You thanks \r\n	 for all You\'ve done;\r\nI am so blessed, my soul is at rest,\r\nO Lord, I give You thanks.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAlways right beside me,\r\n He hears me when I pray,\r\nAnd since I first began\r\n You\'ve been my dearest Friend,\r\nI give You all the praise.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nEven in the valley, \r\nwhen	 everything\'s goin\' wrong,\r\nEven on the mountain\r\n Your loving 	 presence makes me strong;\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nEach and ev\'ry moment,\r\n and each	 and every day\r\nI\'m gonna sing and shout,\r\n	 don\'t let the rocks cry out,\r\nI give You all the praise.\r\n', '', ' 1987 Rex Nelon Music Co. ', '', '', 'Thank You, Lord for the strength You give to simply carry on, Through life\'s toils and tests, the worst and best, never left alone; (W.L.) Thanks, (Cong.) Thanks, (W.L.) Thanks, (Cong.) Thanks, (All)  I give You thanks for all You\'ve done; I am so blessed, my soul is at rest, O Lord, I give You thanks. Always right beside me, He hears me when I pray, And since I first began You\'ve been my dearest Friend, I give You all the praise. Even in the valley, when	 everything\'s goin\' wrong, Even on the mountain Your loving 	 presence makes me strong; Each and ev\'ry moment, and each	 and every day I\'m gonna sing and shout, don\'t let the rocks cry out, I give You all the praise.'),
	(767, 'O Sacred Head, Now Wounded', '', '~Verse 1\r\nO sacred Head, now wounded,\r\nWith grief and shame weighed down,\r\nNow scornfully surrounded\r\nWith thorns Thine only crown;\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHow pale Thou art with anguish,\r\nWith sore abuse and scorn,\r\nHow does that visage languish,\r\nWhich once was bright as morn!\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWhat Thou, my Lord, hast suffered\r\nWas all for sinners\' gain;\r\nMine, mine was the transgression,\r\nBut Thine the deadly pain.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLo, here I fall, my Savior;\r\n\'Tis I deserve Thy place;\r\nLook on me with Thy favor,\r\nAssist me with Thy grace.\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWhat language shall I borrow\r\nTo thank Thee, dearest Friend,\r\nFor this, Thy dying sorrow,\r\nThy pity without end?\r\n~Verse 6\r\nO make me Thine forever,\r\nAnd should I fainting be,\r\nLord, let me never, never\r\nOutlive my love to Thee. Amen.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'O sacred Head, now wounded, With grief and shame weighed down, Now scornfully surrounded With thorns Thine only crown; How pale Thou art with anguish, With sore abuse and scorn, How does that visage languish, Which once was bright as morn! What Thou, my Lord, hast suffered Was all for sinners\\\' gain; Mine, mine was the transgression, But Thine the deadly pain. Lo, here I fall, my Savior; \\\'Tis I deserve Thy place; Look on me with Thy favor, Assist me with Thy grace. What language shall I borrow To thank Thee, dearest Friend, For this, Thy dying sorrow, Thy pity without end? O make me Thine forever, And should I fainting be, Lord, let me never, never Outlive my love to Thee. Amen.'),
	(768, 'He Signed My Deed', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe signed my deed\r\nWith His atoning blood,\r\nHe ever lives to make\r\nHis promise good.\r\nThough all the hosts of hell\r\nMarch in to make a second claim,\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThey\'ll all march out\r\nAt the mention of His name.\r\nThey\'ll all march out\r\nAt the mention of His name.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'He signed my deed With His atoning blood, He ever lives to make His promise good. Though all the hosts of hell March in to make a second claim, They\'ll all march out At the mention of His name. They\'ll all march out At the mention of His name.'),
	(769, 'O Lord To You', 'Gary Sadler.  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nWe will seek You first, Lord,\r\nYou will hear our voices,\r\nEarly in the morning and late in the night;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMay our praise arise as incense,\r\n O Lord, to You;\r\nMay our worship be a fragrance, \r\nO Lord to You.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe will sing Your praises,\r\n Giving You the glory,\r\nOffering our lives to You, a holy sacrifice.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Integrity\'s Hosanna Music', '', '', 'We will seek You first, Lord, You will hear our voices, Early in the morning and late in the night; May our praise arise as incense, O Lord, to You; May our worship be a fragrance, O Lord to You. We will sing Your praises, Giving You the glory, Offering our lives to You, a holy sacrifice.'),
	(770, 'King Jesus Is All', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nKing Jesus is all, my all in all\r\nI know He\'ll answer me when I call\r\nWalking by my side, I\'m satisfied\r\nKing Jesus is all, my all in all\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI went out to meet the Lord (Oh yeah)\r\nI got down on my knees (Praise God)\r\nI prayed my first prayer\r\nAnd the Holy Ghost met me there\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI stood on the rock\r\nThe rock was sound\r\nThe love of God came a\'tumbling down\r\nThe reason I know that He saved my soul\r\nI dug down deep and I found pure gold\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe is all, my all in all\r\nI know He\'ll answer\r\nEvery time I call\r\nWalking by my side I\'m satisfied\r\nKing Jesus is all, my all in all\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'King Jesus is all, my all in all I know He\'ll answer me when I call Walking by my side, I\'m satisfied King Jesus is all, my all in all I went out to meet the Lord (Oh yeah) I got down on my knees (Praise God) I prayed my first prayer And the Holy Ghost met me there I stood on the rock The rock was sound The love of God came a\'tumbling down The reason I know that He saved my soul I dug down deep and I found pure gold He is all, my all in all I know He\'ll answer Every time I call Walking by my side I\'m satisfied King Jesus is all, my all in all'),
