	(793, 'On My Knees', 'Bob Carlisle, R. Hamm & R. Elias.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nStand\r\nWith all my might and still I seem to fall.\r\nI try to walk before I even crawl.\r\nOh it seems I\'m like a child in need again.\r\nA helpless heart.\r\nA broken man.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nStrength\r\nIs something that\'s so very hard to find.\r\nBut still I know that true faith must be blind.\r\nSo I sacrifice my heart to God in prayer.\r\nLay my weakness down\r\nAnd I\'ll find you there.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSee a man,\r\nIn a garden long ago, kneeling alone,\r\nAs the weight of sins unseen\r\nAnd lives unknown\r\nCame to rest upon His weary shoulders.\r\nHe knew my name,\r\nHe took my pain, so ...\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI can stand tall\r\nOn my knees\r\nI can see forever\r\nOn my knees\r\nI can face it all ... I feel like\r\nI can climb a mountain\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nCause on my knees\r\nThe world\'s a little smaller\r\nAnd I stand taller\r\nOn my knees.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nAnd I stand taller\r\nOn my knees ...\r\nThere\'s a peace that shadows\r\nAnything I\'ve known.\r\nI lay down every burden\r\nAnd I\'m free\r\nOn my knees\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nI can see forever\r\nOn my knees\r\nI can face it all ... I feel like\r\nI can climb a mountain\r\nCause on my knees\r\nThe world\'s a little smaller\r\nAnd I stand taller\r\nOn my knees.\r\n', '', ' 1996 Diadem Music Publishing. ', '', '', 'Stand With all my might and still I seem to fall. I try to walk before I even crawl. Oh it seems I\'m like a child in need again. A helpless heart. A broken man. Strength Is something that\'s so very hard to find. But still I know that true faith must be blind. So I sacrifice my heart to God in prayer. Lay my weakness down And I\'ll find you there. See a man, In a garden long ago, kneeling alone, As the weight of sins unseen And lives unknown Came to rest upon His weary shoulders. He knew my name, He took my pain, so ... I can stand tall On my knees I can see forever On my knees I can face it all ... I feel like I can climb a mountain Cause on my knees The world\'s a little smaller And I stand taller On my knees. And I stand taller On my knees ... There\'s a peace that shadows Anything I\'ve known. I lay down every burden And I\'m free On my knees I can see forever On my knees I can face it all ... I feel like I can climb a mountain Cause on my knees The world\'s a little smaller And I stand taller On my knees.'),
	(794, 'Nothing Can Compare', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nNothing can compare to looking at Your face\r\nNothing can compare \r\nTo feeling Your embrace\r\nYou are all I want, You are all I need\r\nThere\'s nothing in this world\r\nCould take Your love from me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nMany are Your thoughts \r\nTowards Your children\r\nAbundant is the grace that I\'ve received\r\nForgiven are the sins \r\nYou\'ve covered in Your blood\r\nSo nothing separates me from Your love.\r\n', '', ' 1990 Mercy Publishing; ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'Nothing can compare to looking at Your face Nothing can compare To feeling Your embrace You are all I want, You are all I need There\'s nothing in this world Could take Your love from me. Many are Your thoughts Towards Your children Abundant is the grace that I\'ve received Forgiven are the sins You\'ve covered in Your blood So nothing separates me from Your love.'),
	(795, 'We\'re Marching To Zion', 'Isaac Watts; Robert Lowry, Refrain; music by Robert Lowry. Public Domain  ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome, we that love the Lord,\r\nAnd let our joys be known,\r\nJoin in a song with sweet accord,\r\nJoin in a song with sweet accord\r\nAnd thus surround the throne,\r\nAnd thus surround the throne.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWe\'re marching to Zion,\r\nBeautiful, beautiful Zion;\r\nWe\'re marching upward to Zion,\r\nThe beautiful city of God.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nLet those refuse to sing\r\nWho never knew our God,\r\nBut children of the heav\'nly King,\r\nBut children of the heav\'nly King\r\nMay speak their joys abroad,\r\nMay speak their joys abroad.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThe hill of Zion yields\r\nA thousand sacred sweets\r\nBefore we reach the heav\'nly fields,\r\nBefore we reach the heav\'nly fields\r\nOr walk the golden streets,\r\nOr walk the golden streets.\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nThen let our songs abound\r\nAnd every tear be dry;\r\nWe\'re marching thro\' Immanuel\'s ground\r\nWe\'re marching thro\' Immanuel\'s ground\r\nTo fairer worlds on high,\r\nTo fairer worlds on high.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Come, we that love the Lord, And let our joys be known, Join in a song with sweet accord, Join in a song with sweet accord And thus surround the throne, And thus surround the throne. We\'re marching to Zion, Beautiful, beautiful Zion; We\'re marching upward to Zion, The beautiful city of God. Let those refuse to sing Who never knew our God, But children of the heav\'nly King, But children of the heav\'nly King May speak their joys abroad, May speak their joys abroad. The hill of Zion yields A thousand sacred sweets Before we reach the heav\'nly fields, Before we reach the heav\'nly fields Or walk the golden streets, Or walk the golden streets. Then let our songs abound And every tear be dry; We\'re marching thro\' Immanuel\'s ground We\'re marching thro\' Immanuel\'s ground To fairer worlds on high, To fairer worlds on high.'),
