	(802, 'My Glory', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nMy glory and the lifter of my head\r\nMy glory and the lifter of my head\r\nBut Thou O Lord art a shield for me\r\nMy glory and the lifter of my head\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI cried unto the Lord with my voice\r\nI cried unto the Lord with my voice\r\nI cried unto the Lord with my voice\r\nAnd He heard me out of His holy hill, Selah.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'My glory and the lifter of my head My glory and the lifter of my head But Thou O Lord art a shield for me My glory and the lifter of my head I cried unto the Lord with my voice I cried unto the Lord with my voice I cried unto the Lord with my voice And He heard me out of His holy hill, Selah.'),
	(803, 'Great Is The Lord Almighty', 'Dennis Jernigan', '~Verse 1\r\nThe Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God!\r\nThe Lord God Reigns! The Lord reigns!\r\nHe is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns!\r\n  \r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThe Lord reigns!  He is a Mighty God!\r\nThe Lord God reigns!  The Lord reigns!\r\nHe is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThe Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God\r\nThe Lord God reigns! The Lord reigns!\r\nHe is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns!\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nGreat is the Lord Almighty!\r\nHe is Lord! He is God indeed!\r\nGreat is the Lord Almighty!\r\nHe is God Supreme!\r\nGreat is the Lord Almighty!\r\nHe is Lord! He is God indeed!\r\nGreat is the Lord!  Great is the Lord!\r\n\r\n~Verse 8\r\nWhen the children of Israel came to the brink\r\nHe led them through letting Pharaoh sink!\r\nThen the children were dancing  \r\nAs old Pharaoh sank down \r\nLifting up a mighty joyful sound singing.\r\n\r\n~Verse 9\r\nWhen the children of God\r\ncame up to Jericho town\r\nThe Lord said, "Children, lets walk around!"\r\nSo for seven whole days \r\nThey walked around that great wall \r\n\'Till the Lord said,\r\n"Shout and watch it fall, Children!"\r\n\r\n~Verse 10\r\nWhen His children were dying \r\n	 And lost in their sin\r\nMy God died and He rose again!\r\nAnd I\'ve been rejoicing \r\n	 Since He took my blame!\r\nI thank you Jesus! Praise Your name!\r\n', '', '1991 Shepherds Heart Music Inc.', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/Rb9iH0uUaXw', '', 'The Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God! The Lord God Reigns! The Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns! The Lord reigns!  He is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns!  The Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns! The Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God The Lord God reigns! The Lord reigns! He is a Mighty God! The Lord God reigns! Great is the Lord Almighty! He is Lord! He is God indeed! Great is the Lord Almighty! He is God Supreme! Great is the Lord Almighty! He is Lord! He is God indeed! Great is the Lord!  Great is the Lord! When the children of Israel came to the brink He led them through letting Pharaoh sink! Then the children were dancing As old Pharaoh sank down Lifting up a mighty joyful sound singing. When the children of God came up to Jericho town The Lord said, "Children, lets walk around!" So for seven whole days They walked around that great wall \'Till the Lord said, "Shout and watch it fall, Children!" When His children were dying And lost in their sin My God died and He rose again! And I\'ve been rejoicing Since He took my blame! I thank you Jesus! Praise Your name!'),
	(804, 'Blessed Assurance', 'Fanny Crosby/Public Domain ', '~Verse 1\r\nBlessed a[D]ssurance, [G]Jesus is [D]mine.\r\nO, what a f[Bm]oret[A]aste of g[E]lory divi[A]ne!\r\nHeir of salv[D]ation, [G]purchase of [D]God,\r\n[Bm]Born of His S[Em]pirit, w[A]ashed in His b[D]lood.\r\n~Chorus\r\nThis is my [D]story, [G]this is my [D]song,\r\nPraising my [G]Savior [A]all the d[E]ay l[A]ong.\r\nThis is my [D]story, [G]this is my [D]song,\r\n[Bm]Praising my [Em]Savior a[A]ll the day l[D]ong.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nPerfect submission, perfect delight,\r\nVisions of rapture now burst on my sight;\r\nAngels descending, bring from above\r\nEchoes of mercy, whispers of love.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nPerfect submission, all is at rest,\r\nI in my Savior am happy and blest;\r\nWatching and waiting, looking above,\r\nFilled with His goodness, lost in His love.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Blessed assurance, Jesus is mine. O, what a foretaste of glory divine! Heir of salvation, purchase of God, Born of His Spirit, washed in His blood. This is my story, this is my song, Praising my Savior all the day long. This is my story, this is my song, Praising my Savior all the day long. Perfect submission, perfect delight, Visions of rapture now burst on my sight; Angels descending, bring from above Echoes of mercy, whispers of love. Perfect submission, all is at rest, I in my Savior am happy and blest; Watching and waiting, looking above, Filled with His goodness, lost in His love.'),
	(805, 'O Magnify The Lord', 'Michael O\'Shields', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO magnify the Lord \r\nFor He is worthy to be praised \r\nO magnify the Lord \r\nFor He is worthy to be praised \r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHosanna, Jesus is the rock\r\nJesus is the rock of my salvation.\r\nHosanna, Jesus is the rock,\r\nJesus is the rock of my salvation.\r\n', '', ' 1981 Sound III Inc. (ASCAP) ', '', '', 'O magnify the Lord For He is worthy to be praised O magnify the Lord For He is worthy to be praised Hosanna, Jesus is the rock Jesus is the rock of my salvation. Hosanna, Jesus is the rock, Jesus is the rock of my salvation.'),
	(806, 'Praise Him (new)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nPraise Him, Praise Him\r\nWith your voices,\r\nRaise Him on High\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nHe is the Lord of Glory !\r\nHe is the King of Kings !\r\nCame to bring redemption\'s story,\r\nWith our hearts let us sing !\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Praise Him, Praise Him With your voices, Raise Him on High He is the Lord of Glory ! He is the King of Kings ! Came to bring redemption\'s story, With our hearts let us sing !'),
	(807, 'Let Us Rejoice And Be Glad', 'Gerrit Hansen', '~Verse 1\r\nLet us rejoice and be glad,\r\nGiving the glory to Him;\r\nFor the marriage of the Lamb has come,\r\nAnd His bride has made herself ready.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nHallelujah, for the Lord our God,\r\n	 The Almighty, reigns;\r\nHallelujah, for the Lord our God,\r\n	 The Almighty, reigns. \r\n', '', '1982 & 1989 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', '', '', 'Let us rejoice and be glad, Giving the glory to Him; For the marriage of the Lamb has come, And His bride has made herself ready. Hallelujah, for the Lord our God, The Almighty, reigns; Hallelujah, for the Lord our God, The Almighty, reigns.'),
