	(809, 'Of All The Things About You', 'Wes Tuttle', '~Verse 1\r\nWell I love the way You made\r\nThe heavens and the earth\r\nAnd I love the starry hosts in the sky\r\nLord, but every time I think about\r\nYour love for me\r\nI just want to stand and testify\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWell I love the way You came\r\nAnd gave Your life for us\r\nAnd I love that we\'ve been\r\nSaved by Your grace\r\nAnd to think You would have done\r\nIt all just for me\r\nMakes me want to sing for all my days\r\n~Chorus\r\nOf all the things about You that I love\r\nOf all the things about You that I love\r\nOf all the things about You that I love\r\nI love the most that You first loved me\r\n', '', '2001 Integrity Music, Inc.', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/_iWD2pZpzvM', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Well I love the way You made The heavens and the earth And I love the starry hosts in the sky Lord, but every time I think about Your love for me I just want to stand and testify Well I love the way You came And gave Your life for us And I love that we\'ve been Saved by Your grace And to think You would have done It all just for me Makes me want to sing for all my days Of all the things about You that I love Of all the things about You that I love Of all the things about You that I love I love the most that You first loved me).'),
	(810, 'Majesty', '', '~Verse 1\r\n[G]Majesty, worship his [C]majesty [Am]\r\nUnto [G]Jesus be all [Em7]glory, honour and [Am7]praise [D]\r\n[G]Majesty, kingdom auth[C]ority [Am7]\r\n[D7]Flows from his [G]throne [Em7]unto his [Am]own\r\n[D]His anthem [G]raise\r\n~Verse 2\r\nSo ex[D]alt, lift up on [Am]high\r\nThe [C/D]name [D]of [G]Jesus\r\nMagni[D]fy, come glori[Am]fy Christ [D]Jesus the [B]King [D]\r\n~Verse 3\r\n[G]Majesty, worship his [C]majesty [Am]\r\n[D7]Jesus who [G]died, [Em7]now glori[Am]fied\r\n[D]King of all [G]kings\r\n', '', '1981, Rocksmith Music c/o Trust Music Management', '', '', 'Majesty, worship his majesty Unto Jesus be all glory, honour and praise Majesty, kingdom authority Flows from his throne unto his own His anthem raise So exalt, lift up on high The name of Jesus Magnify, come glorify Christ Jesus the King Majesty, worship his majesty Jesus who died, now glorified King of all kings'),
	(811, 'Worthy, You Are Worthy (Moen)', 'Don Moen', '~Verse 1\r\n[F]Worthy, You are [C7]worthy, King of [Bb]kings, \r\nLord of [C]lords, You are [F]worthy; \r\nWorthy, You are [C7]worthy, King of [Bb]kings, \r\nLord of [C]lords, I worship [F]You! \r\n~Verse 2\r\nHo -ly, You are Ho - ly, King of kings,  \r\nLord of lords, You are Ho - ly; \r\nHo - ly, You are Ho - ly, King of kings,  \r\nLord of lords, I worship You! \r\n~Verse 3\r\nJe - sus, You are Je - sus, King of kings,  \r\nLord of lords, You are Je - sus; \r\nJe - sus, You are Je - sus, King of kings,  \r\nLord of lords, I worship You! \r\n', '', '1986 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/Qc5A5GGYObM&hl=en&fs=1', '', 'Worthy, You are worthy, King of kings, Lord of lords, You are worthy; Worthy, You are worthy, King of kings, Lord of lords, I worship You! Ho -ly, You are Ho - ly, King of kings, Lord of lords, You are Ho - ly; Ho - ly, You are Ho - ly, King of kings, Lord of lords, I worship You! Je - sus, You are Je - sus, King of kings, Lord of lords, You are Je - sus; Je - sus, You are Je - sus, King of kings, Lord of lords, I worship You!'),
	(812, 'Father', 'Danny Daniels', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFather, I can call You Father\r\nFor I am your child.\r\nToday, tomorrow and always\r\nYou are my Father.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFather, how I love You\r\nFather I will sing your praise\r\nToday, tomorrow and always\r\nFor You\'re my Father.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFather I will serve You\r\nFather I will seek your face\r\nToday, tomorrow and always\r\nYou are my Father.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nFather, Father, Father to me\r\nFather, (oh) Father, Father to me.\r\n', '', ' 1989 Mercy Publishing; ARR; ICS; UBP; ', '', '', 'Father, I can call You Father For I am your child. Today, tomorrow and always You are my Father. Father, how I love You Father I will sing your praise Today, tomorrow and always For You\'re my Father. Father I will serve You Father I will seek your face Today, tomorrow and always You are my Father. Father, Father, Father to me Father, (oh) Father, Father to me.'),
	(813, 'Fairest Lord Jesus', '', '~Verse 1\r\nFairest Lord Jesus, Ruler of all nature,\r\nO Thou of God and Man the Son;\r\nThee will I cherish, Thee will I honor\r\nThou my soul\'s glory, joy, and crown.\r\n\r\nMusic- by Schlesiche Volkslieder,  Words (Anonymous)\r\n1842 Arranged by Richard S. Willis;  CCLI #218004 \r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nFair are the meadows, \r\nFairer still the woodlands,\r\nRobed in the blooming garb of spring;\r\nJesus is fairer, Jesus is purer,\r\nWho makes the woeful heart to sing.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFair is the sunshine,\r\nFairer still the moonlight,\r\nAnd all the twinkling starry host;\r\nJesus shines brighter,\r\nJesus shines purer\r\nThan all the angels heaven can boast.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBeautiful Savior! Lord of the nations!\r\nSon of God and Son of Man!\r\nGlory and honor, praise, adoration\r\nNow and forever more be Thine!\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/M_MumkQUqdU', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(Fairest Lord Jesus, Ruler of all nature, O Thou of God and Man the Son; Thee will I cherish, Thee will I honor Thou my soul\'s glory, joy, and crown. Music- by Schlesiche Volkslieder,  Words (Anonymous) 1842 Arranged by Richard S. Willis;  CCLI #218004 Fair are the meadows, Fairer still the woodlands, Robed in the blooming garb of spring; Jesus is fairer, Jesus is purer, Who makes the woeful heart to sing. Fair is the sunshine, Fairer still the moonlight, And all the twinkling starry host; Jesus shines brighter, Jesus shines purer Than all the angels heaven can boast. Beautiful Savior! Lord of the nations! Son of God and Son of Man! Glory and honor, praise, adoration Now and forever more be Thine!).'),
	(814, 'Heaven Is In My Heart', 'Graham Kendrick, c. 1991 Make Way Music! ', '~Verse 1\r\nThe Kingdom of our God is here\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\nThe presence of His majesty\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nOoooo...Heaven is in my heart\r\nOoooo...Heaven is in my heart\r\nOoooo...Heaven is in my heart\r\nOoooo...Heaven is in my heart\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd in His presence joy abounds\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\nThe light of holiness surrounds\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nWe are a temple for His throne\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\nAnd Christ is the foundation stone\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHe will return to take us home\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\nThe Spirit and the Bride say, "Come"\r\nHeaven is in my heart\r\n', '', ' 1991 Make Way Music! ', 'https://www.youtube.com/v/UKDMFDbqZn0', '', '.mysql_real_escape_string(The Kingdom of our God is here Heaven is in my heart The presence of His majesty Heaven is in my heart Ooooo...Heaven is in my heart Ooooo...Heaven is in my heart Ooooo...Heaven is in my heart Ooooo...Heaven is in my heart And in His presence joy abounds Heaven is in my heart The light of holiness surrounds Heaven is in my heart We are a temple for His throne Heaven is in my heart And Christ is the foundation stone Heaven is in my heart He will return to take us home Heaven is in my heart The Spirit and the Bride say, "Come" Heaven is in my heart).'),
	(816, 'Come Sing A New Psalm Of David', 'Daniel Gardner ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nCome sing a new psalm of David.\r\nCome sing the song of the Lord.\r\nPraise Him with instruments,\r\nPraise Him with music,\r\nPraise to the One we adore! \r\n\r\nHe\'s the Lord  (4X)\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n', '', ' 1982 by Daniel Charles Gardner,', '', '', 'Come sing a new psalm of David. Come sing the song of the Lord. Praise Him with instruments, Praise Him with music, Praise to the One we adore! He\'s the Lord  (4X)'),
	(817, 'We Give You Thanks', 'George Searcy', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIn the middle of the conflict, \r\nIn the valleys of our lives;\r\nWe will lift up songs of worship,\r\nFor Your goodness cannot be denied.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFor we know that every problem\r\nIs a tool in Your own hand\r\nTo refine us for Your glory;\r\nMake us willing and able to stand.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nIn all things, we give You thanks,\r\nWe giveYou praise and thanksgiving; \r\nAt all times, in everything,\r\nWe giveYou thanks, we give You thanks.\r\n', '', ' 1994 Integrity\'s Praise! Music  ', '', '', 'In the middle of the conflict, In the valleys of our lives; We will lift up songs of worship, For Your goodness cannot be denied. For we know that every problem Is a tool in Your own hand To refine us for Your glory; Make us willing and able to stand. In all things, we give You thanks, We giveYou praise and thanksgiving; At all times, in everything, We giveYou thanks, we give You thanks.'),
	(818, 'O Lord Your Tenderness', 'Graham Kendrick. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nO Lord, Yur tenderness,\r\nMelting all my bitterness;\r\nO Lord, I receive Your love.\r\nYour loveliness,\r\nChanging my unworthiness,\r\nO Lord, I receive Yur love.\r\n', '', ' 1986', '', '', 'O Lord, Yur tenderness, Melting all my bitterness; O Lord, I receive Your love. Your loveliness, Changing my unworthiness, O Lord, I receive Yur love.'),
	(819, 'How Majestic', 'Michael W. Smith', '{title:How Majestic Are Your Ways}\n[G]To the Father, [C]to the [G]Son\n[Am]To the [Em]Holy [D]Ghost\n[G]I give glory, [C]I give [G]praise\n[Am]To the [Em]Mighty [D]One\nJe[Em]hovah, [C] Almighty [D] God\nThe [Em]Maker [C] of all the [D] earth\nThe [Em]Awesome, [C] Eternal [D] One\nThe [Em]Ruler [C] of all the [D] earth\n\n{start_of_chorus}\nI [G]worship [C]You  [D]\nHow maj[C]estic are Your [G]ways[C], oh Lord[D]\nI [G]worship [C]You  [D]\nHow maj[C]estic are Your [G]ways[C], oh Lord[D]\nHow maj[C]estic are Your [Em]ways  [C]      [D]\n{end_of_chorus}\n\n{comment:John Barnett}\n{comment:(c)1992 Mercy Publishing}\n', '', ' 1981 Meadowgreen Music Co. ', '', '', 'To the Father, to the Son To the Holy Ghost I give glory, I give praise To the Mighty One Jehovah,  Almighty  God The Maker  of all the  earth The Awesome,  Eternal  One The Ruler  of all the  earth  I worship You How majestic are Your ways, oh Lord I worship You How majestic are Your ways, oh Lord How majestic are Your ways'),
	(820, 'You Are Crowned In Majesty', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are crowned in majesty! \r\nWith the angels I will honor Thee!\r\nAll of You enthroned in me!\r\nOn the wings of worship \r\nI will lift my song to Thee!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI will glorify Your name!\r\nI will glorify Your name!\r\nJesus! Jesus! Jesus! Jesus!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAs priest and king I reign with Thee!\r\nBy Your blood I\'ve been made royalty!\r\nKing of Glory! Prince of Peace!\r\nWords could never fathom \r\nboundless love that washes me!\r\n', '', ' 1989 Shepherd\'s Heart Music. clo Northstar Ltd.', '', '', 'You are crowned in majesty! With the angels I will honor Thee! All of You enthroned in me! On the wings of worship I will lift my song to Thee! I will glorify Your name! I will glorify Your name! Jesus! Jesus! Jesus! Jesus! As priest and king I reign with Thee! By Your blood I\'ve been made royalty! King of Glory! Prince of Peace! Words could never fathom boundless love that washes me!'),
	(821, 'Thank You For The Cross (Its All About You)', 'Paul Oakley ', '~Verse 1\r\nIt\'s all about You, Jesus,\r\nAnd all this is for You,\r\nFor Your glory and Your fame\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIt\'s not about me,\r\nAs if You should do things my way;\r\nYou alone are God, \r\nAnd I surrender to Your ways.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nJesus, lover of my soul,\r\nAll consuming fire is in Your gaze.\r\nJesus, I want You to know\r\nI will follow You all my days.\r\n~Verse 4\r\nFor no one else in history is like You,\r\nAnd history itself belongs to You.\r\nAlpha and Omega, You have loved me,\r\nAnd I will share eternity with You.\r\n', '', '1995 Kingsway Thankyou Music', '', '', 'It\\\'s all about You, Jesus, And all this is for You, For Your glory and Your fame It\\\'s not about me, As if You should do things my way; You alone are God, And I surrender to Your ways. Jesus, lover of my soul, All consuming fire is in Your gaze. Jesus, I want You to know I will follow You all my days. For no one else in history is like You, And history itself belongs to You. Alpha and Omega, You have loved me, And I will share eternity with You.'),
	(822, 'We Are One', 'Brian Doerksen', '~Verse 1\r\nBy our love the world will see,\r\nBy our love the world will believe,\r\nChange our hearts so that we may see\r\nYour heart is broken until we \r\nare brought to unity.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe are one, one in You,\r\nWe are one, one in You,\r\nLet Your fire consume our pride\r\nAnd everything that divides us.\r\nSo that we may love one another,\r\nSo that we may forgive each other,\r\nSo that we may serve one another in love.\r\n', '', '1990 Langley Vineyard Music', '', '', 'By our love the world will see, By our love the world will believe, Change our hearts so that we may see Your heart is broken until we are brought to unity. We are one, one in You, We are one, one in You, Let Your fire consume our pride And everything that divides us. So that we may love one another, So that we may forgive each other, So that we may serve one another in love.'),
	(823, 'For Thou O Lord Art High', 'Pete Sanchez', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nFor thou O Lord art high above all the earth, \r\nThou art exalted far above all gods.\r\nWe exalt Thee, \r\nWe exalt Thee, O Lord. \r\n', '', ' 1977 Pete Sanchez,  ', '', '', 'For thou O Lord art high above all the earth, Thou art exalted far above all gods. We exalt Thee, We exalt Thee, O Lord.'),
	(824, 'Since I Have Been Redeemed', 'Edwin O. Excell.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nI have a song I love to sing,\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nOf my Redeemer, Savior, King,\r\nSince I have been redeemed.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nI have a Christ who satisfies,\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nTo do His will my highest prize,\r\nSince I have been redeemed.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI have a witness bright and clear,\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nDispelling every doubt and fear,\r\nSince I have been redeemed.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nI have a home prepared for me,\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nWhere I shall dwell eternally,\r\nSince I have been redeemed.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nI will glory in His name;\r\nSince I have been redeemed,\r\nI wil glory in my Savior\'s name.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'I have a song I love to sing, Since I have been redeemed, Of my Redeemer, Savior, King, Since I have been redeemed. I have a Christ who satisfies, Since I have been redeemed, To do His will my highest prize, Since I have been redeemed. I have a witness bright and clear, Since I have been redeemed, Dispelling every doubt and fear, Since I have been redeemed. I have a home prepared for me, Since I have been redeemed, Where I shall dwell eternally, Since I have been redeemed. Since I have been redeemed, Since I have been redeemed, I will glory in His name; Since I have been redeemed, I wil glory in my Savior\'s name.'),
	(825, 'Your Love Oh Lord', '', '~Intro\r\n[G] [C] [G] [C9] [G] [C9]\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYour [G]love oh Lord [C9]reaches to the [G]heavens[D/F#]\r\n[Em7]Your faithfulness [C9]stretches to the [G]sky[D/F#]\r\n[Em7]Your righteous[C9]ness is like the mighty [G]mountain[D/F#]\r\nAnd Your [Em7]justice flows [C9]like the oceans [G]tides[D/F#]\r\n~Chorus\r\n[D/F#]And I will lift my [D]voice to [C9]worship you my [G]King\r\n[G]And I will find my [D]strength in the [C9]shadow of Your [Am]wings[D]\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'Your love oh Lord reaches to the heavens Your faithfulness stretches to the sky Your righteousness is like the mighty mountain And Your justice flows like the oceans tides And I will lift my voice to worship you my King And I will find my strength in the shadow of Your wings'),
	(826, 'More Precious Medley', 'Lynn DeShazo.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nLord You are more precious than silver\r\nLord You are more costly than gold\r\nLord You are more beautiful than diamonds\r\nAnd nothing I desire compares with you.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWorthy, oh worthy are You, Lord\r\nWorthy to be thanked and praised\r\nAnd worshipped and adored.\r\nWorthy, oh worthy are You, Lord\r\nWorthy to be thanked and praised\r\nAnd worshipped and adored.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nSinging hallelujah, Lamb upon the Throne\r\nWe worship and adore You\r\nYou\'ve made Your glories known.\r\nHallelujah, glory to the King\r\nYou\'re more than a conqueror\r\nAnd You\'re Lord of everything.\r\n', '', ' 1982 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music, c/o Integrity Music, Inc.', '', '', 'Lord You are more precious than silver Lord You are more costly than gold Lord You are more beautiful than diamonds And nothing I desire compares with you. Worthy, oh worthy are You, Lord Worthy to be thanked and praised And worshipped and adored. Worthy, oh worthy are You, Lord Worthy to be thanked and praised And worshipped and adored. Singing hallelujah, Lamb upon the Throne We worship and adore You You\'ve made Your glories known. Hallelujah, glory to the King You\'re more than a conqueror And You\'re Lord of everything.'),
	(827, 'Over The River (Tag Ending)', '', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIt stings your nose and bites your toes\r\nAs over the ground we go.\r\nIt stings your nose and bites your toes\r\nAs over the ground we go.\r\n\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'It stings your nose and bites your toes As over the ground we go. It stings your nose and bites your toes As over the ground we go.'),
	(828, 'The Butterfly Song', 'Brian Howard. ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nIf I were a butterfly,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, for giving me wings,\r\nAnd if I were a robin in a tree,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, that I could sing.\r\nAnd if I were a fish in the sea,\r\nI\'d wiggle my tail, and I\'d giggle with glee.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nIf I were an elephant,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, by raising my trunk,\r\nAnd if I were a kangaroo,\r\nI\'d just hop right up to You.\r\nAnd if I were an octopus,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, for my good looks.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nIf I were a wiggly worm,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, that I could squirm,\r\nAnd if I were a crocodile,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, for my big smile.\r\nAnd if I were a fuzzy wuzzy bear,\r\nI\'d thank You, Lord, for my fuzzy wuzzy hair.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nBut I just thank You, Father,\r\nFor making me, me.\r\n\'Cause You gave me a heart,\r\nAnd you gave me a smile,\r\nYou gave me Jesus,\r\nAnd You made me Your child,\r\nAnd I just thank You, Father,\r\nFor making me, me.\r\n', '', ' 1974 & 1975 Celebration Services. ', '', '', 'If I were a butterfly, I\'d thank You, Lord, for giving me wings, And if I were a robin in a tree, I\'d thank You, Lord, that I could sing. And if I were a fish in the sea, I\'d wiggle my tail, and I\'d giggle with glee. If I were an elephant, I\'d thank You, Lord, by raising my trunk, And if I were a kangaroo, I\'d just hop right up to You. And if I were an octopus, I\'d thank You, Lord, for my good looks. If I were a wiggly worm, I\'d thank You, Lord, that I could squirm, And if I were a crocodile, I\'d thank You, Lord, for my big smile. And if I were a fuzzy wuzzy bear, I\'d thank You, Lord, for my fuzzy wuzzy hair. But I just thank You, Father, For making me, me. \'Cause You gave me a heart, And you gave me a smile, You gave me Jesus, And You made me Your child, And I just thank You, Father, For making me, me.'),
	(829, 'The Wonder Of It All', 'George Beverly Shea;', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThere\'s the wonder of sunset at evening,\r\nThe wonder as sunrise I see;\r\n But the wonder of wonders \r\nthat thrills my soul \r\nIs the wonder that God loves me.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nO, the wonder of it all!\r\nThe wonder of it all!\r\nJust to think that God loves me.\r\nO, the wonder of it all!\r\nThe wonder of it all!\r\nJust to think that God loves me.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nThere\'s the wonder of \r\nspringtime and harvest, \r\nThe sky, the stars, the sun;\r\nBut the wonder of wonders\r\n that thrills my 	 soul\r\nIs a wonder that\'s only begun.\r\n', '', ' 1957 Chancel Music, Inc. (year date in prior c. notice; 1956).', '', '', 'There\'s the wonder of sunset at evening, The wonder as sunrise I see; But the wonder of wonders that thrills my soul Is the wonder that God loves me. O, the wonder of it all! The wonder of it all! Just to think that God loves me. O, the wonder of it all! The wonder of it all! Just to think that God loves me. There\'s the wonder of springtime and harvest, The sky, the stars, the sun; But the wonder of wonders that thrills my 	 soul Is a wonder that\'s only begun.'),
	(830, 'Blest Be The Tie That Binds', 'John Fawcett & Hans G. Naegeli.', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBlest be the tie that binds\r\nOur hearts in Christian love!\r\nThe fellowship of kindred minds\r\nIs like to that above.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nBefore our Father\'s throne\r\nWe pour our ardent prayers;\r\nOur fears, our hopes, our aims are one,\r\nOur comforts and our cares.\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nWe share our mutual woes,\r\nOur mutual burdens bear;\r\nAnd often for each other flows\r\nThe sympathizing tear.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWhen we asunder part\r\nIt gives us inward pain;\r\nBut we shall still be joined in heart,\r\nAnd hope to meet again.\r\n', '', 'Public Domain', '', '', 'Blest be the tie that binds Our hearts in Christian love! The fellowship of kindred minds Is like to that above. Before our Father\'s throne We pour our ardent prayers; Our fears, our hopes, our aims are one, Our comforts and our cares. We share our mutual woes, Our mutual burdens bear; And often for each other flows The sympathizing tear. When we asunder part It gives us inward pain; But we shall still be joined in heart, And hope to meet again.'),
	(831, 'When I Look Into Your Holiness', 'Cathy & Wayne Perrin', '~Verse 1\r\nWhen I [D]look into Your holiness[G],\r\nWhen I [D]gaze into Your loveli[Bm]ness,\r\nWhen all [D]things that [F#m]surround become [G]shadows\r\nin the light of [Em7]You,[A]\r\n~Verse 2\r\nWhen I [D]find the joy of reaching Your [G]heart,\r\nWhen my [D]will becomes enthroned in Your [Bm]love,\r\nWhen all [D]things that [F#m]surround become [G]shadows\r\nin the [C]light of [A]You.\r\n~Chorus\r\nI worship [G]You[A], I worship [D]You[Bm],\r\nThe [G]reason I live [Em7]is to [A]worship [D]You[D7],\r\nI worship [G]You, [A]I worship [D]You[Bm],\r\nThe [G]reason I live [Em7]is to [A]worship [D]You.\r\n', '', '1980 Integrity\'s Hosanna! Music (c/o Integrity Music Inc.)', '', '', 'When I look into Your holiness, When I gaze into Your loveliness, When all things that surround become shadows in the light of You, When I find the joy of reaching Your heart, When my will becomes enthroned in Your love, When all things that surround become shadows in the light of You. I worship You, I worship You, The reason I live is to worship You, I worship You, I worship You, The reason I live is to worship You.'),
	(832, 'Above All Else', 'Kirk & Deby Dearman  ', '~Verse 1\r\nY[A]ou are e[G]xalted Lord, a[D]bove a[E]ll e[A]lse\r\nWe place you at the h[G]ighest place, a[D]bove a[E]ll e[A]lse\r\nRight here where we s[G]tand and everyw[D]here [E]we [A]go\r\nWe place you at the h[G]ighest place, so the w[D]orld will k[E]now\r\n~Verse 2\r\nY[A]ou are a mighty w[G]arrior, d[D]ressed in armor [E]of l[A]ight\r\nCrushing the deeds of d[G]arkness, l[D]ead us on in t[E]he f[A]ight\r\nThrough the blood of J[G]esus, vict[D]orious [E]we s[A]tand\r\nWe place you at the [G]highest place, [D]above all else in this [E]land\r\nA[D]bove a[E]ll e[A]lse\r\n\r\n', '', '1988 Integrity Music', '', '', 'You are exalted Lord, above all else We place you at the highest place, above all else Right here where we stand and everywhere we go We place you at the highest place, so the world will know You are a mighty warrior, dressed in armor of light Crushing the deeds of darkness, lead us on in the fight Through the blood of Jesus, victorious we stand We place you at the highest place, above all else in this land Above all else'),
	(834, 'Meet With Me', 'Lamont Hiebert. ', '~Verse 1\r\n[A]I\'m [D]here to [E]meet with [A]You\r\n[A]Come [D]and [E]meet with [A]me\r\n[A]I\'m [D]here to [E]find [A]You\r\n[A]Re[D]veal Your[E]self to [A]me\r\n~Verse 2\r\nAs I [A]wait,[D] You [E]make me [A]strong\r\nAs I long, You draw me to Your arms\r\nAs I stand and sing Your praise\r\nYou come, You come and You fill this place\r\nWon\'t You come, Won\'t You come and fill this place\r\n', '', ' 1999 Maranatha! Music', '', '', 'I\'m here to meet with You Come and meet with me I\'m here to find You Reveal Yourself to me As I wait, You make me strong As I long, You draw me to Your arms As I stand and sing Your praise You come, You come and You fill this place Won\'t You come, Won\'t You come and fill this place'),
	(835, 'I Believe In Jesus Christ', 'Stuart Sheehan', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nHe left His mighty throne in heaven,\r\nGod and man upon this filthy ground,\r\nTempted in all ways like me,\r\nBut always kept His purity,\r\nHoly love and life for me laid down.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nI believe He died for me,\r\nPaid my debt and set me free,\r\nI believe He rose again, \r\nNow I\'m free from death and sin,\r\nI believe He went to heaven,\r\nBut He\'s coming back for me,\r\nI believe in Jesus, I believe.\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd now I\'m trusting in His promise,\r\nOf a place where tears will never fall,\r\nWhere there with many others,\r\nMy sisters and my brothers,\r\nI\'ll sing with those who answer to His call.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nI believe He died for me, \r\nPaid my debt and set me free,\r\nI believe He rose again,\r\nNow I\'m free from death and sin,\r\nStanding now in heaven,\r\nSinging thankfully\r\nI believe in Jesus, I believe.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 7\r\nI believe He died for me,\r\nPaid my debt and set me free\r\nI believe He rose again,\r\nNow I\'m free from death and sin,\r\nOne day up in heaven\r\nWe\'ll be singing thankfully,\r\nI believe in Jesus, I believe.\r\n', '', '1999 Life Upon Life Music  ', '', '', 'He left His mighty throne in heaven, God and man upon this filthy ground, Tempted in all ways like me, But always kept His purity, Holy love and life for me laid down. I believe He died for me, Paid my debt and set me free, I believe He rose again, Now I\'m free from death and sin, I believe He went to heaven, But He\'s coming back for me, I believe in Jesus, I believe. And now I\'m trusting in His promise, Of a place where tears will never fall, Where there with many others, My sisters and my brothers, I\'ll sing with those who answer to His call. I believe He died for me, Paid my debt and set me free, I believe He rose again, Now I\'m free from death and sin, Standing now in heaven, Singing thankfully I believe in Jesus, I believe. I believe He died for me, Paid my debt and set me free I believe He rose again, Now I\'m free from death and sin, One day up in heaven We\'ll be singing thankfully, I believe in Jesus, I believe.'),
	(836, 'The Lord Is My Light', 'Jeff D. Nelson. Copyright unknown.', '~Verse 1\r\nThe Lord is my light and my salvation.\r\nWhom shall I fear?\r\nWhom shall I fear?\r\nThe Lord is the strength of my life\r\nOf whom shall I be afraid?\r\n\r\n', '', '', '', '', 'The Lord is my light and my salvation. Whom shall I fear? Whom shall I fear? The Lord is the strength of my life Of whom shall I be afraid?'),
	(837, 'Give Us Clean Hands', 'Charlie Hall', '~Verse 1\r\nWe bow our hearts,\r\nWe bend our knees;\r\nOh Spirit, \r\ncome make us humble.\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGive us clean hands,\r\nGive us pure hearts;\r\nLet us not \r\nlift our souls to another.\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nAnd O God let us be,\r\n a generation that seeks,\r\nThat seeks Your face,\r\nO God of Jacob;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nWe bow our hearts,\r\nWe bend our knees;\r\nOh Spirit, come make us humble.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\n\r\nWe turn our eyes \r\nfrom evil things;\r\nOh Lord, \r\nwe cast down our idols.\r\n\r\n', '', ' 2000 worshiptogether.com songs', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/onGbkeWkA64&list=PLCA82F88D29756B75', '', 'We bow our hearts, We bend our knees; Oh Spirit, come make us humble. Give us clean hands, Give us pure hearts; Let us not lift our souls to another. And O God let us be, a generation that seeks, That seeks Your face, O God of Jacob; We bow our hearts, We bend our knees; Oh Spirit, come make us humble. We turn our eyes from evil things; Oh Lord, we cast down our idols.'),
	(838, 'It Is Well With My Soul', 'Public Domain', '~Verse 1\r\n[C]When peace, li[G]ke a rive[F]r, [G7]attendet[C]h my way,\r\nWhen s[Am]orrows like s[D]ea billows r[G]oll;\r\nWhate[C]ver my l[F]ot, thou h[A7]ast t[Dm]aught me [D7]to s[G]ay,\r\n"It is w[C]ell, [F]it is [C/G]well w[G]ith my s[C]oul."\r\n~Chorus\r\nIt is well [C]          (It is well[G])\r\nWith my soul [G]        (With my soul[C])\r\nIt is w[F]ell, it is w[C/G]ell, w[G7]ith my s[C]oul.\r\n~Verse 2\r\nThough Satan should buffet, though trials should come,\r\nLet this blest assurance control,\r\nThat Christ has regarded my helpless estate,\r\nAnd hath shed his own blood for my soul.\r\n~Verse 3\r\nMy sin, o, the joy of this glorious thought!\r\nMy sin, not in part but the whole\r\nIs nailed to the cross, and I bear it no more,\r\nPraise the Lord, praise the Lord, O my soul!\r\n~Verse 4\r\nAnd, Lord, haste the day when my faith shall be sight,\r\nThe clouds be rolled back as a scroll;\r\nThe trump shall resound, and the Lord shall descend,\r\nEven so, it is well with my soul.\r\n', '', '', 'http://www.youtube.com/v/X6yDFn3OAFo&hl=en&fs=1&', '', 'When peace, like a river, attendeth my way, When sorrows like sea billows roll; Whatever my lot, thou hast taught me to say, "It is well, it is well with my soul." It is well           (It is well) With my soul         (With my soul) It is well, it is well, with my soul. Though Satan should buffet, though trials should come, Let this blest assurance control, That Christ has regarded my helpless estate, And hath shed his own blood for my soul. My sin, o, the joy of this glorious thought! My sin, not in part but the whole Is nailed to the cross, and I bear it no more, Praise the Lord, praise the Lord, O my soul! And, Lord, haste the day when my faith shall be sight, The clouds be rolled back as a scroll; The trump shall resound, and the Lord shall descend, Even so, it is well with my soul.'),
	(839, 'Glorious Is Thy Name', 'B.B. McKinney, ', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nBlessed Savior, we adore Thee,\r\nWe Thy love and grace proclaim;\r\nThou art mighty, Thou art holy,\r\nGlorious is Thy matchless name!\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 2\r\nGreat Redeemer, Lord and Master\r\nLight of all eternal days;\r\nLet the saints of ev\'ry nation\r\nSing Thy just and endless praise!\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nFrom the throne of heaven\'s glory\r\nTo the cross of sin and shame,\r\nThou didst come to die a ransom,\r\nGuilty sinners to reclaim!\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nCome, O come, immortal Savior,\r\nCome and take Thy royal throne;\r\nCome, and reign, and reign forever,\r\nBe the kingdom all Thine own.\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nGlorious, glorious, \r\nGlorious is Thy name, O Lord!\r\n', '', ' 1942 Renewal 1970 Broadman Press', '', '', 'Blessed Savior, we adore Thee, We Thy love and grace proclaim; Thou art mighty, Thou art holy, Glorious is Thy matchless name! Great Redeemer, Lord and Master Light of all eternal days; Let the saints of ev\'ry nation Sing Thy just and endless praise! From the throne of heaven\'s glory To the cross of sin and shame, Thou didst come to die a ransom, Guilty sinners to reclaim! Come, O come, immortal Savior, Come and take Thy royal throne; Come, and reign, and reign forever, Be the kingdom all Thine own. Glorious, glorious, Glorious is Thy name, O Lord!'),
	(840, 'You Are My God (And I Belong To You)', 'Mark Altrogge', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nYou are my God \r\nand I belong to You, Lord,\r\nYou are my God \r\nand I will always follow You;\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nYour ways will be my ways,\r\nAnd Your people my people,\r\nAnd Your truth shall be my truth.\r\nYou are my God,\r\n I have no other God but You.\r\n', '', ' 1992 Integrity\'s Praise! Music/People of Destiny Music', '', '', 'You are my God and I belong to You, Lord, You are my God and I will always follow You; Your ways will be my ways, And Your people my people, And Your truth shall be my truth. You are my God, I have no other God but You.'),
	(841, 'Spirit Of The Sovereign Lord', 'Andy Park', '\r\n~Verse 1\r\nThe Spirit of the Sovereign Lord is upon you\r\nBecause he has anointed you\r\n to preach good news\r\nThe Spirit of the Sovereign God is upon you\r\nBecause he has anointed you\r\n to preach good news\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 3\r\nThis is the year,\r\n Of the favour of the Lord\r\nThis is the day,\r\nOf the vengence of our God\r\nThis is the year, \r\nOf the favour of the Lord\r\nThis is the day,\r\n Of the vengence of our God\r\n\r\n~Verse 4\r\nHe has sent you to the poor, \r\nThis is the year\r\nTo bind up the broken hearted, \r\nThis is the day\r\nTo bring freedom to the captives, \r\nThis is the year\r\nAnd to release the ones in darkness\r\n\r\n~Verse 5\r\nThe Spirit of the Sovereign Lord is upon us\r\nBecause he has anointed us\r\n to preach good news\r\nThe Spirit of the Sovereign God is upon us\r\nBecause he has anointed us\r\n to preach good news\r\n\r\n\r\n~Verse 6\r\nHe will comfort all who mourn, \r\nThis is the year\r\nHe will provide for those who grieve Zion, \r\nThis is the day\r\nHe will pour out the oil of gladness, \r\nThis is the year\r\nInstead of mourning you will praise\r\n', '', ' 1994 Mercy Publishing. ARR. ICS. UBP. ', '', '', 'The Spirit of the Sovereign Lord is upon you Because he has anointed you to preach good news The Spirit of the Sovereign God is upon you Because he has anointed you to preach good news This is the year, Of the favour of the Lord This is the day, Of the vengence of our God This is the year, Of the favour of the Lord This is the day, Of the vengence of our God He has sent you to the poor, This is the year To bind up the broken hearted, This is the day To bring freedom to the captives, This is the year And to release the ones in darkness The Spirit of the Sovereign Lord is upon us Because he has anointed us to preach good news The Spirit of the Sovereign God is upon us Because he has anointed us to preach good news He will comfort all who mourn, This is the 